51  DEBUG_TYPE "-ext-max-web-size", cl::Hidden,
52  cl::desc("Give the maximum size (in number of nodes) of the web of "
53  "instructions that we will consider for VW expansion"),
54  cl::init(18));

57  AllowSplatInVW_W(DEBUG_TYPE "-form-vw-w-with-splat", cl::Hidden,
58  cl::desc("Allow the formation of VW_W operations (e.g., "
59  "VWADD_W) with splat constants"),
60  cl::init(false));

63  DEBUG_TYPE "-fp-repeated-divisors", cl::Hidden,
64  cl::desc("Set the minimum number of repetitions of a divisor to allow "
65  "transformation to multiplications by the reciprocal"),
66  cl::init(2));

69  FPImmCost(DEBUG_TYPE "-fpimm-cost", cl::Hidden,
70  cl::desc("Give the maximum number of instructions that we will "
71  "use for creating a floating-point immediate value"),
72  cl::init(2));

74 RISCVTargetLowering::RISCVTargetLowering(const TargetMachine &TM,
75  const RISCVSubtarget &STI)
76  : TargetLowering(TM), Subtarget(STI) {
77 
78  if (Subtarget.isRV32E())
79  report_fatal_error("Codegen not yet implemented for RV32E");
80 
81  RISCVABI::ABI ABI = Subtarget.getTargetABI();
82  assert(ABI != RISCVABI::ABI_Unknown && "Improperly initialised target ABI");
83 
84  if ((ABI == RISCVABI::ABI_ILP32F || ABI == RISCVABI::ABI_LP64F) &&
85  !Subtarget.hasStdExtF()) {
86  errs() << "Hard-float 'f' ABI can't be used for a target that "
87  "doesn't support the F instruction set extension (ignoring "
88  "target-abi)\n";
89  ABI = Subtarget.is64Bit() ? RISCVABI::ABI_LP64 : RISCVABI::ABI_ILP32;
90  } else if ((ABI == RISCVABI::ABI_ILP32D || ABI == RISCVABI::ABI_LP64D) &&
91  !Subtarget.hasStdExtD()) {
92  errs() << "Hard-float 'd' ABI can't be used for a target that "
93  "doesn't support the D instruction set extension (ignoring "
94  "target-abi)\n";
95  ABI = Subtarget.is64Bit() ? RISCVABI::ABI_LP64 : RISCVABI::ABI_ILP32;
96  }
97 
98  switch (ABI) {
99  default:
100  report_fatal_error("Don't know how to lower this ABI");
101  case RISCVABI::ABI_ILP32:
102  case RISCVABI::ABI_ILP32F:
103  case RISCVABI::ABI_ILP32D:
104  case RISCVABI::ABI_LP64:
105  case RISCVABI::ABI_LP64F:
106  case RISCVABI::ABI_LP64D:
107  break;
108  }
109 
110  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
111 
112  // Set up the register classes.
113  addRegisterClass(XLenVT, &RISCV::GPRRegClass);
114 
115  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZfhOrZfhmin())
116  addRegisterClass(MVT::f16, &RISCV::FPR16RegClass);
117  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtF())
118  addRegisterClass(MVT::f32, &RISCV::FPR32RegClass);
119  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtD())
120  addRegisterClass(MVT::f64, &RISCV::FPR64RegClass);
121 
122  static const MVT::SimpleValueType BoolVecVTs[] = {
123  MVT::nxv1i1, MVT::nxv2i1, MVT::nxv4i1, MVT::nxv8i1,
124  MVT::nxv16i1, MVT::nxv32i1, MVT::nxv64i1};
125  static const MVT::SimpleValueType IntVecVTs[] = {
126  MVT::nxv1i8, MVT::nxv2i8, MVT::nxv4i8, MVT::nxv8i8, MVT::nxv16i8,
127  MVT::nxv32i8, MVT::nxv64i8, MVT::nxv1i16, MVT::nxv2i16, MVT::nxv4i16,
128  MVT::nxv8i16, MVT::nxv16i16, MVT::nxv32i16, MVT::nxv1i32, MVT::nxv2i32,
129  MVT::nxv4i32, MVT::nxv8i32, MVT::nxv16i32, MVT::nxv1i64, MVT::nxv2i64,
130  MVT::nxv4i64, MVT::nxv8i64};
131  static const MVT::SimpleValueType F16VecVTs[] = {
132  MVT::nxv1f16, MVT::nxv2f16, MVT::nxv4f16,
133  MVT::nxv8f16, MVT::nxv16f16, MVT::nxv32f16};
134  static const MVT::SimpleValueType F32VecVTs[] = {
135  MVT::nxv1f32, MVT::nxv2f32, MVT::nxv4f32, MVT::nxv8f32, MVT::nxv16f32};
136  static const MVT::SimpleValueType F64VecVTs[] = {
137  MVT::nxv1f64, MVT::nxv2f64, MVT::nxv4f64, MVT::nxv8f64};
138 
139  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructions()) {
140  auto addRegClassForRVV = [this](MVT VT) {
141  // Disable the smallest fractional LMUL types if ELEN is less than
142  // RVVBitsPerBlock.
143  unsigned MinElts = RISCV::RVVBitsPerBlock / Subtarget.getELEN();
144  if (VT.getVectorMinNumElements() < MinElts)
145  return;
146 
147  unsigned Size = VT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue();
148  const TargetRegisterClass *RC;
149  if (Size <= RISCV::RVVBitsPerBlock)
150  RC = &RISCV::VRRegClass;
151  else if (Size == 2 * RISCV::RVVBitsPerBlock)
152  RC = &RISCV::VRM2RegClass;
153  else if (Size == 4 * RISCV::RVVBitsPerBlock)
154  RC = &RISCV::VRM4RegClass;
155  else if (Size == 8 * RISCV::RVVBitsPerBlock)
156  RC = &RISCV::VRM8RegClass;
157  else
158  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected size");
159 
160  addRegisterClass(VT, RC);
161  };
162 
163  for (MVT VT : BoolVecVTs)
164  addRegClassForRVV(VT);
165  for (MVT VT : IntVecVTs) {
166  if (VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i64 &&
167  !Subtarget.hasVInstructionsI64())
168  continue;
169  addRegClassForRVV(VT);
170  }
171 
172  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructionsF16())
173  for (MVT VT : F16VecVTs)
174  addRegClassForRVV(VT);
175 
176  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructionsF32())
177  for (MVT VT : F32VecVTs)
178  addRegClassForRVV(VT);
179 
180  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructionsF64())
181  for (MVT VT : F64VecVTs)
182  addRegClassForRVV(VT);
183 
184  if (Subtarget.useRVVForFixedLengthVectors()) {
185  auto addRegClassForFixedVectors = [this](MVT VT) {
186  MVT ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
187  unsigned RCID = getRegClassIDForVecVT(ContainerVT);
188  const RISCVRegisterInfo &TRI = *Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
189  addRegisterClass(VT, TRI.getRegClass(RCID));
190  };
191  for (MVT VT : MVT::integer_fixedlen_vector_valuetypes())
192  if (useRVVForFixedLengthVectorVT(VT))
193  addRegClassForFixedVectors(VT);
194 
195  for (MVT VT : MVT::fp_fixedlen_vector_valuetypes())
196  if (useRVVForFixedLengthVectorVT(VT))
197  addRegClassForFixedVectors(VT);
198  }
199  }
200 
201  // Compute derived properties from the register classes.
202  computeRegisterProperties(STI.getRegisterInfo());
203 
204  setStackPointerRegisterToSaveRestore(RISCV::X2);
205 
206  setLoadExtAction({ISD::EXTLOAD, ISD::SEXTLOAD, ISD::ZEXTLOAD}, XLenVT,
207  MVT::i1, Promote);
208  // DAGCombiner can call isLoadExtLegal for types that aren't legal.
209  setLoadExtAction({ISD::EXTLOAD, ISD::SEXTLOAD, ISD::ZEXTLOAD}, MVT::i32,
210  MVT::i1, Promote);
211 
212  // TODO: add all necessary setOperationAction calls.
213  setOperationAction(ISD::DYNAMIC_STACKALLOC, XLenVT, Expand);
214 
215  setOperationAction(ISD::BR_JT, MVT::Other, Expand);
216  setOperationAction(ISD::BR_CC, XLenVT, Expand);
217  setOperationAction(ISD::BRCOND, MVT::Other, Custom);
218  setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, XLenVT, Expand);
219 
220  setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETLE, XLenVT, Expand);
221  setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETGT, XLenVT, Custom);
222  setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETGE, XLenVT, Expand);
223  setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETULE, XLenVT, Expand);
224  setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETUGT, XLenVT, Custom);
225  setCondCodeAction(ISD::SETUGE, XLenVT, Expand);
226 
227  setOperationAction({ISD::STACKSAVE, ISD::STACKRESTORE}, MVT::Other, Expand);
228 
229  setOperationAction(ISD::VASTART, MVT::Other, Custom);
230  setOperationAction({ISD::VAARG, ISD::VACOPY, ISD::VAEND}, MVT::Other, Expand);
231 
232  setOperationAction(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, MVT::i1, Expand);
233 
234  setOperationAction(ISD::EH_DWARF_CFA, MVT::i32, Custom);
235 
236  if (!Subtarget.hasStdExtZbb() && !Subtarget.hasVendorXTHeadBb())
237  setOperationAction(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, {MVT::i8, MVT::i16}, Expand);
238 
239  if (Subtarget.is64Bit()) {
240  setOperationAction(ISD::EH_DWARF_CFA, MVT::i64, Custom);
241 
242  setOperationAction(ISD::LOAD, MVT::i32, Custom);
243 
244  setOperationAction({ISD::ADD, ISD::SUB, ISD::SHL, ISD::SRA, ISD::SRL},
245  MVT::i32, Custom);
246 
247  setOperationAction({ISD::UADDO, ISD::USUBO, ISD::UADDSAT, ISD::USUBSAT},
248  MVT::i32, Custom);
249  } else {
250  setLibcallName(
251  {RTLIB::SHL_I128, RTLIB::SRL_I128, RTLIB::SRA_I128, RTLIB::MUL_I128},
252  nullptr);
253  setLibcallName(RTLIB::MULO_I64, nullptr);
254  }
255 
256  if (!Subtarget.hasStdExtM() && !Subtarget.hasStdExtZmmul()) {
257  setOperationAction({ISD::MUL, ISD::MULHS, ISD::MULHU}, XLenVT, Expand);
258  } else {
259  if (Subtarget.is64Bit()) {
260  setOperationAction(ISD::MUL, {MVT::i32, MVT::i128}, Custom);
261  } else {
262  setOperationAction(ISD::MUL, MVT::i64, Custom);
263  }
264  }
265 
266  if (!Subtarget.hasStdExtM()) {
267  setOperationAction({ISD::SDIV, ISD::UDIV, ISD::SREM, ISD::UREM},
268  XLenVT, Expand);
269  } else {
270  if (Subtarget.is64Bit()) {
271  setOperationAction({ISD::SDIV, ISD::UDIV, ISD::UREM},
272  {MVT::i8, MVT::i16, MVT::i32}, Custom);
273  }
274  }
275 
276  setOperationAction(
277  {ISD::SDIVREM, ISD::UDIVREM, ISD::SMUL_LOHI, ISD::UMUL_LOHI}, XLenVT,
278  Expand);
279 
280  setOperationAction({ISD::SHL_PARTS, ISD::SRL_PARTS, ISD::SRA_PARTS}, XLenVT,
281  Custom);
282 
283  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZbb() || Subtarget.hasStdExtZbkb() ||
284  Subtarget.hasVendorXTHeadBb()) {
285  if (Subtarget.is64Bit())
286  setOperationAction({ISD::ROTL, ISD::ROTR}, MVT::i32, Custom);
287  } else {
288  setOperationAction({ISD::ROTL, ISD::ROTR}, XLenVT, Expand);
289  }
290 
291  // With Zbb we have an XLen rev8 instruction, but not GREVI. So we'll
292  // pattern match it directly in isel.
293  setOperationAction(ISD::BSWAP, XLenVT,
294  (Subtarget.hasStdExtZbb() || Subtarget.hasStdExtZbkb() ||
295  Subtarget.hasVendorXTHeadBb())
296  ? Legal
297  : Expand);
298  // Zbkb can use rev8+brev8 to implement bitreverse.
299  setOperationAction(ISD::BITREVERSE, XLenVT,
300  Subtarget.hasStdExtZbkb() ? Custom : Expand);
301 
302  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZbb()) {
303  setOperationAction({ISD::SMIN, ISD::SMAX, ISD::UMIN, ISD::UMAX}, XLenVT,
304  Legal);
305 
306  if (Subtarget.is64Bit())
307  setOperationAction(
308  {ISD::CTTZ, ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF, ISD::CTLZ, ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF},
309  MVT::i32, Custom);
310  } else {
311  setOperationAction({ISD::CTTZ, ISD::CTLZ, ISD::CTPOP}, XLenVT, Expand);
312  }
313 
314  if (Subtarget.hasVendorXTHeadBb()) {
315  setOperationAction(ISD::CTLZ, XLenVT, Legal);
316 
317  // We need the custom lowering to make sure that the resulting sequence
318  // for the 32bit case is efficient on 64bit targets.
319  if (Subtarget.is64Bit())
320  setOperationAction({ISD::CTLZ, ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF}, MVT::i32, Custom);
321  }
322 
323  if (Subtarget.is64Bit())
324  setOperationAction(ISD::ABS, MVT::i32, Custom);
325 
326  if (!Subtarget.hasVendorXVentanaCondOps())
327  setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, XLenVT, Custom);
328 
329  static const unsigned FPLegalNodeTypes[] = {
330  ISD::FMINNUM, ISD::FMAXNUM, ISD::LRINT,
331  ISD::LLRINT, ISD::LROUND, ISD::LLROUND,
332  ISD::STRICT_LRINT, ISD::STRICT_LLRINT, ISD::STRICT_LROUND,
333  ISD::STRICT_LLROUND, ISD::STRICT_FMA, ISD::STRICT_FADD,
334  ISD::STRICT_FSUB, ISD::STRICT_FMUL, ISD::STRICT_FDIV,
335  ISD::STRICT_FSQRT, ISD::STRICT_FSETCC, ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS};
336 
337  static const ISD::CondCode FPCCToExpand[] = {
338  ISD::SETOGT, ISD::SETOGE, ISD::SETONE, ISD::SETUEQ, ISD::SETUGT,
339  ISD::SETUGE, ISD::SETULT, ISD::SETULE, ISD::SETUNE, ISD::SETGT,
340  ISD::SETGE, ISD::SETNE, ISD::SETO, ISD::SETUO};
341 
342  static const unsigned FPOpToExpand[] = {
343  ISD::FSIN, ISD::FCOS, ISD::FSINCOS, ISD::FPOW,
344  ISD::FREM, ISD::FP16_TO_FP, ISD::FP_TO_FP16};
345 
346  static const unsigned FPRndMode[] = {
347  ISD::FCEIL, ISD::FFLOOR, ISD::FTRUNC, ISD::FRINT, ISD::FROUND,
348  ISD::FROUNDEVEN};
349 
350  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZfhOrZfhmin())
351  setOperationAction(ISD::BITCAST, MVT::i16, Custom);
352 
353  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZfhOrZfhmin()) {
354  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZfh()) {
355  setOperationAction(FPLegalNodeTypes, MVT::f16, Legal);
356  setOperationAction(FPRndMode, MVT::f16, Custom);
357  setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, MVT::f16, Custom);
358  } else {
359  static const unsigned ZfhminPromoteOps[] = {
360  ISD::FMINNUM, ISD::FMAXNUM, ISD::FADD,
361  ISD::FSUB, ISD::FMUL, ISD::FMA,
362  ISD::FDIV, ISD::FSQRT, ISD::FABS,
363  ISD::FNEG, ISD::STRICT_FMA, ISD::STRICT_FADD,
364  ISD::STRICT_FSUB, ISD::STRICT_FMUL, ISD::STRICT_FDIV,
365  ISD::STRICT_FSQRT, ISD::STRICT_FSETCC, ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS,
366  ISD::SETCC, ISD::FCEIL, ISD::FFLOOR,
367  ISD::FTRUNC, ISD::FRINT, ISD::FROUND,
368  ISD::FROUNDEVEN, ISD::SELECT};
369 
370  setOperationAction(ZfhminPromoteOps, MVT::f16, Promote);
371  setOperationAction({ISD::STRICT_LRINT, ISD::STRICT_LLRINT,
372  ISD::STRICT_LROUND, ISD::STRICT_LLROUND},
373  MVT::f16, Legal);
374  // FIXME: Need to promote f16 FCOPYSIGN to f32, but the
375  // DAGCombiner::visitFP_ROUND probably needs improvements first.
376  setOperationAction(ISD::FCOPYSIGN, MVT::f16, Expand);
377  }
378 
379  setOperationAction(ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND, MVT::f16, Legal);
380  setOperationAction(ISD::STRICT_FP_EXTEND, MVT::f32, Legal);
381  setCondCodeAction(FPCCToExpand, MVT::f16, Expand);
382  setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, MVT::f16, Expand);
383  setOperationAction(ISD::BR_CC, MVT::f16, Expand);
384 
385  setOperationAction({ISD::FREM, ISD::FNEARBYINT, ISD::FPOW, ISD::FPOWI,
386  ISD::FCOS, ISD::FSIN, ISD::FSINCOS, ISD::FEXP,
387  ISD::FEXP2, ISD::FLOG, ISD::FLOG2, ISD::FLOG10},
388  MVT::f16, Promote);
389 
390  // FIXME: Need to promote f16 STRICT_* to f32 libcalls, but we don't have
391  // complete support for all operations in LegalizeDAG.
392  setOperationAction({ISD::STRICT_FCEIL, ISD::STRICT_FFLOOR,
393  ISD::STRICT_FNEARBYINT, ISD::STRICT_FRINT,
394  ISD::STRICT_FROUND, ISD::STRICT_FROUNDEVEN,
395  ISD::STRICT_FTRUNC},
396  MVT::f16, Promote);
397 
398  // We need to custom promote this.
399  if (Subtarget.is64Bit())
400  setOperationAction(ISD::FPOWI, MVT::i32, Custom);
401  }
402 
403  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtF()) {
404  setOperationAction(FPLegalNodeTypes, MVT::f32, Legal);
405  setOperationAction(FPRndMode, MVT::f32, Custom);
406  setCondCodeAction(FPCCToExpand, MVT::f32, Expand);
407  setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, MVT::f32, Expand);
408  setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, MVT::f32, Custom);
409  setOperationAction(ISD::BR_CC, MVT::f32, Expand);
410  setOperationAction(FPOpToExpand, MVT::f32, Expand);
411  setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, MVT::f32, MVT::f16, Expand);
412  setTruncStoreAction(MVT::f32, MVT::f16, Expand);
413  }
414 
415  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtF() && Subtarget.is64Bit())
416  setOperationAction(ISD::BITCAST, MVT::i32, Custom);
417 
418  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtD()) {
419  setOperationAction(FPLegalNodeTypes, MVT::f64, Legal);
420  if (Subtarget.is64Bit()) {
421  setOperationAction(FPRndMode, MVT::f64, Custom);
422  }
423  setOperationAction(ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND, MVT::f32, Legal);
424  setOperationAction(ISD::STRICT_FP_EXTEND, MVT::f64, Legal);
425  setCondCodeAction(FPCCToExpand, MVT::f64, Expand);
426  setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, MVT::f64, Expand);
427  setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, MVT::f64, Custom);
428  setOperationAction(ISD::BR_CC, MVT::f64, Expand);
429  setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, MVT::f64, MVT::f32, Expand);
430  setTruncStoreAction(MVT::f64, MVT::f32, Expand);
431  setOperationAction(FPOpToExpand, MVT::f64, Expand);
432  setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, MVT::f64, MVT::f16, Expand);
433  setTruncStoreAction(MVT::f64, MVT::f16, Expand);
434  }
435 
436  if (Subtarget.is64Bit())
437  setOperationAction({ISD::FP_TO_UINT, ISD::FP_TO_SINT,
438  ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT, ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT},
439  MVT::i32, Custom);
440 
441  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtF()) {
442  setOperationAction({ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT, ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT}, XLenVT,
443  Custom);
444 
445  setOperationAction({ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT, ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT,
446  ISD::STRICT_UINT_TO_FP, ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP},
447  XLenVT, Legal);
448 
449  setOperationAction(ISD::GET_ROUNDING, XLenVT, Custom);
450  setOperationAction(ISD::SET_ROUNDING, MVT::Other, Custom);
451  }
452 
453  setOperationAction({ISD::GlobalAddress, ISD::BlockAddress, ISD::ConstantPool,
454  ISD::JumpTable},
455  XLenVT, Custom);
456 
457  setOperationAction(ISD::GlobalTLSAddress, XLenVT, Custom);
458 
459  if (Subtarget.is64Bit())
460  setOperationAction(ISD::Constant, MVT::i64, Custom);
461 
462  // TODO: On M-mode only targets, the cycle[h] CSR may not be present.
463  // Unfortunately this can't be determined just from the ISA naming string.
464  setOperationAction(ISD::READCYCLECOUNTER, MVT::i64,
465  Subtarget.is64Bit() ? Legal : Custom);
466 
467  setOperationAction({ISD::TRAP, ISD::DEBUGTRAP}, MVT::Other, Legal);
468  setOperationAction(ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, MVT::Other, Custom);
469  if (Subtarget.is64Bit())
470  setOperationAction(ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, MVT::i32, Custom);
471 
472  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtA()) {
473  setMaxAtomicSizeInBitsSupported(Subtarget.getXLen());
474  setMinCmpXchgSizeInBits(32);
475  } else if (Subtarget.hasForcedAtomics()) {
476  setMaxAtomicSizeInBitsSupported(Subtarget.getXLen());
477  } else {
478  setMaxAtomicSizeInBitsSupported(0);
479  }
480 
481  setOperationAction(ISD::ATOMIC_FENCE, MVT::Other, Custom);
482 
483  setBooleanContents(ZeroOrOneBooleanContent);
484 
485  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructions()) {
486  setBooleanVectorContents(ZeroOrOneBooleanContent);
487 
488  setOperationAction(ISD::VSCALE, XLenVT, Custom);
489 
490  // RVV intrinsics may have illegal operands.
491  // We also need to custom legalize vmv.x.s.
492  setOperationAction({ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN},
493  {MVT::i8, MVT::i16}, Custom);
494  if (Subtarget.is64Bit())
495  setOperationAction(ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN, MVT::i32, Custom);
496  else
497  setOperationAction({ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN},
498  MVT::i64, Custom);
499 
500  setOperationAction({ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN, ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID},
501  MVT::Other, Custom);

503  static const unsigned IntegerVPOps[] = {
504  ISD::VP_ADD, ISD::VP_SUB, ISD::VP_MUL,

507  ISD::VP_XOR, ISD::VP_ASHR, ISD::VP_LSHR,

514  ISD::VP_SMAX, ISD::VP_UMIN, ISD::VP_UMAX,

518  ISD::VP_FADD, ISD::VP_FSUB, ISD::VP_FMUL,

538  if (!Subtarget.is64Bit()) {
539  // We must custom-lower certain vXi64 operations on RV32 due to the vector
540  // element type being illegal.
541  setOperationAction({ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT},
542  MVT::i64, Custom);

550  MVT::i64, Custom);

553  for (MVT VT : BoolVecVTs) {
554  if (!isTypeLegal(VT))
555  continue;
556 
557  setOperationAction(ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR, VT, Custom);
558 
559  // Mask VTs are custom-expanded into a series of standard nodes
560  setOperationAction({ISD::TRUNCATE, ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS,
561  ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR},
562  VT, Custom);
563 
564  setOperationAction({ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT}, VT,
565  Custom);
566 
567  setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, VT, Custom);
568  setOperationAction(
569  {ISD::SELECT_CC, ISD::VSELECT, ISD::VP_MERGE, ISD::VP_SELECT}, VT,
570  Expand);
571 
572  setOperationAction({ISD::VP_AND, ISD::VP_OR, ISD::VP_XOR}, VT, Custom);
573 
574  setOperationAction(
575  {ISD::VECREDUCE_AND, ISD::VECREDUCE_OR, ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR}, VT,
576  Custom);
577 
578  setOperationAction(
579  {ISD::VP_REDUCE_AND, ISD::VP_REDUCE_OR, ISD::VP_REDUCE_XOR}, VT,
580  Custom);
581 
582  // RVV has native int->float & float->int conversions where the
583  // element type sizes are within one power-of-two of each other. Any
584  // wider distances between type sizes have to be lowered as sequences
585  // which progressively narrow the gap in stages.
586  setOperationAction(
587  {ISD::SINT_TO_FP, ISD::UINT_TO_FP, ISD::FP_TO_SINT, ISD::FP_TO_UINT},
588  VT, Custom);
589  setOperationAction({ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT, ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT}, VT,
590  Custom);
591 
592  // Expand all extending loads to types larger than this, and truncating
593  // stores from types larger than this.
594  for (MVT OtherVT : MVT::integer_scalable_vector_valuetypes()) {
595  setTruncStoreAction(OtherVT, VT, Expand);
596  setLoadExtAction({ISD::EXTLOAD, ISD::SEXTLOAD, ISD::ZEXTLOAD}, OtherVT,
597  VT, Expand);
598  }
599 
600  setOperationAction({ISD::VP_FP_TO_SINT, ISD::VP_FP_TO_UINT,
601  ISD::VP_TRUNCATE, ISD::VP_SETCC},
602  VT, Custom);
603  setOperationAction(ISD::VECTOR_REVERSE, VT, Custom);
604 
605  setOperationPromotedToType(
606  ISD::VECTOR_SPLICE, VT,
607  MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i8, VT.getVectorElementCount()));
608  }
609 
610  for (MVT VT : IntVecVTs) {
611  if (!isTypeLegal(VT))
612  continue;
613 
614  setOperationAction(ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR, VT, Legal);
615  setOperationAction(ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR_PARTS, VT, Custom);
616 
617  // Vectors implement MULHS/MULHU.
618  setOperationAction({ISD::SMUL_LOHI, ISD::UMUL_LOHI}, VT, Expand);
619 
620  // nxvXi64 MULHS/MULHU requires the V extension instead of Zve64*.
621  if (VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i64 && !Subtarget.hasStdExtV())
622  setOperationAction({ISD::MULHU, ISD::MULHS}, VT, Expand);
623 
624  setOperationAction({ISD::SMIN, ISD::SMAX, ISD::UMIN, ISD::UMAX}, VT,
625  Legal);
626 
627  setOperationAction({ISD::ROTL, ISD::ROTR}, VT, Expand);
628 
629  setOperationAction({ISD::CTTZ, ISD::CTLZ, ISD::CTPOP}, VT, Expand);
630 
631  setOperationAction(ISD::BSWAP, VT, Expand);
632  setOperationAction({ISD::VP_BSWAP, ISD::VP_BITREVERSE}, VT, Expand);
633  setOperationAction({ISD::VP_FSHL, ISD::VP_FSHR}, VT, Expand);
634  setOperationAction({ISD::VP_CTLZ, ISD::VP_CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF, ISD::VP_CTTZ,
635  ISD::VP_CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF, ISD::VP_CTPOP},
636  VT, Expand);
637 
638  // Custom-lower extensions and truncations from/to mask types.
639  setOperationAction({ISD::ANY_EXTEND, ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, ISD::ZERO_EXTEND},
640  VT, Custom);
641 
642  // RVV has native int->float & float->int conversions where the
643  // element type sizes are within one power-of-two of each other. Any
644  // wider distances between type sizes have to be lowered as sequences
645  // which progressively narrow the gap in stages.
646  setOperationAction(
647  {ISD::SINT_TO_FP, ISD::UINT_TO_FP, ISD::FP_TO_SINT, ISD::FP_TO_UINT},
648  VT, Custom);
649  setOperationAction({ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT, ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT}, VT,
650  Custom);
651 
652  setOperationAction(
653  {ISD::SADDSAT, ISD::UADDSAT, ISD::SSUBSAT, ISD::USUBSAT}, VT, Legal);
654 
655  // Integer VTs are lowered as a series of "RISCVISD::TRUNCATE_VECTOR_VL"
656  // nodes which truncate by one power of two at a time.
657  setOperationAction(ISD::TRUNCATE, VT, Custom);
658 
659  // Custom-lower insert/extract operations to simplify patterns.
660  setOperationAction({ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT}, VT,
661  Custom);
662 
663  // Custom-lower reduction operations to set up the corresponding custom
664  // nodes' operands.
665  setOperationAction(IntegerVecReduceOps, VT, Custom);
666 
667  setOperationAction(IntegerVPOps, VT, Custom);
668 
669  setOperationAction({ISD::LOAD, ISD::STORE}, VT, Custom);
670 
671  setOperationAction({ISD::MLOAD, ISD::MSTORE, ISD::MGATHER, ISD::MSCATTER},
672  VT, Custom);
673 
674  setOperationAction(
675  {ISD::VP_LOAD, ISD::VP_STORE, ISD::EXPERIMENTAL_VP_STRIDED_LOAD,
676  ISD::EXPERIMENTAL_VP_STRIDED_STORE, ISD::VP_GATHER, ISD::VP_SCATTER},
677  VT, Custom);
678 
679  setOperationAction(
680  {ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR},
681  VT, Custom);
682 
683  setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, VT, Custom);
684  setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, VT, Expand);
685 
686  setOperationAction({ISD::STEP_VECTOR, ISD::VECTOR_REVERSE}, VT, Custom);
687 
688  for (MVT OtherVT : MVT::integer_scalable_vector_valuetypes()) {
689  setTruncStoreAction(VT, OtherVT, Expand);
690  setLoadExtAction({ISD::EXTLOAD, ISD::SEXTLOAD, ISD::ZEXTLOAD}, OtherVT,
691  VT, Expand);
692  }
693 
694  // Splice
695  setOperationAction(ISD::VECTOR_SPLICE, VT, Custom);
696 
697  // Lower CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF and CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF if element of VT in the range
698  // of f32.
699  EVT FloatVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::f32, VT.getVectorElementCount());
700  if (isTypeLegal(FloatVT)) {
701  setOperationAction(
702  {ISD::CTLZ, ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF, ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF}, VT,
703  Custom);
704  }
705  }
706 
707  // Expand various CCs to best match the RVV ISA, which natively supports UNE
708  // but no other unordered comparisons, and supports all ordered comparisons
709  // except ONE. Additionally, we expand GT,OGT,GE,OGE for optimization
710  // purposes; they are expanded to their swapped-operand CCs (LT,OLT,LE,OLE),
711  // and we pattern-match those back to the "original", swapping operands once
712  // more. This way we catch both operations and both "vf" and "fv" forms with
713  // fewer patterns.
714  static const ISD::CondCode VFPCCToExpand[] = {
715  ISD::SETO, ISD::SETONE, ISD::SETUEQ, ISD::SETUGT,
716  ISD::SETUGE, ISD::SETULT, ISD::SETULE, ISD::SETUO,
717  ISD::SETGT, ISD::SETOGT, ISD::SETGE, ISD::SETOGE,
718  };
719 
720  // Sets common operation actions on RVV floating-point vector types.
721  const auto SetCommonVFPActions = [&](MVT VT) {
722  setOperationAction(ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR, VT, Legal);
723  // RVV has native FP_ROUND & FP_EXTEND conversions where the element type
724  // sizes are within one power-of-two of each other. Therefore conversions
725  // between vXf16 and vXf64 must be lowered as sequences which convert via
726  // vXf32.
727  setOperationAction({ISD::FP_ROUND, ISD::FP_EXTEND}, VT, Custom);
728  // Custom-lower insert/extract operations to simplify patterns.
729  setOperationAction({ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT}, VT,
730  Custom);
731  // Expand various condition codes (explained above).
732  setCondCodeAction(VFPCCToExpand, VT, Expand);
733 
734  setOperationAction({ISD::FMINNUM, ISD::FMAXNUM}, VT, Legal);
735 
736  setOperationAction(
737  {ISD::FTRUNC, ISD::FCEIL, ISD::FFLOOR, ISD::FROUND, ISD::FROUNDEVEN},
738  VT, Custom);
739 
740  setOperationAction(FloatingPointVecReduceOps, VT, Custom);
741 
742  // Expand FP operations that need libcalls.
743  setOperationAction(ISD::FREM, VT, Expand);
744  setOperationAction(ISD::FPOW, VT, Expand);
745  setOperationAction(ISD::FCOS, VT, Expand);
746  setOperationAction(ISD::FSIN, VT, Expand);
747  setOperationAction(ISD::FSINCOS, VT, Expand);
748  setOperationAction(ISD::FEXP, VT, Expand);
749  setOperationAction(ISD::FEXP2, VT, Expand);
750  setOperationAction(ISD::FLOG, VT, Expand);
751  setOperationAction(ISD::FLOG2, VT, Expand);
752  setOperationAction(ISD::FLOG10, VT, Expand);
753  setOperationAction(ISD::FRINT, VT, Expand);
754  setOperationAction(ISD::FNEARBYINT, VT, Expand);
755 
756  setOperationAction(ISD::FCOPYSIGN, VT, Legal);
757 
758  setOperationAction({ISD::LOAD, ISD::STORE}, VT, Custom);
759 
760  setOperationAction({ISD::MLOAD, ISD::MSTORE, ISD::MGATHER, ISD::MSCATTER},
761  VT, Custom);
762 
763  setOperationAction(
764  {ISD::VP_LOAD, ISD::VP_STORE, ISD::EXPERIMENTAL_VP_STRIDED_LOAD,
765  ISD::EXPERIMENTAL_VP_STRIDED_STORE, ISD::VP_GATHER, ISD::VP_SCATTER},
766  VT, Custom);
767 
768  setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, VT, Custom);
769  setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, VT, Expand);
770 
771  setOperationAction(
772  {ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR},
773  VT, Custom);
774 
775  setOperationAction({ISD::VECTOR_REVERSE, ISD::VECTOR_SPLICE}, VT, Custom);
776 
777  setOperationAction(FloatingPointVPOps, VT, Custom);
778  };
779 
780  // Sets common extload/truncstore actions on RVV floating-point vector
781  // types.
782  const auto SetCommonVFPExtLoadTruncStoreActions =
783  [&](MVT VT, ArrayRef<MVT::SimpleValueType> SmallerVTs) {
784  for (auto SmallVT : SmallerVTs) {
785  setTruncStoreAction(VT, SmallVT, Expand);
786  setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, VT, SmallVT, Expand);
787  }
788  };
789 
790  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructionsF16()) {
791  for (MVT VT : F16VecVTs) {
792  if (!isTypeLegal(VT))
793  continue;
794  SetCommonVFPActions(VT);
795  }
796  }
797 
798  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructionsF32()) {
799  for (MVT VT : F32VecVTs) {
800  if (!isTypeLegal(VT))
801  continue;
802  SetCommonVFPActions(VT);
803  SetCommonVFPExtLoadTruncStoreActions(VT, F16VecVTs);
804  }
805  }
806 
807  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructionsF64()) {
808  for (MVT VT : F64VecVTs) {
809  if (!isTypeLegal(VT))
810  continue;
811  SetCommonVFPActions(VT);
812  SetCommonVFPExtLoadTruncStoreActions(VT, F16VecVTs);
813  SetCommonVFPExtLoadTruncStoreActions(VT, F32VecVTs);
814  }

817  if (Subtarget.useRVVForFixedLengthVectors()) {
818  for (MVT VT : MVT::integer_fixedlen_vector_valuetypes()) {
819  if (!useRVVForFixedLengthVectorVT(VT))
820  continue;

822  // By default everything must be expanded.
823  for (unsigned Op = 0; Op < ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END; ++Op)
824  setOperationAction(Op, VT, Expand);

826  setTruncStoreAction(VT, OtherVT, Expand);
827  setLoadExtAction({ISD::EXTLOAD, ISD::SEXTLOAD, ISD::ZEXTLOAD},
828  OtherVT, VT, Expand);
829  }
830 
831  // We use EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR as a "cast" from scalable to fixed.
832  setOperationAction({ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR}, VT,
833  Custom);
834 
835  setOperationAction({ISD::BUILD_VECTOR, ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS}, VT,
836  Custom);
837 
838  setOperationAction({ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT},
839  VT, Custom);
840 
841  setOperationAction({ISD::LOAD, ISD::STORE}, VT, Custom);
842 
843  setOperationAction(ISD::SETCC, VT, Custom);
844 
845  setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, VT, Custom);
846 
847  setOperationAction(ISD::TRUNCATE, VT, Custom);
848 
849  setOperationAction(ISD::BITCAST, VT, Custom);
850 
851  setOperationAction(
852  {ISD::VECREDUCE_AND, ISD::VECREDUCE_OR, ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR}, VT,
853  Custom);
854 
855  setOperationAction(
856  {ISD::VP_REDUCE_AND, ISD::VP_REDUCE_OR, ISD::VP_REDUCE_XOR}, VT,
857  Custom);
858 
859  setOperationAction({ISD::SINT_TO_FP, ISD::UINT_TO_FP, ISD::FP_TO_SINT,
860  ISD::FP_TO_UINT},
861  VT, Custom);
862  setOperationAction({ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT, ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT}, VT,
863  Custom);
864 
865  // Operations below are different for between masks and other vectors.
866  if (VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1) {
867  setOperationAction({ISD::VP_AND, ISD::VP_OR, ISD::VP_XOR, ISD::AND,
868  ISD::OR, ISD::XOR},
869  VT, Custom);
870 
871  setOperationAction({ISD::VP_FP_TO_SINT, ISD::VP_FP_TO_UINT,
872  ISD::VP_SETCC, ISD::VP_TRUNCATE},
873  VT, Custom);
874  continue;

878  // it before type legalization for i64 vectors on RV32. It will then be
879  // type legalized to SPLAT_VECTOR_PARTS which we need to Custom handle.
880  // FIXME: Use SPLAT_VECTOR for all types? DAGCombine probably needs
881  // improvements first.

883  setOperationAction(ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR, VT, Legal);
884  setOperationAction(ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR_PARTS, VT, Custom);
885  }

887  setOperationAction(ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE, VT, Custom);

893  ISD::EXPERIMENTAL_VP_STRIDED_LOAD,

898  setOperationAction({ISD::ADD, ISD::MUL, ISD::SUB, ISD::AND, ISD::OR,
899  ISD::XOR, ISD::SDIV, ISD::SREM, ISD::UDIV,

901  VT, Custom);

904  {ISD::SMIN, ISD::SMAX, ISD::UMIN, ISD::UMAX, ISD::ABS}, VT, Custom);

906  // vXi64 MULHS/MULHU requires the V extension instead of Zve64*.
907  if (VT.getVectorElementType() != MVT::i64 || Subtarget.hasStdExtV())
908  setOperationAction({ISD::MULHS, ISD::MULHU}, VT, Custom);
909 
910  setOperationAction(
911  {ISD::SADDSAT, ISD::UADDSAT, ISD::SSUBSAT, ISD::USUBSAT}, VT,
912  Custom);

914  setOperationAction(ISD::VSELECT, VT, Custom);

917  setOperationAction(
918  {ISD::ANY_EXTEND, ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, ISD::ZERO_EXTEND}, VT, Custom);

920  // Custom-lower reduction operations to set up the corresponding custom
921  // nodes' operands.
922  setOperationAction({ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD, ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX,
923  ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN, ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX,
924  ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN},
925  VT, Custom);

927  setOperationAction(IntegerVPOps, VT, Custom);

930  // range of f32.

932  if (isTypeLegal(FloatVT))

940  continue;

944  setOperationAction(Op, VT, Expand);

946  setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, OtherVT, VT, Expand);
947  setTruncStoreAction(VT, OtherVT, Expand);
948  }

950  // We use EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR as a "cast" from scalable to fixed.
951  setOperationAction({ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR}, VT,
952  Custom);
953 
954  setOperationAction({ISD::BUILD_VECTOR, ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS,
955  ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE, ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT,
956  ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT},
957  VT, Custom);

959  setOperationAction({ISD::LOAD, ISD::STORE, ISD::MLOAD, ISD::MSTORE,
960  ISD::MGATHER, ISD::MSCATTER},
961  VT, Custom);
962 
963  setOperationAction({ISD::VP_LOAD, ISD::VP_STORE,
964  ISD::EXPERIMENTAL_VP_STRIDED_LOAD,
965  ISD::EXPERIMENTAL_VP_STRIDED_STORE, ISD::VP_GATHER,
966  ISD::VP_SCATTER},
967  VT, Custom);

970  ISD::FNEG, ISD::FABS, ISD::FCOPYSIGN, ISD::FSQRT,
971  ISD::FMA, ISD::FMINNUM, ISD::FMAXNUM},

974  setOperationAction({ISD::FP_ROUND, ISD::FP_EXTEND}, VT, Custom);
975 
976  setOperationAction({ISD::FTRUNC, ISD::FCEIL, ISD::FFLOOR, ISD::FROUND,
977  ISD::FROUNDEVEN},
978  VT, Custom);
979 
980  setCondCodeAction(VFPCCToExpand, VT, Expand);
981 
982  setOperationAction({ISD::VSELECT, ISD::SELECT}, VT, Custom);
983  setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, VT, Expand);
984 
985  setOperationAction(ISD::BITCAST, VT, Custom);
986 
987  setOperationAction(FloatingPointVecReduceOps, VT, Custom);
988 
989  setOperationAction(FloatingPointVPOps, VT, Custom);
990  }
991 
992  // Custom-legalize bitcasts from fixed-length vectors to scalar types.
993  setOperationAction(ISD::BITCAST, {MVT::i8, MVT::i16, MVT::i32, MVT::i64},
994  Custom);
995  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZfhOrZfhmin())
996  setOperationAction(ISD::BITCAST, MVT::f16, Custom);
997  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtF())
998  setOperationAction(ISD::BITCAST, MVT::f32, Custom);
999  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtD())
1000  setOperationAction(ISD::BITCAST, MVT::f64, Custom);
1001  }
1002  }
1003 
1004  if (Subtarget.hasForcedAtomics()) {
1005  // Set atomic rmw/cas operations to expand to force __sync libcalls.
1006  setOperationAction(
1007  {ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP, ISD::ATOMIC_SWAP, ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD,
1008  ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB, ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND, ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR,
1009  ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR, ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND, ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN,
1010  ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX, ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN, ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX},
1011  XLenVT, Expand);
1012  }
1013 
1014  // Function alignments.
1015  const Align FunctionAlignment(Subtarget.hasStdExtCOrZca() ? 2 : 4);
1016  setMinFunctionAlignment(FunctionAlignment);
1017  setPrefFunctionAlignment(FunctionAlignment);
1018 
1019  setMinimumJumpTableEntries(5);
1020 
1021  // Jumps are expensive, compared to logic
1022  setJumpIsExpensive();
1023 
1024  setTargetDAGCombine({ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, ISD::ADD, ISD::SUB, ISD::AND,
1025  ISD::OR, ISD::XOR, ISD::SETCC, ISD::SELECT});
1026  if (Subtarget.is64Bit())
1027  setTargetDAGCombine(ISD::SRA);
1028 
1029  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtF())
1030  setTargetDAGCombine({ISD::FADD, ISD::FMAXNUM, ISD::FMINNUM});
1031 
1032  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZbb())
1033  setTargetDAGCombine({ISD::UMAX, ISD::UMIN, ISD::SMAX, ISD::SMIN});
1034 
1035  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZbs() && Subtarget.is64Bit())
1036  setTargetDAGCombine(ISD::TRUNCATE);
1037 
1038  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZbkb())
1039  setTargetDAGCombine(ISD::BITREVERSE);
1040  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZfhOrZfhmin())
1041  setTargetDAGCombine(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG);
1042  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtF())
1043  setTargetDAGCombine({ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, ISD::FP_TO_SINT, ISD::FP_TO_UINT,
1044  ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT, ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT});
1045  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructions())
1046  setTargetDAGCombine({ISD::FCOPYSIGN, ISD::MGATHER, ISD::MSCATTER,
1047  ISD::VP_GATHER, ISD::VP_SCATTER, ISD::SRA, ISD::SRL,
1048  ISD::SHL, ISD::STORE, ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR});
1049  if (Subtarget.useRVVForFixedLengthVectors())
1050  setTargetDAGCombine(ISD::BITCAST);
1051 
1052  setLibcallName(RTLIB::FPEXT_F16_F32, "__extendhfsf2");
1053  setLibcallName(RTLIB::FPROUND_F32_F16, "__truncsfhf2");
1054 }

1062  (VT.isScalableVector() || Subtarget.useRVVForFixedLengthVectors()))

1071 bool RISCVTargetLowering::getTgtMemIntrinsic(IntrinsicInfo &Info,
1072  const CallInst &I,
1073  MachineFunction &MF,
1074  unsigned Intrinsic) const {
1075  auto &DL = I.getModule()->getDataLayout();
1076  switch (Intrinsic) {
1077  default:
1078  return false;
1079  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_xchg_i32:
1080  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_add_i32:
1081  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_sub_i32:
1082  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_nand_i32:
1083  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_max_i32:
1084  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_min_i32:
1085  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_umax_i32:
1086  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_umin_i32:
1087  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_cmpxchg_i32:
1088  Info.opc = ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN;
1089  Info.memVT = MVT::i32;
1090  Info.ptrVal = I.getArgOperand(0);
1091  Info.offset = 0;
1092  Info.align = Align(4);
1093  Info.flags = MachineMemOperand::MOLoad | MachineMemOperand::MOStore |
1094  MachineMemOperand::MOVolatile;
1095  return true;
1096  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_strided_load:
1097  Info.opc = ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN;
1098  Info.ptrVal = I.getArgOperand(1);
1099  Info.memVT = getValueType(DL, I.getType()->getScalarType());
1100  Info.align = Align(DL.getTypeSizeInBits(I.getType()->getScalarType()) / 8);
1101  Info.size = MemoryLocation::UnknownSize;
1102  Info.flags |= MachineMemOperand::MOLoad;
1103  return true;
1104  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_strided_store:
1105  Info.opc = ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID;
1106  Info.ptrVal = I.getArgOperand(1);
1107  Info.memVT =
1108  getValueType(DL, I.getArgOperand(0)->getType()->getScalarType());
1109  Info.align = Align(
1110  DL.getTypeSizeInBits(I.getArgOperand(0)->getType()->getScalarType()) /
1111  8);
1112  Info.size = MemoryLocation::UnknownSize;
1113  Info.flags |= MachineMemOperand::MOStore;
1114  return true;
1115  case Intrinsic::riscv_seg2_load:
1116  case Intrinsic::riscv_seg3_load:
1117  case Intrinsic::riscv_seg4_load:
1118  case Intrinsic::riscv_seg5_load:
1119  case Intrinsic::riscv_seg6_load:
1120  case Intrinsic::riscv_seg7_load:
1121  case Intrinsic::riscv_seg8_load:
1122  Info.opc = ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN;
1123  Info.ptrVal = I.getArgOperand(0);
1124  Info.memVT =
1125  getValueType(DL, I.getType()->getStructElementType(0)->getScalarType());
1126  Info.align =
1127  Align(DL.getTypeSizeInBits(
1128  I.getType()->getStructElementType(0)->getScalarType()) /
1129  8);
1130  Info.size = MemoryLocation::UnknownSize;
1131  Info.flags |= MachineMemOperand::MOLoad;
1132  return true;
1133  }
1134 }
1135 
1136 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isLegalAddressingMode(const DataLayout &DL,
1137  const AddrMode &AM, Type *Ty,
1138  unsigned AS,
1139  Instruction *I) const {
1140  // No global is ever allowed as a base.
1141  if (AM.BaseGV)
1142  return false;
1143 
1144  // RVV instructions only support register addressing.
1145  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructions() && isa<VectorType>(Ty))
1146  return AM.HasBaseReg && AM.Scale == 0 && !AM.BaseOffs;
1147 
1148  // Require a 12-bit signed offset.
1149  if (!isInt<12>(AM.BaseOffs))
1150  return false;
1151 
1152  switch (AM.Scale) {
1153  case 0: // "r+i" or just "i", depending on HasBaseReg.
1154  break;
1155  case 1:
1156  if (!AM.HasBaseReg) // allow "r+i".
1157  break;
1158  return false; // disallow "r+r" or "r+r+i".
1159  default:
1160  return false;
1161  }
1162 
1163  return true;
1164 }
1165 
1166 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isLegalICmpImmediate(int64_t Imm) const {
1167  return isInt<12>(Imm);
1168 }
1169 
1170 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isLegalAddImmediate(int64_t Imm) const {
1171  return isInt<12>(Imm);
1172 }
1173 
1174 // On RV32, 64-bit integers are split into their high and low parts and held
1175 // in two different registers, so the trunc is free since the low register can
1176 // just be used.
1177 // FIXME: Should we consider i64->i32 free on RV64 to match the EVT version of
1178 // isTruncateFree?
1179 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isTruncateFree(Type *SrcTy, Type *DstTy) const {
1180  if (Subtarget.is64Bit() || !SrcTy->isIntegerTy() || !DstTy->isIntegerTy())
1181  return false;
1182  unsigned SrcBits = SrcTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
1183  unsigned DestBits = DstTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
1184  return (SrcBits == 64 && DestBits == 32);
1185 }
1186 
1187 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isTruncateFree(EVT SrcVT, EVT DstVT) const {
1188  // We consider i64->i32 free on RV64 since we have good selection of W
1189  // instructions that make promoting operations back to i64 free in many cases.
1190  if (SrcVT.isVector() || DstVT.isVector() || !SrcVT.isInteger() ||
1191  !DstVT.isInteger())
1192  return false;
1193  unsigned SrcBits = SrcVT.getSizeInBits();
1194  unsigned DestBits = DstVT.getSizeInBits();
1195  return (SrcBits == 64 && DestBits == 32);
1196 }

1198 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isZExtFree(SDValue Val, EVT VT2) const {
1199  // Zexts are free if they can be combined with a load.
1200  // Don't advertise i32->i64 zextload as being free for RV64. It interacts
1201  // poorly with type legalization of compares preferring sext.
1202  if (auto *LD = dyn_cast<LoadSDNode>(Val)) {
1203  EVT MemVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
1204  if ((MemVT == MVT::i8 || MemVT == MVT::i16) &&
1205  (LD->getExtensionType() == ISD::NON_EXTLOAD ||
1206  LD->getExtensionType() == ISD::ZEXTLOAD))
1207  return true;
1208  }
1209 
1210  return TargetLowering::isZExtFree(Val, VT2);
1211 }

1215 }

1228 
1229 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isMaskAndCmp0FoldingBeneficial(
1230  const Instruction &AndI) const {
1231  // We expect to be able to match a bit extraction instruction if the Zbs
1232  // extension is supported and the mask is a power of two. However, we
1233  // conservatively return false if the mask would fit in an ANDI instruction,
1234  // on the basis that it's possible the sinking+duplication of the AND in
1235  // CodeGenPrepare triggered by this hook wouldn't decrease the instruction
1236  // count and would increase code size (e.g. ANDI+BNEZ => BEXTI+BNEZ).
1237  if (!Subtarget.hasStdExtZbs() && !Subtarget.hasVendorXTHeadBs())
1238  return false;
1239  ConstantInt *Mask = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(AndI.getOperand(1));
1240  if (!Mask)
1241  return false;
1242  return !Mask->getValue().isSignedIntN(12) && Mask->getValue().isPowerOf2();
1243 }

1245 bool RISCVTargetLowering::hasAndNotCompare(SDValue Y) const {
1246  EVT VT = Y.getValueType();
1247 
1248  // FIXME: Support vectors once we have tests.
1249  if (VT.isVector())
1250  return false;
1251 
1252  return (Subtarget.hasStdExtZbb() || Subtarget.hasStdExtZbkb()) &&
1253  !isa<ConstantSDNode>(Y);
1254 }
1255 
1256 bool RISCVTargetLowering::hasBitTest(SDValue X, SDValue Y) const {
1257  // Zbs provides BEXT[_I], which can be used with SEQZ/SNEZ as a bit test.
1258  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZbs())
1259  return X.getValueType().isScalarInteger();
1260  auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Y);
1261  // XTheadBs provides th.tst (similar to bexti), if Y is a constant
1262  if (Subtarget.hasVendorXTHeadBs())
1263  return C != nullptr;
1264  // We can use ANDI+SEQZ/SNEZ as a bit test. Y contains the bit position.
1265  return C && C->getAPIntValue().ule(10);
1266 }

1268 bool RISCVTargetLowering::shouldFoldSelectWithIdentityConstant(unsigned Opcode,
1269  EVT VT) const {
1270  // Only enable for rvv.
1271  if (!VT.isVector() || !Subtarget.hasVInstructions())
1272  return false;
1273 
1274  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector() && !isTypeLegal(VT))
1275  return false;
1276 
1277  return true;
1278 }
1279 
1280 bool RISCVTargetLowering::shouldConvertConstantLoadToIntImm(const APInt &Imm,
1281  Type *Ty) const {
1282  assert(Ty->isIntegerTy());
1283 
1284  unsigned BitSize = Ty->getIntegerBitWidth();
1285  if (BitSize > Subtarget.getXLen())
1286  return false;
1287 
1288  // Fast path, assume 32-bit immediates are cheap.
1289  int64_t Val = Imm.getSExtValue();
1290  if (isInt<32>(Val))
1291  return true;
1292 
1293  // A constant pool entry may be more aligned thant he load we're trying to
1294  // replace. If we don't support unaligned scalar mem, prefer the constant
1295  // pool.
1296  // TODO: Can the caller pass down the alignment?
1297  if (!Subtarget.enableUnalignedScalarMem())
1298  return true;
1299 
1300  // Prefer to keep the load if it would require many instructions.
1301  // This uses the same threshold we use for constant pools but doesn't
1302  // check useConstantPoolForLargeInts.
1303  // TODO: Should we keep the load only when we're definitely going to emit a
1304  // constant pool?
1305 
1306  RISCVMatInt::InstSeq Seq =
1307  RISCVMatInt::generateInstSeq(Val, Subtarget.getFeatureBits());
1308  return Seq.size() <= Subtarget.getMaxBuildIntsCost();
1309 }
1310 
1311 bool RISCVTargetLowering::
1312  shouldProduceAndByConstByHoistingConstFromShiftsLHSOfAnd(
1313  SDValue X, ConstantSDNode *XC, ConstantSDNode *CC, SDValue Y,
1314  unsigned OldShiftOpcode, unsigned NewShiftOpcode,
1315  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1316  // One interesting pattern that we'd want to form is 'bit extract':
1317  // ((1 >> Y) & 1) ==/!= 0
1318  // But we also need to be careful not to try to reverse that fold.
1319 
1320  // Is this '((1 >> Y) & 1)'?
1321  if (XC && OldShiftOpcode == ISD::SRL && XC->isOne())
1322  return false; // Keep the 'bit extract' pattern.
1323 
1324  // Will this be '((1 >> Y) & 1)' after the transform?
1325  if (NewShiftOpcode == ISD::SRL && CC->isOne())
1326  return true; // Do form the 'bit extract' pattern.
1327 
1328  // If 'X' is a constant, and we transform, then we will immediately
1329  // try to undo the fold, thus causing endless combine loop.
1330  // So only do the transform if X is not a constant. This matches the default
1331  // implementation of this function.
1332  return !XC;
1333 }
1334 
1335 bool RISCVTargetLowering::canSplatOperand(unsigned Opcode, int Operand) const {
1336  switch (Opcode) {
1337  case Instruction::Add:
1338  case Instruction::Sub:
1339  case Instruction::Mul:
1340  case Instruction::And:
1341  case Instruction::Or:
1342  case Instruction::Xor:
1343  case Instruction::FAdd:
1344  case Instruction::FSub:
1345  case Instruction::FMul:
1346  case Instruction::FDiv:
1347  case Instruction::ICmp:
1348  case Instruction::FCmp:
1349  return true;
1350  case Instruction::Shl:
1351  case Instruction::LShr:
1352  case Instruction::AShr:
1353  case Instruction::UDiv:
1354  case Instruction::SDiv:
1355  case Instruction::URem:
1356  case Instruction::SRem:
1357  return Operand == 1;
1358  default:
1359  return false;
1360  }
1361 }
1362 
1363 
1364 bool RISCVTargetLowering::canSplatOperand(Instruction *I, int Operand) const {
1365  if (!I->getType()->isVectorTy() || !Subtarget.hasVInstructions())
1366  return false;
1367 
1368  if (canSplatOperand(I->getOpcode(), Operand))
1369  return true;
1370 
1371  auto *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(I);
1372  if (!II)
1373  return false;
1374 
1375  switch (II->getIntrinsicID()) {
1376  case Intrinsic::fma:
1377  case Intrinsic::vp_fma:
1378  return Operand == 0 || Operand == 1;
1379  case Intrinsic::vp_shl:
1380  case Intrinsic::vp_lshr:
1381  case Intrinsic::vp_ashr:
1382  case Intrinsic::vp_udiv:
1383  case Intrinsic::vp_sdiv:
1384  case Intrinsic::vp_urem:
1385  case Intrinsic::vp_srem:
1386  return Operand == 1;
1387  // These intrinsics are commutative.
1388  case Intrinsic::vp_add:
1389  case Intrinsic::vp_mul:
1390  case Intrinsic::vp_and:
1391  case Intrinsic::vp_or:
1392  case Intrinsic::vp_xor:
1393  case Intrinsic::vp_fadd:
1394  case Intrinsic::vp_fmul:
1395  // These intrinsics have 'vr' versions.
1396  case Intrinsic::vp_sub:
1397  case Intrinsic::vp_fsub:
1398  case Intrinsic::vp_fdiv:
1399  return Operand == 0 || Operand == 1;
1400  default:
1401  return false;
1402  }
1403 }
1404 
1405 /// Check if sinking \p I's operands to I's basic block is profitable, because
1406 /// the operands can be folded into a target instruction, e.g.
1407 /// splats of scalars can fold into vector instructions.
1408 bool RISCVTargetLowering::shouldSinkOperands(
1409  Instruction *I, SmallVectorImpl<Use *> &Ops) const {
1410  using namespace llvm::PatternMatch;
1411 
1412  if (!I->getType()->isVectorTy() || !Subtarget.hasVInstructions())
1413  return false;
1414 
1415  for (auto OpIdx : enumerate(I->operands())) {
1416  if (!canSplatOperand(I, OpIdx.index()))
1417  continue;
1418 
1419  Instruction *Op = dyn_cast<Instruction>(OpIdx.value().get());
1420  // Make sure we are not already sinking this operand
1421  if (!Op || any_of(Ops, [&](Use *U) { return U->get() == Op; }))
1422  continue;
1423 
1424  // We are looking for a splat that can be sunk.
1425  if (!match(Op, m_Shuffle(m_InsertElt(m_Undef(), m_Value(), m_ZeroInt()),
1426  m_Undef(), m_ZeroMask())))
1427  continue;
1428 
1429  // All uses of the shuffle should be sunk to avoid duplicating it across gpr
1430  // and vector registers
1431  for (Use &U : Op->uses()) {
1432  Instruction *Insn = cast<Instruction>(U.getUser());
1433  if (!canSplatOperand(Insn, U.getOperandNo()))
1434  return false;
1435  }
1436 
1437  Ops.push_back(&Op->getOperandUse(0));
1438  Ops.push_back(&OpIdx.value());
1439  }
1440  return true;
1441 }
1442 
1443 bool RISCVTargetLowering::shouldScalarizeBinop(SDValue VecOp) const {
1444  unsigned Opc = VecOp.getOpcode();
1445 
1446  // Assume target opcodes can't be scalarized.
1447  // TODO - do we have any exceptions?
1448  if (Opc >= ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END)
1449  return false;
1450 
1451  // If the vector op is not supported, try to convert to scalar.
1452  EVT VecVT = VecOp.getValueType();
1453  if (!isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(Opc, VecVT))
1454  return true;
1455 
1456  // If the vector op is supported, but the scalar op is not, the transform may
1457  // not be worthwhile.
1458  EVT ScalarVT = VecVT.getScalarType();
1459  return isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(Opc, ScalarVT);
1460 }
1461 
1462 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isOffsetFoldingLegal(
1463  const GlobalAddressSDNode *GA) const {
1464  // In order to maximise the opportunity for common subexpression elimination,
1465  // keep a separate ADD node for the global address offset instead of folding
1466  // it in the global address node. Later peephole optimisations may choose to
1467  // fold it back in when profitable.
1468  return false;
1469 }
1470 
1471 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isFPImmLegal(const APFloat &Imm, EVT VT,
1472  bool ForCodeSize) const {
1473  if (VT == MVT::f16 && !Subtarget.hasStdExtZfhOrZfhmin())
1474  return false;
1475  if (VT == MVT::f32 && !Subtarget.hasStdExtF())
1476  return false;
1477  if (VT == MVT::f64 && !Subtarget.hasStdExtD())
1478  return false;
1479  // Cannot create a 64 bit floating-point immediate value for rv32.
1480  if (Subtarget.getXLen() < VT.getScalarSizeInBits()) {
1481  // td can handle +0.0 or -0.0 already.
1482  // -0.0 can be created by fmv + fneg.
1483  return Imm.isZero();
1484  }
1485  // Special case: the cost for -0.0 is 1.
1486  int Cost = Imm.isNegZero()
1487  ? 1
1488  : RISCVMatInt::getIntMatCost(Imm.bitcastToAPInt(),
1489  Subtarget.getXLen(),
1490  Subtarget.getFeatureBits());
1491  // If the constantpool data is already in cache, only Cost 1 is cheaper.
1492  return Cost < FPImmCost;
1493 }
1494 
1495 // TODO: This is very conservative.
1496 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isExtractSubvectorCheap(EVT ResVT, EVT SrcVT,
1497  unsigned Index) const {
1498  if (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, ResVT))
1499  return false;
1500 
1501  // Only support extracting a fixed from a fixed vector for now.
1502  if (ResVT.isScalableVector() || SrcVT.isScalableVector())
1503  return false;
1504 
1505  unsigned ResElts = ResVT.getVectorNumElements();
1506  unsigned SrcElts = SrcVT.getVectorNumElements();
1507 
1508  // Convervatively only handle extracting half of a vector.
1509  // TODO: Relax this.
1510  if ((ResElts * 2) != SrcElts)
1511  return false;
1512 
1513  // The smallest type we can slide is i8.
1514  // TODO: We can extract index 0 from a mask vector without a slide.
1515  if (ResVT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
1516  return false;
1517 
1518  // Slide can support arbitrary index, but we only treat vslidedown.vi as
1519  // cheap.
1520  if (Index >= 32)
1521  return false;
1522 
1523  // TODO: We can do arbitrary slidedowns, but for now only support extracting
1524  // the upper half of a vector until we have more test coverage.
1525  return Index == 0 || Index == ResElts;
1526 }
1527 
1528 MVT RISCVTargetLowering::getRegisterTypeForCallingConv(LLVMContext &Context,
1529  CallingConv::ID CC,
1530  EVT VT) const {
1531  // Use f32 to pass f16 if it is legal and Zfh/Zfhmin is not enabled.
1532  // We might still end up using a GPR but that will be decided based on ABI.
1533  if (VT == MVT::f16 && Subtarget.hasStdExtF() &&
1534  !Subtarget.hasStdExtZfhOrZfhmin())
1535  return MVT::f32;
1536 
1537  return TargetLowering::getRegisterTypeForCallingConv(Context, CC, VT);
1538 }
1539 
1540 unsigned RISCVTargetLowering::getNumRegistersForCallingConv(LLVMContext &Context,
1541  CallingConv::ID CC,
1542  EVT VT) const {
1543  // Use f32 to pass f16 if it is legal and Zfh/Zfhmin is not enabled.
1544  // We might still end up using a GPR but that will be decided based on ABI.
1545  if (VT == MVT::f16 && Subtarget.hasStdExtF() &&
1546  !Subtarget.hasStdExtZfhOrZfhmin())
1547  return 1;
1548 
1549  return TargetLowering::getNumRegistersForCallingConv(Context, CC, VT);
1550 }
1551 
1552 // Changes the condition code and swaps operands if necessary, so the SetCC
1553 // operation matches one of the comparisons supported directly by branches
1554 // in the RISC-V ISA. May adjust compares to favor compare with 0 over compare
1555 // with 1/-1.
1556 static void translateSetCCForBranch(const SDLoc &DL, SDValue &LHS, SDValue &RHS,
1557  ISD::CondCode &CC, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
1558  // If this is a single bit test that can't be handled by ANDI, shift the
1559  // bit to be tested to the MSB and perform a signed compare with 0.
1560  if (isIntEqualitySetCC(CC) && isNullConstant(RHS) &&
1561  LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::AND && LHS.hasOneUse() &&
1562  isa<ConstantSDNode>(LHS.getOperand(1))) {
1563  uint64_t Mask = LHS.getConstantOperandVal(1);
1564  if ((isPowerOf2_64(Mask) || isMask_64(Mask)) && !isInt<12>(Mask)) {
1565  unsigned ShAmt = 0;
1566  if (isPowerOf2_64(Mask)) {
1567  CC = CC == ISD::SETEQ ? ISD::SETGE : ISD::SETLT;
1568  ShAmt = LHS.getValueSizeInBits() - 1 - Log2_64(Mask);
1569  } else {
1570  ShAmt = LHS.getValueSizeInBits() - llvm::bit_width(Mask);
1571  }
1572 
1573  LHS = LHS.getOperand(0);
1574  if (ShAmt != 0)
1575  LHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, LHS.getValueType(), LHS,
1576  DAG.getConstant(ShAmt, DL, LHS.getValueType()));
1577  return;
1578  }
1579  }
1580 
1581  if (auto *RHSC = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS)) {
1582  int64_t C = RHSC->getSExtValue();
1583  switch (CC) {
1584  default: break;
1585  case ISD::SETGT:
1586  // Convert X > -1 to X >= 0.
1587  if (C == -1) {
1588  RHS = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, RHS.getValueType());
1589  CC = ISD::SETGE;
1590  return;
1591  }
1592  break;
1593  case ISD::SETLT:
1594  // Convert X < 1 to 0 <= X.
1595  if (C == 1) {
1596  RHS = LHS;
1597  LHS = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, RHS.getValueType());
1598  CC = ISD::SETGE;
1599  return;
1600  }
1601  break;
1602  }
1603  }
1604 
1605  switch (CC) {
1606  default:
1607  break;
1608  case ISD::SETGT:
1609  case ISD::SETLE:
1610  case ISD::SETUGT:
1611  case ISD::SETULE:
1612  CC = ISD::getSetCCSwappedOperands(CC);
1613  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
1614  break;
1615  }
1616 }
1617 
1618 RISCVII::VLMUL RISCVTargetLowering::getLMUL(MVT VT) {
1619  assert(VT.isScalableVector() && "Expecting a scalable vector type");
1620  unsigned KnownSize = VT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue();
1621  if (VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
1622  KnownSize *= 8;
1623 
1624  switch (KnownSize) {
1625  default:
1626  llvm_unreachable("Invalid LMUL.");
1627  case 8:
1628  return RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F8;
1629  case 16:
1630  return RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F4;
1631  case 32:
1632  return RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F2;
1633  case 64:
1634  return RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_1;
1635  case 128:
1636  return RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_2;
1637  case 256:
1638  return RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_4;
1639  case 512:
1640  return RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_8;
1641  }
1642 }
1643 
1644 unsigned RISCVTargetLowering::getRegClassIDForLMUL(RISCVII::VLMUL LMul) {
1645  switch (LMul) {
1646  default:
1647  llvm_unreachable("Invalid LMUL.");
1648  case RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F8:
1649  case RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F4:
1650  case RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F2:
1651  case RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_1:
1652  return RISCV::VRRegClassID;
1653  case RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_2:
1654  return RISCV::VRM2RegClassID;
1655  case RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_4:
1656  return RISCV::VRM4RegClassID;
1657  case RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_8:
1658  return RISCV::VRM8RegClassID;
1659  }
1660 }
1661 
1662 unsigned RISCVTargetLowering::getSubregIndexByMVT(MVT VT, unsigned Index) {
1663  RISCVII::VLMUL LMUL = getLMUL(VT);
1664  if (LMUL == RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F8 ||
1665  LMUL == RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F4 ||
1666  LMUL == RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F2 ||
1667  LMUL == RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_1) {
1668  static_assert(RISCV::sub_vrm1_7 == RISCV::sub_vrm1_0 + 7,
1669  "Unexpected subreg numbering");
1670  return RISCV::sub_vrm1_0 + Index;
1671  }
1672  if (LMUL == RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_2) {
1673  static_assert(RISCV::sub_vrm2_3 == RISCV::sub_vrm2_0 + 3,
1674  "Unexpected subreg numbering");
1675  return RISCV::sub_vrm2_0 + Index;
1676  }
1677  if (LMUL == RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_4) {
1678  static_assert(RISCV::sub_vrm4_1 == RISCV::sub_vrm4_0 + 1,
1679  "Unexpected subreg numbering");
1680  return RISCV::sub_vrm4_0 + Index;
1681  }
1682  llvm_unreachable("Invalid vector type.");
1683 }
1684 
1685 unsigned RISCVTargetLowering::getRegClassIDForVecVT(MVT VT) {
1686  if (VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
1687  return RISCV::VRRegClassID;
1688  return getRegClassIDForLMUL(getLMUL(VT));
1689 }
1690 
1691 // Attempt to decompose a subvector insert/extract between VecVT and
1692 // SubVecVT via subregister indices. Returns the subregister index that
1693 // can perform the subvector insert/extract with the given element index, as
1694 // well as the index corresponding to any leftover subvectors that must be
1695 // further inserted/extracted within the register class for SubVecVT.
1696 std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>
1697 RISCVTargetLowering::decomposeSubvectorInsertExtractToSubRegs(
1698  MVT VecVT, MVT SubVecVT, unsigned InsertExtractIdx,
1699  const RISCVRegisterInfo *TRI) {
1700  static_assert((RISCV::VRM8RegClassID > RISCV::VRM4RegClassID &&
1701  RISCV::VRM4RegClassID > RISCV::VRM2RegClassID &&
1702  RISCV::VRM2RegClassID > RISCV::VRRegClassID),
1703  "Register classes not ordered");
1704  unsigned VecRegClassID = getRegClassIDForVecVT(VecVT);
1705  unsigned SubRegClassID = getRegClassIDForVecVT(SubVecVT);
1706  // Try to compose a subregister index that takes us from the incoming
1707  // LMUL>1 register class down to the outgoing one. At each step we half
1708  // the LMUL:
1709  // nxv16i32@12 -> nxv2i32: sub_vrm4_1_then_sub_vrm2_1_then_sub_vrm1_0
1710  // Note that this is not guaranteed to find a subregister index, such as
1711  // when we are extracting from one VR type to another.
1712  unsigned SubRegIdx = RISCV::NoSubRegister;
1713  for (const unsigned RCID :
1714  {RISCV::VRM4RegClassID, RISCV::VRM2RegClassID, RISCV::VRRegClassID})
1715  if (VecRegClassID > RCID && SubRegClassID <= RCID) {
1716  VecVT = VecVT.getHalfNumVectorElementsVT();
1717  bool IsHi =
1718  InsertExtractIdx >= VecVT.getVectorElementCount().getKnownMinValue();
1719  SubRegIdx = TRI->composeSubRegIndices(SubRegIdx,
1720  getSubregIndexByMVT(VecVT, IsHi));
1721  if (IsHi)
1722  InsertExtractIdx -= VecVT.getVectorElementCount().getKnownMinValue();
1723  }
1724  return {SubRegIdx, InsertExtractIdx};
1725 }
1726 
1727 // Permit combining of mask vectors as BUILD_VECTOR never expands to scalar
1728 // stores for those types.
1729 bool RISCVTargetLowering::mergeStoresAfterLegalization(EVT VT) const {
1730  return !Subtarget.useRVVForFixedLengthVectors() ||
1731  (VT.isFixedLengthVector() && VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1);
1732 }
1733 
1734 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isLegalElementTypeForRVV(Type *ScalarTy) const {
1735  if (ScalarTy->isPointerTy())
1736  return true;
1737 
1738  if (ScalarTy->isIntegerTy(8) || ScalarTy->isIntegerTy(16) ||
1739  ScalarTy->isIntegerTy(32))
1740  return true;
1741 
1742  if (ScalarTy->isIntegerTy(64))
1743  return Subtarget.hasVInstructionsI64();
1744 
1745  if (ScalarTy->isHalfTy())
1746  return Subtarget.hasVInstructionsF16();
1747  if (ScalarTy->isFloatTy())
1748  return Subtarget.hasVInstructionsF32();
1749  if (ScalarTy->isDoubleTy())
1750  return Subtarget.hasVInstructionsF64();
1751 
1752  return false;
1753 }

1755 unsigned RISCVTargetLowering::combineRepeatedFPDivisors() const {
1756  return NumRepeatedDivisors;
1757 }

1759 static SDValue getVLOperand(SDValue Op) {
1760  assert((Op.getOpcode() == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN ||
1761  Op.getOpcode() == ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN) &&
1762  "Unexpected opcode");
1763  bool HasChain = Op.getOpcode() == ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN;
1764  unsigned IntNo = Op.getConstantOperandVal(HasChain ? 1 : 0);
1765  const RISCVVIntrinsicsTable::RISCVVIntrinsicInfo *II =
1766  RISCVVIntrinsicsTable::getRISCVVIntrinsicInfo(IntNo);
1767  if (!II)
1768  return SDValue();
1769  return Op.getOperand(II->VLOperand + 1 + HasChain);
1770 }
1771 
1772 static bool useRVVForFixedLengthVectorVT(MVT VT,
1773  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
1774  assert(VT.isFixedLengthVector() && "Expected a fixed length vector type!");
1775  if (!Subtarget.useRVVForFixedLengthVectors())
1776  return false;
1777 
1778  // We only support a set of vector types with a consistent maximum fixed size
1779  // across all supported vector element types to avoid legalization issues.
1780  // Therefore -- since the largest is v1024i8/v512i16/etc -- the largest
1781  // fixed-length vector type we support is 1024 bytes.
1782  if (VT.getFixedSizeInBits() > 1024 * 8)
1783  return false;
1784 
1785  unsigned MinVLen = Subtarget.getRealMinVLen();
1786 
1787  MVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
1788 
1789  // Don't use RVV for vectors we cannot scalarize if required.
1790  switch (EltVT.SimpleTy) {
1791  // i1 is supported but has different rules.
1792  default:
1793  return false;
1794  case MVT::i1:
1795  // Masks can only use a single register.
1796  if (VT.getVectorNumElements() > MinVLen)
1797  return false;
1798  MinVLen /= 8;
1799  break;
1800  case MVT::i8:
1801  case MVT::i16:
1802  case MVT::i32:
1803  break;
1804  case MVT::i64:
1805  if (!Subtarget.hasVInstructionsI64())
1806  return false;
1807  break;
1808  case MVT::f16:
1809  if (!Subtarget.hasVInstructionsF16())
1810  return false;
1811  break;
1812  case MVT::f32:
1813  if (!Subtarget.hasVInstructionsF32())
1814  return false;
1815  break;
1816  case MVT::f64:
1817  if (!Subtarget.hasVInstructionsF64())
1818  return false;
1819  break;
1820  }
1821 
1822  // Reject elements larger than ELEN.
1823  if (EltVT.getSizeInBits() > Subtarget.getELEN())
1824  return false;
1825 
1826  unsigned LMul = divideCeil(VT.getSizeInBits(), MinVLen);
1827  // Don't use RVV for types that don't fit.
1828  if (LMul > Subtarget.getMaxLMULForFixedLengthVectors())
1829  return false;
1830 
1831  // TODO: Perhaps an artificial restriction, but worth having whilst getting
1832  // the base fixed length RVV support in place.
1833  if (!VT.isPow2VectorType())
1834  return false;
1835 
1836  return true;
1837 }
1838 
1839 bool RISCVTargetLowering::useRVVForFixedLengthVectorVT(MVT VT) const {
1840  return ::useRVVForFixedLengthVectorVT(VT, Subtarget);
1841 }
1842 
1843 // Return the largest legal scalable vector type that matches VT's element type.
1844 static MVT getContainerForFixedLengthVector(const TargetLowering &TLI, MVT VT,
1845  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
1846  // This may be called before legal types are setup.
1847  assert(((VT.isFixedLengthVector() && TLI.isTypeLegal(VT)) ||
1848  useRVVForFixedLengthVectorVT(VT, Subtarget)) &&
1849  "Expected legal fixed length vector!");
1850 
1851  unsigned MinVLen = Subtarget.getRealMinVLen();
1852  unsigned MaxELen = Subtarget.getELEN();
1853 
1854  MVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
1855  switch (EltVT.SimpleTy) {
1856  default:
1857  llvm_unreachable("unexpected element type for RVV container");
1858  case MVT::i1:
1859  case MVT::i8:
1860  case MVT::i16:
1861  case MVT::i32:
1862  case MVT::i64:
1863  case MVT::f16:
1864  case MVT::f32:
1865  case MVT::f64: {
1866  // We prefer to use LMUL=1 for VLEN sized types. Use fractional lmuls for
1867  // narrower types. The smallest fractional LMUL we support is 8/ELEN. Within
1868  // each fractional LMUL we support SEW between 8 and LMUL*ELEN.
1869  unsigned NumElts =
1870  (VT.getVectorNumElements() * RISCV::RVVBitsPerBlock) / MinVLen;
1871  NumElts = std::max(NumElts, RISCV::RVVBitsPerBlock / MaxELen);
1872  assert(isPowerOf2_32(NumElts) && "Expected power of 2 NumElts");
1873  return MVT::getScalableVectorVT(EltVT, NumElts);
1874  }
1875  }
1876 }
1877 
1878 static MVT getContainerForFixedLengthVector(SelectionDAG &DAG, MVT VT,
1879  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
1880  return getContainerForFixedLengthVector(DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo(), VT,
1881  Subtarget);
1882 }
1883 
1884 MVT RISCVTargetLowering::getContainerForFixedLengthVector(MVT VT) const {
1885  return ::getContainerForFixedLengthVector(*this, VT, getSubtarget());
1886 }

1888 // Grow V to consume an entire RVV register.
1889 static SDValue convertToScalableVector(EVT VT, SDValue V, SelectionDAG &DAG,
1890  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
1891  assert(VT.isScalableVector() &&
1892  "Expected to convert into a scalable vector!");
1893  assert(V.getValueType().isFixedLengthVector() &&
1894  "Expected a fixed length vector operand!");
1895  SDLoc DL(V);
1896  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, Subtarget.getXLenVT());
1897  return DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, VT, DAG.getUNDEF(VT), V, Zero);
1898 }
1899 
1900 // Shrink V so it's just big enough to maintain a VT's worth of data.
1901 static SDValue convertFromScalableVector(EVT VT, SDValue V, SelectionDAG &DAG,
1902  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
1903  assert(VT.isFixedLengthVector() &&
1904  "Expected to convert into a fixed length vector!");
1905  assert(V.getValueType().isScalableVector() &&
1906  "Expected a scalable vector operand!");
1907  SDLoc DL(V);
1908  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, Subtarget.getXLenVT());
1909  return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, VT, V, Zero);
1910 }

1912 /// Return the type of the mask type suitable for masking the provided
1913 /// vector type. This is simply an i1 element type vector of the same
1914 /// (possibly scalable) length.
1915 static MVT getMaskTypeFor(MVT VecVT) {
1916  assert(VecVT.isVector());
1917  ElementCount EC = VecVT.getVectorElementCount();
1918  return MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i1, EC);
1919 }

1921 /// Creates an all ones mask suitable for masking a vector of type VecTy with
1922 /// vector length VL. .
1923 static SDValue getAllOnesMask(MVT VecVT, SDValue VL, SDLoc DL,
1924  SelectionDAG &DAG) {
1925  MVT MaskVT = getMaskTypeFor(VecVT);
1926  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMSET_VL, DL, MaskVT, VL);
1927 }

1934 static std::pair<SDValue, SDValue>
1935 getDefaultVLOps(uint64_t NumElts, MVT ContainerVT, SDLoc DL, SelectionDAG &DAG,
1936  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
1937  assert(ContainerVT.isScalableVector() && "Expecting scalable container type");
1938  SDValue VL = getVLOp(NumElts, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
1939  SDValue Mask = getAllOnesMask(ContainerVT, VL, DL, DAG);
1940  return {Mask, VL};
1941 }
1942 
1943 // Gets the two common "VL" operands: an all-ones mask and the vector length.
1944 // VecVT is a vector type, either fixed-length or scalable, and ContainerVT is
1945 // the vector type that the fixed-length vector is contained in. Otherwise if
1946 // VecVT is scalable, then ContainerVT should be the same as VecVT.
1947 static std::pair<SDValue, SDValue>
1948 getDefaultVLOps(MVT VecVT, MVT ContainerVT, SDLoc DL, SelectionDAG &DAG,
1949  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
1950  if (VecVT.isFixedLengthVector())
1951  return getDefaultVLOps(VecVT.getVectorNumElements(), ContainerVT, DL, DAG,
1952  Subtarget);
1953  assert(ContainerVT.isScalableVector() && "Expecting scalable container type");
1954  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
1955  SDValue VL = DAG.getRegister(RISCV::X0, XLenVT);
1956  SDValue Mask = getAllOnesMask(ContainerVT, VL, DL, DAG);
1957  return {Mask, VL};
1958 }
1959 
1960 // As above but assuming the given type is a scalable vector type.
1961 static std::pair<SDValue, SDValue>
1962 getDefaultScalableVLOps(MVT VecVT, SDLoc DL, SelectionDAG &DAG,
1963  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
1964  assert(VecVT.isScalableVector() && "Expecting a scalable vector");
1965  return getDefaultVLOps(VecVT, VecVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
1966 }
1967 
1968 // The state of RVV BUILD_VECTOR and VECTOR_SHUFFLE lowering is that very few
1969 // of either is (currently) supported. This can get us into an infinite loop
1970 // where we try to lower a BUILD_VECTOR as a VECTOR_SHUFFLE as a BUILD_VECTOR
1971 // as a ..., etc.
1972 // Until either (or both) of these can reliably lower any node, reporting that
1973 // we don't want to expand BUILD_VECTORs via VECTOR_SHUFFLEs at least breaks
1974 // the infinite loop. Note that this lowers BUILD_VECTOR through the stack,
1975 // which is not desirable.
1976 bool RISCVTargetLowering::shouldExpandBuildVectorWithShuffles(
1977  EVT VT, unsigned DefinedValues) const {
1978  return false;
1979 }
1980 
1981 static SDValue lowerFP_TO_INT_SAT(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
1982  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
1983  // RISCV FP-to-int conversions saturate to the destination register size, but
1984  // don't produce 0 for nan. We can use a conversion instruction and fix the
1985  // nan case with a compare and a select.
1986  SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
1987 
1988  MVT DstVT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
1989  EVT SatVT = cast<VTSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))->getVT();
1990 
1991  bool IsSigned = Op.getOpcode() == ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT;
1992 
1993  if (!DstVT.isVector()) {
1994  // In absense of Zfh, promote f16 to f32, then saturate the result.
1995  if (Src.getSimpleValueType() == MVT::f16 && !Subtarget.hasStdExtZfh()) {
1996  Src = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, SDLoc(Op), MVT::f32, Src);
1997  }
1998 
1999  unsigned Opc;
2000  if (SatVT == DstVT)
2001  Opc = IsSigned ? RISCVISD::FCVT_X : RISCVISD::FCVT_XU;
2002  else if (DstVT == MVT::i64 && SatVT == MVT::i32)
2003  Opc = IsSigned ? RISCVISD::FCVT_W_RV64 : RISCVISD::FCVT_WU_RV64;
2004  else
2005  return SDValue();
2006  // FIXME: Support other SatVTs by clamping before or after the conversion.
2007 
2008  SDLoc DL(Op);
2009  SDValue FpToInt = DAG.getNode(
2010  Opc, DL, DstVT, Src,
2011  DAG.getTargetConstant(RISCVFPRndMode::RTZ, DL, Subtarget.getXLenVT()));
2012 
2013  if (Opc == RISCVISD::FCVT_WU_RV64)
2014  FpToInt = DAG.getZeroExtendInReg(FpToInt, DL, MVT::i32);
2015 
2016  SDValue ZeroInt = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, DstVT);
2017  return DAG.getSelectCC(DL, Src, Src, ZeroInt, FpToInt,
2018  ISD::CondCode::SETUO);
2019  }
2020 
2021  // Vectors.
2022 
2023  MVT DstEltVT = DstVT.getVectorElementType();
2024  MVT SrcVT = Src.getSimpleValueType();
2025  MVT SrcEltVT = SrcVT.getVectorElementType();
2026  unsigned SrcEltSize = SrcEltVT.getSizeInBits();
2027  unsigned DstEltSize = DstEltVT.getSizeInBits();
2028 
2029  // Only handle saturating to the destination type.
2030  if (SatVT != DstEltVT)
2031  return SDValue();
2032 
2033  // FIXME: Don't support narrowing by more than 1 steps for now.
2034  if (SrcEltSize > (2 * DstEltSize))
2035  return SDValue();
2036 
2037  MVT DstContainerVT = DstVT;
2038  MVT SrcContainerVT = SrcVT;
2039  if (DstVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
2040  DstContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(DAG, DstVT, Subtarget);
2041  SrcContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(DAG, SrcVT, Subtarget);
2042  assert(DstContainerVT.getVectorElementCount() ==
2043  SrcContainerVT.getVectorElementCount() &&
2044  "Expected same element count");
2045  Src = convertToScalableVector(SrcContainerVT, Src, DAG, Subtarget);
2046  }
2047 
2048  SDLoc DL(Op);
2049 
2050  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(DstVT, DstContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
2051 
2052  SDValue IsNan = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SETCC_VL, DL, Mask.getValueType(),
2053  {Src, Src, DAG.getCondCode(ISD::SETNE),
2054  DAG.getUNDEF(Mask.getValueType()), Mask, VL});
2055 
2056  // Need to widen by more than 1 step, promote the FP type, then do a widening
2057  // convert.
2058  if (DstEltSize > (2 * SrcEltSize)) {
2059  assert(SrcContainerVT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::f16 && "Unexpected VT!");
2060  MVT InterVT = SrcContainerVT.changeVectorElementType(MVT::f32);
2061  Src = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FP_EXTEND_VL, DL, InterVT, Src, Mask, VL);
2062  }
2063 
2064  unsigned RVVOpc =
2065  IsSigned ? RISCVISD::VFCVT_RTZ_X_F_VL : RISCVISD::VFCVT_RTZ_XU_F_VL;
2066  SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(RVVOpc, DL, DstContainerVT, Src, Mask, VL);
2067 
2068  SDValue SplatZero = DAG.getNode(
2069  RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, DstContainerVT, DAG.getUNDEF(DstContainerVT),
2070  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, Subtarget.getXLenVT()), VL);
2071  Res = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VSELECT_VL, DL, DstContainerVT, IsNan, SplatZero,
2072  Res, VL);
2073 
2074  if (DstVT.isFixedLengthVector())
2075  Res = convertFromScalableVector(DstVT, Res, DAG, Subtarget);
2076 
2077  return Res;
2078 }
2079 
2080 static RISCVFPRndMode::RoundingMode matchRoundingOp(unsigned Opc) {
2081  switch (Opc) {
2082  case ISD::FROUNDEVEN:
2083  case ISD::VP_FROUNDEVEN:
2084  return RISCVFPRndMode::RNE;
2085  case ISD::FTRUNC:
2086  case ISD::VP_FROUNDTOZERO:
2087  return RISCVFPRndMode::RTZ;
2088  case ISD::FFLOOR:
2089  case ISD::VP_FFLOOR:
2090  return RISCVFPRndMode::RDN;
2091  case ISD::FCEIL:
2092  case ISD::VP_FCEIL:
2093  return RISCVFPRndMode::RUP;
2094  case ISD::FROUND:
2095  case ISD::VP_FROUND:
2096  return RISCVFPRndMode::RMM;
2097  case ISD::FRINT:
2098  return RISCVFPRndMode::DYN;
2099  }
2100 
2101  return RISCVFPRndMode::Invalid;
2102 }
2103 
2104 // Expand vector FTRUNC, FCEIL, FFLOOR, FROUND, VP_FCEIL, VP_FFLOOR, VP_FROUND
2105 // VP_FROUNDEVEN, VP_FROUNDTOZERO, VP_FRINT and VP_FNEARBYINT by converting to
2106 // the integer domain and back. Taking care to avoid converting values that are
2107 // nan or already correct.
2108 static SDValue
2109 lowerVectorFTRUNC_FCEIL_FFLOOR_FROUND(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
2110  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
2111  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
2112  assert(VT.isVector() && "Unexpected type");
2113 
2114  SDLoc DL(Op);
2115 
2116  SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
2117 
2118  MVT ContainerVT = VT;
2119  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
2120  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(DAG, VT, Subtarget);
2121  Src = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Src, DAG, Subtarget);
2122  }
2123 
2124  SDValue Mask, VL;
2125  if (Op->isVPOpcode()) {
2126  Mask = Op.getOperand(1);
2127  VL = Op.getOperand(2);
2128  } else {
2129  std::tie(Mask, VL) = getDefaultVLOps(VT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
2130  }
2131 
2132  // Freeze the source since we are increasing the number of uses.
2133  Src = DAG.getFreeze(Src);
2134 
2135  // We do the conversion on the absolute value and fix the sign at the end.
2136  SDValue Abs = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FABS_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Src, Mask, VL);
2137 
2138  // Determine the largest integer that can be represented exactly. This and
2139  // values larger than it don't have any fractional bits so don't need to
2140  // be converted.
2141  const fltSemantics &FltSem = DAG.EVTToAPFloatSemantics(ContainerVT);
2142  unsigned Precision = APFloat::semanticsPrecision(FltSem);
2143  APFloat MaxVal = APFloat(FltSem);
2144  MaxVal.convertFromAPInt(APInt::getOneBitSet(Precision, Precision - 1),
2145  /*IsSigned*/ false, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
2146  SDValue MaxValNode =
2147  DAG.getConstantFP(MaxVal, DL, ContainerVT.getVectorElementType());
2148  SDValue MaxValSplat = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VFMV_V_F_VL, DL, ContainerVT,
2149  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), MaxValNode, VL);
2150 
2151  // If abs(Src) was larger than MaxVal or nan, keep it.
2152  MVT SetccVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i1, ContainerVT.getVectorElementCount());
2153  Mask =
2154  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SETCC_VL, DL, SetccVT,
2155  {Abs, MaxValSplat, DAG.getCondCode(ISD::SETOLT),
2156  Mask, Mask, VL});
2157 
2158  // Truncate to integer and convert back to FP.
2159  MVT IntVT = ContainerVT.changeVectorElementTypeToInteger();
2160  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
2161  SDValue Truncated;
2162 
2163  switch (Op.getOpcode()) {
2164  default:
2165  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected opcode");
2166  case ISD::FCEIL:
2167  case ISD::VP_FCEIL:
2168  case ISD::FFLOOR:
2169  case ISD::VP_FFLOOR:
2170  case ISD::FROUND:
2171  case ISD::FROUNDEVEN:
2172  case ISD::VP_FROUND:
2173  case ISD::VP_FROUNDEVEN:
2174  case ISD::VP_FROUNDTOZERO: {
2175  RISCVFPRndMode::RoundingMode FRM = matchRoundingOp(Op.getOpcode());
2176  assert(FRM != RISCVFPRndMode::Invalid);
2177  Truncated = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VFCVT_RM_X_F_VL, DL, IntVT, Src, Mask,
2178  DAG.getTargetConstant(FRM, DL, XLenVT), VL);
2179  break;
2180  }
2181  case ISD::FTRUNC:
2182  Truncated = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VFCVT_RTZ_X_F_VL, DL, IntVT, Src,
2183  Mask, VL);
2184  break;
2185  case ISD::VP_FRINT:
2186  Truncated = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VFCVT_X_F_VL, DL, IntVT, Src, Mask, VL);
2187  break;
2188  case ISD::VP_FNEARBYINT:
2189  Truncated = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VFROUND_NOEXCEPT_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Src,
2190  Mask, VL);
2191  break;
2192  }
2193 
2194  // VFROUND_NOEXCEPT_VL includes SINT_TO_FP_VL.
2195  if (Op.getOpcode() != ISD::VP_FNEARBYINT)
2196  Truncated = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SINT_TO_FP_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Truncated,
2197  Mask, VL);
2198 
2199  // Restore the original sign so that -0.0 is preserved.
2200  Truncated = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FCOPYSIGN_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Truncated,
2201  Src, Src, Mask, VL);
2202 
2203  if (!VT.isFixedLengthVector())
2204  return Truncated;
2205 
2206  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, Truncated, DAG, Subtarget);
2207 }
2208 
2209 static SDValue
2210 lowerFTRUNC_FCEIL_FFLOOR_FROUND(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
2211  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
2212  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
2213  if (VT.isVector())
2214  return lowerVectorFTRUNC_FCEIL_FFLOOR_FROUND(Op, DAG, Subtarget);
2215 
2216  if (DAG.shouldOptForSize())
2217  return SDValue();
2218 
2219  SDLoc DL(Op);
2220  SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
2221 
2222  // Create an integer the size of the mantissa with the MSB set. This and all
2223  // values larger than it don't have any fractional bits so don't need to be
2224  // converted.
2225  const fltSemantics &FltSem = DAG.EVTToAPFloatSemantics(VT);
2226  unsigned Precision = APFloat::semanticsPrecision(FltSem);
2227  APFloat MaxVal = APFloat(FltSem);
2228  MaxVal.convertFromAPInt(APInt::getOneBitSet(Precision, Precision - 1),
2229  /*IsSigned*/ false, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
2230  SDValue MaxValNode = DAG.getConstantFP(MaxVal, DL, VT);
2231 
2232  RISCVFPRndMode::RoundingMode FRM = matchRoundingOp(Op.getOpcode());
2233  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FROUND, DL, VT, Src, MaxValNode,
2234  DAG.getTargetConstant(FRM, DL, Subtarget.getXLenVT()));
2235 }
2236 
2237 struct VIDSequence {
2238  int64_t StepNumerator;
2239  unsigned StepDenominator;
2240  int64_t Addend;
2241 };
2242 
2243 static std::optional<uint64_t> getExactInteger(const APFloat &APF,
2244  uint32_t BitWidth) {
2245  APSInt ValInt(BitWidth, !APF.isNegative());
2246  // We use an arbitrary rounding mode here. If a floating-point is an exact
2247  // integer (e.g., 1.0), the rounding mode does not affect the output value. If
2248  // the rounding mode changes the output value, then it is not an exact
2249  // integer.
