2250  RoundingMode ArbitraryRM = RoundingMode::TowardZero;
2251  bool IsExact;
2252  // If it is out of signed integer range, it will return an invalid operation.
2253  // If it is not an exact integer, IsExact is false.
2254  if ((APF.convertToInteger(ValInt, ArbitraryRM, &IsExact) ==
2255  APFloatBase::opInvalidOp) ||
2256  !IsExact)
2257  return std::nullopt;
2258  return ValInt.extractBitsAsZExtValue(BitWidth, 0);
2259 }
2260 
2261 // Try to match an arithmetic-sequence BUILD_VECTOR [X,X+S,X+2*S,...,X+(N-1)*S]
2262 // to the (non-zero) step S and start value X. This can be then lowered as the
2263 // RVV sequence (VID * S) + X, for example.
2264 // The step S is represented as an integer numerator divided by a positive
2265 // denominator. Note that the implementation currently only identifies
2266 // sequences in which either the numerator is +/- 1 or the denominator is 1. It
2267 // cannot detect 2/3, for example.
2268 // Note that this method will also match potentially unappealing index
2269 // sequences, like <i32 0, i32 50939494>, however it is left to the caller to
2270 // determine whether this is worth generating code for.
2271 static std::optional<VIDSequence> isSimpleVIDSequence(SDValue Op) {
2272  unsigned NumElts = Op.getNumOperands();
2273  assert(Op.getOpcode() == ISD::BUILD_VECTOR && "Unexpected BUILD_VECTOR");
2274  bool IsInteger = Op.getValueType().isInteger();
2275 
2276  std::optional<unsigned> SeqStepDenom;
2277  std::optional<int64_t> SeqStepNum, SeqAddend;
2278  std::optional<std::pair<uint64_t, unsigned>> PrevElt;
2279  unsigned EltSizeInBits = Op.getValueType().getScalarSizeInBits();
2280  for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < NumElts; Idx++) {
2281  // Assume undef elements match the sequence; we just have to be careful
2282  // when interpolating across them.
2283  if (Op.getOperand(Idx).isUndef())
2284  continue;
2285 
2286  uint64_t Val;
2287  if (IsInteger) {
2288  // The BUILD_VECTOR must be all constants.
2289  if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(Idx)))
2290  return std::nullopt;
2291  Val = Op.getConstantOperandVal(Idx) &
2292  maskTrailingOnes<uint64_t>(EltSizeInBits);
2293  } else {
2294  // The BUILD_VECTOR must be all constants.
2295  if (!isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(Op.getOperand(Idx)))
2296  return std::nullopt;
2297  if (auto ExactInteger = getExactInteger(
2298  cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Op.getOperand(Idx))->getValueAPF(),
2299  EltSizeInBits))
2300  Val = *ExactInteger;
2301  else
2302  return std::nullopt;
2303  }
2304 
2305  if (PrevElt) {
2306  // Calculate the step since the last non-undef element, and ensure
2307  // it's consistent across the entire sequence.
2308  unsigned IdxDiff = Idx - PrevElt->second;
2309  int64_t ValDiff = SignExtend64(Val - PrevElt->first, EltSizeInBits);
2310 
2311  // A zero-value value difference means that we're somewhere in the middle
2312  // of a fractional step, e.g. <0,0,0*,0,1,1,1,1>. Wait until we notice a
2313  // step change before evaluating the sequence.
2314  if (ValDiff == 0)
2315  continue;
2316 
2317  int64_t Remainder = ValDiff % IdxDiff;
2318  // Normalize the step if it's greater than 1.
2319  if (Remainder != ValDiff) {
2320  // The difference must cleanly divide the element span.
2321  if (Remainder != 0)
2322  return std::nullopt;
2323  ValDiff /= IdxDiff;
2324  IdxDiff = 1;
2325  }
2326 
2327  if (!SeqStepNum)
2328  SeqStepNum = ValDiff;
2329  else if (ValDiff != SeqStepNum)
2330  return std::nullopt;
2331 
2332  if (!SeqStepDenom)
2333  SeqStepDenom = IdxDiff;
2334  else if (IdxDiff != *SeqStepDenom)
2335  return std::nullopt;
2336  }
2337 
2338  // Record this non-undef element for later.
2339  if (!PrevElt || PrevElt->first != Val)
2340  PrevElt = std::make_pair(Val, Idx);
2341  }
2342 
2343  // We need to have logged a step for this to count as a legal index sequence.
2344  if (!SeqStepNum || !SeqStepDenom)
2345  return std::nullopt;
2346 
2347  // Loop back through the sequence and validate elements we might have skipped
2348  // while waiting for a valid step. While doing this, log any sequence addend.
2349  for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < NumElts; Idx++) {
2350  if (Op.getOperand(Idx).isUndef())
2351  continue;
2352  uint64_t Val;
2353  if (IsInteger) {
2354  Val = Op.getConstantOperandVal(Idx) &
2355  maskTrailingOnes<uint64_t>(EltSizeInBits);
2356  } else {
2357  Val = *getExactInteger(
2358  cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Op.getOperand(Idx))->getValueAPF(),
2359  EltSizeInBits);
2360  }
2361  uint64_t ExpectedVal =
2362  (int64_t)(Idx * (uint64_t)*SeqStepNum) / *SeqStepDenom;
2363  int64_t Addend = SignExtend64(Val - ExpectedVal, EltSizeInBits);
2364  if (!SeqAddend)
2365  SeqAddend = Addend;
2366  else if (Addend != SeqAddend)
2367  return std::nullopt;
2368  }
2369 
2370  assert(SeqAddend && "Must have an addend if we have a step");
2371 
2372  return VIDSequence{*SeqStepNum, *SeqStepDenom, *SeqAddend};
2373 }
2374 
2375 // Match a splatted value (SPLAT_VECTOR/BUILD_VECTOR) of an EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT
2376 // and lower it as a VRGATHER_VX_VL from the source vector.
2377 static SDValue matchSplatAsGather(SDValue SplatVal, MVT VT, const SDLoc &DL,
2378  SelectionDAG &DAG,
2379  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
2380  if (SplatVal.getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT)
2381  return SDValue();
2382  SDValue Vec = SplatVal.getOperand(0);
2383  // Only perform this optimization on vectors of the same size for simplicity.
2384  // Don't perform this optimization for i1 vectors.
2385  // FIXME: Support i1 vectors, maybe by promoting to i8?
2386  if (Vec.getValueType() != VT || VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
2387  return SDValue();
2388  SDValue Idx = SplatVal.getOperand(1);
2389  // The index must be a legal type.
2390  if (Idx.getValueType() != Subtarget.getXLenVT())
2391  return SDValue();
2392 
2393  MVT ContainerVT = VT;
2394  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
2395  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(DAG, VT, Subtarget);
2396  Vec = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Vec, DAG, Subtarget);
2397  }
2398 
2399  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(VT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
2400 
2401  SDValue Gather = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VRGATHER_VX_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Vec,
2402  Idx, DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), Mask, VL);
2403 
2404  if (!VT.isFixedLengthVector())
2405  return Gather;
2406 
2407  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, Gather, DAG, Subtarget);
2408 }
2409 
2410 static SDValue lowerBUILD_VECTOR(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
2411  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
2412  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
2413  assert(VT.isFixedLengthVector() && "Unexpected vector!");
2414 
2415  MVT ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(DAG, VT, Subtarget);
2416 
2417  SDLoc DL(Op);
2418  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(VT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
2419 
2420  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
2421  unsigned NumElts = Op.getNumOperands();
2422 
2423  if (VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1) {
2424  if (ISD::isBuildVectorAllZeros(Op.getNode())) {
2425  SDValue VMClr = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMCLR_VL, DL, ContainerVT, VL);
2426  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, VMClr, DAG, Subtarget);
2427  }
2428 
2429  if (ISD::isBuildVectorAllOnes(Op.getNode())) {
2430  SDValue VMSet = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMSET_VL, DL, ContainerVT, VL);
2431  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, VMSet, DAG, Subtarget);
2432  }
2433 
2434  // Lower constant mask BUILD_VECTORs via an integer vector type, in
2435  // scalar integer chunks whose bit-width depends on the number of mask
2436  // bits and XLEN.
2437  // First, determine the most appropriate scalar integer type to use. This
2438  // is at most XLenVT, but may be shrunk to a smaller vector element type
2439  // according to the size of the final vector - use i8 chunks rather than
2440  // XLenVT if we're producing a v8i1. This results in more consistent
2441  // codegen across RV32 and RV64.
2442  unsigned NumViaIntegerBits = std::clamp(NumElts, 8u, Subtarget.getXLen());
2443  NumViaIntegerBits = std::min(NumViaIntegerBits, Subtarget.getELEN());
2444  if (ISD::isBuildVectorOfConstantSDNodes(Op.getNode())) {
2445  // If we have to use more than one INSERT_VECTOR_ELT then this
2446  // optimization is likely to increase code size; avoid peforming it in
2447  // such a case. We can use a load from a constant pool in this case.
2448  if (DAG.shouldOptForSize() && NumElts > NumViaIntegerBits)
2449  return SDValue();
2450  // Now we can create our integer vector type. Note that it may be larger
2451  // than the resulting mask type: v4i1 would use v1i8 as its integer type.
2452  MVT IntegerViaVecVT =
2453  MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::getIntegerVT(NumViaIntegerBits),
2454  divideCeil(NumElts, NumViaIntegerBits));
2455 
2456  uint64_t Bits = 0;
2457  unsigned BitPos = 0, IntegerEltIdx = 0;
2458  SDValue Vec = DAG.getUNDEF(IntegerViaVecVT);
2459 
2460  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumElts; I++, BitPos++) {
2461  // Once we accumulate enough bits to fill our scalar type, insert into
2462  // our vector and clear our accumulated data.
2463  if (I != 0 && I % NumViaIntegerBits == 0) {
2464  if (NumViaIntegerBits <= 32)
2465  Bits = SignExtend64<32>(Bits);
2466  SDValue Elt = DAG.getConstant(Bits, DL, XLenVT);
2467  Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, IntegerViaVecVT, Vec,
2468  Elt, DAG.getConstant(IntegerEltIdx, DL, XLenVT));
2469  Bits = 0;
2470  BitPos = 0;
2471  IntegerEltIdx++;
2472  }
2473  SDValue V = Op.getOperand(I);
2474  bool BitValue = !V.isUndef() && cast<ConstantSDNode>(V)->getZExtValue();
2475  Bits |= ((uint64_t)BitValue << BitPos);
2476  }
2477 
2478  // Insert the (remaining) scalar value into position in our integer
2479  // vector type.
2480  if (NumViaIntegerBits <= 32)
2481  Bits = SignExtend64<32>(Bits);
2482  SDValue Elt = DAG.getConstant(Bits, DL, XLenVT);
2483  Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, IntegerViaVecVT, Vec, Elt,
2484  DAG.getConstant(IntegerEltIdx, DL, XLenVT));
2485 
2486  if (NumElts < NumViaIntegerBits) {
2487  // If we're producing a smaller vector than our minimum legal integer
2488  // type, bitcast to the equivalent (known-legal) mask type, and extract
2489  // our final mask.
2490  assert(IntegerViaVecVT == MVT::v1i8 && "Unexpected mask vector type");
2491  Vec = DAG.getBitcast(MVT::v8i1, Vec);
2492  Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, VT, Vec,
2493  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT));
2494  } else {
2495  // Else we must have produced an integer type with the same size as the
2496  // mask type; bitcast for the final result.
2497  assert(VT.getSizeInBits() == IntegerViaVecVT.getSizeInBits());
2498  Vec = DAG.getBitcast(VT, Vec);
2499  }
2500 
2501  return Vec;
2502  }
2503 
2504  // A BUILD_VECTOR can be lowered as a SETCC. For each fixed-length mask
2505  // vector type, we have a legal equivalently-sized i8 type, so we can use
2506  // that.
2507  MVT WideVecVT = VT.changeVectorElementType(MVT::i8);
2508  SDValue VecZero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, WideVecVT);
2509 
2510  SDValue WideVec;
2511  if (SDValue Splat = cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(Op)->getSplatValue()) {
2512  // For a splat, perform a scalar truncate before creating the wider
2513  // vector.
2514  assert(Splat.getValueType() == XLenVT &&
2515  "Unexpected type for i1 splat value");
2516  Splat = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, XLenVT, Splat,
2517  DAG.getConstant(1, DL, XLenVT));
2518  WideVec = DAG.getSplatBuildVector(WideVecVT, DL, Splat);
2519  } else {
2520  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops(Op->op_values());
2521  WideVec = DAG.getBuildVector(WideVecVT, DL, Ops);
2522  SDValue VecOne = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, WideVecVT);
2523  WideVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, WideVecVT, WideVec, VecOne);
2524  }
2525 
2526  return DAG.getSetCC(DL, VT, WideVec, VecZero, ISD::SETNE);
2527  }
2528 
2529  if (SDValue Splat = cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(Op)->getSplatValue()) {
2530  if (auto Gather = matchSplatAsGather(Splat, VT, DL, DAG, Subtarget))
2531  return Gather;
2532  unsigned Opc = VT.isFloatingPoint() ? RISCVISD::VFMV_V_F_VL
2533  : RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL;
2534  Splat =
2535  DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, ContainerVT, DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), Splat, VL);
2536  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, Splat, DAG, Subtarget);
2537  }
2538 
2539  // Try and match index sequences, which we can lower to the vid instruction
2540  // with optional modifications. An all-undef vector is matched by
2541  // getSplatValue, above.
2542  if (auto SimpleVID = isSimpleVIDSequence(Op)) {
2543  int64_t StepNumerator = SimpleVID->StepNumerator;
2544  unsigned StepDenominator = SimpleVID->StepDenominator;
2545  int64_t Addend = SimpleVID->Addend;
2546 
2547  assert(StepNumerator != 0 && "Invalid step");
2548  bool Negate = false;
2549  int64_t SplatStepVal = StepNumerator;
2550  unsigned StepOpcode = ISD::MUL;
2551  if (StepNumerator != 1) {
2552  if (isPowerOf2_64(std::abs(StepNumerator))) {
2553  Negate = StepNumerator < 0;
2554  StepOpcode = ISD::SHL;
2555  SplatStepVal = Log2_64(std::abs(StepNumerator));
2556  }
2557  }
2558 
2559  // Only emit VIDs with suitably-small steps/addends. We use imm5 is a
2560  // threshold since it's the immediate value many RVV instructions accept.
2561  // There is no vmul.vi instruction so ensure multiply constant can fit in
2562  // a single addi instruction.
2563  if (((StepOpcode == ISD::MUL && isInt<12>(SplatStepVal)) ||
2564  (StepOpcode == ISD::SHL && isUInt<5>(SplatStepVal))) &&
2565  isPowerOf2_32(StepDenominator) &&
2566  (SplatStepVal >= 0 || StepDenominator == 1) && isInt<5>(Addend)) {
2567  MVT VIDVT =
2568  VT.isFloatingPoint() ? VT.changeVectorElementTypeToInteger() : VT;
2569  MVT VIDContainerVT =
2570  getContainerForFixedLengthVector(DAG, VIDVT, Subtarget);
2571  SDValue VID = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VID_VL, DL, VIDContainerVT, Mask, VL);
2572  // Convert right out of the scalable type so we can use standard ISD
2573  // nodes for the rest of the computation. If we used scalable types with
2574  // these, we'd lose the fixed-length vector info and generate worse
2575  // vsetvli code.
2576  VID = convertFromScalableVector(VIDVT, VID, DAG, Subtarget);
2577  if ((StepOpcode == ISD::MUL && SplatStepVal != 1) ||
2578  (StepOpcode == ISD::SHL && SplatStepVal != 0)) {
2579  SDValue SplatStep = DAG.getSplatBuildVector(
2580  VIDVT, DL, DAG.getConstant(SplatStepVal, DL, XLenVT));
2581  VID = DAG.getNode(StepOpcode, DL, VIDVT, VID, SplatStep);
2582  }
2583  if (StepDenominator != 1) {
2584  SDValue SplatStep = DAG.getSplatBuildVector(
2585  VIDVT, DL, DAG.getConstant(Log2_64(StepDenominator), DL, XLenVT));
2586  VID = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VIDVT, VID, SplatStep);
2587  }
2588  if (Addend != 0 || Negate) {
2589  SDValue SplatAddend = DAG.getSplatBuildVector(
2590  VIDVT, DL, DAG.getConstant(Addend, DL, XLenVT));
2591  VID = DAG.getNode(Negate ? ISD::SUB : ISD::ADD, DL, VIDVT, SplatAddend,
2592  VID);
2593  }
2594  if (VT.isFloatingPoint()) {
2595  // TODO: Use vfwcvt to reduce register pressure.
2596  VID = DAG.getNode(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, DL, VT, VID);
2597  }
2598  return VID;
2599  }
2600  }
2601 
2602  // Attempt to detect "hidden" splats, which only reveal themselves as splats
2603  // when re-interpreted as a vector with a larger element type. For example,
2604  // v4i16 = build_vector i16 0, i16 1, i16 0, i16 1
2605  // could be instead splat as
2606  // v2i32 = build_vector i32 0x00010000, i32 0x00010000
2607  // TODO: This optimization could also work on non-constant splats, but it
2608  // would require bit-manipulation instructions to construct the splat value.
2609  SmallVector<SDValue> Sequence;
2610  unsigned EltBitSize = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
2611  const auto *BV = cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(Op);
2612  if (VT.isInteger() && EltBitSize < 64 &&
2613  ISD::isBuildVectorOfConstantSDNodes(Op.getNode()) &&
2614  BV->getRepeatedSequence(Sequence) &&
2615  (Sequence.size() * EltBitSize) <= 64) {
2616  unsigned SeqLen = Sequence.size();
2617  MVT ViaIntVT = MVT::getIntegerVT(EltBitSize * SeqLen);
2618  MVT ViaVecVT = MVT::getVectorVT(ViaIntVT, NumElts / SeqLen);
2619  assert((ViaIntVT == MVT::i16 || ViaIntVT == MVT::i32 ||
2620  ViaIntVT == MVT::i64) &&
2621  "Unexpected sequence type");
2622 
2623  unsigned EltIdx = 0;
2624  uint64_t EltMask = maskTrailingOnes<uint64_t>(EltBitSize);
2625  uint64_t SplatValue = 0;
2626  // Construct the amalgamated value which can be splatted as this larger
2627  // vector type.
2628  for (const auto &SeqV : Sequence) {
2629  if (!SeqV.isUndef())
2630  SplatValue |= ((cast<ConstantSDNode>(SeqV)->getZExtValue() & EltMask)
2631  << (EltIdx * EltBitSize));
2632  EltIdx++;
2633  }
2634 
2635  // On RV64, sign-extend from 32 to 64 bits where possible in order to
2636  // achieve better constant materializion.
2637  if (Subtarget.is64Bit() && ViaIntVT == MVT::i32)
2638  SplatValue = SignExtend64<32>(SplatValue);
2639 
2640  // Since we can't introduce illegal i64 types at this stage, we can only
2641  // perform an i64 splat on RV32 if it is its own sign-extended value. That
2642  // way we can use RVV instructions to splat.
2643  assert((ViaIntVT.bitsLE(XLenVT) ||
2644  (!Subtarget.is64Bit() && ViaIntVT == MVT::i64)) &&
2645  "Unexpected bitcast sequence");
2646  if (ViaIntVT.bitsLE(XLenVT) || isInt<32>(SplatValue)) {
2647  SDValue ViaVL =
2648  DAG.getConstant(ViaVecVT.getVectorNumElements(), DL, XLenVT);
2649  MVT ViaContainerVT =
2650  getContainerForFixedLengthVector(DAG, ViaVecVT, Subtarget);
2651  SDValue Splat =
2652  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, ViaContainerVT,
2653  DAG.getUNDEF(ViaContainerVT),
2654  DAG.getConstant(SplatValue, DL, XLenVT), ViaVL);
2655  Splat = convertFromScalableVector(ViaVecVT, Splat, DAG, Subtarget);
2656  return DAG.getBitcast(VT, Splat);
2657  }
2658  }
2659 
2660  // Try and optimize BUILD_VECTORs with "dominant values" - these are values
2661  // which constitute a large proportion of the elements. In such cases we can
2662  // splat a vector with the dominant element and make up the shortfall with
2663  // INSERT_VECTOR_ELTs.
2664  // Note that this includes vectors of 2 elements by association. The
2665  // upper-most element is the "dominant" one, allowing us to use a splat to
2666  // "insert" the upper element, and an insert of the lower element at position
2667  // 0, which improves codegen.
2668  SDValue DominantValue;
2669  unsigned MostCommonCount = 0;
2670  DenseMap<SDValue, unsigned> ValueCounts;
2671  unsigned NumUndefElts =
2672  count_if(Op->op_values(), [](const SDValue &V) { return V.isUndef(); });
2673 
2674  // Track the number of scalar loads we know we'd be inserting, estimated as
2675  // any non-zero floating-point constant. Other kinds of element are either
2676  // already in registers or are materialized on demand. The threshold at which
2677  // a vector load is more desirable than several scalar materializion and
2678  // vector-insertion instructions is not known.
2679  unsigned NumScalarLoads = 0;
2680 
2681  for (SDValue V : Op->op_values()) {
2682  if (V.isUndef())
2683  continue;
2684 
2685  ValueCounts.insert(std::make_pair(V, 0));
2686  unsigned &Count = ValueCounts[V];
2687 
2688  if (auto *CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(V))
2689  NumScalarLoads += !CFP->isExactlyValue(+0.0);
2690 
2691  // Is this value dominant? In case of a tie, prefer the highest element as
2692  // it's cheaper to insert near the beginning of a vector than it is at the
2693  // end.
2694  if (++Count >= MostCommonCount) {
2695  DominantValue = V;
2696  MostCommonCount = Count;
2697  }
2698  }
2699 
2700  assert(DominantValue && "Not expecting an all-undef BUILD_VECTOR");
2701  unsigned NumDefElts = NumElts - NumUndefElts;
2702  unsigned DominantValueCountThreshold = NumDefElts <= 2 ? 0 : NumDefElts - 2;
2703 
2704  // Don't perform this optimization when optimizing for size, since
2705  // materializing elements and inserting them tends to cause code bloat.
2706  if (!DAG.shouldOptForSize() && NumScalarLoads < NumElts &&
2707  ((MostCommonCount > DominantValueCountThreshold) ||
2708  (ValueCounts.size() <= Log2_32(NumDefElts)))) {
2709  // Start by splatting the most common element.
2710  SDValue Vec = DAG.getSplatBuildVector(VT, DL, DominantValue);
2711 
2712  DenseSet<SDValue> Processed{DominantValue};
2713  MVT SelMaskTy = VT.changeVectorElementType(MVT::i1);
2714  for (const auto &OpIdx : enumerate(Op->ops())) {
2715  const SDValue &V = OpIdx.value();
2716  if (V.isUndef() || !Processed.insert(V).second)
2717  continue;
2718  if (ValueCounts[V] == 1) {
2719  Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, VT, Vec, V,
2720  DAG.getConstant(OpIdx.index(), DL, XLenVT));
2721  } else {
2722  // Blend in all instances of this value using a VSELECT, using a
2723  // mask where each bit signals whether that element is the one
2724  // we're after.
2725  SmallVector<SDValue> Ops;
2726  transform(Op->op_values(), std::back_inserter(Ops), [&](SDValue V1) {
2727  return DAG.getConstant(V == V1, DL, XLenVT);
2728  });
2729  Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::VSELECT, DL, VT,
2730  DAG.getBuildVector(SelMaskTy, DL, Ops),
2731  DAG.getSplatBuildVector(VT, DL, V), Vec);
2732  }
2733  }
2734 
2735  return Vec;
2736  }
2737 
2738  return SDValue();
2739 }
2740 
2741 static SDValue splatPartsI64WithVL(const SDLoc &DL, MVT VT, SDValue Passthru,
2742  SDValue Lo, SDValue Hi, SDValue VL,
2743  SelectionDAG &DAG) {
2744  if (!Passthru)
2745  Passthru = DAG.getUNDEF(VT);
2746  if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(Lo) && isa<ConstantSDNode>(Hi)) {
2747  int32_t LoC = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Lo)->getSExtValue();
2748  int32_t HiC = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Hi)->getSExtValue();
2749  // If Hi constant is all the same sign bit as Lo, lower this as a custom
2750  // node in order to try and match RVV vector/scalar instructions.
2751  if ((LoC >> 31) == HiC)
2752  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, VT, Passthru, Lo, VL);
2753 
2754  // If vl is equal to XLEN_MAX and Hi constant is equal to Lo, we could use
2755  // vmv.v.x whose EEW = 32 to lower it.
2756  auto *Const = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(VL);
2757  if (LoC == HiC && Const && Const->isAllOnesValue()) {
2758  MVT InterVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i32, VT.getVectorElementCount() * 2);
2759  // TODO: if vl <= min(VLMAX), we can also do this. But we could not
2760  // access the subtarget here now.
2761  auto InterVec = DAG.getNode(
2762  RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, InterVT, DAG.getUNDEF(InterVT), Lo,
2763  DAG.getRegister(RISCV::X0, MVT::i32));
2764  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VT, InterVec);
2765  }
2766  }
2767 
2768  // Fall back to a stack store and stride x0 vector load.
2769  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SPLAT_VECTOR_SPLIT_I64_VL, DL, VT, Passthru, Lo,
2770  Hi, VL);
2771 }
2772 
2773 // Called by type legalization to handle splat of i64 on RV32.
2774 // FIXME: We can optimize this when the type has sign or zero bits in one
2775 // of the halves.
2776 static SDValue splatSplitI64WithVL(const SDLoc &DL, MVT VT, SDValue Passthru,
2777  SDValue Scalar, SDValue VL,
2778  SelectionDAG &DAG) {
2779  assert(Scalar.getValueType() == MVT::i64 && "Unexpected VT!");
2780  SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, DL, MVT::i32, Scalar,
2781  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32));
2782  SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, DL, MVT::i32, Scalar,
2783  DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32));
2784  return splatPartsI64WithVL(DL, VT, Passthru, Lo, Hi, VL, DAG);
2785 }
2786 
2787 // This function lowers a splat of a scalar operand Splat with the vector
2788 // length VL. It ensures the final sequence is type legal, which is useful when
2789 // lowering a splat after type legalization.
2790 static SDValue lowerScalarSplat(SDValue Passthru, SDValue Scalar, SDValue VL,
2791  MVT VT, SDLoc DL, SelectionDAG &DAG,
2792  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
2793  bool HasPassthru = Passthru && !Passthru.isUndef();
2794  if (!HasPassthru && !Passthru)
2795  Passthru = DAG.getUNDEF(VT);
2796  if (VT.isFloatingPoint()) {
2797  // If VL is 1, we could use vfmv.s.f.
2798  if (isOneConstant(VL))
2799  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VFMV_S_F_VL, DL, VT, Passthru, Scalar, VL);
2800  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VFMV_V_F_VL, DL, VT, Passthru, Scalar, VL);
2801  }
2802 
2803  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
2804 
2805  // Simplest case is that the operand needs to be promoted to XLenVT.
2806  if (Scalar.getValueType().bitsLE(XLenVT)) {
2807  // If the operand is a constant, sign extend to increase our chances
2808  // of being able to use a .vi instruction. ANY_EXTEND would become a
2809  // a zero extend and the simm5 check in isel would fail.
2810  // FIXME: Should we ignore the upper bits in isel instead?
2811  unsigned ExtOpc =
2812  isa<ConstantSDNode>(Scalar) ? ISD::SIGN_EXTEND : ISD::ANY_EXTEND;
2813  Scalar = DAG.getNode(ExtOpc, DL, XLenVT, Scalar);
2814  ConstantSDNode *Const = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Scalar);
2815  // If VL is 1 and the scalar value won't benefit from immediate, we could
2816  // use vmv.s.x.
2817  if (isOneConstant(VL) &&
2818  (!Const || isNullConstant(Scalar) || !isInt<5>(Const->getSExtValue())))
2819  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_S_X_VL, DL, VT, Passthru, Scalar, VL);
2820  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, VT, Passthru, Scalar, VL);
2821  }
2822 
2823  assert(XLenVT == MVT::i32 && Scalar.getValueType() == MVT::i64 &&
2824  "Unexpected scalar for splat lowering!");
2825 
2826  if (isOneConstant(VL) && isNullConstant(Scalar))
2827  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_S_X_VL, DL, VT, Passthru,
2828  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT), VL);
2829 
2830  // Otherwise use the more complicated splatting algorithm.
2831  return splatSplitI64WithVL(DL, VT, Passthru, Scalar, VL, DAG);
2832 }
2833 
2834 static MVT getLMUL1VT(MVT VT) {
2835  assert(VT.getVectorElementType().getSizeInBits() <= 64 &&
2836  "Unexpected vector MVT");
2837  return MVT::getScalableVectorVT(
2838  VT.getVectorElementType(),
2839  RISCV::RVVBitsPerBlock / VT.getVectorElementType().getSizeInBits());
2840 }
2841 
2842 // This function lowers an insert of a scalar operand Scalar into lane
2843 // 0 of the vector regardless of the value of VL. The contents of the
2844 // remaining lanes of the result vector are unspecified. VL is assumed
2845 // to be non-zero.
2846 static SDValue lowerScalarInsert(SDValue Scalar, SDValue VL,
2847  MVT VT, SDLoc DL, SelectionDAG &DAG,
2848  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
2849  const MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
2850 
2851  SDValue Passthru = DAG.getUNDEF(VT);
2852  if (VT.isFloatingPoint()) {
2853  // TODO: Use vmv.v.i for appropriate constants
2854  // Use M1 or smaller to avoid over constraining register allocation
2855  const MVT M1VT = getLMUL1VT(VT);
2856  auto InnerVT = VT.bitsLE(M1VT) ? VT : M1VT;
2857  SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VFMV_S_F_VL, DL, InnerVT,
2858  DAG.getUNDEF(InnerVT), Scalar, VL);
2859  if (VT != InnerVT)
2860  Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, VT,
2861  DAG.getUNDEF(VT),
2862  Result, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT));
2863  return Result;
2864  }
2865 
2866 
2867  // Avoid the tricky legalization cases by falling back to using the
2868  // splat code which already handles it gracefully.
2869  if (!Scalar.getValueType().bitsLE(XLenVT))
2870  return lowerScalarSplat(DAG.getUNDEF(VT), Scalar,
2871  DAG.getConstant(1, DL, XLenVT),
2872  VT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
2873 
2874  // If the operand is a constant, sign extend to increase our chances
2875  // of being able to use a .vi instruction. ANY_EXTEND would become a
2876  // a zero extend and the simm5 check in isel would fail.
2877  // FIXME: Should we ignore the upper bits in isel instead?
2878  unsigned ExtOpc =
2879  isa<ConstantSDNode>(Scalar) ? ISD::SIGN_EXTEND : ISD::ANY_EXTEND;
2880  Scalar = DAG.getNode(ExtOpc, DL, XLenVT, Scalar);
2881  // We use a vmv.v.i if possible. We limit this to LMUL1. LMUL2 or
2882  // higher would involve overly constraining the register allocator for
2883  // no purpose.
2884  if (ConstantSDNode *Const = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Scalar)) {
2885  if (!isNullConstant(Scalar) && isInt<5>(Const->getSExtValue()) &&
2886  VT.bitsLE(getLMUL1VT(VT)))
2887  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, VT, Passthru, Scalar, VL);
2888  }
2889  // Use M1 or smaller to avoid over constraining register allocation
2890  const MVT M1VT = getLMUL1VT(VT);
2891  auto InnerVT = VT.bitsLE(M1VT) ? VT : M1VT;
2892  SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_S_X_VL, DL, InnerVT,
2893  DAG.getUNDEF(InnerVT), Scalar, VL);
2894  if (VT != InnerVT)
2895  Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, VT,
2896  DAG.getUNDEF(VT),
2897  Result, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT));
2898  return Result;
2899 
2900 }
2901 
2902 static bool isInterleaveShuffle(ArrayRef<int> Mask, MVT VT, bool &SwapSources,
2903  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
2904  // We need to be able to widen elements to the next larger integer type.
2905  if (VT.getScalarSizeInBits() >= Subtarget.getELEN())
2906  return false;
2907 
2908  int Size = Mask.size();
2909  assert(Size == (int)VT.getVectorNumElements() && "Unexpected mask size");
2910 
2911  int Srcs[] = {-1, -1};
2912  for (int i = 0; i != Size; ++i) {
2913  // Ignore undef elements.
2914  if (Mask[i] < 0)
2915  continue;
2916 
2917  // Is this an even or odd element.
2918  int Pol = i % 2;
2919 
2920  // Ensure we consistently use the same source for this element polarity.
2921  int Src = Mask[i] / Size;
2922  if (Srcs[Pol] < 0)
2923  Srcs[Pol] = Src;
2924  if (Srcs[Pol] != Src)
2925  return false;
2926 
2927  // Make sure the element within the source is appropriate for this element
2928  // in the destination.
2929  int Elt = Mask[i] % Size;
2930  if (Elt != i / 2)
2931  return false;
2932  }
2933 
2934  // We need to find a source for each polarity and they can't be the same.
2935  if (Srcs[0] < 0 || Srcs[1] < 0 || Srcs[0] == Srcs[1])
2936  return false;
2937 
2938  // Swap the sources if the second source was in the even polarity.
2939  SwapSources = Srcs[0] > Srcs[1];
2940 
2941  return true;
2942 }
2943 
2944 /// Match shuffles that concatenate two vectors, rotate the concatenation,
2945 /// and then extract the original number of elements from the rotated result.
2946 /// This is equivalent to vector.splice or X86's PALIGNR instruction. The
2947 /// returned rotation amount is for a rotate right, where elements move from
2948 /// higher elements to lower elements. \p LoSrc indicates the first source
2949 /// vector of the rotate or -1 for undef. \p HiSrc indicates the second vector
2950 /// of the rotate or -1 for undef. At least one of \p LoSrc and \p HiSrc will be
2951 /// 0 or 1 if a rotation is found.
2952 ///
2953 /// NOTE: We talk about rotate to the right which matches how bit shift and
2954 /// rotate instructions are described where LSBs are on the right, but LLVM IR
2955 /// and the table below write vectors with the lowest elements on the left.
2956 static int isElementRotate(int &LoSrc, int &HiSrc, ArrayRef<int> Mask) {
2957  int Size = Mask.size();
2958 
2959  // We need to detect various ways of spelling a rotation:
2960  // [11, 12, 13, 14, 15, 0, 1, 2]
2961  // [-1, 12, 13, 14, -1, -1, 1, -1]
2962  // [-1, -1, -1, -1, -1, -1, 1, 2]
2963  // [ 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10]
2964  // [-1, 4, 5, 6, -1, -1, 9, -1]
2965  // [-1, 4, 5, 6, -1, -1, -1, -1]
2966  int Rotation = 0;
2967  LoSrc = -1;
2968  HiSrc = -1;
2969  for (int i = 0; i != Size; ++i) {
2970  int M = Mask[i];
2971  if (M < 0)
2972  continue;
2973 
2974  // Determine where a rotate vector would have started.
2975  int StartIdx = i - (M % Size);
2976  // The identity rotation isn't interesting, stop.
2977  if (StartIdx == 0)
2978  return -1;
2979 
2980  // If we found the tail of a vector the rotation must be the missing
2981  // front. If we found the head of a vector, it must be how much of the
2982  // head.
2983  int CandidateRotation = StartIdx < 0 ? -StartIdx : Size - StartIdx;
2984 
2985  if (Rotation == 0)
2986  Rotation = CandidateRotation;
2987  else if (Rotation != CandidateRotation)
2988  // The rotations don't match, so we can't match this mask.
2989  return -1;
2990 
2991  // Compute which value this mask is pointing at.
2992  int MaskSrc = M < Size ? 0 : 1;
2993 
2994  // Compute which of the two target values this index should be assigned to.
2995  // This reflects whether the high elements are remaining or the low elemnts
2996  // are remaining.
2997  int &TargetSrc = StartIdx < 0 ? HiSrc : LoSrc;
2998 
2999  // Either set up this value if we've not encountered it before, or check
3000  // that it remains consistent.
3001  if (TargetSrc < 0)
3002  TargetSrc = MaskSrc;
3003  else if (TargetSrc != MaskSrc)
3004  // This may be a rotation, but it pulls from the inputs in some
3005  // unsupported interleaving.
3006  return -1;
3007  }
3008 
3009  // Check that we successfully analyzed the mask, and normalize the results.
3010  assert(Rotation != 0 && "Failed to locate a viable rotation!");
3011  assert((LoSrc >= 0 || HiSrc >= 0) &&
3012  "Failed to find a rotated input vector!");
3013 
3014  return Rotation;
3015 }
3016 
3017 // Lower the following shuffles to vnsrl.
3018 // t34: v8i8 = extract_subvector t11, Constant:i64<0>
3019 // t33: v8i8 = extract_subvector t11, Constant:i64<8>
3020 // a) t35: v8i8 = vector_shuffle<0,2,4,6,8,10,12,14> t34, t33
3021 // b) t35: v8i8 = vector_shuffle<1,3,5,7,9,11,13,15> t34, t33
3022 static SDValue lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLEAsVNSRL(const SDLoc &DL, MVT VT,
3023  MVT ContainerVT, SDValue V1,
3024  SDValue V2, SDValue TrueMask,
3025  SDValue VL, ArrayRef<int> Mask,
3026  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget,
3027  SelectionDAG &DAG) {
3028  // Need to be able to widen the vector.
3029  if (VT.getScalarSizeInBits() >= Subtarget.getELEN())
3030  return SDValue();
3031 
3032  // Both input must be extracts.
3033  if (V1.getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR ||
3034  V2.getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR)
3035  return SDValue();
3036 
3037  // Extracting from the same source.
3038  SDValue Src = V1.getOperand(0);
3039  if (Src != V2.getOperand(0))
3040  return SDValue();
3041 
3042  // Src needs to have twice the number of elements.
3043  if (Src.getValueType().getVectorNumElements() != (Mask.size() * 2))
3044  return SDValue();
3045 
3046  // The extracts must extract the two halves of the source.
3047  if (V1.getConstantOperandVal(1) != 0 ||
3048  V2.getConstantOperandVal(1) != Mask.size())
3049  return SDValue();
3050 
3051  // First index must be the first even or odd element from V1.
3052  if (Mask[0] != 0 && Mask[0] != 1)
3053  return SDValue();
3054 
3055  // The others must increase by 2 each time.
3056  // TODO: Support undef elements?
3057  for (unsigned i = 1; i != Mask.size(); ++i)
3058  if (Mask[i] != Mask[i - 1] + 2)
3059  return SDValue();
3060 
3061  // Convert the source using a container type with twice the elements. Since
3062  // source VT is legal and twice this VT, we know VT isn't LMUL=8 so it is
3063  // safe to double.
3064  MVT DoubleContainerVT =
3065  MVT::getVectorVT(ContainerVT.getVectorElementType(),
3066  ContainerVT.getVectorElementCount() * 2);
3067  Src = convertToScalableVector(DoubleContainerVT, Src, DAG, Subtarget);
3068 
3069  // Convert the vector to a wider integer type with the original element
3070  // count. This also converts FP to int.
3071  unsigned EltBits = ContainerVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
3072  MVT WideIntEltVT = MVT::getIntegerVT(EltBits * 2);
3073  MVT WideIntContainerVT =
3074  MVT::getVectorVT(WideIntEltVT, ContainerVT.getVectorElementCount());
3075  Src = DAG.getBitcast(WideIntContainerVT, Src);
3076 
3077  // Convert to the integer version of the container type.
3078  MVT IntEltVT = MVT::getIntegerVT(EltBits);
3079  MVT IntContainerVT =
3080  MVT::getVectorVT(IntEltVT, ContainerVT.getVectorElementCount());
3081 
3082  // If we want even elements, then the shift amount is 0. Otherwise, shift by
3083  // the original element size.
3084  unsigned Shift = Mask[0] == 0 ? 0 : EltBits;
3085  SDValue SplatShift = DAG.getNode(
3086  RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, IntContainerVT, DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT),
3087  DAG.getConstant(Shift, DL, Subtarget.getXLenVT()), VL);
3088  SDValue Res =
3089  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VNSRL_VL, DL, IntContainerVT, Src, SplatShift,
3090  DAG.getUNDEF(IntContainerVT), TrueMask, VL);
3091  // Cast back to FP if needed.
3092  Res = DAG.getBitcast(ContainerVT, Res);
3093 
3094  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, Res, DAG, Subtarget);
3095 }
3096 
3097 static SDValue
3098 getVSlidedown(SelectionDAG &DAG, const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget, SDLoc DL,
3099  EVT VT, SDValue Merge, SDValue Op, SDValue Offset, SDValue Mask,
3100  SDValue VL,
3101  unsigned Policy = RISCVII::TAIL_UNDISTURBED_MASK_UNDISTURBED) {
3102  if (Merge.isUndef())
3103  Policy = RISCVII::TAIL_AGNOSTIC | RISCVII::MASK_AGNOSTIC;
3104  SDValue PolicyOp = DAG.getTargetConstant(Policy, DL, Subtarget.getXLenVT());
3105  SDValue Ops[] = {Merge, Op, Offset, Mask, VL, PolicyOp};
3106  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VSLIDEDOWN_VL, DL, VT, Ops);
3107 }
3108 
3109 static SDValue
3110 getVSlideup(SelectionDAG &DAG, const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget, SDLoc DL,
3111  EVT VT, SDValue Merge, SDValue Op, SDValue Offset, SDValue Mask,
3112  SDValue VL,
3113  unsigned Policy = RISCVII::TAIL_UNDISTURBED_MASK_UNDISTURBED) {
3114  if (Merge.isUndef())
3115  Policy = RISCVII::TAIL_AGNOSTIC | RISCVII::MASK_AGNOSTIC;
3116  SDValue PolicyOp = DAG.getTargetConstant(Policy, DL, Subtarget.getXLenVT());
3117  SDValue Ops[] = {Merge, Op, Offset, Mask, VL, PolicyOp};
3118  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VSLIDEUP_VL, DL, VT, Ops);
3119 }
3120 
3121 // Lower the following shuffle to vslidedown.
3122 // a)
3123 // t49: v8i8 = extract_subvector t13, Constant:i64<0>
3124 // t109: v8i8 = extract_subvector t13, Constant:i64<8>
3125 // t108: v8i8 = vector_shuffle<1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8> t49, t106
3126 // b)
3127 // t69: v16i16 = extract_subvector t68, Constant:i64<0>
3128 // t23: v8i16 = extract_subvector t69, Constant:i64<0>
3129 // t29: v4i16 = extract_subvector t23, Constant:i64<4>
3130 // t26: v8i16 = extract_subvector t69, Constant:i64<8>
3131 // t30: v4i16 = extract_subvector t26, Constant:i64<0>
3132 // t54: v4i16 = vector_shuffle<1,2,3,4> t29, t30
3133 static SDValue lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLEAsVSlidedown(const SDLoc &DL, MVT VT,
3134  SDValue V1, SDValue V2,
3135  ArrayRef<int> Mask,
3136  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget,
3137  SelectionDAG &DAG) {
3138  auto findNonEXTRACT_SUBVECTORParent =
3139  [](SDValue Parent) -> std::pair<SDValue, uint64_t> {
3140  uint64_t Offset = 0;
3141  while (Parent.getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR &&
3142  // EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR can be used to extract a fixed-width vector from
3143  // a scalable vector. But we don't want to match the case.
3144  Parent.getOperand(0).getSimpleValueType().isFixedLengthVector()) {
3145  Offset += Parent.getConstantOperandVal(1);
3146  Parent = Parent.getOperand(0);
3147  }
3148  return std::make_pair(Parent, Offset);
3149  };
3150 
3151  auto [V1Src, V1IndexOffset] = findNonEXTRACT_SUBVECTORParent(V1);
3152  auto [V2Src, V2IndexOffset] = findNonEXTRACT_SUBVECTORParent(V2);
3153 
3154  // Extracting from the same source.
3155  SDValue Src = V1Src;
3156  if (Src != V2Src)
3157  return SDValue();
3158 
3159  // Rebuild mask because Src may be from multiple EXTRACT_SUBVECTORs.
3160  SmallVector<int, 16> NewMask(Mask);
3161  for (size_t i = 0; i != NewMask.size(); ++i) {
3162  if (NewMask[i] == -1)
3163  continue;
3164 
3165  if (static_cast<size_t>(NewMask[i]) < NewMask.size()) {
3166  NewMask[i] = NewMask[i] + V1IndexOffset;
3167  } else {
3168  // Minus NewMask.size() is needed. Otherwise, the b case would be
3169  // <5,6,7,12> instead of <5,6,7,8>.
3170  NewMask[i] = NewMask[i] - NewMask.size() + V2IndexOffset;
3171  }
3172  }
3173 
3174  // First index must be known and non-zero. It will be used as the slidedown
3175  // amount.
3176  if (NewMask[0] <= 0)
3177  return SDValue();
3178 
3179  // NewMask is also continuous.
3180  for (unsigned i = 1; i != NewMask.size(); ++i)
3181  if (NewMask[i - 1] + 1 != NewMask[i])
3182  return SDValue();
3183 
3184  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
3185  MVT SrcVT = Src.getSimpleValueType();
3186  MVT ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(DAG, SrcVT, Subtarget);
3187  auto [TrueMask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(SrcVT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
3188  SDValue Slidedown =
3189  getVSlidedown(DAG, Subtarget, DL, ContainerVT, DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT),
3190  convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Src, DAG, Subtarget),
3191  DAG.getConstant(NewMask[0], DL, XLenVT), TrueMask, VL);
3192  return DAG.getNode(
3193  ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, VT,
3194  convertFromScalableVector(SrcVT, Slidedown, DAG, Subtarget),
3195  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT));
3196 }
3197 
3198 static SDValue lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
3199  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
3200  SDValue V1 = Op.getOperand(0);
3201  SDValue V2 = Op.getOperand(1);
3202  SDLoc DL(Op);
3203  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
3204  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
3205  unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
3206  ShuffleVectorSDNode *SVN = cast<ShuffleVectorSDNode>(Op.getNode());
3207 
3208  MVT ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(DAG, VT, Subtarget);
3209 
3210  auto [TrueMask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(VT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
3211 
3212  if (SVN->isSplat()) {
3213  const int Lane = SVN->getSplatIndex();
3214  if (Lane >= 0) {
3215  MVT SVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
3216 
3217  // Turn splatted vector load into a strided load with an X0 stride.
3218  SDValue V = V1;
3219  // Peek through CONCAT_VECTORS as VectorCombine can concat a vector
3220  // with undef.
3221  // FIXME: Peek through INSERT_SUBVECTOR, EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, bitcasts?
3222  int Offset = Lane;
3223  if (V.getOpcode() == ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS) {
3224  int OpElements =
3225  V.getOperand(0).getSimpleValueType().getVectorNumElements();
3226  V = V.getOperand(Offset / OpElements);
3227  Offset %= OpElements;
3228  }
3229 
3230  // We need to ensure the load isn't atomic or volatile.
3231  if (ISD::isNormalLoad(V.getNode()) && cast<LoadSDNode>(V)->isSimple()) {
3232  auto *Ld = cast<LoadSDNode>(V);
3233  Offset *= SVT.getStoreSize();
3234  SDValue NewAddr = DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(Ld->getBasePtr(),
3235  TypeSize::Fixed(Offset), DL);
3236 
3237  // If this is SEW=64 on RV32, use a strided load with a stride of x0.
3238  if (SVT.isInteger() && SVT.bitsGT(XLenVT)) {
3239  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList({ContainerVT, MVT::Other});
3240  SDValue IntID =
3241  DAG.getTargetConstant(Intrinsic::riscv_vlse, DL, XLenVT);
3242  SDValue Ops[] = {Ld->getChain(),
3243  IntID,
3244  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT),
3245  NewAddr,
3246  DAG.getRegister(RISCV::X0, XLenVT),
3247  VL};
3248  SDValue NewLoad = DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(
3249  ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN, DL, VTs, Ops, SVT,
3250  DAG.getMachineFunction().getMachineMemOperand(
3251  Ld->getMemOperand(), Offset, SVT.getStoreSize()));
3252  DAG.makeEquivalentMemoryOrdering(Ld, NewLoad);
3253  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, NewLoad, DAG, Subtarget);
3254  }
3255 
3256  // Otherwise use a scalar load and splat. This will give the best
3257  // opportunity to fold a splat into the operation. ISel can turn it into
3258  // the x0 strided load if we aren't able to fold away the select.
3259  if (SVT.isFloatingPoint())
3260  V = DAG.getLoad(SVT, DL, Ld->getChain(), NewAddr,
3261  Ld->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Offset),
3262  Ld->getOriginalAlign(),
3263  Ld->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
3264  else
3265  V = DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::SEXTLOAD, DL, XLenVT, Ld->getChain(), NewAddr,
3266  Ld->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Offset), SVT,
3267  Ld->getOriginalAlign(),
3268  Ld->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
3269  DAG.makeEquivalentMemoryOrdering(Ld, V);
3270 
3271  unsigned Opc =
3272  VT.isFloatingPoint() ? RISCVISD::VFMV_V_F_VL : RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL;
3273  SDValue Splat =
3274  DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, ContainerVT, DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), V, VL);
3275  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, Splat, DAG, Subtarget);
3276  }
3277 
3278  V1 = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, V1, DAG, Subtarget);
3279  assert(Lane < (int)NumElts && "Unexpected lane!");
3280  SDValue Gather = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VRGATHER_VX_VL, DL, ContainerVT,
3281  V1, DAG.getConstant(Lane, DL, XLenVT),
3282  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), TrueMask, VL);
3283  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, Gather, DAG, Subtarget);
3284  }
3285  }
3286 
3287  ArrayRef<int> Mask = SVN->getMask();
3288 
3289  if (SDValue V =
3290  lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLEAsVSlidedown(DL, VT, V1, V2, Mask, Subtarget, DAG))
3291  return V;
3292 
3293  // Lower rotations to a SLIDEDOWN and a SLIDEUP. One of the source vectors may
3294  // be undef which can be handled with a single SLIDEDOWN/UP.
3295  int LoSrc, HiSrc;
3296  int Rotation = isElementRotate(LoSrc, HiSrc, Mask);
3297  if (Rotation > 0) {
3298  SDValue LoV, HiV;
3299  if (LoSrc >= 0) {
3300  LoV = LoSrc == 0 ? V1 : V2;
3301  LoV = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, LoV, DAG, Subtarget);
3302  }
3303  if (HiSrc >= 0) {
3304  HiV = HiSrc == 0 ? V1 : V2;
3305  HiV = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, HiV, DAG, Subtarget);
3306  }
3307 
3308  // We found a rotation. We need to slide HiV down by Rotation. Then we need
3309  // to slide LoV up by (NumElts - Rotation).
3310  unsigned InvRotate = NumElts - Rotation;
3311 
3312  SDValue Res = DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT);
3313  if (HiV) {
3314  // If we are doing a SLIDEDOWN+SLIDEUP, reduce the VL for the SLIDEDOWN.
3315  // FIXME: If we are only doing a SLIDEDOWN, don't reduce the VL as it
3316  // causes multiple vsetvlis in some test cases such as lowering
3317  // reduce.mul
3318  SDValue DownVL = VL;
3319  if (LoV)
3320  DownVL = DAG.getConstant(InvRotate, DL, XLenVT);
3321  Res = getVSlidedown(DAG, Subtarget, DL, ContainerVT, Res, HiV,
3322  DAG.getConstant(Rotation, DL, XLenVT), TrueMask,
3323  DownVL);
3324  }
3325  if (LoV)
3326  Res = getVSlideup(DAG, Subtarget, DL, ContainerVT, Res, LoV,
3327  DAG.getConstant(InvRotate, DL, XLenVT), TrueMask, VL,
3328  RISCVII::TAIL_AGNOSTIC);
3329 
3330  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, Res, DAG, Subtarget);
3331  }
3332 
3333  if (SDValue V = lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLEAsVNSRL(
3334  DL, VT, ContainerVT, V1, V2, TrueMask, VL, Mask, Subtarget, DAG))
3335  return V;
3336 
3337  // Detect an interleave shuffle and lower to
3338  // (vmaccu.vx (vwaddu.vx lohalf(V1), lohalf(V2)), lohalf(V2), (2^eltbits - 1))
3339  bool SwapSources;
3340  if (isInterleaveShuffle(Mask, VT, SwapSources, Subtarget)) {
3341  // Swap sources if needed.
3342  if (SwapSources)
3343  std::swap(V1, V2);
3344 
3345  // Extract the lower half of the vectors.
3346  MVT HalfVT = VT.getHalfNumVectorElementsVT();
3347  V1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, HalfVT, V1,
3348  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT));
3349  V2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, HalfVT, V2,
3350  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT));
3351 
3352  // Double the element width and halve the number of elements in an int type.
3353  unsigned EltBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
3354  MVT WideIntEltVT = MVT::getIntegerVT(EltBits * 2);
3355  MVT WideIntVT =
3356  MVT::getVectorVT(WideIntEltVT, VT.getVectorNumElements() / 2);
3357  // Convert this to a scalable vector. We need to base this on the
3358  // destination size to ensure there's always a type with a smaller LMUL.
3359  MVT WideIntContainerVT =
3360  getContainerForFixedLengthVector(DAG, WideIntVT, Subtarget);
3361 
3362  // Convert sources to scalable vectors with the same element count as the
3363  // larger type.
3364  MVT HalfContainerVT = MVT::getVectorVT(
3365  VT.getVectorElementType(), WideIntContainerVT.getVectorElementCount());
3366  V1 = convertToScalableVector(HalfContainerVT, V1, DAG, Subtarget);
3367  V2 = convertToScalableVector(HalfContainerVT, V2, DAG, Subtarget);
3368 
3369  // Cast sources to integer.
3370  MVT IntEltVT = MVT::getIntegerVT(EltBits);
3371  MVT IntHalfVT =
3372  MVT::getVectorVT(IntEltVT, HalfContainerVT.getVectorElementCount());
3373  V1 = DAG.getBitcast(IntHalfVT, V1);
3374  V2 = DAG.getBitcast(IntHalfVT, V2);
3375 
3376  // Freeze V2 since we use it twice and we need to be sure that the add and
3377  // multiply see the same value.
3378  V2 = DAG.getFreeze(V2);
3379 
3380  // Recreate TrueMask using the widened type's element count.
3381  TrueMask = getAllOnesMask(HalfContainerVT, VL, DL, DAG);
3382 
3383  // Widen V1 and V2 with 0s and add one copy of V2 to V1.
3384  SDValue Add =
3385  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VWADDU_VL, DL, WideIntContainerVT, V1, V2,
3386  DAG.getUNDEF(WideIntContainerVT), TrueMask, VL);
3387  // Create 2^eltbits - 1 copies of V2 by multiplying by the largest integer.
3388  SDValue Multiplier = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, IntHalfVT,
3389  DAG.getUNDEF(IntHalfVT),
3390  DAG.getAllOnesConstant(DL, XLenVT), VL);
3391  SDValue WidenMul =
3392  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VWMULU_VL, DL, WideIntContainerVT, V2, Multiplier,
3393  DAG.getUNDEF(WideIntContainerVT), TrueMask, VL);
3394  // Add the new copies to our previous addition giving us 2^eltbits copies of
3395  // V2. This is equivalent to shifting V2 left by eltbits. This should
3396  // combine with the vwmulu.vv above to form vwmaccu.vv.
3397  Add = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::ADD_VL, DL, WideIntContainerVT, Add, WidenMul,
3398  DAG.getUNDEF(WideIntContainerVT), TrueMask, VL);
3399  // Cast back to ContainerVT. We need to re-create a new ContainerVT in case
3400  // WideIntContainerVT is a larger fractional LMUL than implied by the fixed
3401  // vector VT.
3402  ContainerVT =
3403  MVT::getVectorVT(VT.getVectorElementType(),
3404  WideIntContainerVT.getVectorElementCount() * 2);
3405  Add = DAG.getBitcast(ContainerVT, Add);
3406  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, Add, DAG, Subtarget);
3407  }
3408 
3409  // Detect shuffles which can be re-expressed as vector selects; these are
3410  // shuffles in which each element in the destination is taken from an element
3411  // at the corresponding index in either source vectors.
3412  bool IsSelect = all_of(enumerate(Mask), [&](const auto &MaskIdx) {
3413  int MaskIndex = MaskIdx.value();
3414  return MaskIndex < 0 || MaskIdx.index() == (unsigned)MaskIndex % NumElts;
3415  });
3416 
3417  assert(!V1.isUndef() && "Unexpected shuffle canonicalization");
3418 
3419  SmallVector<SDValue> MaskVals;
3420  // As a backup, shuffles can be lowered via a vrgather instruction, possibly
3421  // merged with a second vrgather.
3422  SmallVector<SDValue> GatherIndicesLHS, GatherIndicesRHS;
3423 
3424  // By default we preserve the original operand order, and use a mask to
3425  // select LHS as true and RHS as false. However, since RVV vector selects may
3426  // feature splats but only on the LHS, we may choose to invert our mask and
3427  // instead select between RHS and LHS.
3428  bool SwapOps = DAG.isSplatValue(V2) && !DAG.isSplatValue(V1);
3429  bool InvertMask = IsSelect == SwapOps;
3430 
3431  // Keep a track of which non-undef indices are used by each LHS/RHS shuffle
3432  // half.
3433  DenseMap<int, unsigned> LHSIndexCounts, RHSIndexCounts;
3434 
3435  // Now construct the mask that will be used by the vselect or blended
3436  // vrgather operation. For vrgathers, construct the appropriate indices into
3437  // each vector.
3438  for (int MaskIndex : Mask) {
3439  bool SelectMaskVal = (MaskIndex < (int)NumElts) ^ InvertMask;
3440  MaskVals.push_back(DAG.getConstant(SelectMaskVal, DL, XLenVT));
3441  if (!IsSelect) {
3442  bool IsLHSOrUndefIndex = MaskIndex < (int)NumElts;
3443  GatherIndicesLHS.push_back(IsLHSOrUndefIndex && MaskIndex >= 0
3444  ? DAG.getConstant(MaskIndex, DL, XLenVT)
3445  : DAG.getUNDEF(XLenVT));
3446  GatherIndicesRHS.push_back(
3447  IsLHSOrUndefIndex ? DAG.getUNDEF(XLenVT)
3448  : DAG.getConstant(MaskIndex - NumElts, DL, XLenVT));
3449  if (IsLHSOrUndefIndex && MaskIndex >= 0)
3450  ++LHSIndexCounts[MaskIndex];
3451  if (!IsLHSOrUndefIndex)
3452  ++RHSIndexCounts[MaskIndex - NumElts];
3453  }
3454  }
3455 
3456  if (SwapOps) {
3457  std::swap(V1, V2);
3458  std::swap(GatherIndicesLHS, GatherIndicesRHS);
3459  }
3460 
3461  assert(MaskVals.size() == NumElts && "Unexpected select-like shuffle");
3462  MVT MaskVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i1, NumElts);
3463  SDValue SelectMask = DAG.getBuildVector(MaskVT, DL, MaskVals);
3464 
3465  if (IsSelect)
3466  return DAG.getNode(ISD::VSELECT, DL, VT, SelectMask, V1, V2);
3467 
3468  if (VT.getScalarSizeInBits() == 8 && VT.getVectorNumElements() > 256) {
3469  // On such a large vector we're unable to use i8 as the index type.
3470  // FIXME: We could promote the index to i16 and use vrgatherei16, but that
3471  // may involve vector splitting if we're already at LMUL=8, or our
3472  // user-supplied maximum fixed-length LMUL.
3473  return SDValue();
3474  }
3475 
3476  unsigned GatherVXOpc = RISCVISD::VRGATHER_VX_VL;
3477  unsigned GatherVVOpc = RISCVISD::VRGATHER_VV_VL;
3478  MVT IndexVT = VT.changeTypeToInteger();
3479  // Since we can't introduce illegal index types at this stage, use i16 and
3480  // vrgatherei16 if the corresponding index type for plain vrgather is greater
3481  // than XLenVT.
3482  if (IndexVT.getScalarType().bitsGT(XLenVT)) {
3483  GatherVVOpc = RISCVISD::VRGATHEREI16_VV_VL;
3484  IndexVT = IndexVT.changeVectorElementType(MVT::i16);
3485  }
3486 
3487  MVT IndexContainerVT =
3488  ContainerVT.changeVectorElementType(IndexVT.getScalarType());
3489 
3490  SDValue Gather;
3491  // TODO: This doesn't trigger for i64 vectors on RV32, since there we
3492  // encounter a bitcasted BUILD_VECTOR with low/high i32 values.
3493  if (SDValue SplatValue = DAG.getSplatValue(V1, /*LegalTypes*/ true)) {
3494  Gather = lowerScalarSplat(SDValue(), SplatValue, VL, ContainerVT, DL, DAG,
3495  Subtarget);
3496  } else {
3497  V1 = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, V1, DAG, Subtarget);
3498  // If only one index is used, we can use a "splat" vrgather.
3499  // TODO: We can splat the most-common index and fix-up any stragglers, if
3500  // that's beneficial.
3501  if (LHSIndexCounts.size() == 1) {
3502  int SplatIndex = LHSIndexCounts.begin()->getFirst();
3503  Gather = DAG.getNode(GatherVXOpc, DL, ContainerVT, V1,
3504  DAG.getConstant(SplatIndex, DL, XLenVT),
3505  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), TrueMask, VL);
3506  } else {
3507  SDValue LHSIndices = DAG.getBuildVector(IndexVT, DL, GatherIndicesLHS);
3508  LHSIndices =
3509  convertToScalableVector(IndexContainerVT, LHSIndices, DAG, Subtarget);
3510 
3511  Gather = DAG.getNode(GatherVVOpc, DL, ContainerVT, V1, LHSIndices,
3512  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), TrueMask, VL);
3513  }
3514  }
3515 
3516  // If a second vector operand is used by this shuffle, blend it in with an
3517  // additional vrgather.
3518  if (!V2.isUndef()) {
3519  V2 = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, V2, DAG, Subtarget);
3520 
3521  MVT MaskContainerVT = ContainerVT.changeVectorElementType(MVT::i1);
3522  SelectMask =
3523  convertToScalableVector(MaskContainerVT, SelectMask, DAG, Subtarget);
3524 
3525  // If only one index is used, we can use a "splat" vrgather.
3526  // TODO: We can splat the most-common index and fix-up any stragglers, if
3527  // that's beneficial.
3528  if (RHSIndexCounts.size() == 1) {
3529  int SplatIndex = RHSIndexCounts.begin()->getFirst();
3530  Gather = DAG.getNode(GatherVXOpc, DL, ContainerVT, V2,
3531  DAG.getConstant(SplatIndex, DL, XLenVT), Gather,
3532  SelectMask, VL);
3533  } else {
3534  SDValue RHSIndices = DAG.getBuildVector(IndexVT, DL, GatherIndicesRHS);
3535  RHSIndices =
3536  convertToScalableVector(IndexContainerVT, RHSIndices, DAG, Subtarget);
3537  Gather = DAG.getNode(GatherVVOpc, DL, ContainerVT, V2, RHSIndices, Gather,
3538  SelectMask, VL);
3539  }
3540  }
3541 
3542  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, Gather, DAG, Subtarget);
3543 }
3544 
3545 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isShuffleMaskLegal(ArrayRef<int> M, EVT VT) const {
3546  // Support splats for any type. These should type legalize well.
3547  if (ShuffleVectorSDNode::isSplatMask(M.data(), VT))
3548  return true;
3549 
3550  // Only support legal VTs for other shuffles for now.
3551  if (!isTypeLegal(VT))
3552  return false;
3553 
3554  MVT SVT = VT.getSimpleVT();
3555 
3556  bool SwapSources;
3557  int LoSrc, HiSrc;
3558  return (isElementRotate(LoSrc, HiSrc, M) > 0) ||
3559  isInterleaveShuffle(M, SVT, SwapSources, Subtarget);
3560 }
3561 
3562 // Lower CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF or CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF by converting to FP and extracting
3563 // the exponent.
3564 SDValue
3565 RISCVTargetLowering::lowerCTLZ_CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF(SDValue Op,
3566  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
3567  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
3568  unsigned EltSize = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
3569  SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
3570  SDLoc DL(Op);
3571 
3572  // We choose FP type that can represent the value if possible. Otherwise, we
3573  // use rounding to zero conversion for correct exponent of the result.
3574  // TODO: Use f16 for i8 when possible?
3575  MVT FloatEltVT = (EltSize >= 32) ? MVT::f64 : MVT::f32;
3576  if (!isTypeLegal(MVT::getVectorVT(FloatEltVT, VT.getVectorElementCount())))
3577  FloatEltVT = MVT::f32;
3578  MVT FloatVT = MVT::getVectorVT(FloatEltVT, VT.getVectorElementCount());
3579 
3580  // Legal types should have been checked in the RISCVTargetLowering
3581  // constructor.
3582  // TODO: Splitting may make sense in some cases.
3583  assert(DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo().isTypeLegal(FloatVT) &&
3584  "Expected legal float type!");
3585 
3586  // For CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF, we need to extract the lowest set bit using X & -X.
3587  // The trailing zero count is equal to log2 of this single bit value.
3588  if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF) {
3589  SDValue Neg = DAG.getNegative(Src, DL, VT);
3590  Src = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, Src, Neg);
3591  }
3592 
3593  // We have a legal FP type, convert to it.
3594  SDValue FloatVal;
3595  if (FloatVT.bitsGT(VT)) {
3596  FloatVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::UINT_TO_FP, DL, FloatVT, Src);
3597  } else {
3598  // Use RTZ to avoid rounding influencing exponent of FloatVal.
3599  MVT ContainerVT = VT;
3600  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
3601  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
3602  Src = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Src, DAG, Subtarget);
3603  }
3604 
3605  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(VT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
3606  SDValue RTZRM =
3607  DAG.getTargetConstant(RISCVFPRndMode::RTZ, DL, Subtarget.getXLenVT());
3608  MVT ContainerFloatVT =
3609  MVT::getVectorVT(FloatEltVT, ContainerVT.getVectorElementCount());
3610  FloatVal = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VFCVT_RM_F_XU_VL, DL, ContainerFloatVT,
3611  Src, Mask, RTZRM, VL);
3612  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector())
3613  FloatVal = convertFromScalableVector(FloatVT, FloatVal, DAG, Subtarget);
3614  }
3615  // Bitcast to integer and shift the exponent to the LSB.
3616  EVT IntVT = FloatVT.changeVectorElementTypeToInteger();
3617  SDValue Bitcast = DAG.getBitcast(IntVT, FloatVal);
3618  unsigned ShiftAmt = FloatEltVT == MVT::f64 ? 52 : 23;
3619  SDValue Exp = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, IntVT, Bitcast,
3620  DAG.getConstant(ShiftAmt, DL, IntVT));
3621  // Restore back to original type. Truncation after SRL is to generate vnsrl.
3622  if (IntVT.bitsLT(VT))
3623  Exp = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, VT, Exp);
3624  else if (IntVT.bitsGT(VT))
3625  Exp = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VT, Exp);
3626  // The exponent contains log2 of the value in biased form.
3627  unsigned ExponentBias = FloatEltVT == MVT::f64 ? 1023 : 127;
3628 
3629  // For trailing zeros, we just need to subtract the bias.
3630  if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF)
3631  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, VT, Exp,
3632  DAG.getConstant(ExponentBias, DL, VT));
3633 
3634  // For leading zeros, we need to remove the bias and convert from log2 to
3635  // leading zeros. We can do this by subtracting from (Bias + (EltSize - 1)).
3636  unsigned Adjust = ExponentBias + (EltSize - 1);
3637  SDValue Res =
3638  DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, VT, DAG.getConstant(Adjust, DL, VT), Exp);
3639  // The above result with zero input equals to Adjust which is greater than
3640  // EltSize. Hence, we can do min(Res, EltSize) for CTLZ.
3641  if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::CTLZ)
3642  Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::UMIN, DL, VT, Res, DAG.getConstant(EltSize, DL, VT));
3643  return Res;
3644 }
3645 
3646 // While RVV has alignment restrictions, we should always be able to load as a
3647 // legal equivalently-sized byte-typed vector instead. This method is
3648 // responsible for re-expressing a ISD::LOAD via a correctly-aligned type. If
3649 // the load is already correctly-aligned, it returns SDValue().
3650 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::expandUnalignedRVVLoad(SDValue Op,
3651  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
3652  auto *Load = cast<LoadSDNode>(Op);
3653  assert(Load && Load->getMemoryVT().isVector() && "Expected vector load");
3654 
3655  if (allowsMemoryAccessForAlignment(*DAG.getContext(), DAG.getDataLayout(),
3656  Load->getMemoryVT(),
3657  *Load->getMemOperand()))
3658  return SDValue();
3659 
3660  SDLoc DL(Op);
3661  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
3662  unsigned EltSizeBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
3663  assert((EltSizeBits == 16 || EltSizeBits == 32 || EltSizeBits == 64) &&
3664  "Unexpected unaligned RVV load type");
3665  MVT NewVT =
3666  MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i8, VT.getVectorElementCount() * (EltSizeBits / 8));
3667  assert(NewVT.isValid() &&
3668  "Expecting equally-sized RVV vector types to be legal");
3669  SDValue L = DAG.getLoad(NewVT, DL, Load->getChain(), Load->getBasePtr(),
3670  Load->getPointerInfo(), Load->getOriginalAlign(),
3671  Load->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
3672  return DAG.getMergeValues({DAG.getBitcast(VT, L), L.getValue(1)}, DL);
3673 }
3674 
3675 // While RVV has alignment restrictions, we should always be able to store as a
3676 // legal equivalently-sized byte-typed vector instead. This method is
3677 // responsible for re-expressing a ISD::STORE via a correctly-aligned type. It
3678 // returns SDValue() if the store is already correctly aligned.
3679 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::expandUnalignedRVVStore(SDValue Op,
3680  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
3681  auto *Store = cast<StoreSDNode>(Op);
3682  assert(Store && Store->getValue().getValueType().isVector() &&
3683  "Expected vector store");
3684 
3685  if (allowsMemoryAccessForAlignment(*DAG.getContext(), DAG.getDataLayout(),
3686  Store->getMemoryVT(),
3687  *Store->getMemOperand()))
3688  return SDValue();
3689 
3690  SDLoc DL(Op);
3691  SDValue StoredVal = Store->getValue();
3692  MVT VT = StoredVal.getSimpleValueType();
3693  unsigned EltSizeBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
3694  assert((EltSizeBits == 16 || EltSizeBits == 32 || EltSizeBits == 64) &&
3695  "Unexpected unaligned RVV store type");
3696  MVT NewVT =
3697  MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i8, VT.getVectorElementCount() * (EltSizeBits / 8));
3698  assert(NewVT.isValid() &&
3699  "Expecting equally-sized RVV vector types to be legal");
3700  StoredVal = DAG.getBitcast(NewVT, StoredVal);
3701  return DAG.getStore(Store->getChain(), DL, StoredVal, Store->getBasePtr(),
3702  Store->getPointerInfo(), Store->getOriginalAlign(),
3703  Store->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
3704 }
3705 
3706 static SDValue lowerConstant(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
3707  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
3708  assert(Op.getValueType() == MVT::i64 && "Unexpected VT");
3709 
3710  int64_t Imm = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)->getSExtValue();
3711 
3712  // All simm32 constants should be handled by isel.
3713  // NOTE: The getMaxBuildIntsCost call below should return a value >= 2 making
3714  // this check redundant, but small immediates are common so this check
3715  // should have better compile time.
3716  if (isInt<32>(Imm))
3717  return Op;
3718 
3719  // We only need to cost the immediate, if constant pool lowering is enabled.
3720  if (!Subtarget.useConstantPoolForLargeInts())
3721  return Op;
3722 
3723  RISCVMatInt::InstSeq Seq =
3724  RISCVMatInt::generateInstSeq(Imm, Subtarget.getFeatureBits());
3725  if (Seq.size() <= Subtarget.getMaxBuildIntsCost())
3726  return Op;
3727 
3728  // Expand to a constant pool using the default expansion code.
3729  return SDValue();
3730 }
3731 
3732 static SDValue LowerATOMIC_FENCE(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
3733  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
3734  SDLoc dl(Op);
3735  AtomicOrdering FenceOrdering =
3736  static_cast<AtomicOrdering>(Op.getConstantOperandVal(1));
3737  SyncScope::ID FenceSSID =
3738  static_cast<SyncScope::ID>(Op.getConstantOperandVal(2));
3739 
3740  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZtso()) {
3741  // The only fence that needs an instruction is a sequentially-consistent
3742  // cross-thread fence.
3743  if (FenceOrdering == AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent &&
3744  FenceSSID == SyncScope::System)
3745  return Op;
3746 
3747  // MEMBARRIER is a compiler barrier; it codegens to a no-op.
3748  return DAG.getNode(ISD::MEMBARRIER, dl, MVT::Other, Op.getOperand(0));
3749  }
3750 
3751  // singlethread fences only synchronize with signal handlers on the same
3752  // thread and thus only need to preserve instruction order, not actually
3753  // enforce memory ordering.
3754  if (FenceSSID == SyncScope::SingleThread)
3755  // MEMBARRIER is a compiler barrier; it codegens to a no-op.
3756  return DAG.getNode(ISD::MEMBARRIER, dl, MVT::Other, Op.getOperand(0));
3757 
3758  return Op;
3759 }
3760 
3761 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::LowerOperation(SDValue Op,
3762  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
3763  switch (Op.getOpcode()) {
3764  default:
3765  report_fatal_error("unimplemented operand");
3766  case ISD::ATOMIC_FENCE:
3767  return LowerATOMIC_FENCE(Op, DAG, Subtarget);
3768  case ISD::GlobalAddress:
3769  return lowerGlobalAddress(Op, DAG);
3770  case ISD::BlockAddress:
3771  return lowerBlockAddress(Op, DAG);
3772  case ISD::ConstantPool:
3773  return lowerConstantPool(Op, DAG);
3774  case ISD::JumpTable:
3775  return lowerJumpTable(Op, DAG);
3776  case ISD::GlobalTLSAddress:
3777  return lowerGlobalTLSAddress(Op, DAG);
3778  case ISD::Constant:
3779  return lowerConstant(Op, DAG, Subtarget);
3780  case ISD::SELECT:
3781  return lowerSELECT(Op, DAG);
3782  case ISD::BRCOND:
3783  return lowerBRCOND(Op, DAG);
3784  case ISD::VASTART:
3785  return lowerVASTART(Op, DAG);
3786  case ISD::FRAMEADDR:
3787  return lowerFRAMEADDR(Op, DAG);
3788  case ISD::RETURNADDR:
3789  return lowerRETURNADDR(Op, DAG);
3790  case ISD::SHL_PARTS:
3791  return lowerShiftLeftParts(Op, DAG);
3792  case ISD::SRA_PARTS:
3793  return lowerShiftRightParts(Op, DAG, true);
3794  case ISD::SRL_PARTS:
3795  return lowerShiftRightParts(Op, DAG, false);
3796  case ISD::BITCAST: {
3797  SDLoc DL(Op);
3798  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
3799  SDValue Op0 = Op.getOperand(0);
3800  EVT Op0VT = Op0.getValueType();
3801  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
3802  if (VT == MVT::f16 && Op0VT == MVT::i16 &&
3803  Subtarget.hasStdExtZfhOrZfhmin()) {
3804  SDValue NewOp0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, XLenVT, Op0);
3805  SDValue FPConv = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FMV_H_X, DL, MVT::f16, NewOp0);
3806  return FPConv;
3807  }
3808  if (VT == MVT::f32 && Op0VT == MVT::i32 && Subtarget.is64Bit() &&
3809  Subtarget.hasStdExtF()) {
3810  SDValue NewOp0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, Op0);
3811  SDValue FPConv =
3812  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FMV_W_X_RV64, DL, MVT::f32, NewOp0);
3813  return FPConv;
3814  }
3815 
3816  // Consider other scalar<->scalar casts as legal if the types are legal.
3817  // Otherwise expand them.
3818  if (!VT.isVector() && !Op0VT.isVector()) {
3819  if (isTypeLegal(VT) && isTypeLegal(Op0VT))
3820  return Op;
3821  return SDValue();
3822  }
3823 
3824  assert(!VT.isScalableVector() && !Op0VT.isScalableVector() &&
3825  "Unexpected types");
3826 
3827  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
3828  // We can handle fixed length vector bitcasts with a simple replacement
3829  // in isel.
3830  if (Op0VT.isFixedLengthVector())
3831  return Op;
3832  // When bitcasting from scalar to fixed-length vector, insert the scalar
3833  // into a one-element vector of the result type, and perform a vector
3834  // bitcast.
3835  if (!Op0VT.isVector()) {
3836  EVT BVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), Op0VT, 1);
3837  if (!isTypeLegal(BVT))
3838  return SDValue();
3839  return DAG.getBitcast(VT, DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, BVT,
3840  DAG.getUNDEF(BVT), Op0,
3841  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT)));
3842  }
3843  return SDValue();
3844  }
3845  // Custom-legalize bitcasts from fixed-length vector types to scalar types
3846  // thus: bitcast the vector to a one-element vector type whose element type
3847  // is the same as the result type, and extract the first element.
3848  if (!VT.isVector() && Op0VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
3849  EVT BVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), VT, 1);
3850  if (!isTypeLegal(BVT))
3851  return SDValue();
3852  SDValue BVec = DAG.getBitcast(BVT, Op0);
3853  return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, VT, BVec,
3854  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT));
3855  }
3856  return SDValue();
3857  }
3858  case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN:
3859  return LowerINTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN(Op, DAG);
3860  case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN:
3861  return LowerINTRINSIC_W_CHAIN(Op, DAG);
3862  case ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID:
3863  return LowerINTRINSIC_VOID(Op, DAG);
3864  case ISD::BITREVERSE: {
3865  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
3866  SDLoc DL(Op);
3867  assert(Subtarget.hasStdExtZbkb() && "Unexpected custom legalization");
3868  assert(Op.getOpcode() == ISD::BITREVERSE && "Unexpected opcode");
3869  // Expand bitreverse to a bswap(rev8) followed by brev8.
3870  SDValue BSwap = DAG.getNode(ISD::BSWAP, DL, VT, Op.getOperand(0));
3871  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::BREV8, DL, VT, BSwap);
3872  }
3873  case ISD::TRUNCATE:
3874  // Only custom-lower vector truncates
3875  if (!Op.getSimpleValueType().isVector())
3876  return Op;
3877  return lowerVectorTruncLike(Op, DAG);
3878  case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
3879  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
3880  if (Op.getOperand(0).getValueType().isVector() &&
3881  Op.getOperand(0).getValueType().getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
3882  return lowerVectorMaskExt(Op, DAG, /*ExtVal*/ 1);
3883  return lowerFixedLengthVectorExtendToRVV(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::VZEXT_VL);
3884  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
3885  if (Op.getOperand(0).getValueType().isVector() &&
3886  Op.getOperand(0).getValueType().getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
3887  return lowerVectorMaskExt(Op, DAG, /*ExtVal*/ -1);
3888  return lowerFixedLengthVectorExtendToRVV(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::VSEXT_VL);
3889  case ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR_PARTS:
3890  return lowerSPLAT_VECTOR_PARTS(Op, DAG);
3891  case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT:
3892  return lowerINSERT_VECTOR_ELT(Op, DAG);
3893  case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT:
3894  return lowerEXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(Op, DAG);
3895  case ISD::VSCALE: {
3896  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
3897  SDLoc DL(Op);
3898  SDValue VLENB = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::READ_VLENB, DL, VT);
3899  // We define our scalable vector types for lmul=1 to use a 64 bit known
3900  // minimum size. e.g. <vscale x 2 x i32>. VLENB is in bytes so we calculate
3901  // vscale as VLENB / 8.
3902  static_assert(RISCV::RVVBitsPerBlock == 64, "Unexpected bits per block!");
3903  if (Subtarget.getRealMinVLen() < RISCV::RVVBitsPerBlock)
3904  report_fatal_error("Support for VLEN==32 is incomplete.");
3905  // We assume VLENB is a multiple of 8. We manually choose the best shift
3906  // here because SimplifyDemandedBits isn't always able to simplify it.
3907  uint64_t Val = Op.getConstantOperandVal(0);
3908  if (isPowerOf2_64(Val)) {
3909  uint64_t Log2 = Log2_64(Val);
3910  if (Log2 < 3)
3911  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, VLENB,
3912  DAG.getConstant(3 - Log2, DL, VT));
3913  if (Log2 > 3)
3914  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, VLENB,
3915  DAG.getConstant(Log2 - 3, DL, VT));
3916  return VLENB;
3917  }
3918  // If the multiplier is a multiple of 8, scale it down to avoid needing
3919  // to shift the VLENB value.
3920  if ((Val % 8) == 0)
3921  return DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, DL, VT, VLENB,
3922  DAG.getConstant(Val / 8, DL, VT));
3923 
3924  SDValue VScale = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, VLENB,
3925  DAG.getConstant(3, DL, VT));
3926  return DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, DL, VT, VScale, Op.getOperand(0));
3927  }
3928  case ISD::FPOWI: {
3929  // Custom promote f16 powi with illegal i32 integer type on RV64. Once
3930  // promoted this will be legalized into a libcall by LegalizeIntegerTypes.
3931  if (Op.getValueType() == MVT::f16 && Subtarget.is64Bit() &&
3932  Op.getOperand(1).getValueType() == MVT::i32) {
3933  SDLoc DL(Op);
3934  SDValue Op0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, DL, MVT::f32, Op.getOperand(0));
3935  SDValue Powi =
3936  DAG.getNode(ISD::FPOWI, DL, MVT::f32, Op0, Op.getOperand(1));
3937  return DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_ROUND, DL, MVT::f16, Powi,
3938  DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, DL, /*isTarget=*/true));
3939  }
3940  return SDValue();
3941  }
3942  case ISD::FP_EXTEND:
3943  case ISD::FP_ROUND:
3944  if (!Op.getValueType().isVector())
3945  return Op;
3946  return lowerVectorFPExtendOrRoundLike(Op, DAG);
3947  case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
3948  case ISD::FP_TO_UINT:
3949  case ISD::SINT_TO_FP:
3950  case ISD::UINT_TO_FP: {
3951  // RVV can only do fp<->int conversions to types half/double the size as
3952  // the source. We custom-lower any conversions that do two hops into
3953  // sequences.
3954  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
3955  if (!VT.isVector())
3956  return Op;
3957  SDLoc DL(Op);
3958  SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
3959  MVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
3960  MVT SrcVT = Src.getSimpleValueType();
3961  MVT SrcEltVT = SrcVT.getVectorElementType();
3962  unsigned EltSize = EltVT.getSizeInBits();
3963  unsigned SrcEltSize = SrcEltVT.getSizeInBits();
3964  assert(isPowerOf2_32(EltSize) && isPowerOf2_32(SrcEltSize) &&
3965  "Unexpected vector element types");
3966 
3967  bool IsInt2FP = SrcEltVT.isInteger();
3968  // Widening conversions
3969  if (EltSize > (2 * SrcEltSize)) {
3970  if (IsInt2FP) {
3971  // Do a regular integer sign/zero extension then convert to float.
3972  MVT IVecVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::getIntegerVT(EltSize / 2),
3973  VT.getVectorElementCount());
3974  unsigned ExtOpcode = Op.getOpcode() == ISD::UINT_TO_FP
3975  ? ISD::ZERO_EXTEND
3976  : ISD::SIGN_EXTEND;
3977  SDValue Ext = DAG.getNode(ExtOpcode, DL, IVecVT, Src);
3978  return DAG.getNode(Op.getOpcode(), DL, VT, Ext);
3979  }
3980  // FP2Int
3981  assert(SrcEltVT == MVT::f16 && "Unexpected FP_TO_[US]INT lowering");
3982  // Do one doubling fp_extend then complete the operation by converting
3983  // to int.
3984  MVT InterimFVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::f32, VT.getVectorElementCount());
3985  SDValue FExt = DAG.getFPExtendOrRound(Src, DL, InterimFVT);
3986  return DAG.getNode(Op.getOpcode(), DL, VT, FExt);
3987  }
3988 
3989  // Narrowing conversions
3990  if (SrcEltSize > (2 * EltSize)) {
3991  if (IsInt2FP) {
3992  // One narrowing int_to_fp, then an fp_round.
3993  assert(EltVT == MVT::f16 && "Unexpected [US]_TO_FP lowering");
3994  MVT InterimFVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::f32, VT.getVectorElementCount());
3995  SDValue Int2FP = DAG.getNode(Op.getOpcode(), DL, InterimFVT, Src);
3996  return DAG.getFPExtendOrRound(Int2FP, DL, VT);
3997  }
3998  // FP2Int
3999  // One narrowing fp_to_int, then truncate the integer. If the float isn't
4000  // representable by the integer, the result is poison.
4001  MVT IVecVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::getIntegerVT(SrcEltSize / 2),
4002  VT.getVectorElementCount());
4003  SDValue FP2Int = DAG.getNode(Op.getOpcode(), DL, IVecVT, Src);
4004  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VT, FP2Int);
4005  }
4006 
4007  // Scalable vectors can exit here. Patterns will handle equally-sized
4008  // conversions halving/doubling ones.
4009  if (!VT.isFixedLengthVector())
4010  return Op;
4011 
4012  // For fixed-length vectors we lower to a custom "VL" node.
4013  unsigned RVVOpc = 0;
4014  switch (Op.getOpcode()) {
4015  default:
4016  llvm_unreachable("Impossible opcode");
4017  case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
4018  RVVOpc = RISCVISD::VFCVT_RTZ_X_F_VL;
4019  break;
4020  case ISD::FP_TO_UINT:
4021  RVVOpc = RISCVISD::VFCVT_RTZ_XU_F_VL;
4022  break;
4023  case ISD::SINT_TO_FP:
4024  RVVOpc = RISCVISD::SINT_TO_FP_VL;
4025  break;
4026  case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
4027  RVVOpc = RISCVISD::UINT_TO_FP_VL;
4028  break;
4029  }
4030 
4031  MVT ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
4032  MVT SrcContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(SrcVT);
4033  assert(ContainerVT.getVectorElementCount() == SrcContainerVT.getVectorElementCount() &&
4034  "Expected same element count");
4035 
4036  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(VT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
4037 
4038  Src = convertToScalableVector(SrcContainerVT, Src, DAG, Subtarget);
4039  Src = DAG.getNode(RVVOpc, DL, ContainerVT, Src, Mask, VL);
4040  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, Src, DAG, Subtarget);
4041  }
4042  case ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT:
4043  case ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT:
4044  return lowerFP_TO_INT_SAT(Op, DAG, Subtarget);
4045  case ISD::FTRUNC:
4046  case ISD::FCEIL:
4047  case ISD::FFLOOR:
4048  case ISD::FRINT:
4049  case ISD::FROUND:
4050  case ISD::FROUNDEVEN:
4051  return lowerFTRUNC_FCEIL_FFLOOR_FROUND(Op, DAG, Subtarget);
4052  case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD:
4053  case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX:
4054  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX:
4055  case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN:
4056  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN:
4057  return lowerVECREDUCE(Op, DAG);
4058  case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND:
4059  case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR:
4060  case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR:
4061  if (Op.getOperand(0).getValueType().getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
4062  return lowerVectorMaskVecReduction(Op, DAG, /*IsVP*/ false);
4063  return lowerVECREDUCE(Op, DAG);
4064  case ISD::VECREDUCE_FADD:
4065  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FADD:
4066  case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMIN:
4067  case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMAX:
4068  return lowerFPVECREDUCE(Op, DAG);
4069  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_ADD:
4070  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_UMAX:
4071  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SMAX:
4072  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_UMIN:
4073  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SMIN:
4074  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FADD:
4075  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SEQ_FADD:
4076  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FMIN:
4077  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FMAX:
4078  return lowerVPREDUCE(Op, DAG);
4079  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_AND:
4080  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_OR:
4081  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_XOR:
4082  if (Op.getOperand(1).getValueType().getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
4083  return lowerVectorMaskVecReduction(Op, DAG, /*IsVP*/ true);
4084  return lowerVPREDUCE(Op, DAG);
4085  case ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR:
4086  return lowerINSERT_SUBVECTOR(Op, DAG);
4087  case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR:
4088  return lowerEXTRACT_SUBVECTOR(Op, DAG);
4089  case ISD::STEP_VECTOR:
4090  return lowerSTEP_VECTOR(Op, DAG);
4091  case ISD::VECTOR_REVERSE:
4092  return lowerVECTOR_REVERSE(Op, DAG);
4093  case ISD::VECTOR_SPLICE:
4094  return lowerVECTOR_SPLICE(Op, DAG);
4095  case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR:
4096  return lowerBUILD_VECTOR(Op, DAG, Subtarget);
4097  case ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR:
4098  if (Op.getValueType().getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
4099  return lowerVectorMaskSplat(Op, DAG);
4100  return SDValue();
4101  case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE:
4102  return lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE(Op, DAG, Subtarget);
4103  case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS: {
4104  // Split CONCAT_VECTORS into a series of INSERT_SUBVECTOR nodes. This is
4105  // better than going through the stack, as the default expansion does.
4106  SDLoc DL(Op);
4107  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
4108  unsigned NumOpElts =
4109  Op.getOperand(0).getSimpleValueType().getVectorMinNumElements();
4110  SDValue Vec = DAG.getUNDEF(VT);
4111  for (const auto &OpIdx : enumerate(Op->ops())) {
4112  SDValue SubVec = OpIdx.value();
4113  // Don't insert undef subvectors.
4114  if (SubVec.isUndef())
4115  continue;
4116  Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, VT, Vec, SubVec,
4117  DAG.getIntPtrConstant(OpIdx.index() * NumOpElts, DL));
4118  }
4119  return Vec;
4120  }
4121  case ISD::LOAD:
