4122  if (auto V = expandUnalignedRVVLoad(Op, DAG))
4123  return V;
4124  if (Op.getValueType().isFixedLengthVector())
4125  return lowerFixedLengthVectorLoadToRVV(Op, DAG);
4126  return Op;
4127  case ISD::STORE:
4128  if (auto V = expandUnalignedRVVStore(Op, DAG))
4129  return V;
4130  if (Op.getOperand(1).getValueType().isFixedLengthVector())
4131  return lowerFixedLengthVectorStoreToRVV(Op, DAG);
4132  return Op;
4133  case ISD::MLOAD:
4134  case ISD::VP_LOAD:
4135  return lowerMaskedLoad(Op, DAG);
4136  case ISD::MSTORE:
4137  case ISD::VP_STORE:
4138  return lowerMaskedStore(Op, DAG);
4139  case ISD::SELECT_CC: {
4140  // This occurs because we custom legalize SETGT and SETUGT for setcc. That
4141  // causes LegalizeDAG to think we need to custom legalize select_cc. Expand
4142  // into separate SETCC+SELECT_CC just like LegalizeDAG.
4143  SDValue Tmp1 = Op.getOperand(0);
4144  SDValue Tmp2 = Op.getOperand(1);
4145  SDValue True = Op.getOperand(2);
4146  SDValue False = Op.getOperand(3);
4147  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
4148  SDValue CC = Op.getOperand(4);
4149  EVT CmpVT = Tmp1.getValueType();
4150  EVT CCVT =
4151  getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), CmpVT);
4152  SDLoc DL(Op);
4153  SDValue Cond =
4154  DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCC, DL, CCVT, Tmp1, Tmp2, CC, Op->getFlags());
4155  return DAG.getSelect(DL, VT, Cond, True, False);
4156  }
4157  case ISD::SETCC: {
4158  MVT OpVT = Op.getOperand(0).getSimpleValueType();
4159  if (OpVT.isScalarInteger()) {
4160  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
4161  SDValue LHS = Op.getOperand(0);
4162  SDValue RHS = Op.getOperand(1);
4163  ISD::CondCode CCVal = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2))->get();
4164  assert((CCVal == ISD::SETGT || CCVal == ISD::SETUGT) &&
4165  "Unexpected CondCode");
4166 
4167  SDLoc DL(Op);
4168 
4169  // If the RHS is a constant in the range [-2049, 0) or (0, 2046], we can
4170  // convert this to the equivalent of (set(u)ge X, C+1) by using
4171  // (xori (slti(u) X, C+1), 1). This avoids materializing a small constant
4172  // in a register.
4173  if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(RHS)) {
4174  int64_t Imm = cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS)->getSExtValue();
4175  if (Imm != 0 && isInt<12>((uint64_t)Imm + 1)) {
4176  // X > -1 should have been replaced with false.
4177  assert((CCVal != ISD::SETUGT || Imm != -1) &&
4178  "Missing canonicalization");
4179  // Using getSetCCSwappedOperands will convert SET(U)GT->SET(U)LT.
4180  CCVal = ISD::getSetCCSwappedOperands(CCVal);
4181  SDValue SetCC = DAG.getSetCC(
4182  DL, VT, LHS, DAG.getConstant(Imm + 1, DL, OpVT), CCVal);
4183  return DAG.getLogicalNOT(DL, SetCC, VT);
4184  }
4185  }
4186 
4187  // Not a constant we could handle, swap the operands and condition code to
4188  // SETLT/SETULT.
4189  CCVal = ISD::getSetCCSwappedOperands(CCVal);
4190  return DAG.getSetCC(DL, VT, RHS, LHS, CCVal);
4191  }
4192 
4193  return lowerFixedLengthVectorSetccToRVV(Op, DAG);
4194  }
4195  case ISD::ADD:
4196  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::ADD_VL, /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4197  case ISD::SUB:
4198  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::SUB_VL, /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4199  case ISD::MUL:
4200  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::MUL_VL, /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4201  case ISD::MULHS:
4202  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::MULHS_VL, /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4203  case ISD::MULHU:
4204  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::MULHU_VL, /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4205  case ISD::AND:
4206  return lowerFixedLengthVectorLogicOpToRVV(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::VMAND_VL,
4207  RISCVISD::AND_VL);
4208  case ISD::OR:
4209  return lowerFixedLengthVectorLogicOpToRVV(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::VMOR_VL,
4210  RISCVISD::OR_VL);
4211  case ISD::XOR:
4212  return lowerFixedLengthVectorLogicOpToRVV(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::VMXOR_VL,
4213  RISCVISD::XOR_VL);
4214  case ISD::SDIV:
4215  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::SDIV_VL, /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4216  case ISD::SREM:
4217  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::SREM_VL, /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4218  case ISD::UDIV:
4219  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::UDIV_VL, /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4220  case ISD::UREM:
4221  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::UREM_VL, /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4222  case ISD::SHL:
4223  case ISD::SRA:
4224  case ISD::SRL:
4225  if (Op.getSimpleValueType().isFixedLengthVector())
4226  return lowerFixedLengthVectorShiftToRVV(Op, DAG);
4227  // This can be called for an i32 shift amount that needs to be promoted.
4228  assert(Op.getOperand(1).getValueType() == MVT::i32 && Subtarget.is64Bit() &&
4229  "Unexpected custom legalisation");
4230  return SDValue();
4231  case ISD::SADDSAT:
4232  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::SADDSAT_VL,
4233  /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4234  case ISD::UADDSAT:
4235  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::UADDSAT_VL,
4236  /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4237  case ISD::SSUBSAT:
4238  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::SSUBSAT_VL,
4239  /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4240  case ISD::USUBSAT:

4242  /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4243  case ISD::FADD:
4244  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::FADD_VL, /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4245  case ISD::FSUB:
4246  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::FSUB_VL, /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4247  case ISD::FMUL:
4248  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::FMUL_VL, /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4249  case ISD::FDIV:
4250  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::FDIV_VL, /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4251  case ISD::FNEG:
4252  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::FNEG_VL);
4253  case ISD::FABS:
4254  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::FABS_VL);

4263  case ISD::UMIN:

4377  case ISD::VP_UMIN:
4378  return lowerVPOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::UMIN_VL, /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4379  case ISD::VP_UMAX:
4380  return lowerVPOp(Op, DAG, RISCVISD::UMAX_VL, /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
4381  case ISD::EXPERIMENTAL_VP_STRIDED_LOAD:
4382  return lowerVPStridedLoad(Op, DAG);
4383  case ISD::EXPERIMENTAL_VP_STRIDED_STORE:
4384  return lowerVPStridedStore(Op, DAG);
4385  case ISD::VP_FCEIL:
4386  case ISD::VP_FFLOOR:
4387  case ISD::VP_FRINT:
4388  case ISD::VP_FNEARBYINT:
4389  case ISD::VP_FROUND:
4390  case ISD::VP_FROUNDEVEN:
4391  case ISD::VP_FROUNDTOZERO:
4392  return lowerVectorFTRUNC_FCEIL_FFLOOR_FROUND(Op, DAG, Subtarget);
4393  }
4394 }

4399 }

4404  Flags);

4417 
4418 template <class NodeTy>
4419 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::getAddr(NodeTy *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
4420  bool IsLocal) const {
4421  SDLoc DL(N);
4422  EVT Ty = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
4423 
4424  // When HWASAN is used and tagging of global variables is enabled
4425  // they should be accessed via the GOT, since the tagged address of a global
4426  // is incompatible with existing code models. This also applies to non-pic
4427  // mode.
4428  if (isPositionIndependent() || Subtarget.allowTaggedGlobals()) {
4429  SDValue Addr = getTargetNode(N, DL, Ty, DAG, 0);
4430  if (IsLocal && !Subtarget.allowTaggedGlobals())
4431  // Use PC-relative addressing to access the symbol. This generates the
4432  // pattern (PseudoLLA sym), which expands to (addi (auipc %pcrel_hi(sym))
4433  // %pcrel_lo(auipc)).
4434  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::LLA, DL, Ty, Addr);
4435 
4436  // Use PC-relative addressing to access the GOT for this symbol, then load
4437  // the address from the GOT. This generates the pattern (PseudoLA sym),
4438  // which expands to (ld (addi (auipc %got_pcrel_hi(sym)) %pcrel_lo(auipc))).
4439  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
4440  MachineMemOperand *MemOp = MF.getMachineMemOperand(
4441  MachinePointerInfo::getGOT(MF),
4442  MachineMemOperand::MOLoad | MachineMemOperand::MODereferenceable |
4443  MachineMemOperand::MOInvariant,
4444  LLT(Ty.getSimpleVT()), Align(Ty.getFixedSizeInBits() / 8));
4445  SDValue Load =
4446  DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(RISCVISD::LA, DL, DAG.getVTList(Ty, MVT::Other),
4447  {DAG.getEntryNode(), Addr}, Ty, MemOp);
4448  return Load;
4449  }
4450 
4451  switch (getTargetMachine().getCodeModel()) {
4452  default:
4453  report_fatal_error("Unsupported code model for lowering");
4454  case CodeModel::Small: {
4455  // Generate a sequence for accessing addresses within the first 2 GiB of
4456  // address space. This generates the pattern (addi (lui %hi(sym)) %lo(sym)).
4457  SDValue AddrHi = getTargetNode(N, DL, Ty, DAG, RISCVII::MO_HI);
4458  SDValue AddrLo = getTargetNode(N, DL, Ty, DAG, RISCVII::MO_LO);
4459  SDValue MNHi = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::HI, DL, Ty, AddrHi);
4460  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::ADD_LO, DL, Ty, MNHi, AddrLo);
4461  }
4462  case CodeModel::Medium: {
4463  // Generate a sequence for accessing addresses within any 2GiB range within
4464  // the address space. This generates the pattern (PseudoLLA sym), which
4465  // expands to (addi (auipc %pcrel_hi(sym)) %pcrel_lo(auipc)).
4466  SDValue Addr = getTargetNode(N, DL, Ty, DAG, 0);
4467  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::LLA, DL, Ty, Addr);
4468  }
4469  }
4470 }

4473  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4474  GlobalAddressSDNode *N = cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Op);
4475  assert(N->getOffset() == 0 && "unexpected offset in global node");
4476  return getAddr(N, DAG, N->getGlobal()->isDSOLocal());

4499 
4500 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::getStaticTLSAddr(GlobalAddressSDNode *N,
4501  SelectionDAG &DAG,
4502  bool UseGOT) const {
4503  SDLoc DL(N);
4504  EVT Ty = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
4505  const GlobalValue *GV = N->getGlobal();
4506  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
4507 
4508  if (UseGOT) {
4509  // Use PC-relative addressing to access the GOT for this TLS symbol, then
4510  // load the address from the GOT and add the thread pointer. This generates
4511  // the pattern (PseudoLA_TLS_IE sym), which expands to
4512  // (ld (auipc %tls_ie_pcrel_hi(sym)) %pcrel_lo(auipc)).
4513  SDValue Addr = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, Ty, 0, 0);
4514  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
4515  MachineMemOperand *MemOp = MF.getMachineMemOperand(
4516  MachinePointerInfo::getGOT(MF),
4517  MachineMemOperand::MOLoad | MachineMemOperand::MODereferenceable |
4518  MachineMemOperand::MOInvariant,
4519  LLT(Ty.getSimpleVT()), Align(Ty.getFixedSizeInBits() / 8));
4520  SDValue Load = DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(
4521  RISCVISD::LA_TLS_IE, DL, DAG.getVTList(Ty, MVT::Other),
4522  {DAG.getEntryNode(), Addr}, Ty, MemOp);
4523 
4524  // Add the thread pointer.
4525  SDValue TPReg = DAG.getRegister(RISCV::X4, XLenVT);
4526  return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, Ty, Load, TPReg);
4527  }
4528 
4529  // Generate a sequence for accessing the address relative to the thread
4530  // pointer, with the appropriate adjustment for the thread pointer offset.
4531  // This generates the pattern
4532  // (add (add_tprel (lui %tprel_hi(sym)) tp %tprel_add(sym)) %tprel_lo(sym))
4533  SDValue AddrHi =
4534  DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, Ty, 0, RISCVII::MO_TPREL_HI);
4535  SDValue AddrAdd =
4536  DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, Ty, 0, RISCVII::MO_TPREL_ADD);
4537  SDValue AddrLo =
4538  DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, Ty, 0, RISCVII::MO_TPREL_LO);
4539 
4540  SDValue MNHi = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::HI, DL, Ty, AddrHi);
4541  SDValue TPReg = DAG.getRegister(RISCV::X4, XLenVT);
4542  SDValue MNAdd =
4543  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::ADD_TPREL, DL, Ty, MNHi, TPReg, AddrAdd);
4544  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::ADD_LO, DL, Ty, MNAdd, AddrLo);
4545 }
4546 
4547 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::getDynamicTLSAddr(GlobalAddressSDNode *N,
4548  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4549  SDLoc DL(N);
4550  EVT Ty = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
4551  IntegerType *CallTy = Type::getIntNTy(*DAG.getContext(), Ty.getSizeInBits());
4552  const GlobalValue *GV = N->getGlobal();
4553 
4554  // Use a PC-relative addressing mode to access the global dynamic GOT address.
4555  // This generates the pattern (PseudoLA_TLS_GD sym), which expands to
4556  // (addi (auipc %tls_gd_pcrel_hi(sym)) %pcrel_lo(auipc)).
4557  SDValue Addr = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, Ty, 0, 0);
4558  SDValue Load = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::LA_TLS_GD, DL, Ty, Addr);
4559 
4560  // Prepare argument list to generate call.
4561  ArgListTy Args;
4562  ArgListEntry Entry;
4563  Entry.Node = Load;
4564  Entry.Ty = CallTy;
4565  Args.push_back(Entry);
4566 
4567  // Setup call to __tls_get_addr.
4568  TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG);
4569  CLI.setDebugLoc(DL)
4570  .setChain(DAG.getEntryNode())
4571  .setLibCallee(CallingConv::C, CallTy,
4572  DAG.getExternalSymbol("__tls_get_addr", Ty),
4573  std::move(Args));
4574 
4575  return LowerCallTo(CLI).first;
4576 }
4577 
4578 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerGlobalTLSAddress(SDValue Op,
4579  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4580  GlobalAddressSDNode *N = cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Op);
4581  assert(N->getOffset() == 0 && "unexpected offset in global node");
4582 
4583  TLSModel::Model Model = getTargetMachine().getTLSModel(N->getGlobal());
4584 
4585  if (DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction().getCallingConv() ==
4586  CallingConv::GHC)
4587  report_fatal_error("In GHC calling convention TLS is not supported");
4588 
4589  SDValue Addr;
4590  switch (Model) {
4591  case TLSModel::LocalExec:
4592  Addr = getStaticTLSAddr(N, DAG, /*UseGOT=*/false);
4593  break;
4594  case TLSModel::InitialExec:
4595  Addr = getStaticTLSAddr(N, DAG, /*UseGOT=*/true);
4596  break;
4597  case TLSModel::LocalDynamic:
4598  case TLSModel::GeneralDynamic:
4599  Addr = getDynamicTLSAddr(N, DAG);
4600  break;
4601  }
4602 
4603  return Addr;
4604 }
4605 
4606 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerSELECT(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4607  SDValue CondV = Op.getOperand(0);
4608  SDValue TrueV = Op.getOperand(1);
4609  SDValue FalseV = Op.getOperand(2);
4610  SDLoc DL(Op);
4611  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
4612  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
4613 
4614  // Lower vector SELECTs to VSELECTs by splatting the condition.
4615  if (VT.isVector()) {
4616  MVT SplatCondVT = VT.changeVectorElementType(MVT::i1);
4617  SDValue CondSplat = DAG.getSplat(SplatCondVT, DL, CondV);
4618  return DAG.getNode(ISD::VSELECT, DL, VT, CondSplat, TrueV, FalseV);
4619  }
4620 
4621  if (!Subtarget.hasShortForwardBranchOpt()) {
4622  // (select c, -1, y) -> -c | y
4623  if (isAllOnesConstant(TrueV)) {
4624  SDValue Neg = DAG.getNegative(CondV, DL, VT);
4625  return DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, Neg, FalseV);
4626  }
4627  // (select c, y, -1) -> (c-1) | y
4628  if (isAllOnesConstant(FalseV)) {
4629  SDValue Neg = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, CondV,
4630  DAG.getAllOnesConstant(DL, VT));
4631  return DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, Neg, TrueV);
4632  }
4633 
4634  // (select c, 0, y) -> (c-1) & y
4635  if (isNullConstant(TrueV)) {
4636  SDValue Neg = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, CondV,
4637  DAG.getAllOnesConstant(DL, VT));
4638  return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, Neg, FalseV);
4639  }
4640  // (select c, y, 0) -> -c & y
4641  if (isNullConstant(FalseV)) {
4642  SDValue Neg = DAG.getNegative(CondV, DL, VT);
4643  return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, Neg, TrueV);
4644  }
4645  }
4646 
4647  // If the condition is not an integer SETCC which operates on XLenVT, we need
4648  // to emit a RISCVISD::SELECT_CC comparing the condition to zero. i.e.:
4649  // (select condv, truev, falsev)
4650  // -> (riscvisd::select_cc condv, zero, setne, truev, falsev)
4651  if (CondV.getOpcode() != ISD::SETCC ||
4652  CondV.getOperand(0).getSimpleValueType() != XLenVT) {
4653  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT);
4654  SDValue SetNE = DAG.getCondCode(ISD::SETNE);
4655 
4656  SDValue Ops[] = {CondV, Zero, SetNE, TrueV, FalseV};
4657 
4658  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SELECT_CC, DL, VT, Ops);
4659  }
4660 
4661  // If the CondV is the output of a SETCC node which operates on XLenVT inputs,
4662  // then merge the SETCC node into the lowered RISCVISD::SELECT_CC to take
4663  // advantage of the integer compare+branch instructions. i.e.:
4664  // (select (setcc lhs, rhs, cc), truev, falsev)
4665  // -> (riscvisd::select_cc lhs, rhs, cc, truev, falsev)
4666  SDValue LHS = CondV.getOperand(0);
4667  SDValue RHS = CondV.getOperand(1);
4668  ISD::CondCode CCVal = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(CondV.getOperand(2))->get();
4669 
4670  // Special case for a select of 2 constants that have a diffence of 1.
4671  // Normally this is done by DAGCombine, but if the select is introduced by
4672  // type legalization or op legalization, we miss it. Restricting to SETLT
4673  // case for now because that is what signed saturating add/sub need.
4674  // FIXME: We don't need the condition to be SETLT or even a SETCC,
4675  // but we would probably want to swap the true/false values if the condition
4676  // is SETGE/SETLE to avoid an XORI.
4677  if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(TrueV) && isa<ConstantSDNode>(FalseV) &&
4678  CCVal == ISD::SETLT) {
4679  const APInt &TrueVal = cast<ConstantSDNode>(TrueV)->getAPIntValue();
4680  const APInt &FalseVal = cast<ConstantSDNode>(FalseV)->getAPIntValue();
4681  if (TrueVal - 1 == FalseVal)
4682  return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, CondV, FalseV);
4683  if (TrueVal + 1 == FalseVal)
4684  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, VT, FalseV, CondV);
4685  }
4686 
4687  translateSetCCForBranch(DL, LHS, RHS, CCVal, DAG);
4688  // 1 < x ? x : 1 -> 0 < x ? x : 1
4689  if (isOneConstant(LHS) && (CCVal == ISD::SETLT || CCVal == ISD::SETULT) &&
4690  RHS == TrueV && LHS == FalseV) {
4691  LHS = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT);
4692  // 0 <u x is the same as x != 0.
4693  if (CCVal == ISD::SETULT) {
4694  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
4695  CCVal = ISD::SETNE;
4696  }
4697  }
4698 
4699  // x <s -1 ? x : -1 -> x <s 0 ? x : -1
4700  if (isAllOnesConstant(RHS) && CCVal == ISD::SETLT && LHS == TrueV &&
4701  RHS == FalseV) {
4702  RHS = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT);
4703  }
4704 
4705  SDValue TargetCC = DAG.getCondCode(CCVal);
4706 
4707  if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(TrueV) && !isa<ConstantSDNode>(FalseV)) {
4708  // (select (setcc lhs, rhs, CC), constant, falsev)
4709  // -> (select (setcc lhs, rhs, InverseCC), falsev, constant)
4710  std::swap(TrueV, FalseV);
4711  TargetCC = DAG.getCondCode(ISD::getSetCCInverse(CCVal, LHS.getValueType()));
4712  }
4713 
4714  SDValue Ops[] = {LHS, RHS, TargetCC, TrueV, FalseV};
4715  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SELECT_CC, DL, VT, Ops);
4716 }
4717 
4718 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerBRCOND(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4719  SDValue CondV = Op.getOperand(1);
4720  SDLoc DL(Op);
4721  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
4722 
4723  if (CondV.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC &&
4724  CondV.getOperand(0).getValueType() == XLenVT) {
4725  SDValue LHS = CondV.getOperand(0);
4726  SDValue RHS = CondV.getOperand(1);
4727  ISD::CondCode CCVal = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(CondV.getOperand(2))->get();
4728 
4729  translateSetCCForBranch(DL, LHS, RHS, CCVal, DAG);
4730 
4731  SDValue TargetCC = DAG.getCondCode(CCVal);
4732  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::BR_CC, DL, Op.getValueType(), Op.getOperand(0),
4733  LHS, RHS, TargetCC, Op.getOperand(2));
4734  }
4735 
4736  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::BR_CC, DL, Op.getValueType(), Op.getOperand(0),
4737  CondV, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT),
4738  DAG.getCondCode(ISD::SETNE), Op.getOperand(2));
4739 }

4741 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerVASTART(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4742  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
4743  RISCVMachineFunctionInfo *FuncInfo = MF.getInfo<RISCVMachineFunctionInfo>();
4744 
4745  SDLoc DL(Op);
4746  SDValue FI = DAG.getFrameIndex(FuncInfo->getVarArgsFrameIndex(),
4747  getPointerTy(MF.getDataLayout()));
4748 
4749  // vastart just stores the address of the VarArgsFrameIndex slot into the
4750  // memory location argument.
4751  const Value *SV = cast<SrcValueSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2))->getValue();
4752  return DAG.getStore(Op.getOperand(0), DL, FI, Op.getOperand(1),
4753  MachinePointerInfo(SV));
4754 }
4755 
4756 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerFRAMEADDR(SDValue Op,
4757  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4758  const RISCVRegisterInfo &RI = *Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
4759  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
4760  MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
4761  MFI.setFrameAddressIsTaken(true);
4762  Register FrameReg = RI.getFrameRegister(MF);
4763  int XLenInBytes = Subtarget.getXLen() / 8;
4764 
4765  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
4766  SDLoc DL(Op);
4767  SDValue FrameAddr = DAG.getCopyFromReg(DAG.getEntryNode(), DL, FrameReg, VT);
4768  unsigned Depth = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(0))->getZExtValue();
4769  while (Depth--) {
4770  int Offset = -(XLenInBytes * 2);
4771  SDValue Ptr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, FrameAddr,
4772  DAG.getIntPtrConstant(Offset, DL));
4773  FrameAddr =
4774  DAG.getLoad(VT, DL, DAG.getEntryNode(), Ptr, MachinePointerInfo());
4775  }
4776  return FrameAddr;
4777 }
4778 
4779 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerRETURNADDR(SDValue Op,
4780  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4781  const RISCVRegisterInfo &RI = *Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
4782  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
4783  MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
4784  MFI.setReturnAddressIsTaken(true);
4785  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
4786  int XLenInBytes = Subtarget.getXLen() / 8;
4787 
4788  if (verifyReturnAddressArgumentIsConstant(Op, DAG))
4789  return SDValue();
4790 
4791  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
4792  SDLoc DL(Op);
4793  unsigned Depth = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(0))->getZExtValue();
4794  if (Depth) {
4795  int Off = -XLenInBytes;
4796  SDValue FrameAddr = lowerFRAMEADDR(Op, DAG);
4797  SDValue Offset = DAG.getConstant(Off, DL, VT);
4798  return DAG.getLoad(VT, DL, DAG.getEntryNode(),
4799  DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, FrameAddr, Offset),
4800  MachinePointerInfo());
4801  }
4802 
4803  // Return the value of the return address register, marking it an implicit
4804  // live-in.
4805  Register Reg = MF.addLiveIn(RI.getRARegister(), getRegClassFor(XLenVT));
4806  return DAG.getCopyFromReg(DAG.getEntryNode(), DL, Reg, XLenVT);
4807 }
4808 
4809 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerShiftLeftParts(SDValue Op,
4810  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4811  SDLoc DL(Op);
4812  SDValue Lo = Op.getOperand(0);
4813  SDValue Hi = Op.getOperand(1);
4814  SDValue Shamt = Op.getOperand(2);
4815  EVT VT = Lo.getValueType();
4816 
4817  // if Shamt-XLEN < 0: // Shamt < XLEN
4818  // Lo = Lo << Shamt
4819  // Hi = (Hi << Shamt) | ((Lo >>u 1) >>u (XLEN-1 ^ Shamt))
4820  // else:
4821  // Lo = 0
4822  // Hi = Lo << (Shamt-XLEN)
4823 
4824  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT);
4825  SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, VT);
4826  SDValue MinusXLen = DAG.getConstant(-(int)Subtarget.getXLen(), DL, VT);
4827  SDValue XLenMinus1 = DAG.getConstant(Subtarget.getXLen() - 1, DL, VT);
4828  SDValue ShamtMinusXLen = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, Shamt, MinusXLen);
4829  SDValue XLenMinus1Shamt = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, VT, XLenMinus1, Shamt);
4830 
4831  SDValue LoTrue = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Lo, Shamt);
4832  SDValue ShiftRight1Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, Lo, One);
4833  SDValue ShiftRightLo =
4834  DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, ShiftRight1Lo, XLenMinus1Shamt);
4835  SDValue ShiftLeftHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Hi, Shamt);
4836  SDValue HiTrue = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, ShiftLeftHi, ShiftRightLo);
4837  SDValue HiFalse = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Lo, ShamtMinusXLen);
4838 
4839  SDValue CC = DAG.getSetCC(DL, VT, ShamtMinusXLen, Zero, ISD::SETLT);
4840 
4841  Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, VT, CC, LoTrue, Zero);
4842  Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, VT, CC, HiTrue, HiFalse);
4843 
4844  SDValue Parts[2] = {Lo, Hi};
4845  return DAG.getMergeValues(Parts, DL);
4846 }
4847 
4848 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerShiftRightParts(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
4849  bool IsSRA) const {
4850  SDLoc DL(Op);
4851  SDValue Lo = Op.getOperand(0);
4852  SDValue Hi = Op.getOperand(1);
4853  SDValue Shamt = Op.getOperand(2);
4854  EVT VT = Lo.getValueType();
4855 
4856  // SRA expansion:
4857  // if Shamt-XLEN < 0: // Shamt < XLEN
4858  // Lo = (Lo >>u Shamt) | ((Hi << 1) << (ShAmt ^ XLEN-1))
4859  // Hi = Hi >>s Shamt
4860  // else:
4861  // Lo = Hi >>s (Shamt-XLEN);
4862  // Hi = Hi >>s (XLEN-1)
4863  //
4864  // SRL expansion:
4865  // if Shamt-XLEN < 0: // Shamt < XLEN
4866  // Lo = (Lo >>u Shamt) | ((Hi << 1) << (ShAmt ^ XLEN-1))
4867  // Hi = Hi >>u Shamt
4868  // else:
4869  // Lo = Hi >>u (Shamt-XLEN);
4870  // Hi = 0;
4871 
4872  unsigned ShiftRightOp = IsSRA ? ISD::SRA : ISD::SRL;
4873 
4874  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT);
4875  SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, VT);
4876  SDValue MinusXLen = DAG.getConstant(-(int)Subtarget.getXLen(), DL, VT);
4877  SDValue XLenMinus1 = DAG.getConstant(Subtarget.getXLen() - 1, DL, VT);
4878  SDValue ShamtMinusXLen = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, Shamt, MinusXLen);
4879  SDValue XLenMinus1Shamt = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, VT, XLenMinus1, Shamt);
4880 
4881  SDValue ShiftRightLo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, Lo, Shamt);
4882  SDValue ShiftLeftHi1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Hi, One);
4883  SDValue ShiftLeftHi =
4884  DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, ShiftLeftHi1, XLenMinus1Shamt);
4885  SDValue LoTrue = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, ShiftRightLo, ShiftLeftHi);
4886  SDValue HiTrue = DAG.getNode(ShiftRightOp, DL, VT, Hi, Shamt);
4887  SDValue LoFalse = DAG.getNode(ShiftRightOp, DL, VT, Hi, ShamtMinusXLen);
4888  SDValue HiFalse =
4889  IsSRA ? DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, DL, VT, Hi, XLenMinus1) : Zero;
4890 
4891  SDValue CC = DAG.getSetCC(DL, VT, ShamtMinusXLen, Zero, ISD::SETLT);
4892 
4893  Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, VT, CC, LoTrue, LoFalse);
4894  Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, VT, CC, HiTrue, HiFalse);
4895 
4896  SDValue Parts[2] = {Lo, Hi};
4897  return DAG.getMergeValues(Parts, DL);
4898 }
4899 
4900 // Lower splats of i1 types to SETCC. For each mask vector type, we have a
4901 // legal equivalently-sized i8 type, so we can use that as a go-between.
4902 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerVectorMaskSplat(SDValue Op,
4903  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4904  SDLoc DL(Op);
4905  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
4906  SDValue SplatVal = Op.getOperand(0);
4907  // All-zeros or all-ones splats are handled specially.
4908  if (ISD::isConstantSplatVectorAllOnes(Op.getNode())) {
4909  SDValue VL = getDefaultScalableVLOps(VT, DL, DAG, Subtarget).second;
4910  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMSET_VL, DL, VT, VL);
4911  }
4912  if (ISD::isConstantSplatVectorAllZeros(Op.getNode())) {
4913  SDValue VL = getDefaultScalableVLOps(VT, DL, DAG, Subtarget).second;
4914  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMCLR_VL, DL, VT, VL);
4915  }
4916  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
4917  assert(SplatVal.getValueType() == XLenVT &&
4918  "Unexpected type for i1 splat value");
4919  MVT InterVT = VT.changeVectorElementType(MVT::i8);
4920  SplatVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, XLenVT, SplatVal,
4921  DAG.getConstant(1, DL, XLenVT));
4922  SDValue LHS = DAG.getSplatVector(InterVT, DL, SplatVal);
4923  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, InterVT);
4924  return DAG.getSetCC(DL, VT, LHS, Zero, ISD::SETNE);
4925 }
4926 
4927 // Custom-lower a SPLAT_VECTOR_PARTS where XLEN<SEW, as the SEW element type is
4928 // illegal (currently only vXi64 RV32).
4929 // FIXME: We could also catch non-constant sign-extended i32 values and lower
4930 // them to VMV_V_X_VL.
4931 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerSPLAT_VECTOR_PARTS(SDValue Op,
4932  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4933  SDLoc DL(Op);
4934  MVT VecVT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
4935  assert(!Subtarget.is64Bit() && VecVT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i64 &&
4936  "Unexpected SPLAT_VECTOR_PARTS lowering");
4937 
4938  assert(Op.getNumOperands() == 2 && "Unexpected number of operands!");
4939  SDValue Lo = Op.getOperand(0);
4940  SDValue Hi = Op.getOperand(1);
4941 
4942  if (VecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
4943  MVT ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VecVT);
4944  SDLoc DL(Op);
4945  auto VL = getDefaultVLOps(VecVT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget).second;
4946 
4947  SDValue Res =
4948  splatPartsI64WithVL(DL, ContainerVT, SDValue(), Lo, Hi, VL, DAG);
4949  return convertFromScalableVector(VecVT, Res, DAG, Subtarget);
4950  }
4951 
4952  if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(Lo) && isa<ConstantSDNode>(Hi)) {
4953  int32_t LoC = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Lo)->getSExtValue();
4954  int32_t HiC = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Hi)->getSExtValue();
4955  // If Hi constant is all the same sign bit as Lo, lower this as a custom
4956  // node in order to try and match RVV vector/scalar instructions.
4957  if ((LoC >> 31) == HiC)
4958  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, VecVT, DAG.getUNDEF(VecVT),
4959  Lo, DAG.getRegister(RISCV::X0, MVT::i32));
4960  }
4961 
4962  // Detect cases where Hi is (SRA Lo, 31) which means Hi is Lo sign extended.
4963  if (Hi.getOpcode() == ISD::SRA && Hi.getOperand(0) == Lo &&
4964  isa<ConstantSDNode>(Hi.getOperand(1)) &&
4965  Hi.getConstantOperandVal(1) == 31)
4966  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, VecVT, DAG.getUNDEF(VecVT), Lo,
4967  DAG.getRegister(RISCV::X0, MVT::i32));
4968 
4969  // Fall back to use a stack store and stride x0 vector load. Use X0 as VL.
4970  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SPLAT_VECTOR_SPLIT_I64_VL, DL, VecVT,
4971  DAG.getUNDEF(VecVT), Lo, Hi,
4972  DAG.getRegister(RISCV::X0, MVT::i32));
4973 }
4974 
4975 // Custom-lower extensions from mask vectors by using a vselect either with 1
4976 // for zero/any-extension or -1 for sign-extension:
4977 // (vXiN = (s|z)ext vXi1:vmask) -> (vXiN = vselect vmask, (-1 or 1), 0)
4978 // Note that any-extension is lowered identically to zero-extension.
4979 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerVectorMaskExt(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
4980  int64_t ExtTrueVal) const {
4981  SDLoc DL(Op);
4982  MVT VecVT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
4983  SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
4984  // Only custom-lower extensions from mask types
4985  assert(Src.getValueType().isVector() &&
4986  Src.getValueType().getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1);
4987 
4988  if (VecVT.isScalableVector()) {
4989  SDValue SplatZero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VecVT);
4990  SDValue SplatTrueVal = DAG.getConstant(ExtTrueVal, DL, VecVT);
4991  return DAG.getNode(ISD::VSELECT, DL, VecVT, Src, SplatTrueVal, SplatZero);
4992  }
4993 
4994  MVT ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VecVT);
4995  MVT I1ContainerVT =
4996  MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i1, ContainerVT.getVectorElementCount());
4997 
4998  SDValue CC = convertToScalableVector(I1ContainerVT, Src, DAG, Subtarget);
4999 
5000  SDValue VL = getDefaultVLOps(VecVT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget).second;
5001 
5002  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
5003  SDValue SplatZero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT);
5004  SDValue SplatTrueVal = DAG.getConstant(ExtTrueVal, DL, XLenVT);
5005 
5006  SplatZero = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, ContainerVT,
5007  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), SplatZero, VL);
5008  SplatTrueVal = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, ContainerVT,
5009  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), SplatTrueVal, VL);
5010  SDValue Select = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VSELECT_VL, DL, ContainerVT, CC,
5011  SplatTrueVal, SplatZero, VL);
5012 
5013  return convertFromScalableVector(VecVT, Select, DAG, Subtarget);
5014 }
5015 
5016 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerFixedLengthVectorExtendToRVV(
5017  SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, unsigned ExtendOpc) const {
5018  MVT ExtVT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
5019  // Only custom-lower extensions from fixed-length vector types.
5020  if (!ExtVT.isFixedLengthVector())
5021  return Op;
5022  MVT VT = Op.getOperand(0).getSimpleValueType();
5023  // Grab the canonical container type for the extended type. Infer the smaller
5024  // type from that to ensure the same number of vector elements, as we know
5025  // the LMUL will be sufficient to hold the smaller type.
5026  MVT ContainerExtVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(ExtVT);
5027  // Get the extended container type manually to ensure the same number of
5028  // vector elements between source and dest.
5029  MVT ContainerVT = MVT::getVectorVT(VT.getVectorElementType(),
5030  ContainerExtVT.getVectorElementCount());
5031 
5032  SDValue Op1 =
5033  convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Op.getOperand(0), DAG, Subtarget);
5034 
5035  SDLoc DL(Op);
5036  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(VT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
5037 
5038  SDValue Ext = DAG.getNode(ExtendOpc, DL, ContainerExtVT, Op1, Mask, VL);
5039 
5040  return convertFromScalableVector(ExtVT, Ext, DAG, Subtarget);
5041 }
5042 
5043 // Custom-lower truncations from vectors to mask vectors by using a mask and a
5044 // setcc operation:
5045 // (vXi1 = trunc vXiN vec) -> (vXi1 = setcc (and vec, 1), 0, ne)
5046 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerVectorMaskTruncLike(SDValue Op,
5047  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5048  bool IsVPTrunc = Op.getOpcode() == ISD::VP_TRUNCATE;
5049  SDLoc DL(Op);
5050  EVT MaskVT = Op.getValueType();
5051  // Only expect to custom-lower truncations to mask types
5052  assert(MaskVT.isVector() && MaskVT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1 &&
5053  "Unexpected type for vector mask lowering");
5054  SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
5055  MVT VecVT = Src.getSimpleValueType();
5056  SDValue Mask, VL;
5057  if (IsVPTrunc) {
5058  Mask = Op.getOperand(1);
5059  VL = Op.getOperand(2);
5060  }
5061  // If this is a fixed vector, we need to convert it to a scalable vector.
5062  MVT ContainerVT = VecVT;
5063 
5064  if (VecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
5065  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VecVT);
5066  Src = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Src, DAG, Subtarget);
5067  if (IsVPTrunc) {
5068  MVT MaskContainerVT =
5069  getContainerForFixedLengthVector(Mask.getSimpleValueType());
5070  Mask = convertToScalableVector(MaskContainerVT, Mask, DAG, Subtarget);
5071  }
5072  }
5073 
5074  if (!IsVPTrunc) {
5075  std::tie(Mask, VL) =
5076  getDefaultVLOps(VecVT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
5077  }
5078 
5079  SDValue SplatOne = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, Subtarget.getXLenVT());
5080  SDValue SplatZero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, Subtarget.getXLenVT());
5081 
5082  SplatOne = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, ContainerVT,
5083  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), SplatOne, VL);
5084  SplatZero = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, ContainerVT,
5085  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), SplatZero, VL);
5086 
5087  MVT MaskContainerVT = ContainerVT.changeVectorElementType(MVT::i1);
5088  SDValue Trunc = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::AND_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Src, SplatOne,
5089  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), Mask, VL);
5090  Trunc = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SETCC_VL, DL, MaskContainerVT,
5091  {Trunc, SplatZero, DAG.getCondCode(ISD::SETNE),
5092  DAG.getUNDEF(MaskContainerVT), Mask, VL});
5093  if (MaskVT.isFixedLengthVector())
5094  Trunc = convertFromScalableVector(MaskVT, Trunc, DAG, Subtarget);
5095  return Trunc;
5096 }
5097 
5098 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerVectorTruncLike(SDValue Op,
5099  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5100  bool IsVPTrunc = Op.getOpcode() == ISD::VP_TRUNCATE;
5101  SDLoc DL(Op);
5102 
5103  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
5104  // Only custom-lower vector truncates
5105  assert(VT.isVector() && "Unexpected type for vector truncate lowering");
5106 
5107  // Truncates to mask types are handled differently
5108  if (VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
5109  return lowerVectorMaskTruncLike(Op, DAG);
5110 
5111  // RVV only has truncates which operate from SEW*2->SEW, so lower arbitrary
5112  // truncates as a series of "RISCVISD::TRUNCATE_VECTOR_VL" nodes which
5113  // truncate by one power of two at a time.
5114  MVT DstEltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
5115 
5116  SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
5117  MVT SrcVT = Src.getSimpleValueType();
5118  MVT SrcEltVT = SrcVT.getVectorElementType();
5119 
5120  assert(DstEltVT.bitsLT(SrcEltVT) && isPowerOf2_64(DstEltVT.getSizeInBits()) &&
5121  isPowerOf2_64(SrcEltVT.getSizeInBits()) &&
5122  "Unexpected vector truncate lowering");
5123 
5124  MVT ContainerVT = SrcVT;
5125  SDValue Mask, VL;
5126  if (IsVPTrunc) {
5127  Mask = Op.getOperand(1);
5128  VL = Op.getOperand(2);
5129  }
5130  if (SrcVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
5131  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(SrcVT);
5132  Src = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Src, DAG, Subtarget);
5133  if (IsVPTrunc) {
5134  MVT MaskVT = getMaskTypeFor(ContainerVT);
5135  Mask = convertToScalableVector(MaskVT, Mask, DAG, Subtarget);
5136  }
5137  }
5138 
5139  SDValue Result = Src;
5140  if (!IsVPTrunc) {
5141  std::tie(Mask, VL) =
5142  getDefaultVLOps(SrcVT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
5143  }
5144 
5145  LLVMContext &Context = *DAG.getContext();
5146  const ElementCount Count = ContainerVT.getVectorElementCount();
5147  do {
5148  SrcEltVT = MVT::getIntegerVT(SrcEltVT.getSizeInBits() / 2);
5149  EVT ResultVT = EVT::getVectorVT(Context, SrcEltVT, Count);
5150  Result = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::TRUNCATE_VECTOR_VL, DL, ResultVT, Result,
5151  Mask, VL);
5152  } while (SrcEltVT != DstEltVT);
5153 
5154  if (SrcVT.isFixedLengthVector())
5155  Result = convertFromScalableVector(VT, Result, DAG, Subtarget);
5156 
5157  return Result;
5158 }
5159 
5160 SDValue
5161 RISCVTargetLowering::lowerVectorFPExtendOrRoundLike(SDValue Op,
5162  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5163  bool IsVP =
5164  Op.getOpcode() == ISD::VP_FP_ROUND || Op.getOpcode() == ISD::VP_FP_EXTEND;
5165  bool IsExtend =
5166  Op.getOpcode() == ISD::VP_FP_EXTEND || Op.getOpcode() == ISD::FP_EXTEND;
5167  // RVV can only do truncate fp to types half the size as the source. We
5168  // custom-lower f64->f16 rounds via RVV's round-to-odd float
5169  // conversion instruction.
5170  SDLoc DL(Op);
5171  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
5172 
5173  assert(VT.isVector() && "Unexpected type for vector truncate lowering");
5174 
5175  SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
5176  MVT SrcVT = Src.getSimpleValueType();
5177 
5178  bool IsDirectExtend = IsExtend && (VT.getVectorElementType() != MVT::f64 ||
5179  SrcVT.getVectorElementType() != MVT::f16);
5180  bool IsDirectTrunc = !IsExtend && (VT.getVectorElementType() != MVT::f16 ||
5181  SrcVT.getVectorElementType() != MVT::f64);
5182 
5183  bool IsDirectConv = IsDirectExtend || IsDirectTrunc;
5184 
5185  // Prepare any fixed-length vector operands.
5186  MVT ContainerVT = VT;
5187  SDValue Mask, VL;
5188  if (IsVP) {
5189  Mask = Op.getOperand(1);
5190  VL = Op.getOperand(2);
5191  }
5192  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
5193  MVT SrcContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(SrcVT);
5194  ContainerVT =
5195  SrcContainerVT.changeVectorElementType(VT.getVectorElementType());
5196  Src = convertToScalableVector(SrcContainerVT, Src, DAG, Subtarget);
5197  if (IsVP) {
5198  MVT MaskVT = getMaskTypeFor(ContainerVT);
5199  Mask = convertToScalableVector(MaskVT, Mask, DAG, Subtarget);
5200  }
5201  }
5202 
5203  if (!IsVP)
5204  std::tie(Mask, VL) =
5205  getDefaultVLOps(SrcVT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
5206 
5207  unsigned ConvOpc = IsExtend ? RISCVISD::FP_EXTEND_VL : RISCVISD::FP_ROUND_VL;
5208 
5209  if (IsDirectConv) {
5210  Src = DAG.getNode(ConvOpc, DL, ContainerVT, Src, Mask, VL);
5211  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector())
5212  Src = convertFromScalableVector(VT, Src, DAG, Subtarget);
5213  return Src;
5214  }
5215 
5216  unsigned InterConvOpc =
5217  IsExtend ? RISCVISD::FP_EXTEND_VL : RISCVISD::VFNCVT_ROD_VL;
5218 
5219  MVT InterVT = ContainerVT.changeVectorElementType(MVT::f32);
5220  SDValue IntermediateConv =
5221  DAG.getNode(InterConvOpc, DL, InterVT, Src, Mask, VL);
5222  SDValue Result =
5223  DAG.getNode(ConvOpc, DL, ContainerVT, IntermediateConv, Mask, VL);
5224  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector())
5225  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, Result, DAG, Subtarget);
5226  return Result;
5227 }
5228 
5229 // Custom-legalize INSERT_VECTOR_ELT so that the value is inserted into the
5230 // first position of a vector, and that vector is slid up to the insert index.
5231 // By limiting the active vector length to index+1 and merging with the
5232 // original vector (with an undisturbed tail policy for elements >= VL), we
5233 // achieve the desired result of leaving all elements untouched except the one
5234 // at VL-1, which is replaced with the desired value.
5235 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerINSERT_VECTOR_ELT(SDValue Op,
5236  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5237  SDLoc DL(Op);
5238  MVT VecVT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
5239  SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(0);
5240  SDValue Val = Op.getOperand(1);
5241  SDValue Idx = Op.getOperand(2);
5242 
5243  if (VecVT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1) {
5244  // FIXME: For now we just promote to an i8 vector and insert into that,
5245  // but this is probably not optimal.
5246  MVT WideVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i8, VecVT.getVectorElementCount());
5247  Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, WideVT, Vec);
5248  Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, WideVT, Vec, Val, Idx);
5249  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VecVT, Vec);
5250  }
5251 
5252  MVT ContainerVT = VecVT;
5253  // If the operand is a fixed-length vector, convert to a scalable one.
5254  if (VecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
5255  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VecVT);
5256  Vec = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Vec, DAG, Subtarget);
5257  }
5258 
5259  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
5260 
5261  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT);
5262  bool IsLegalInsert = Subtarget.is64Bit() || Val.getValueType() != MVT::i64;
5263  // Even i64-element vectors on RV32 can be lowered without scalar
5264  // legalization if the most-significant 32 bits of the value are not affected
5265  // by the sign-extension of the lower 32 bits.
5266  // TODO: We could also catch sign extensions of a 32-bit value.
5267  if (!IsLegalInsert && isa<ConstantSDNode>(Val)) {
5268  const auto *CVal = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Val);
5269  if (isInt<32>(CVal->getSExtValue())) {
5270  IsLegalInsert = true;
5271  Val = DAG.getConstant(CVal->getSExtValue(), DL, MVT::i32);
5272  }
5273  }
5274 
5275  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(VecVT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
5276 
5277  SDValue ValInVec;
5278 
5279  if (IsLegalInsert) {
5280  unsigned Opc =
5281  VecVT.isFloatingPoint() ? RISCVISD::VFMV_S_F_VL : RISCVISD::VMV_S_X_VL;
5282  if (isNullConstant(Idx)) {
5283  Vec = DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, ContainerVT, Vec, Val, VL);
5284  if (!VecVT.isFixedLengthVector())
5285  return Vec;
5286  return convertFromScalableVector(VecVT, Vec, DAG, Subtarget);
5287  }
5288  ValInVec = lowerScalarInsert(Val, VL, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
5289  } else {
5290  // On RV32, i64-element vectors must be specially handled to place the
5291  // value at element 0, by using two vslide1down instructions in sequence on
5292  // the i32 split lo/hi value. Use an equivalently-sized i32 vector for
5293  // this.
5294  SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, XLenVT);
5295  SDValue ValLo = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, DL, MVT::i32, Val, Zero);
5296  SDValue ValHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, DL, MVT::i32, Val, One);
5297  MVT I32ContainerVT =
5298  MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i32, ContainerVT.getVectorElementCount() * 2);
5299  SDValue I32Mask =
5300  getDefaultScalableVLOps(I32ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget).first;
5301  // Limit the active VL to two.
5302  SDValue InsertI64VL = DAG.getConstant(2, DL, XLenVT);
5303  // If the Idx is 0 we can insert directly into the vector.
5304  if (isNullConstant(Idx)) {
5305  // First slide in the lo value, then the hi in above it. We use slide1down
5306  // to avoid the register group overlap constraint of vslide1up.
5307  ValInVec = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VSLIDE1DOWN_VL, DL, I32ContainerVT,
5308  Vec, Vec, ValLo, I32Mask, InsertI64VL);
5309  // If the source vector is undef don't pass along the tail elements from
5310  // the previous slide1down.
5311  SDValue Tail = Vec.isUndef() ? Vec : ValInVec;
5312  ValInVec = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VSLIDE1DOWN_VL, DL, I32ContainerVT,
5313  Tail, ValInVec, ValHi, I32Mask, InsertI64VL);
5314  // Bitcast back to the right container type.
5315  ValInVec = DAG.getBitcast(ContainerVT, ValInVec);
5316 
5317  if (!VecVT.isFixedLengthVector())
5318  return ValInVec;
5319  return convertFromScalableVector(VecVT, ValInVec, DAG, Subtarget);
5320  }
5321 
5322  // First slide in the lo value, then the hi in above it. We use slide1down
5323  // to avoid the register group overlap constraint of vslide1up.
5324  ValInVec = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VSLIDE1DOWN_VL, DL, I32ContainerVT,
5325  DAG.getUNDEF(I32ContainerVT),
5326  DAG.getUNDEF(I32ContainerVT), ValLo,
5327  I32Mask, InsertI64VL);
5328  ValInVec = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VSLIDE1DOWN_VL, DL, I32ContainerVT,
5329  DAG.getUNDEF(I32ContainerVT), ValInVec, ValHi,
5330  I32Mask, InsertI64VL);
5331  // Bitcast back to the right container type.
5332  ValInVec = DAG.getBitcast(ContainerVT, ValInVec);
5333  }
5334 
5335  // Now that the value is in a vector, slide it into position.
5336  SDValue InsertVL =
5337  DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, XLenVT, Idx, DAG.getConstant(1, DL, XLenVT));
5338 
5339  // Use tail agnostic policy if Idx is the last index of Vec.
5340  unsigned Policy = RISCVII::TAIL_UNDISTURBED_MASK_UNDISTURBED;
5341  if (VecVT.isFixedLengthVector() && isa<ConstantSDNode>(Idx) &&
5342  cast<ConstantSDNode>(Idx)->getZExtValue() + 1 ==
5343  VecVT.getVectorNumElements())
5344  Policy = RISCVII::TAIL_AGNOSTIC;
5345  SDValue Slideup = getVSlideup(DAG, Subtarget, DL, ContainerVT, Vec, ValInVec,
5346  Idx, Mask, InsertVL, Policy);
5347  if (!VecVT.isFixedLengthVector())
5348  return Slideup;
5349  return convertFromScalableVector(VecVT, Slideup, DAG, Subtarget);
5350 }
5351 
5352 // Custom-lower EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT operations to slide the vector down, then
5353 // extract the first element: (extractelt (slidedown vec, idx), 0). For integer
5354 // types this is done using VMV_X_S to allow us to glean information about the
5355 // sign bits of the result.
5356 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerEXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(SDValue Op,
5357  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5358  SDLoc DL(Op);
5359  SDValue Idx = Op.getOperand(1);
5360  SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(0);
5361  EVT EltVT = Op.getValueType();
5362  MVT VecVT = Vec.getSimpleValueType();
5363  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
5364 
5365  if (VecVT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1) {
5366  // Use vfirst.m to extract the first bit.
5367  if (isNullConstant(Idx)) {
5368  MVT ContainerVT = VecVT;
5369  if (VecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
5370  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VecVT);
5371  Vec = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Vec, DAG, Subtarget);
5372  }
5373  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(VecVT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
5374  SDValue Vfirst =
5375  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VFIRST_VL, DL, XLenVT, Vec, Mask, VL);
5376  return DAG.getSetCC(DL, XLenVT, Vfirst, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT),
5377  ISD::SETEQ);
5378  }
5379  if (VecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
5380  unsigned NumElts = VecVT.getVectorNumElements();
5381  if (NumElts >= 8) {
5382  MVT WideEltVT;
5383  unsigned WidenVecLen;
5384  SDValue ExtractElementIdx;
5385  SDValue ExtractBitIdx;
5386  unsigned MaxEEW = Subtarget.getELEN();
5387  MVT LargestEltVT = MVT::getIntegerVT(
5388  std::min(MaxEEW, unsigned(XLenVT.getSizeInBits())));
5389  if (NumElts <= LargestEltVT.getSizeInBits()) {
5390  assert(isPowerOf2_32(NumElts) &&
5391  "the number of elements should be power of 2");
5392  WideEltVT = MVT::getIntegerVT(NumElts);
5393  WidenVecLen = 1;
5394  ExtractElementIdx = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT);
5395  ExtractBitIdx = Idx;
5396  } else {
5397  WideEltVT = LargestEltVT;
5398  WidenVecLen = NumElts / WideEltVT.getSizeInBits();
5399  // extract element index = index / element width
5400  ExtractElementIdx = DAG.getNode(
5401  ISD::SRL, DL, XLenVT, Idx,
5402  DAG.getConstant(Log2_64(WideEltVT.getSizeInBits()), DL, XLenVT));
5403  // mask bit index = index % element width
5404  ExtractBitIdx = DAG.getNode(
5405  ISD::AND, DL, XLenVT, Idx,
5406  DAG.getConstant(WideEltVT.getSizeInBits() - 1, DL, XLenVT));
5407  }
5408  MVT WideVT = MVT::getVectorVT(WideEltVT, WidenVecLen);
5409  Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, WideVT, Vec);
5410  SDValue ExtractElt = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, XLenVT,
5411  Vec, ExtractElementIdx);
5412  // Extract the bit from GPR.
5413  SDValue ShiftRight =
5414  DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, XLenVT, ExtractElt, ExtractBitIdx);
5415  return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, XLenVT, ShiftRight,
5416  DAG.getConstant(1, DL, XLenVT));
5417  }
5418  }
5419  // Otherwise, promote to an i8 vector and extract from that.
5420  MVT WideVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i8, VecVT.getVectorElementCount());
5421  Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, WideVT, Vec);
5422  return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, EltVT, Vec, Idx);
5423  }
5424 
5425  // If this is a fixed vector, we need to convert it to a scalable vector.
5426  MVT ContainerVT = VecVT;
5427  if (VecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
5428  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VecVT);
5429  Vec = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Vec, DAG, Subtarget);
5430  }
5431 
5432  // If the index is 0, the vector is already in the right position.
5433  if (!isNullConstant(Idx)) {
5434  // Use a VL of 1 to avoid processing more elements than we need.
5435  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(1, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
5436  Vec = getVSlidedown(DAG, Subtarget, DL, ContainerVT,
5437  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), Vec, Idx, Mask, VL);
5438  }
5439 
5440  if (!EltVT.isInteger()) {
5441  // Floating-point extracts are handled in TableGen.
5442  return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, EltVT, Vec,
5443  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT));
5444  }
5445 
5446  SDValue Elt0 = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_X_S, DL, XLenVT, Vec);
5447  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, EltVT, Elt0);
5448 }
5449 
5450 // Some RVV intrinsics may claim that they want an integer operand to be
5451 // promoted or expanded.
5452 static SDValue lowerVectorIntrinsicScalars(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
5453  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
5454  assert((Op.getOpcode() == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN ||
5455  Op.getOpcode() == ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN) &&
5456  "Unexpected opcode");
5457 
5458  if (!Subtarget.hasVInstructions())
5459  return SDValue();
5460 
5461  bool HasChain = Op.getOpcode() == ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN;
5462  unsigned IntNo = Op.getConstantOperandVal(HasChain ? 1 : 0);
5463  SDLoc DL(Op);
5464 
5465  const RISCVVIntrinsicsTable::RISCVVIntrinsicInfo *II =
5466  RISCVVIntrinsicsTable::getRISCVVIntrinsicInfo(IntNo);
5467  if (!II || !II->hasScalarOperand())
5468  return SDValue();
5469 
5470  unsigned SplatOp = II->ScalarOperand + 1 + HasChain;
5471  assert(SplatOp < Op.getNumOperands());
5472 
5473  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Operands(Op->op_begin(), Op->op_end());
5474  SDValue &ScalarOp = Operands[SplatOp];
5475  MVT OpVT = ScalarOp.getSimpleValueType();
5476  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
5477 
5478  // If this isn't a scalar, or its type is XLenVT we're done.
5479  if (!OpVT.isScalarInteger() || OpVT == XLenVT)
5480  return SDValue();
5481 
5482  // Simplest case is that the operand needs to be promoted to XLenVT.
5483  if (OpVT.bitsLT(XLenVT)) {
5484  // If the operand is a constant, sign extend to increase our chances
5485  // of being able to use a .vi instruction. ANY_EXTEND would become a
5486  // a zero extend and the simm5 check in isel would fail.
5487  // FIXME: Should we ignore the upper bits in isel instead?
5488  unsigned ExtOpc =
5489  isa<ConstantSDNode>(ScalarOp) ? ISD::SIGN_EXTEND : ISD::ANY_EXTEND;
5490  ScalarOp = DAG.getNode(ExtOpc, DL, XLenVT, ScalarOp);
5491  return DAG.getNode(Op->getOpcode(), DL, Op->getVTList(), Operands);
5492  }
5493 
5494  // Use the previous operand to get the vXi64 VT. The result might be a mask
5495  // VT for compares. Using the previous operand assumes that the previous
5496  // operand will never have a smaller element size than a scalar operand and
5497  // that a widening operation never uses SEW=64.
5498  // NOTE: If this fails the below assert, we can probably just find the
5499  // element count from any operand or result and use it to construct the VT.
5500  assert(II->ScalarOperand > 0 && "Unexpected splat operand!");
5501  MVT VT = Op.getOperand(SplatOp - 1).getSimpleValueType();
5502 
5503  // The more complex case is when the scalar is larger than XLenVT.
5504  assert(XLenVT == MVT::i32 && OpVT == MVT::i64 &&
5505  VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i64 && "Unexpected VTs!");
5506 
5507  // If this is a sign-extended 32-bit value, we can truncate it and rely on the
5508  // instruction to sign-extend since SEW>XLEN.
5509  if (DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(ScalarOp) > 32) {
5510  ScalarOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, ScalarOp);
5511  return DAG.getNode(Op->getOpcode(), DL, Op->getVTList(), Operands);
5512  }
5513 
5514  switch (IntNo) {
5515  case Intrinsic::riscv_vslide1up:
5516  case Intrinsic::riscv_vslide1down:
5517  case Intrinsic::riscv_vslide1up_mask:
5518  case Intrinsic::riscv_vslide1down_mask: {
5519  // We need to special case these when the scalar is larger than XLen.
5520  unsigned NumOps = Op.getNumOperands();
5521  bool IsMasked = NumOps == 7;
5522 
5523  // Convert the vector source to the equivalent nxvXi32 vector.
5524  MVT I32VT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i32, VT.getVectorElementCount() * 2);
5525  SDValue Vec = DAG.getBitcast(I32VT, Operands[2]);
5526 
5527  SDValue ScalarLo = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, DL, MVT::i32, ScalarOp,
5528  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT));
5529  SDValue ScalarHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, DL, MVT::i32, ScalarOp,
5530  DAG.getConstant(1, DL, XLenVT));
5531 
5532  // Double the VL since we halved SEW.
5533  SDValue AVL = getVLOperand(Op);
5534  SDValue I32VL;
5535 
5536  // Optimize for constant AVL
5537  if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(AVL)) {
5538  unsigned EltSize = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
5539  unsigned MinSize = VT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue();
5540 
5541  unsigned VectorBitsMax = Subtarget.getRealMaxVLen();
5542  unsigned MaxVLMAX =
5543  RISCVTargetLowering::computeVLMAX(VectorBitsMax, EltSize, MinSize);
5544 
5545  unsigned VectorBitsMin = Subtarget.getRealMinVLen();
5546  unsigned MinVLMAX =
5547  RISCVTargetLowering::computeVLMAX(VectorBitsMin, EltSize, MinSize);
5548 
5549  uint64_t AVLInt = cast<ConstantSDNode>(AVL)->getZExtValue();
5550  if (AVLInt <= MinVLMAX) {
5551  I32VL = DAG.getConstant(2 * AVLInt, DL, XLenVT);
5552  } else if (AVLInt >= 2 * MaxVLMAX) {
5553  // Just set vl to VLMAX in this situation
5554  RISCVII::VLMUL Lmul = RISCVTargetLowering::getLMUL(I32VT);
5555  SDValue LMUL = DAG.getConstant(Lmul, DL, XLenVT);
5556  unsigned Sew = RISCVVType::encodeSEW(I32VT.getScalarSizeInBits());
5557  SDValue SEW = DAG.getConstant(Sew, DL, XLenVT);
5558  SDValue SETVLMAX = DAG.getTargetConstant(
5559  Intrinsic::riscv_vsetvlimax, DL, MVT::i32);
5560  I32VL = DAG.getNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, DL, XLenVT, SETVLMAX, SEW,
5561  LMUL);
5562  } else {
5563  // For AVL between (MinVLMAX, 2 * MaxVLMAX), the actual working vl
5564  // is related to the hardware implementation.
5565  // So let the following code handle
5566  }
5567  }
5568  if (!I32VL) {
5569  RISCVII::VLMUL Lmul = RISCVTargetLowering::getLMUL(VT);
5570  SDValue LMUL = DAG.getConstant(Lmul, DL, XLenVT);
5571  unsigned Sew = RISCVVType::encodeSEW(VT.getScalarSizeInBits());
5572  SDValue SEW = DAG.getConstant(Sew, DL, XLenVT);
5573  SDValue SETVL =
5574  DAG.getTargetConstant(Intrinsic::riscv_vsetvli, DL, MVT::i32);
5575  // Using vsetvli instruction to get actually used length which related to
5576  // the hardware implementation
5577  SDValue VL = DAG.getNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, DL, XLenVT, SETVL, AVL,
5578  SEW, LMUL);
5579  I32VL =
5580  DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, XLenVT, VL, DAG.getConstant(1, DL, XLenVT));
5581  }
5582 
5583  SDValue I32Mask = getAllOnesMask(I32VT, I32VL, DL, DAG);
5584 
5585  // Shift the two scalar parts in using SEW=32 slide1up/slide1down
5586  // instructions.
5587  SDValue Passthru;
5588  if (IsMasked)
5589  Passthru = DAG.getUNDEF(I32VT);
5590  else
5591  Passthru = DAG.getBitcast(I32VT, Operands[1]);
5592 
5593  if (IntNo == Intrinsic::riscv_vslide1up ||
5594  IntNo == Intrinsic::riscv_vslide1up_mask) {
5595  Vec = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VSLIDE1UP_VL, DL, I32VT, Passthru, Vec,
5596  ScalarHi, I32Mask, I32VL);
5597  Vec = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VSLIDE1UP_VL, DL, I32VT, Passthru, Vec,
5598  ScalarLo, I32Mask, I32VL);
5599  } else {
5600  Vec = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VSLIDE1DOWN_VL, DL, I32VT, Passthru, Vec,
5601  ScalarLo, I32Mask, I32VL);
5602  Vec = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VSLIDE1DOWN_VL, DL, I32VT, Passthru, Vec,
5603  ScalarHi, I32Mask, I32VL);
5604  }
5605 
5606  // Convert back to nxvXi64.
5607  Vec = DAG.getBitcast(VT, Vec);
5608 
5609  if (!IsMasked)
5610  return Vec;
5611  // Apply mask after the operation.
5612  SDValue Mask = Operands[NumOps - 3];
5613  SDValue MaskedOff = Operands[1];
5614  // Assume Policy operand is the last operand.
5615  uint64_t Policy =
5616  cast<ConstantSDNode>(Operands[NumOps - 1])->getZExtValue();
5617  // We don't need to select maskedoff if it's undef.
5618  if (MaskedOff.isUndef())
5619  return Vec;
5620  // TAMU
5621  if (Policy == RISCVII::TAIL_AGNOSTIC)
5622  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VSELECT_VL, DL, VT, Mask, Vec, MaskedOff,
5623  AVL);
5624  // TUMA or TUMU: Currently we always emit tumu policy regardless of tuma.
5625  // It's fine because vmerge does not care mask policy.
5626  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VP_MERGE_VL, DL, VT, Mask, Vec, MaskedOff,
5627  AVL);
5628  }
5629  }
5630 
5631  // We need to convert the scalar to a splat vector.
5632  SDValue VL = getVLOperand(Op);
5633  assert(VL.getValueType() == XLenVT);
5634  ScalarOp = splatSplitI64WithVL(DL, VT, SDValue(), ScalarOp, VL, DAG);
5635  return DAG.getNode(Op->getOpcode(), DL, Op->getVTList(), Operands);
5636 }
5637 
5638 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::LowerINTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN(SDValue Op,
5639  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5640  unsigned IntNo = Op.getConstantOperandVal(0);
5641  SDLoc DL(Op);
5642  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
5643 
5644  switch (IntNo) {
5645  default:
5646  break; // Don't custom lower most intrinsics.
5647  case Intrinsic::thread_pointer: {
5648  EVT PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
5649  return DAG.getRegister(RISCV::X4, PtrVT);
5650  }
5651  case Intrinsic::riscv_orc_b:
5652  case Intrinsic::riscv_brev8: {
5653  unsigned Opc =
5654  IntNo == Intrinsic::riscv_brev8 ? RISCVISD::BREV8 : RISCVISD::ORC_B;
5655  return DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, XLenVT, Op.getOperand(1));
5656  }
5657  case Intrinsic::riscv_zip:
5658  case Intrinsic::riscv_unzip: {
5659  unsigned Opc =
5660  IntNo == Intrinsic::riscv_zip ? RISCVISD::ZIP : RISCVISD::UNZIP;
5661  return DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, XLenVT, Op.getOperand(1));
5662  }
5663  case Intrinsic::riscv_vmv_x_s:
5664  assert(Op.getValueType() == XLenVT && "Unexpected VT!");
5665  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_X_S, DL, Op.getValueType(),
5666  Op.getOperand(1));
5667  case Intrinsic::riscv_vfmv_f_s:
5668  return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, Op.getValueType(),
5669  Op.getOperand(1), DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT));
5670  case Intrinsic::riscv_vmv_v_x:
5671  return lowerScalarSplat(Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2),
5672  Op.getOperand(3), Op.getSimpleValueType(), DL, DAG,
5673  Subtarget);
5674  case Intrinsic::riscv_vfmv_v_f:
5675  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VFMV_V_F_VL, DL, Op.getValueType(),
5676  Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2), Op.getOperand(3));
5677  case Intrinsic::riscv_vmv_s_x: {
5678  SDValue Scalar = Op.getOperand(2);
5679 
5680  if (Scalar.getValueType().bitsLE(XLenVT)) {
5681  Scalar = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, XLenVT, Scalar);
5682  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_S_X_VL, DL, Op.getValueType(),
5683  Op.getOperand(1), Scalar, Op.getOperand(3));
5684  }
5685 
5686  assert(Scalar.getValueType() == MVT::i64 && "Unexpected scalar VT!");
5687 
5688  // This is an i64 value that lives in two scalar registers. We have to
5689  // insert this in a convoluted way. First we build vXi64 splat containing
5690  // the two values that we assemble using some bit math. Next we'll use
5691  // vid.v and vmseq to build a mask with bit 0 set. Then we'll use that mask
5692  // to merge element 0 from our splat into the source vector.
5693  // FIXME: This is probably not the best way to do this, but it is
5694  // consistent with INSERT_VECTOR_ELT lowering so it is a good starting
5695  // point.
5696  // sw lo, (a0)
5697  // sw hi, 4(a0)
5698  // vlse vX, (a0)
5699  //
5700  // vid.v vVid
5701  // vmseq.vx mMask, vVid, 0
5702  // vmerge.vvm vDest, vSrc, vVal, mMask
5703  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
5704  SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(1);
5705  SDValue VL = getVLOperand(Op);
5706 
5707  SDValue SplattedVal = splatSplitI64WithVL(DL, VT, SDValue(), Scalar, VL, DAG);
5708  if (Op.getOperand(1).isUndef())
5709  return SplattedVal;
5710  SDValue SplattedIdx =
5711  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, VT, DAG.getUNDEF(VT),
5712  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32), VL);
5713 
5714  MVT MaskVT = getMaskTypeFor(VT);
5715  SDValue Mask = getAllOnesMask(VT, VL, DL, DAG);
5716  SDValue VID = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VID_VL, DL, VT, Mask, VL);
5717  SDValue SelectCond =
5718  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SETCC_VL, DL, MaskVT,
5719  {VID, SplattedIdx, DAG.getCondCode(ISD::SETEQ),
5720  DAG.getUNDEF(MaskVT), Mask, VL});
5721  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VSELECT_VL, DL, VT, SelectCond, SplattedVal,
5722  Vec, VL);
5723  }
5724  }
5725 
5726  return lowerVectorIntrinsicScalars(Op, DAG, Subtarget);
5727 }
5728 
5729 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::LowerINTRINSIC_W_CHAIN(SDValue Op,
5730  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5731  unsigned IntNo = Op.getConstantOperandVal(1);
5732  switch (IntNo) {
5733  default:
5734  break;
5735  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_strided_load: {
5736  SDLoc DL(Op);
5737  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
5738 
5739  // If the mask is known to be all ones, optimize to an unmasked intrinsic;
5740  // the selection of the masked intrinsics doesn't do this for us.
5741  SDValue Mask = Op.getOperand(5);
5742  bool IsUnmasked = ISD::isConstantSplatVectorAllOnes(Mask.getNode());
5743 
5744  MVT VT = Op->getSimpleValueType(0);
5745  MVT ContainerVT = VT;
5746  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector())
5747  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
5748 
5749  SDValue PassThru = Op.getOperand(2);
5750  if (!IsUnmasked) {
5751  MVT MaskVT = getMaskTypeFor(ContainerVT);
5752  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
5753  Mask = convertToScalableVector(MaskVT, Mask, DAG, Subtarget);
5754  PassThru = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, PassThru, DAG, Subtarget);
5755  }
5756  }
5757 
5758  auto *Load = cast<MemIntrinsicSDNode>(Op);
5759  SDValue VL = getDefaultVLOps(VT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget).second;
5760  SDValue Ptr = Op.getOperand(3);
5761  SDValue Stride = Op.getOperand(4);
5762  SDValue Result, Chain;
5763 
5764  // TODO: We restrict this to unmasked loads currently in consideration of
5765  // the complexity of hanlding all falses masks.
5766  if (IsUnmasked && isNullConstant(Stride)) {
5767  MVT ScalarVT = ContainerVT.getVectorElementType();
5768  SDValue ScalarLoad =
5769  DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, DL, XLenVT, Load->getChain(), Ptr,
5770  ScalarVT, Load->getMemOperand());
5771  Chain = ScalarLoad.getValue(1);
5772  Result = lowerScalarSplat(SDValue(), ScalarLoad, VL, ContainerVT, DL, DAG,
5773  Subtarget);
5774  } else {
5775  SDValue IntID = DAG.getTargetConstant(
5776  IsUnmasked ? Intrinsic::riscv_vlse : Intrinsic::riscv_vlse_mask, DL,
5777  XLenVT);
5778 
5779  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops{Load->getChain(), IntID};
5780  if (IsUnmasked)
5781  Ops.push_back(DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT));
5782  else
5783  Ops.push_back(PassThru);
5784  Ops.push_back(Ptr);
5785  Ops.push_back(Stride);
5786  if (!IsUnmasked)
5787  Ops.push_back(Mask);
5788  Ops.push_back(VL);
5789  if (!IsUnmasked) {
5790  SDValue Policy =
5791  DAG.getTargetConstant(RISCVII::TAIL_AGNOSTIC, DL, XLenVT);
5792  Ops.push_back(Policy);
5793  }
5794 
5795  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList({ContainerVT, MVT::Other});
5796  Result =
5797  DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN, DL, VTs, Ops,
5798  Load->getMemoryVT(), Load->getMemOperand());
5799  Chain = Result.getValue(1);
5800  }
5801  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector())
5802  Result = convertFromScalableVector(VT, Result, DAG, Subtarget);
5803  return DAG.getMergeValues({Result, Chain}, DL);
5804  }
5805  case Intrinsic::riscv_seg2_load:
5806  case Intrinsic::riscv_seg3_load:
5807  case Intrinsic::riscv_seg4_load:
5808  case Intrinsic::riscv_seg5_load:
5809  case Intrinsic::riscv_seg6_load:
5810  case Intrinsic::riscv_seg7_load:
5811  case Intrinsic::riscv_seg8_load: {
5812  SDLoc DL(Op);
5813  static const Intrinsic::ID VlsegInts[7] = {
5814  Intrinsic::riscv_vlseg2, Intrinsic::riscv_vlseg3,
5815  Intrinsic::riscv_vlseg4, Intrinsic::riscv_vlseg5,
5816  Intrinsic::riscv_vlseg6, Intrinsic::riscv_vlseg7,
5817  Intrinsic::riscv_vlseg8};
5818  unsigned NF = Op->getNumValues() - 1;
5819  assert(NF >= 2 && NF <= 8 && "Unexpected seg number");
5820  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
5821  MVT VT = Op->getSimpleValueType(0);
5822  MVT ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
5823 
5824  SDValue VL = getVLOp(VT.getVectorNumElements(), DL, DAG, Subtarget);
5825  SDValue IntID = DAG.getTargetConstant(VlsegInts[NF - 2], DL, XLenVT);
5826  auto *Load = cast<MemIntrinsicSDNode>(Op);
5827  SmallVector<EVT, 9> ContainerVTs(NF, ContainerVT);
5828  ContainerVTs.push_back(MVT::Other);
5829  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(ContainerVTs);
5830  SmallVector<SDValue, 12> Ops = {Load->getChain(), IntID};
5831  Ops.insert(Ops.end(), NF, DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT));
5832  Ops.push_back(Op.getOperand(2));
5833  Ops.push_back(VL);
5834  SDValue Result =
5835  DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN, DL, VTs, Ops,
5836  Load->getMemoryVT(), Load->getMemOperand());
5837  SmallVector<SDValue, 9> Results;
5838  for (unsigned int RetIdx = 0; RetIdx < NF; RetIdx++)
5839  Results.push_back(convertFromScalableVector(VT, Result.getValue(RetIdx),
5840  DAG, Subtarget));
5841  Results.push_back(Result.getValue(NF));
5842  return DAG.getMergeValues(Results, DL);
5843  }
5844  }
5845 
5846  return lowerVectorIntrinsicScalars(Op, DAG, Subtarget);
5847 }
5848 
5849 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::LowerINTRINSIC_VOID(SDValue Op,
5850  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5851  unsigned IntNo = Op.getConstantOperandVal(1);
5852  switch (IntNo) {
5853  default:
5854  break;
5855  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_strided_store: {
5856  SDLoc DL(Op);
5857  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
5858 
5859  // If the mask is known to be all ones, optimize to an unmasked intrinsic;
5860  // the selection of the masked intrinsics doesn't do this for us.
5861  SDValue Mask = Op.getOperand(5);
5862  bool IsUnmasked = ISD::isConstantSplatVectorAllOnes(Mask.getNode());
5863 
5864  SDValue Val = Op.getOperand(2);
5865  MVT VT = Val.getSimpleValueType();
5866  MVT ContainerVT = VT;
5867  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
5868  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
5869  Val = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Val, DAG, Subtarget);
5870  }
5871  if (!IsUnmasked) {
5872  MVT MaskVT = getMaskTypeFor(ContainerVT);
5873  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector())
5874  Mask = convertToScalableVector(MaskVT, Mask, DAG, Subtarget);
5875  }
5876 
5877  SDValue VL = getDefaultVLOps(VT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget).second;
5878 
5879  SDValue IntID = DAG.getTargetConstant(
5880  IsUnmasked ? Intrinsic::riscv_vsse : Intrinsic::riscv_vsse_mask, DL,
5881  XLenVT);
5882 
5883  auto *Store = cast<MemIntrinsicSDNode>(Op);
5884  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops{Store->getChain(), IntID};
5885  Ops.push_back(Val);
5886  Ops.push_back(Op.getOperand(3)); // Ptr
5887  Ops.push_back(Op.getOperand(4)); // Stride
5888  if (!IsUnmasked)
5889  Ops.push_back(Mask);
5890  Ops.push_back(VL);
5891 
5892  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID, DL, Store->getVTList(),
5893  Ops, Store->getMemoryVT(),
5894  Store->getMemOperand());
5895  }
5896  }
5897 
5898  return SDValue();
5899 }
5900 
5901 static unsigned getRVVReductionOp(unsigned ISDOpcode) {
5902  switch (ISDOpcode) {
5903  default:
5904  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled reduction");
5905  case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD:
5906  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_ADD_VL;
5907  case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX:
5908  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX_VL;
5909  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX:
5910  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX_VL;
5911  case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN:
5912  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN_VL;
5913  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN:
5914  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN_VL;
5915  case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND:
5916  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_AND_VL;
5917  case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR:
5918  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_OR_VL;
5919  case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR:
5920  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_XOR_VL;
5921  }
5922 }
5923 
5924 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerVectorMaskVecReduction(SDValue Op,
5925  SelectionDAG &DAG,
5926  bool IsVP) const {
5927  SDLoc DL(Op);
5928  SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(IsVP ? 1 : 0);
5929  MVT VecVT = Vec.getSimpleValueType();
5930  assert((Op.getOpcode() == ISD::VECREDUCE_AND ||
5931  Op.getOpcode() == ISD::VECREDUCE_OR ||
5932  Op.getOpcode() == ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR ||
5933  Op.getOpcode() == ISD::VP_REDUCE_AND ||
5934  Op.getOpcode() == ISD::VP_REDUCE_OR ||
5935  Op.getOpcode() == ISD::VP_REDUCE_XOR) &&
5936  "Unexpected reduction lowering");
5937 
5938  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
5939  assert(Op.getValueType() == XLenVT &&
5940  "Expected reduction output to be legalized to XLenVT");
5941 
5942  MVT ContainerVT = VecVT;
5943  if (VecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
5944  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VecVT);
5945  Vec = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Vec, DAG, Subtarget);
5946  }
5947 
5948  SDValue Mask, VL;
5949  if (IsVP) {
5950  Mask = Op.getOperand(2);
5951  VL = Op.getOperand(3);
5952  } else {
5953  std::tie(Mask, VL) =
5954  getDefaultVLOps(VecVT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
5955  }
5956 
5957  unsigned BaseOpc;
5958  ISD::CondCode CC;
5959  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT);
5960 
5961  switch (Op.getOpcode()) {
5962  default:
5963  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled reduction");
5964  case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND:
5965  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_AND: {
5966  // vcpop ~x == 0
5967  SDValue TrueMask = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMSET_VL, DL, ContainerVT, VL);
5968  Vec = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMXOR_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Vec, TrueMask, VL);
5969  Vec = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VCPOP_VL, DL, XLenVT, Vec, Mask, VL);
5970  CC = ISD::SETEQ;
5971  BaseOpc = ISD::AND;
5972  break;
5973  }
5974  case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR:
5975  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_OR:
5976  // vcpop x != 0
5977  Vec = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VCPOP_VL, DL, XLenVT, Vec, Mask, VL);
5978  CC = ISD::SETNE;
5979  BaseOpc = ISD::OR;
5980  break;
5981  case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR:
5982  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_XOR: {
5983  // ((vcpop x) & 1) != 0
5984  SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, XLenVT);
5985  Vec = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VCPOP_VL, DL, XLenVT, Vec, Mask, VL);
5986  Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, XLenVT, Vec, One);
5987  CC = ISD::SETNE;
5988  BaseOpc = ISD::XOR;
5989  break;
5990  }
5991  }
5992 
5993  SDValue SetCC = DAG.getSetCC(DL, XLenVT, Vec, Zero, CC);
5994 
5995  if (!IsVP)
5996  return SetCC;
5997 
5998  // Now include the start value in the operation.
5999  // Note that we must return the start value when no elements are operated
6000  // upon. The vcpop instructions we've emitted in each case above will return
6001  // 0 for an inactive vector, and so we've already received the neutral value:
6002  // AND gives us (0 == 0) -> 1 and OR/XOR give us (0 != 0) -> 0. Therefore we
6003  // can simply include the start value.
6004  return DAG.getNode(BaseOpc, DL, XLenVT, SetCC, Op.getOperand(0));
6005 }
6006 
6007 static bool hasNonZeroAVL(SDValue AVL) {
6008  auto *RegisterAVL = dyn_cast<RegisterSDNode>(AVL);
6009  auto *ImmAVL = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(AVL);
6010  return (RegisterAVL && RegisterAVL->getReg() == RISCV::X0) ||
6011  (ImmAVL && ImmAVL->getZExtValue() >= 1);
6012 }
6013 
6014 /// Helper to lower a reduction sequence of the form:
6015 /// scalar = reduce_op vec, scalar_start
6016 static SDValue lowerReductionSeq(unsigned RVVOpcode, MVT ResVT,
6017  SDValue StartValue, SDValue Vec, SDValue Mask,
6018  SDValue VL, SDLoc DL, SelectionDAG &DAG,
6019  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
6020  const MVT VecVT = Vec.getSimpleValueType();
6021  const MVT M1VT = getLMUL1VT(VecVT);
6022  const MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
6023  const bool NonZeroAVL = hasNonZeroAVL(VL);
6024 
6025  // The reduction needs an LMUL1 input; do the splat at either LMUL1
6026  // or the original VT if fractional.
6027  auto InnerVT = VecVT.bitsLE(M1VT) ? VecVT : M1VT;
6028  // We reuse the VL of the reduction to reduce vsetvli toggles if we can
6029  // prove it is non-zero. For the AVL=0 case, we need the scalar to
6030  // be the result of the reduction operation.
6031  auto InnerVL = NonZeroAVL ? VL : DAG.getConstant(1, DL, XLenVT);
6032  SDValue InitialValue = lowerScalarInsert(StartValue, InnerVL, InnerVT, DL,
6033  DAG, Subtarget);
6034  if (M1VT != InnerVT)
6035  InitialValue = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, M1VT,
6036  DAG.getUNDEF(M1VT),
6037  InitialValue, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT));
6038  SDValue PassThru = NonZeroAVL ? DAG.getUNDEF(M1VT) : InitialValue;
6039  SDValue Reduction = DAG.getNode(RVVOpcode, DL, M1VT, PassThru, Vec,
6040  InitialValue, Mask, VL);
6041  return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, ResVT, Reduction,
6042  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT));
6043 }
6044 
6045 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerVECREDUCE(SDValue Op,
6046  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6047  SDLoc DL(Op);
6048  SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(0);
6049  EVT VecEVT = Vec.getValueType();
6050 
6051  unsigned BaseOpc = ISD::getVecReduceBaseOpcode(Op.getOpcode());
6052 
6053  // Due to ordering in legalize types we may have a vector type that needs to
6054  // be split. Do that manually so we can get down to a legal type.
6055  while (getTypeAction(*DAG.getContext(), VecEVT) ==
6056  TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector) {
6057  auto [Lo, Hi] = DAG.SplitVector(Vec, DL);
6058  VecEVT = Lo.getValueType();
6059  Vec = DAG.getNode(BaseOpc, DL, VecEVT, Lo, Hi);
6060  }
6061 
6062  // TODO: The type may need to be widened rather than split. Or widened before
6063  // it can be split.
6064  if (!isTypeLegal(VecEVT))
6065  return SDValue();
6066 
6067  MVT VecVT = VecEVT.getSimpleVT();
6068  MVT VecEltVT = VecVT.getVectorElementType();
6069  unsigned RVVOpcode = getRVVReductionOp(Op.getOpcode());
6070 
6071  MVT ContainerVT = VecVT;
6072  if (VecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
6073  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VecVT);
6074  Vec = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Vec, DAG, Subtarget);
6075  }
6076 
6077  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(VecVT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
6078 
6079  SDValue NeutralElem =
6080  DAG.getNeutralElement(BaseOpc, DL, VecEltVT, SDNodeFlags());
6081  return lowerReductionSeq(RVVOpcode, Op.getSimpleValueType(), NeutralElem, Vec,
6082  Mask, VL, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
6083 }
6084 
6085 // Given a reduction op, this function returns the matching reduction opcode,
6086 // the vector SDValue and the scalar SDValue required to lower this to a
6087 // RISCVISD node.
6088 static std::tuple<unsigned, SDValue, SDValue>
6089 getRVVFPReductionOpAndOperands(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, EVT EltVT) {
6090  SDLoc DL(Op);
6091  auto Flags = Op->getFlags();
6092  unsigned Opcode = Op.getOpcode();
6093  unsigned BaseOpcode = ISD::getVecReduceBaseOpcode(Opcode);
6094  switch (Opcode) {
6095  default:
6096  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled reduction");
6097  case ISD::VECREDUCE_FADD: {
6098  // Use positive zero if we can. It is cheaper to materialize.
6099  SDValue Zero =
6100  DAG.getConstantFP(Flags.hasNoSignedZeros() ? 0.0 : -0.0, DL, EltVT);
6101  return std::make_tuple(RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_FADD_VL, Op.getOperand(0), Zero);
6102  }
6103  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FADD:
6104  return std::make_tuple(RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FADD_VL, Op.getOperand(1),
6105  Op.getOperand(0));
6106  case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMIN:
6107  return std::make_tuple(RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_FMIN_VL, Op.getOperand(0),
6108  DAG.getNeutralElement(BaseOpcode, DL, EltVT, Flags));
6109  case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMAX:
6110  return std::make_tuple(RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_FMAX_VL, Op.getOperand(0),
6111  DAG.getNeutralElement(BaseOpcode, DL, EltVT, Flags));
6112  }
6113 }
6114 
6115 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerFPVECREDUCE(SDValue Op,
6116  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6117  SDLoc DL(Op);
6118  MVT VecEltVT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
6119 
6120  unsigned RVVOpcode;
6121  SDValue VectorVal, ScalarVal;
6122  std::tie(RVVOpcode, VectorVal, ScalarVal) =
6123  getRVVFPReductionOpAndOperands(Op, DAG, VecEltVT);
6124  MVT VecVT = VectorVal.getSimpleValueType();
6125 
6126  MVT ContainerVT = VecVT;
6127  if (VecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
6128  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VecVT);
6129  VectorVal = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, VectorVal, DAG, Subtarget);
6130  }
6131 
6132  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(VecVT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
6133  return lowerReductionSeq(RVVOpcode, Op.getSimpleValueType(), ScalarVal,
6134  VectorVal, Mask, VL, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
6135 }
6136 
6137 static unsigned getRVVVPReductionOp(unsigned ISDOpcode) {
6138  switch (ISDOpcode) {
6139  default:
6140  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled reduction");
6141  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_ADD:
6142  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_ADD_VL;
6143  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_UMAX:
6144  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX_VL;
6145  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SMAX:
6146  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX_VL;
6147  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_UMIN:
6148  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN_VL;
6149  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SMIN:
6150  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN_VL;
6151  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_AND:
6152  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_AND_VL;
6153  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_OR:
6154  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_OR_VL;
6155  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_XOR:
6156  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_XOR_VL;
6157  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FADD:
6158  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_FADD_VL;
6159  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SEQ_FADD:
6160  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FADD_VL;
6161  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FMAX:
6162  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_FMAX_VL;
6163  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_FMIN:
6164  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_FMIN_VL;
6165  }
6166 }
6167 
6168 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerVPREDUCE(SDValue Op,
6169  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6170  SDLoc DL(Op);
6171  SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(1);
6172  EVT VecEVT = Vec.getValueType();
6173 
6174  // TODO: The type may need to be widened rather than split. Or widened before
6175  // it can be split.
6176  if (!isTypeLegal(VecEVT))
6177  return SDValue();
6178 
6179  MVT VecVT = VecEVT.getSimpleVT();
6180  unsigned RVVOpcode = getRVVVPReductionOp(Op.getOpcode());
6181 
6182  if (VecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
6183  auto ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VecVT);
6184  Vec = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Vec, DAG, Subtarget);
6185  }
6186 
6187  SDValue VL = Op.getOperand(3);
6188  SDValue Mask = Op.getOperand(2);
6189  return lowerReductionSeq(RVVOpcode, Op.getSimpleValueType(), Op.getOperand(0),
6190  Vec, Mask, VL, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
6191 }
6192 
6193 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerINSERT_SUBVECTOR(SDValue Op,
6194  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6195  SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(0);
6196  SDValue SubVec = Op.getOperand(1);
6197  MVT VecVT = Vec.getSimpleValueType();
6198  MVT SubVecVT = SubVec.getSimpleValueType();
6199 
6200  SDLoc DL(Op);
6201  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
6202  unsigned OrigIdx = Op.getConstantOperandVal(2);
6203  const RISCVRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
6204 
6205  // We don't have the ability to slide mask vectors up indexed by their i1
6206  // elements; the smallest we can do is i8. Often we are able to bitcast to
6207  // equivalent i8 vectors. Note that when inserting a fixed-length vector
