6208  // into a scalable one, we might not necessarily have enough scalable
6209  // elements to safely divide by 8: nxv1i1 = insert nxv1i1, v4i1 is valid.
6210  if (SubVecVT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1 &&
6211  (OrigIdx != 0 || !Vec.isUndef())) {
6212  if (VecVT.getVectorMinNumElements() >= 8 &&
6213  SubVecVT.getVectorMinNumElements() >= 8) {
6214  assert(OrigIdx % 8 == 0 && "Invalid index");
6215  assert(VecVT.getVectorMinNumElements() % 8 == 0 &&
6216  SubVecVT.getVectorMinNumElements() % 8 == 0 &&
6217  "Unexpected mask vector lowering");
6218  OrigIdx /= 8;
6219  SubVecVT =
6220  MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i8, SubVecVT.getVectorMinNumElements() / 8,
6221  SubVecVT.isScalableVector());
6222  VecVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i8, VecVT.getVectorMinNumElements() / 8,
6223  VecVT.isScalableVector());
6224  Vec = DAG.getBitcast(VecVT, Vec);
6225  SubVec = DAG.getBitcast(SubVecVT, SubVec);
6226  } else {
6227  // We can't slide this mask vector up indexed by its i1 elements.
6228  // This poses a problem when we wish to insert a scalable vector which
6229  // can't be re-expressed as a larger type. Just choose the slow path and
6230  // extend to a larger type, then truncate back down.
6231  MVT ExtVecVT = VecVT.changeVectorElementType(MVT::i8);
6232  MVT ExtSubVecVT = SubVecVT.changeVectorElementType(MVT::i8);
6233  Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, ExtVecVT, Vec);
6234  SubVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, ExtSubVecVT, SubVec);
6235  Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, ExtVecVT, Vec, SubVec,
6236  Op.getOperand(2));
6237  SDValue SplatZero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, ExtVecVT);
6238  return DAG.getSetCC(DL, VecVT, Vec, SplatZero, ISD::SETNE);
6239  }
6240  }
6241 
6242  // If the subvector vector is a fixed-length type, we cannot use subregister
6243  // manipulation to simplify the codegen; we don't know which register of a
6244  // LMUL group contains the specific subvector as we only know the minimum
6245  // register size. Therefore we must slide the vector group up the full
6246  // amount.
6247  if (SubVecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
6248  if (OrigIdx == 0 && Vec.isUndef() && !VecVT.isFixedLengthVector())
6249  return Op;
6250  MVT ContainerVT = VecVT;
6251  if (VecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
6252  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VecVT);
6253  Vec = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Vec, DAG, Subtarget);
6254  }
6255  SubVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, ContainerVT,
6256  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), SubVec,
6257  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT));
6258  if (OrigIdx == 0 && Vec.isUndef() && VecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
6259  SubVec = convertFromScalableVector(VecVT, SubVec, DAG, Subtarget);
6260  return DAG.getBitcast(Op.getValueType(), SubVec);
6261  }
6262  SDValue Mask =
6263  getDefaultVLOps(VecVT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget).first;
6264  // Set the vector length to only the number of elements we care about. Note
6265  // that for slideup this includes the offset.
6266  SDValue VL =
6267  getVLOp(OrigIdx + SubVecVT.getVectorNumElements(), DL, DAG, Subtarget);
6268  SDValue SlideupAmt = DAG.getConstant(OrigIdx, DL, XLenVT);
6269 
6270  // Use tail agnostic policy if OrigIdx is the last index of Vec.
6271  unsigned Policy = RISCVII::TAIL_UNDISTURBED_MASK_UNDISTURBED;
6272  if (VecVT.isFixedLengthVector() &&
6273  OrigIdx + 1 == VecVT.getVectorNumElements())
6274  Policy = RISCVII::TAIL_AGNOSTIC;
6275  SDValue Slideup = getVSlideup(DAG, Subtarget, DL, ContainerVT, Vec, SubVec,
6276  SlideupAmt, Mask, VL, Policy);
6277  if (VecVT.isFixedLengthVector())
6278  Slideup = convertFromScalableVector(VecVT, Slideup, DAG, Subtarget);
6279  return DAG.getBitcast(Op.getValueType(), Slideup);
6280  }
6281 
6282  unsigned SubRegIdx, RemIdx;
6283  std::tie(SubRegIdx, RemIdx) =
6284  RISCVTargetLowering::decomposeSubvectorInsertExtractToSubRegs(
6285  VecVT, SubVecVT, OrigIdx, TRI);
6286 
6287  RISCVII::VLMUL SubVecLMUL = RISCVTargetLowering::getLMUL(SubVecVT);
6288  bool IsSubVecPartReg = SubVecLMUL == RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F2 ||
6289  SubVecLMUL == RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F4 ||
6290  SubVecLMUL == RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F8;
6291 
6292  // 1. If the Idx has been completely eliminated and this subvector's size is
6293  // a vector register or a multiple thereof, or the surrounding elements are
6294  // undef, then this is a subvector insert which naturally aligns to a vector
6295  // register. These can easily be handled using subregister manipulation.
6296  // 2. If the subvector is smaller than a vector register, then the insertion
6297  // must preserve the undisturbed elements of the register. We do this by
6298  // lowering to an EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR grabbing the nearest LMUL=1 vector type
6299  // (which resolves to a subregister copy), performing a VSLIDEUP to place the
6300  // subvector within the vector register, and an INSERT_SUBVECTOR of that
6301  // LMUL=1 type back into the larger vector (resolving to another subregister
6302  // operation). See below for how our VSLIDEUP works. We go via a LMUL=1 type
6303  // to avoid allocating a large register group to hold our subvector.
6304  if (RemIdx == 0 && (!IsSubVecPartReg || Vec.isUndef()))
6305  return Op;
6306 
6307  // VSLIDEUP works by leaving elements 0<i<OFFSET undisturbed, elements
6308  // OFFSET<=i<VL set to the "subvector" and vl<=i<VLMAX set to the tail policy
6309  // (in our case undisturbed). This means we can set up a subvector insertion
6310  // where OFFSET is the insertion offset, and the VL is the OFFSET plus the
6311  // size of the subvector.
6312  MVT InterSubVT = VecVT;
6313  SDValue AlignedExtract = Vec;
6314  unsigned AlignedIdx = OrigIdx - RemIdx;
6315  if (VecVT.bitsGT(getLMUL1VT(VecVT))) {
6316  InterSubVT = getLMUL1VT(VecVT);
6317  // Extract a subvector equal to the nearest full vector register type. This
6318  // should resolve to a EXTRACT_SUBREG instruction.
6319  AlignedExtract = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, InterSubVT, Vec,
6320  DAG.getConstant(AlignedIdx, DL, XLenVT));
6321  }
6322 
6323  SDValue SlideupAmt = DAG.getConstant(RemIdx, DL, XLenVT);
6324  // For scalable vectors this must be further multiplied by vscale.
6325  SlideupAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::VSCALE, DL, XLenVT, SlideupAmt);
6326 
6327  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultScalableVLOps(VecVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
6328 
6329  // Construct the vector length corresponding to RemIdx + length(SubVecVT).
6330  VL = DAG.getConstant(SubVecVT.getVectorMinNumElements(), DL, XLenVT);
6331  VL = DAG.getNode(ISD::VSCALE, DL, XLenVT, VL);
6332  VL = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, XLenVT, SlideupAmt, VL);
6333 
6334  SubVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, InterSubVT,
6335  DAG.getUNDEF(InterSubVT), SubVec,
6336  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT));
6337 
6338  SDValue Slideup = getVSlideup(DAG, Subtarget, DL, InterSubVT, AlignedExtract,
6339  SubVec, SlideupAmt, Mask, VL);
6340 
6341  // If required, insert this subvector back into the correct vector register.
6342  // This should resolve to an INSERT_SUBREG instruction.
6343  if (VecVT.bitsGT(InterSubVT))
6344  Slideup = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, VecVT, Vec, Slideup,
6345  DAG.getConstant(AlignedIdx, DL, XLenVT));
6346 
6347  // We might have bitcast from a mask type: cast back to the original type if
6348  // required.
6349  return DAG.getBitcast(Op.getSimpleValueType(), Slideup);
6350 }
6351 
6352 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerEXTRACT_SUBVECTOR(SDValue Op,
6353  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6354  SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(0);
6355  MVT SubVecVT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
6356  MVT VecVT = Vec.getSimpleValueType();
6357 
6358  SDLoc DL(Op);
6359  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
6360  unsigned OrigIdx = Op.getConstantOperandVal(1);
6361  const RISCVRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
6362 
6363  // We don't have the ability to slide mask vectors down indexed by their i1
6364  // elements; the smallest we can do is i8. Often we are able to bitcast to
6365  // equivalent i8 vectors. Note that when extracting a fixed-length vector
6366  // from a scalable one, we might not necessarily have enough scalable
6367  // elements to safely divide by 8: v8i1 = extract nxv1i1 is valid.
6368  if (SubVecVT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1 && OrigIdx != 0) {
6369  if (VecVT.getVectorMinNumElements() >= 8 &&
6370  SubVecVT.getVectorMinNumElements() >= 8) {
6371  assert(OrigIdx % 8 == 0 && "Invalid index");
6372  assert(VecVT.getVectorMinNumElements() % 8 == 0 &&
6373  SubVecVT.getVectorMinNumElements() % 8 == 0 &&
6374  "Unexpected mask vector lowering");
6375  OrigIdx /= 8;
6376  SubVecVT =
6377  MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i8, SubVecVT.getVectorMinNumElements() / 8,
6378  SubVecVT.isScalableVector());
6379  VecVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i8, VecVT.getVectorMinNumElements() / 8,
6380  VecVT.isScalableVector());
6381  Vec = DAG.getBitcast(VecVT, Vec);
6382  } else {
6383  // We can't slide this mask vector down, indexed by its i1 elements.
6384  // This poses a problem when we wish to extract a scalable vector which
6385  // can't be re-expressed as a larger type. Just choose the slow path and
6386  // extend to a larger type, then truncate back down.
6387  // TODO: We could probably improve this when extracting certain fixed
6388  // from fixed, where we can extract as i8 and shift the correct element
6389  // right to reach the desired subvector?
6390  MVT ExtVecVT = VecVT.changeVectorElementType(MVT::i8);
6391  MVT ExtSubVecVT = SubVecVT.changeVectorElementType(MVT::i8);
6392  Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, ExtVecVT, Vec);
6393  Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, ExtSubVecVT, Vec,
6394  Op.getOperand(1));
6395  SDValue SplatZero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, ExtSubVecVT);
6396  return DAG.getSetCC(DL, SubVecVT, Vec, SplatZero, ISD::SETNE);
6397  }
6398  }
6399 
6400  // If the subvector vector is a fixed-length type, we cannot use subregister
6401  // manipulation to simplify the codegen; we don't know which register of a
6402  // LMUL group contains the specific subvector as we only know the minimum
6403  // register size. Therefore we must slide the vector group down the full
6404  // amount.
6405  if (SubVecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
6406  // With an index of 0 this is a cast-like subvector, which can be performed
6407  // with subregister operations.
6408  if (OrigIdx == 0)
6409  return Op;
6410  MVT ContainerVT = VecVT;
6411  if (VecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
6412  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VecVT);
6413  Vec = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Vec, DAG, Subtarget);
6414  }
6415  SDValue Mask =
6416  getDefaultVLOps(VecVT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget).first;
6417  // Set the vector length to only the number of elements we care about. This
6418  // avoids sliding down elements we're going to discard straight away.
6419  SDValue VL = getVLOp(SubVecVT.getVectorNumElements(), DL, DAG, Subtarget);
6420  SDValue SlidedownAmt = DAG.getConstant(OrigIdx, DL, XLenVT);
6421  SDValue Slidedown =
6422  getVSlidedown(DAG, Subtarget, DL, ContainerVT,
6423  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), Vec, SlidedownAmt, Mask, VL);
6424  // Now we can use a cast-like subvector extract to get the result.
6425  Slidedown = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, SubVecVT, Slidedown,
6426  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT));
6427  return DAG.getBitcast(Op.getValueType(), Slidedown);
6428  }
6429 
6430  unsigned SubRegIdx, RemIdx;
6431  std::tie(SubRegIdx, RemIdx) =
6432  RISCVTargetLowering::decomposeSubvectorInsertExtractToSubRegs(
6433  VecVT, SubVecVT, OrigIdx, TRI);
6434 
6435  // If the Idx has been completely eliminated then this is a subvector extract
6436  // which naturally aligns to a vector register. These can easily be handled
6437  // using subregister manipulation.
6438  if (RemIdx == 0)
6439  return Op;
6440 
6441  // Else we must shift our vector register directly to extract the subvector.
6442  // Do this using VSLIDEDOWN.
6443 
6444  // If the vector type is an LMUL-group type, extract a subvector equal to the
6445  // nearest full vector register type. This should resolve to a EXTRACT_SUBREG
6446  // instruction.
6447  MVT InterSubVT = VecVT;
6448  if (VecVT.bitsGT(getLMUL1VT(VecVT))) {
6449  InterSubVT = getLMUL1VT(VecVT);
6450  Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, InterSubVT, Vec,
6451  DAG.getConstant(OrigIdx - RemIdx, DL, XLenVT));
6452  }
6453 
6454  // Slide this vector register down by the desired number of elements in order
6455  // to place the desired subvector starting at element 0.
6456  SDValue SlidedownAmt = DAG.getConstant(RemIdx, DL, XLenVT);
6457  // For scalable vectors this must be further multiplied by vscale.
6458  SlidedownAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::VSCALE, DL, XLenVT, SlidedownAmt);
6459 
6460  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultScalableVLOps(InterSubVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
6461  SDValue Slidedown =
6462  getVSlidedown(DAG, Subtarget, DL, InterSubVT, DAG.getUNDEF(InterSubVT),
6463  Vec, SlidedownAmt, Mask, VL);
6464 
6465  // Now the vector is in the right position, extract our final subvector. This
6466  // should resolve to a COPY.
6467  Slidedown = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, SubVecVT, Slidedown,
6468  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT));
6469 
6470  // We might have bitcast from a mask type: cast back to the original type if
6471  // required.
6472  return DAG.getBitcast(Op.getSimpleValueType(), Slidedown);
6473 }
6474 
6475 // Lower step_vector to the vid instruction. Any non-identity step value must
6476 // be accounted for my manual expansion.
6477 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerSTEP_VECTOR(SDValue Op,
6478  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6479  SDLoc DL(Op);
6480  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
6481  assert(VT.isScalableVector() && "Expected scalable vector");
6482  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
6483  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultScalableVLOps(VT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
6484  SDValue StepVec = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VID_VL, DL, VT, Mask, VL);
6485  uint64_t StepValImm = Op.getConstantOperandVal(0);
6486  if (StepValImm != 1) {
6487  if (isPowerOf2_64(StepValImm)) {
6488  SDValue StepVal =
6489  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, VT, DAG.getUNDEF(VT),
6490  DAG.getConstant(Log2_64(StepValImm), DL, XLenVT), VL);
6491  StepVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, StepVec, StepVal);
6492  } else {
6493  SDValue StepVal = lowerScalarSplat(
6494  SDValue(), DAG.getConstant(StepValImm, DL, VT.getVectorElementType()),
6495  VL, VT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
6496  StepVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, DL, VT, StepVec, StepVal);
6497  }
6498  }
6499  return StepVec;
6500 }
6501 
6502 // Implement vector_reverse using vrgather.vv with indices determined by
6503 // subtracting the id of each element from (VLMAX-1). This will convert
6504 // the indices like so:
6505 // (0, 1,..., VLMAX-2, VLMAX-1) -> (VLMAX-1, VLMAX-2,..., 1, 0).
6506 // TODO: This code assumes VLMAX <= 65536 for LMUL=8 SEW=16.
6507 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerVECTOR_REVERSE(SDValue Op,
6508  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6509  SDLoc DL(Op);
6510  MVT VecVT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
6511  if (VecVT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1) {
6512  MVT WidenVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i8, VecVT.getVectorElementCount());
6513  SDValue Op1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, WidenVT, Op.getOperand(0));
6514  SDValue Op2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VECTOR_REVERSE, DL, WidenVT, Op1);
6515  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VecVT, Op2);
6516  }
6517  unsigned EltSize = VecVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
6518  unsigned MinSize = VecVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue();
6519  unsigned VectorBitsMax = Subtarget.getRealMaxVLen();
6520  unsigned MaxVLMAX =
6521  RISCVTargetLowering::computeVLMAX(VectorBitsMax, EltSize, MinSize);
6522 
6523  unsigned GatherOpc = RISCVISD::VRGATHER_VV_VL;
6524  MVT IntVT = VecVT.changeVectorElementTypeToInteger();
6525 
6526  // If this is SEW=8 and VLMAX is potentially more than 256, we need
6527  // to use vrgatherei16.vv.
6528  // TODO: It's also possible to use vrgatherei16.vv for other types to
6529  // decrease register width for the index calculation.
6530  if (MaxVLMAX > 256 && EltSize == 8) {
6531  // If this is LMUL=8, we have to split before can use vrgatherei16.vv.
6532  // Reverse each half, then reassemble them in reverse order.
6533  // NOTE: It's also possible that after splitting that VLMAX no longer
6534  // requires vrgatherei16.vv.
6535  if (MinSize == (8 * RISCV::RVVBitsPerBlock)) {
6536  auto [Lo, Hi] = DAG.SplitVectorOperand(Op.getNode(), 0);
6537  auto [LoVT, HiVT] = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(VecVT);
6538  Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::VECTOR_REVERSE, DL, LoVT, Lo);
6539  Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::VECTOR_REVERSE, DL, HiVT, Hi);
6540  // Reassemble the low and high pieces reversed.
6541  // FIXME: This is a CONCAT_VECTORS.
6542  SDValue Res =
6543  DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, VecVT, DAG.getUNDEF(VecVT), Hi,
6544  DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, DL));
6545  return DAG.getNode(
6546  ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, VecVT, Res, Lo,
6547  DAG.getIntPtrConstant(LoVT.getVectorMinNumElements(), DL));
6548  }
6549 
6550  // Just promote the int type to i16 which will double the LMUL.
6551  IntVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i16, VecVT.getVectorElementCount());
6552  GatherOpc = RISCVISD::VRGATHEREI16_VV_VL;
6553  }
6554 
6555  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
6556  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultScalableVLOps(VecVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
6557 
6558  // Calculate VLMAX-1 for the desired SEW.
6559  unsigned MinElts = VecVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
6560  SDValue VLMax = DAG.getNode(ISD::VSCALE, DL, XLenVT,
6561  getVLOp(MinElts, DL, DAG, Subtarget));
6562  SDValue VLMinus1 =
6563  DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, XLenVT, VLMax, DAG.getConstant(1, DL, XLenVT));
6564 
6565  // Splat VLMAX-1 taking care to handle SEW==64 on RV32.
6566  bool IsRV32E64 =
6567  !Subtarget.is64Bit() && IntVT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i64;
6568  SDValue SplatVL;
6569  if (!IsRV32E64)
6570  SplatVL = DAG.getSplatVector(IntVT, DL, VLMinus1);
6571  else
6572  SplatVL = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, IntVT, DAG.getUNDEF(IntVT),
6573  VLMinus1, DAG.getRegister(RISCV::X0, XLenVT));
6574 
6575  SDValue VID = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VID_VL, DL, IntVT, Mask, VL);
6576  SDValue Indices = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SUB_VL, DL, IntVT, SplatVL, VID,
6577  DAG.getUNDEF(IntVT), Mask, VL);
6578 
6579  return DAG.getNode(GatherOpc, DL, VecVT, Op.getOperand(0), Indices,
6580  DAG.getUNDEF(VecVT), Mask, VL);
6581 }
6582 
6583 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerVECTOR_SPLICE(SDValue Op,
6584  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6585  SDLoc DL(Op);
6586  SDValue V1 = Op.getOperand(0);
6587  SDValue V2 = Op.getOperand(1);
6588  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
6589  MVT VecVT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
6590 
6591  unsigned MinElts = VecVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
6592  SDValue VLMax = DAG.getNode(ISD::VSCALE, DL, XLenVT,
6593  getVLOp(MinElts, DL, DAG, Subtarget));
6594 
6595  int64_t ImmValue = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2))->getSExtValue();
6596  SDValue DownOffset, UpOffset;
6597  if (ImmValue >= 0) {
6598  // The operand is a TargetConstant, we need to rebuild it as a regular
6599  // constant.
6600  DownOffset = DAG.getConstant(ImmValue, DL, XLenVT);
6601  UpOffset = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, XLenVT, VLMax, DownOffset);
6602  } else {
6603  // The operand is a TargetConstant, we need to rebuild it as a regular
6604  // constant rather than negating the original operand.
6605  UpOffset = DAG.getConstant(-ImmValue, DL, XLenVT);
6606  DownOffset = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, XLenVT, VLMax, UpOffset);
6607  }
6608 
6609  SDValue TrueMask = getAllOnesMask(VecVT, VLMax, DL, DAG);
6610 
6611  SDValue SlideDown =
6612  getVSlidedown(DAG, Subtarget, DL, VecVT, DAG.getUNDEF(VecVT), V1,
6613  DownOffset, TrueMask, UpOffset);
6614  return getVSlideup(DAG, Subtarget, DL, VecVT, SlideDown, V2, UpOffset,
6615  TrueMask, DAG.getRegister(RISCV::X0, XLenVT),
6616  RISCVII::TAIL_AGNOSTIC);
6617 }
6618 
6619 SDValue
6620 RISCVTargetLowering::lowerFixedLengthVectorLoadToRVV(SDValue Op,
6621  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6622  SDLoc DL(Op);
6623  auto *Load = cast<LoadSDNode>(Op);
6624 
6625  assert(allowsMemoryAccessForAlignment(*DAG.getContext(), DAG.getDataLayout(),
6626  Load->getMemoryVT(),
6627  *Load->getMemOperand()) &&
6628  "Expecting a correctly-aligned load");
6629 
6630  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
6631  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
6632  MVT ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
6633 
6634  SDValue VL = getVLOp(VT.getVectorNumElements(), DL, DAG, Subtarget);
6635 
6636  bool IsMaskOp = VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1;
6637  SDValue IntID = DAG.getTargetConstant(
6638  IsMaskOp ? Intrinsic::riscv_vlm : Intrinsic::riscv_vle, DL, XLenVT);
6639  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Ops{Load->getChain(), IntID};
6640  if (!IsMaskOp)
6641  Ops.push_back(DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT));
6642  Ops.push_back(Load->getBasePtr());
6643  Ops.push_back(VL);
6644  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList({ContainerVT, MVT::Other});
6645  SDValue NewLoad =
6646  DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN, DL, VTs, Ops,
6647  Load->getMemoryVT(), Load->getMemOperand());
6648 
6649  SDValue Result = convertFromScalableVector(VT, NewLoad, DAG, Subtarget);
6650  return DAG.getMergeValues({Result, NewLoad.getValue(1)}, DL);
6651 }
6652 
6653 SDValue
6654 RISCVTargetLowering::lowerFixedLengthVectorStoreToRVV(SDValue Op,
6655  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6656  SDLoc DL(Op);
6657  auto *Store = cast<StoreSDNode>(Op);
6658 
6659  assert(allowsMemoryAccessForAlignment(*DAG.getContext(), DAG.getDataLayout(),
6660  Store->getMemoryVT(),
6661  *Store->getMemOperand()) &&
6662  "Expecting a correctly-aligned store");
6663 
6664  SDValue StoreVal = Store->getValue();
6665  MVT VT = StoreVal.getSimpleValueType();
6666  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
6667 
6668  // If the size less than a byte, we need to pad with zeros to make a byte.
6669  if (VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1 && VT.getVectorNumElements() < 8) {
6670  VT = MVT::v8i1;
6671  StoreVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, VT,
6672  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT), StoreVal,
6673  DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, DL));
6674  }
6675 
6676  MVT ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
6677 
6678  SDValue VL = getVLOp(VT.getVectorNumElements(), DL, DAG, Subtarget);
6679 
6680  SDValue NewValue =
6681  convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, StoreVal, DAG, Subtarget);
6682 
6683  bool IsMaskOp = VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1;
6684  SDValue IntID = DAG.getTargetConstant(
6685  IsMaskOp ? Intrinsic::riscv_vsm : Intrinsic::riscv_vse, DL, XLenVT);
6686  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(
6687  ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID, DL, DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other),
6688  {Store->getChain(), IntID, NewValue, Store->getBasePtr(), VL},
6689  Store->getMemoryVT(), Store->getMemOperand());
6690 }
6691 
6692 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerMaskedLoad(SDValue Op,
6693  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6694  SDLoc DL(Op);
6695  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
6696 
6697  const auto *MemSD = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
6698  EVT MemVT = MemSD->getMemoryVT();
6699  MachineMemOperand *MMO = MemSD->getMemOperand();
6700  SDValue Chain = MemSD->getChain();
6701  SDValue BasePtr = MemSD->getBasePtr();
6702 
6703  SDValue Mask, PassThru, VL;
6704  if (const auto *VPLoad = dyn_cast<VPLoadSDNode>(Op)) {
6705  Mask = VPLoad->getMask();
6706  PassThru = DAG.getUNDEF(VT);
6707  VL = VPLoad->getVectorLength();
6708  } else {
6709  const auto *MLoad = cast<MaskedLoadSDNode>(Op);
6710  Mask = MLoad->getMask();
6711  PassThru = MLoad->getPassThru();
6712  }
6713 
6714  bool IsUnmasked = ISD::isConstantSplatVectorAllOnes(Mask.getNode());
6715 
6716  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
6717 
6718  MVT ContainerVT = VT;
6719  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
6720  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
6721  PassThru = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, PassThru, DAG, Subtarget);
6722  if (!IsUnmasked) {
6723  MVT MaskVT = getMaskTypeFor(ContainerVT);
6724  Mask = convertToScalableVector(MaskVT, Mask, DAG, Subtarget);
6725  }
6726  }
6727 
6728  if (!VL)
6729  VL = getDefaultVLOps(VT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget).second;
6730 
6731  unsigned IntID =
6732  IsUnmasked ? Intrinsic::riscv_vle : Intrinsic::riscv_vle_mask;
6733  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops{Chain, DAG.getTargetConstant(IntID, DL, XLenVT)};
6734  if (IsUnmasked)
6735  Ops.push_back(DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT));
6736  else
6737  Ops.push_back(PassThru);
6738  Ops.push_back(BasePtr);
6739  if (!IsUnmasked)
6740  Ops.push_back(Mask);
6741  Ops.push_back(VL);
6742  if (!IsUnmasked)
6743  Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetConstant(RISCVII::TAIL_AGNOSTIC, DL, XLenVT));
6744 
6745  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList({ContainerVT, MVT::Other});
6746 
6747  SDValue Result =
6748  DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN, DL, VTs, Ops, MemVT, MMO);
6749  Chain = Result.getValue(1);
6750 
6751  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector())
6752  Result = convertFromScalableVector(VT, Result, DAG, Subtarget);
6753 
6754  return DAG.getMergeValues({Result, Chain}, DL);
6755 }
6756 
6757 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerMaskedStore(SDValue Op,
6758  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6759  SDLoc DL(Op);
6760 
6761  const auto *MemSD = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
6762  EVT MemVT = MemSD->getMemoryVT();
6763  MachineMemOperand *MMO = MemSD->getMemOperand();
6764  SDValue Chain = MemSD->getChain();
6765  SDValue BasePtr = MemSD->getBasePtr();
6766  SDValue Val, Mask, VL;
6767 
6768  if (const auto *VPStore = dyn_cast<VPStoreSDNode>(Op)) {
6769  Val = VPStore->getValue();
6770  Mask = VPStore->getMask();
6771  VL = VPStore->getVectorLength();
6772  } else {
6773  const auto *MStore = cast<MaskedStoreSDNode>(Op);
6774  Val = MStore->getValue();
6775  Mask = MStore->getMask();
6776  }
6777 
6778  bool IsUnmasked = ISD::isConstantSplatVectorAllOnes(Mask.getNode());
6779 
6780  MVT VT = Val.getSimpleValueType();
6781  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
6782 
6783  MVT ContainerVT = VT;
6784  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
6785  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
6786 
6787  Val = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Val, DAG, Subtarget);
6788  if (!IsUnmasked) {
6789  MVT MaskVT = getMaskTypeFor(ContainerVT);
6790  Mask = convertToScalableVector(MaskVT, Mask, DAG, Subtarget);
6791  }
6792  }
6793 
6794  if (!VL)
6795  VL = getDefaultVLOps(VT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget).second;
6796 
6797  unsigned IntID =
6798  IsUnmasked ? Intrinsic::riscv_vse : Intrinsic::riscv_vse_mask;
6799  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops{Chain, DAG.getTargetConstant(IntID, DL, XLenVT)};
6800  Ops.push_back(Val);
6801  Ops.push_back(BasePtr);
6802  if (!IsUnmasked)
6803  Ops.push_back(Mask);
6804  Ops.push_back(VL);
6805 
6806  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID, DL,
6807  DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other), Ops, MemVT, MMO);
6808 }

6810 SDValue
6811 RISCVTargetLowering::lowerFixedLengthVectorSetccToRVV(SDValue Op,
6812  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6813  MVT InVT = Op.getOperand(0).getSimpleValueType();
6814  MVT ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(InVT);
6815 
6816  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
6817 
6818  SDValue Op1 =
6819  convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Op.getOperand(0), DAG, Subtarget);
6820  SDValue Op2 =
6821  convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Op.getOperand(1), DAG, Subtarget);
6822 
6823  SDLoc DL(Op);
6824  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(VT.getVectorNumElements(), ContainerVT, DL,
6825  DAG, Subtarget);
6826  MVT MaskVT = getMaskTypeFor(ContainerVT);
6827 
6828  SDValue Cmp =
6829  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SETCC_VL, DL, MaskVT,
6830  {Op1, Op2, Op.getOperand(2), DAG.getUNDEF(MaskVT), Mask, VL});
6831 
6832  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, Cmp, DAG, Subtarget);
6833 }

6835 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerFixedLengthVectorLogicOpToRVV(
6836  SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, unsigned MaskOpc, unsigned VecOpc) const {
6837  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
6838 
6839  if (VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
6840  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, MaskOpc, /*HasMergeOp*/ false,
6841  /*HasMask*/ false);
6842 
6843  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, VecOpc, /*HasMergeOp*/ true);

6846 SDValue
6847 RISCVTargetLowering::lowerFixedLengthVectorShiftToRVV(SDValue Op,
6848  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6849  unsigned Opc;
6850  switch (Op.getOpcode()) {
6851  default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected opcode!");
6852  case ISD::SHL: Opc = RISCVISD::SHL_VL; break;
6853  case ISD::SRA: Opc = RISCVISD::SRA_VL; break;
6854  case ISD::SRL: Opc = RISCVISD::SRL_VL; break;
6855  }
6856 
6857  return lowerToScalableOp(Op, DAG, Opc, /*HasMergeOp*/ true);
6858 }

6860 // Lower vector ABS to smax(X, sub(0, X)).
6861 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerABS(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6862  SDLoc DL(Op);
6863  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
6864  SDValue X = Op.getOperand(0);
6865 
6866  assert((Op.getOpcode() == ISD::VP_ABS || VT.isFixedLengthVector()) &&
6867  "Unexpected type for ISD::ABS");
6868 
6869  MVT ContainerVT = VT;
6870  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
6871  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
6872  X = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, X, DAG, Subtarget);
6873  }
6874 
6875  SDValue Mask, VL;
6876  if (Op->getOpcode() == ISD::VP_ABS) {
6877  Mask = Op->getOperand(1);
6878  VL = Op->getOperand(2);
6879  } else
6880  std::tie(Mask, VL) = getDefaultVLOps(VT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
6881 
6882  SDValue SplatZero = DAG.getNode(
6883  RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, ContainerVT, DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT),
6884  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, Subtarget.getXLenVT()), VL);
6885  SDValue NegX = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SUB_VL, DL, ContainerVT, SplatZero, X,
6886  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), Mask, VL);
6887  SDValue Max = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SMAX_VL, DL, ContainerVT, X, NegX,
6888  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), Mask, VL);
6889 
6890  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector())
6891  Max = convertFromScalableVector(VT, Max, DAG, Subtarget);
6892  return Max;
6893 }

6895 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerFixedLengthVectorFCOPYSIGNToRVV(
6896  SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6897  SDLoc DL(Op);
6898  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
6899  SDValue Mag = Op.getOperand(0);
6900  SDValue Sign = Op.getOperand(1);
6901  assert(Mag.getValueType() == Sign.getValueType() &&
6902  "Can only handle COPYSIGN with matching types.");
6903 
6904  MVT ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
6905  Mag = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Mag, DAG, Subtarget);
6906  Sign = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Sign, DAG, Subtarget);
6907 
6908  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(VT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
6909 
6910  SDValue CopySign = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FCOPYSIGN_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Mag,
6911  Sign, DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), Mask, VL);
6912 
6913  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, CopySign, DAG, Subtarget);
6914 }

6916 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerFixedLengthVectorSelectToRVV(
6917  SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6918  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
6919  MVT ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
6920 
6921  MVT I1ContainerVT =
6922  MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i1, ContainerVT.getVectorElementCount());
6923 
6924  SDValue CC =
6925  convertToScalableVector(I1ContainerVT, Op.getOperand(0), DAG, Subtarget);
6926  SDValue Op1 =
6927  convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Op.getOperand(1), DAG, Subtarget);
6928  SDValue Op2 =
6929  convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Op.getOperand(2), DAG, Subtarget);
6930 
6931  SDLoc DL(Op);
6932  SDValue VL = getDefaultVLOps(VT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget).second;
6933 
6934  SDValue Select =
6935  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VSELECT_VL, DL, ContainerVT, CC, Op1, Op2, VL);
6936 
6937  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, Select, DAG, Subtarget);
6938 }
6939 
6940 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerToScalableOp(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
6941  unsigned NewOpc, bool HasMergeOp,
6942  bool HasMask) const {
6943  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
6944  MVT ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
6945 
6946  // Create list of operands by converting existing ones to scalable types.
6947  SmallVector<SDValue, 6> Ops;
6948  for (const SDValue &V : Op->op_values()) {
6949  assert(!isa<VTSDNode>(V) && "Unexpected VTSDNode node!");
6950 
6951  // Pass through non-vector operands.
6952  if (!V.getValueType().isVector()) {
6953  Ops.push_back(V);
6954  continue;
6955  }
6956 
6957  // "cast" fixed length vector to a scalable vector.
6958  assert(useRVVForFixedLengthVectorVT(V.getSimpleValueType()) &&
6959  "Only fixed length vectors are supported!");
6960  Ops.push_back(convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, V, DAG, Subtarget));
6961  }
6962 
6963  SDLoc DL(Op);
6964  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(VT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
6965  if (HasMergeOp)
6966  Ops.push_back(DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT));
6967  if (HasMask)
6968  Ops.push_back(Mask);
6969  Ops.push_back(VL);
6970 
6971  SDValue ScalableRes =
6972  DAG.getNode(NewOpc, DL, ContainerVT, Ops, Op->getFlags());
6973  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, ScalableRes, DAG, Subtarget);
6974 }
6975 
6976 // Lower a VP_* ISD node to the corresponding RISCVISD::*_VL node:
6977 // * Operands of each node are assumed to be in the same order.
6978 // * The EVL operand is promoted from i32 to i64 on RV64.
6979 // * Fixed-length vectors are converted to their scalable-vector container
6980 // types.
6981 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerVPOp(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
6982  unsigned RISCVISDOpc,
6983  bool HasMergeOp) const {
6984  SDLoc DL(Op);
6985  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
6986  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Ops;
6987 
6988  MVT ContainerVT = VT;
6989  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector())
6990  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
6991 
6992  for (const auto &OpIdx : enumerate(Op->ops())) {
6993  SDValue V = OpIdx.value();
6994  assert(!isa<VTSDNode>(V) && "Unexpected VTSDNode node!");
6995  // Add dummy merge value before the mask.
6996  if (HasMergeOp && *ISD::getVPMaskIdx(Op.getOpcode()) == OpIdx.index())
6997  Ops.push_back(DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT));
6998  // Pass through operands which aren't fixed-length vectors.
6999  if (!V.getValueType().isFixedLengthVector()) {
7000  Ops.push_back(V);
7001  continue;
7002  }
7003  // "cast" fixed length vector to a scalable vector.
7004  MVT OpVT = V.getSimpleValueType();
7005  MVT ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(OpVT);
7006  assert(useRVVForFixedLengthVectorVT(OpVT) &&
7007  "Only fixed length vectors are supported!");
7008  Ops.push_back(convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, V, DAG, Subtarget));
7009  }
7010 
7011  if (!VT.isFixedLengthVector())
7012  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISDOpc, DL, VT, Ops, Op->getFlags());
7013 
7014  SDValue VPOp = DAG.getNode(RISCVISDOpc, DL, ContainerVT, Ops, Op->getFlags());
7015 
7016  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, VPOp, DAG, Subtarget);
7017 }
7018 
7019 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerVPExtMaskOp(SDValue Op,
7020  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7021  SDLoc DL(Op);
7022  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
7023 
7024  SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
7025  // NOTE: Mask is dropped.
7026  SDValue VL = Op.getOperand(2);
7027 
7028  MVT ContainerVT = VT;
7029  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
7030  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
7031  MVT SrcVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i1, ContainerVT.getVectorElementCount());
7032  Src = convertToScalableVector(SrcVT, Src, DAG, Subtarget);
7033  }
7034 
7035  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
7036  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT);
7037  SDValue ZeroSplat = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, ContainerVT,
7038  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), Zero, VL);
7039 
7040  SDValue SplatValue = DAG.getConstant(
7041  Op.getOpcode() == ISD::VP_ZERO_EXTEND ? 1 : -1, DL, XLenVT);
7042  SDValue Splat = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, ContainerVT,
7043  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), SplatValue, VL);
7044 
7045  SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VSELECT_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Src,
7046  Splat, ZeroSplat, VL);
7047  if (!VT.isFixedLengthVector())
7048  return Result;
7049  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, Result, DAG, Subtarget);
7050 }
7051 
7052 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerVPSetCCMaskOp(SDValue Op,
7053  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7054  SDLoc DL(Op);
7055  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
7056 
7057  SDValue Op1 = Op.getOperand(0);
7058  SDValue Op2 = Op.getOperand(1);
7059  ISD::CondCode Condition = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2))->get();
7060  // NOTE: Mask is dropped.
7061  SDValue VL = Op.getOperand(4);
7062 
7063  MVT ContainerVT = VT;
7064  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
7065  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
7066  Op1 = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Op1, DAG, Subtarget);
7067  Op2 = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Op2, DAG, Subtarget);
7068  }
7069 
7070  SDValue Result;
7071  SDValue AllOneMask = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMSET_VL, DL, ContainerVT, VL);
7072 
7073  switch (Condition) {
7074  default:
7075  break;
7076  // X != Y --> (X^Y)
7077  case ISD::SETNE:
7078  Result = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMXOR_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Op1, Op2, VL);
7079  break;
7080  // X == Y --> ~(X^Y)
7081  case ISD::SETEQ: {
7082  SDValue Temp =
7083  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMXOR_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Op1, Op2, VL);
7084  Result =
7085  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMXOR_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Temp, AllOneMask, VL);
7086  break;
7087  }
7088  // X >s Y --> X == 0 & Y == 1 --> ~X & Y
7089  // X <u Y --> X == 0 & Y == 1 --> ~X & Y
7090  case ISD::SETGT:
7091  case ISD::SETULT: {
7092  SDValue Temp =
7093  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMXOR_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Op1, AllOneMask, VL);
7094  Result = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMAND_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Temp, Op2, VL);
7095  break;
7096  }
7097  // X <s Y --> X == 1 & Y == 0 --> ~Y & X
7098  // X >u Y --> X == 1 & Y == 0 --> ~Y & X
7099  case ISD::SETLT:
7100  case ISD::SETUGT: {
7101  SDValue Temp =
7102  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMXOR_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Op2, AllOneMask, VL);
7103  Result = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMAND_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Op1, Temp, VL);
7104  break;
7105  }
7106  // X >=s Y --> X == 0 | Y == 1 --> ~X | Y
7107  // X <=u Y --> X == 0 | Y == 1 --> ~X | Y
7108  case ISD::SETGE:
7109  case ISD::SETULE: {
7110  SDValue Temp =
7111  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMXOR_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Op1, AllOneMask, VL);
7112  Result = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMXOR_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Temp, Op2, VL);
7113  break;
7114  }
7115  // X <=s Y --> X == 1 | Y == 0 --> ~Y | X
7116  // X >=u Y --> X == 1 | Y == 0 --> ~Y | X
7117  case ISD::SETLE:
7118  case ISD::SETUGE: {
7119  SDValue Temp =
7120  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMXOR_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Op2, AllOneMask, VL);
7121  Result = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMXOR_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Temp, Op1, VL);
7122  break;
7123  }
7124  }
7125 
7126  if (!VT.isFixedLengthVector())
7127  return Result;
7128  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, Result, DAG, Subtarget);
7129 }
7130 
7131 // Lower Floating-Point/Integer Type-Convert VP SDNodes
7132 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerVPFPIntConvOp(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
7133  unsigned RISCVISDOpc) const {
7134  SDLoc DL(Op);
7135 
7136  SDValue Src = Op.getOperand(0);
7137  SDValue Mask = Op.getOperand(1);
7138  SDValue VL = Op.getOperand(2);
7139 
7140  MVT DstVT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
7141  MVT SrcVT = Src.getSimpleValueType();
7142  if (DstVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
7143  DstVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(DstVT);
7144  SrcVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(SrcVT);
7145  Src = convertToScalableVector(SrcVT, Src, DAG, Subtarget);
7146  MVT MaskVT = getMaskTypeFor(DstVT);
7147  Mask = convertToScalableVector(MaskVT, Mask, DAG, Subtarget);
7148  }
7149 
7150  unsigned DstEltSize = DstVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
7151  unsigned SrcEltSize = SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
7152 
7153  SDValue Result;
7154  if (DstEltSize >= SrcEltSize) { // Single-width and widening conversion.
7155  if (SrcVT.isInteger()) {
7156  assert(DstVT.isFloatingPoint() && "Wrong input/output vector types");
7157 
7158  unsigned RISCVISDExtOpc = RISCVISDOpc == RISCVISD::SINT_TO_FP_VL
7159  ? RISCVISD::VSEXT_VL
7160  : RISCVISD::VZEXT_VL;
7161 
7162  // Do we need to do any pre-widening before converting?
7163  if (SrcEltSize == 1) {
7164  MVT IntVT = DstVT.changeVectorElementTypeToInteger();
7165  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
7166  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT);
7167  SDValue ZeroSplat = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, IntVT,
7168  DAG.getUNDEF(IntVT), Zero, VL);
7169  SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(
7170  RISCVISDExtOpc == RISCVISD::VZEXT_VL ? 1 : -1, DL, XLenVT);
7171  SDValue OneSplat = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, IntVT,
7172  DAG.getUNDEF(IntVT), One, VL);
7173  Src = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VSELECT_VL, DL, IntVT, Src, OneSplat,
7174  ZeroSplat, VL);
7175  } else if (DstEltSize > (2 * SrcEltSize)) {
7176  // Widen before converting.
7177  MVT IntVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::getIntegerVT(DstEltSize / 2),
7178  DstVT.getVectorElementCount());
7179  Src = DAG.getNode(RISCVISDExtOpc, DL, IntVT, Src, Mask, VL);
7180  }
7181 
7182  Result = DAG.getNode(RISCVISDOpc, DL, DstVT, Src, Mask, VL);
7183  } else {
7184  assert(SrcVT.isFloatingPoint() && DstVT.isInteger() &&
7185  "Wrong input/output vector types");
7186 
7187  // Convert f16 to f32 then convert f32 to i64.
7188  if (DstEltSize > (2 * SrcEltSize)) {
7189  assert(SrcVT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::f16 && "Unexpected type!");
7190  MVT InterimFVT =
7191  MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::f32, DstVT.getVectorElementCount());
7192  Src =
7193  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FP_EXTEND_VL, DL, InterimFVT, Src, Mask, VL);
7194  }
7195 
7196  Result = DAG.getNode(RISCVISDOpc, DL, DstVT, Src, Mask, VL);
7197  }
7198  } else { // Narrowing + Conversion
7199  if (SrcVT.isInteger()) {
7200  assert(DstVT.isFloatingPoint() && "Wrong input/output vector types");
7201  // First do a narrowing convert to an FP type half the size, then round
7202  // the FP type to a small FP type if needed.
7203 
7204  MVT InterimFVT = DstVT;
7205  if (SrcEltSize > (2 * DstEltSize)) {
7206  assert(SrcEltSize == (4 * DstEltSize) && "Unexpected types!");
7207  assert(DstVT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::f16 && "Unexpected type!");
7208  InterimFVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::f32, DstVT.getVectorElementCount());
7209  }
7210 
7211  Result = DAG.getNode(RISCVISDOpc, DL, InterimFVT, Src, Mask, VL);
7212 
7213  if (InterimFVT != DstVT) {
7214  Src = Result;
7215  Result = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FP_ROUND_VL, DL, DstVT, Src, Mask, VL);
7216  }
7217  } else {
7218  assert(SrcVT.isFloatingPoint() && DstVT.isInteger() &&
7219  "Wrong input/output vector types");
7220  // First do a narrowing conversion to an integer half the size, then
7221  // truncate if needed.
7222 
7223  if (DstEltSize == 1) {
7224  // First convert to the same size integer, then convert to mask using
7225  // setcc.
7226  assert(SrcEltSize >= 16 && "Unexpected FP type!");
7227  MVT InterimIVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::getIntegerVT(SrcEltSize),
7228  DstVT.getVectorElementCount());
7229  Result = DAG.getNode(RISCVISDOpc, DL, InterimIVT, Src, Mask, VL);
7230 
7231  // Compare the integer result to 0. The integer should be 0 or 1/-1,
7232  // otherwise the conversion was undefined.
7233  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
7234  SDValue SplatZero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT);
7235  SplatZero = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, InterimIVT,
7236  DAG.getUNDEF(InterimIVT), SplatZero, VL);
7237  Result = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SETCC_VL, DL, DstVT,
7238  {Result, SplatZero, DAG.getCondCode(ISD::SETNE),
7239  DAG.getUNDEF(DstVT), Mask, VL});
7240  } else {
7241  MVT InterimIVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::getIntegerVT(SrcEltSize / 2),
7242  DstVT.getVectorElementCount());
7243 
7244  Result = DAG.getNode(RISCVISDOpc, DL, InterimIVT, Src, Mask, VL);
7245 
7246  while (InterimIVT != DstVT) {
7247  SrcEltSize /= 2;
7248  Src = Result;
7249  InterimIVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::getIntegerVT(SrcEltSize / 2),
7250  DstVT.getVectorElementCount());
7251  Result = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::TRUNCATE_VECTOR_VL, DL, InterimIVT,
7252  Src, Mask, VL);
7253  }
7254  }
7255  }
7256  }
7257 
7258  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
7259  if (!VT.isFixedLengthVector())
7260  return Result;
7261  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, Result, DAG, Subtarget);
7262 }
7263 
7264 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerLogicVPOp(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
7265  unsigned MaskOpc,
7266  unsigned VecOpc) const {
7267  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
7268  if (VT.getVectorElementType() != MVT::i1)
7269  return lowerVPOp(Op, DAG, VecOpc, true);
7270 
7271  // It is safe to drop mask parameter as masked-off elements are undef.
7272  SDValue Op1 = Op->getOperand(0);
7273  SDValue Op2 = Op->getOperand(1);
7274  SDValue VL = Op->getOperand(3);
7275 
7276  MVT ContainerVT = VT;
7277  const bool IsFixed = VT.isFixedLengthVector();
7278  if (IsFixed) {
7279  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
7280  Op1 = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Op1, DAG, Subtarget);
7281  Op2 = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Op2, DAG, Subtarget);
7282  }
7283 
7284  SDLoc DL(Op);
7285  SDValue Val = DAG.getNode(MaskOpc, DL, ContainerVT, Op1, Op2, VL);
7286  if (!IsFixed)
7287  return Val;
7288  return convertFromScalableVector(VT, Val, DAG, Subtarget);
7289 }
7290 
7291 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerVPStridedLoad(SDValue Op,
7292  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7293  SDLoc DL(Op);
7294  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
7295  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
7296  MVT ContainerVT = VT;
7297  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector())
7298  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
7299 
7300  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList({ContainerVT, MVT::Other});
7301 
7302  auto *VPNode = cast<VPStridedLoadSDNode>(Op);
7303  // Check if the mask is known to be all ones
7304  SDValue Mask = VPNode->getMask();
7305  bool IsUnmasked = ISD::isConstantSplatVectorAllOnes(Mask.getNode());
7306 
7307  SDValue IntID = DAG.getTargetConstant(IsUnmasked ? Intrinsic::riscv_vlse
7308  : Intrinsic::riscv_vlse_mask,
7309  DL, XLenVT);
7310  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops{VPNode->getChain(), IntID,
7311  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), VPNode->getBasePtr(),
7312  VPNode->getStride()};
7313  if (!IsUnmasked) {
7314  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
7315  MVT MaskVT = ContainerVT.changeVectorElementType(MVT::i1);
7316  Mask = convertToScalableVector(MaskVT, Mask, DAG, Subtarget);
7317  }
7318  Ops.push_back(Mask);
7319  }
7320  Ops.push_back(VPNode->getVectorLength());
7321  if (!IsUnmasked) {
7322  SDValue Policy = DAG.getTargetConstant(RISCVII::TAIL_AGNOSTIC, DL, XLenVT);
7323  Ops.push_back(Policy);
7324  }
7325 
7326  SDValue Result =
7327  DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN, DL, VTs, Ops,
7328  VPNode->getMemoryVT(), VPNode->getMemOperand());
7329  SDValue Chain = Result.getValue(1);
7330 
7331  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector())
7332  Result = convertFromScalableVector(VT, Result, DAG, Subtarget);
7333 
7334  return DAG.getMergeValues({Result, Chain}, DL);
7335 }
7336 
7337 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerVPStridedStore(SDValue Op,
7338  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7339  SDLoc DL(Op);
7340  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
7341 
7342  auto *VPNode = cast<VPStridedStoreSDNode>(Op);
7343  SDValue StoreVal = VPNode->getValue();
7344  MVT VT = StoreVal.getSimpleValueType();
7345  MVT ContainerVT = VT;
7346  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
7347  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
7348  StoreVal = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, StoreVal, DAG, Subtarget);
7349  }
7350 
7351  // Check if the mask is known to be all ones
7352  SDValue Mask = VPNode->getMask();
7353  bool IsUnmasked = ISD::isConstantSplatVectorAllOnes(Mask.getNode());
7354 
7355  SDValue IntID = DAG.getTargetConstant(IsUnmasked ? Intrinsic::riscv_vsse
7356  : Intrinsic::riscv_vsse_mask,
7357  DL, XLenVT);
7358  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops{VPNode->getChain(), IntID, StoreVal,
7359  VPNode->getBasePtr(), VPNode->getStride()};
7360  if (!IsUnmasked) {
7361  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
7362  MVT MaskVT = ContainerVT.changeVectorElementType(MVT::i1);
7363  Mask = convertToScalableVector(MaskVT, Mask, DAG, Subtarget);
7364  }
7365  Ops.push_back(Mask);
7366  }
7367  Ops.push_back(VPNode->getVectorLength());
7368 
7369  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID, DL, VPNode->getVTList(),
7370  Ops, VPNode->getMemoryVT(),
7371  VPNode->getMemOperand());
7372 }
7373 
7374 // Custom lower MGATHER/VP_GATHER to a legalized form for RVV. It will then be
7375 // matched to a RVV indexed load. The RVV indexed load instructions only
7376 // support the "unsigned unscaled" addressing mode; indices are implicitly
7377 // zero-extended or truncated to XLEN and are treated as byte offsets. Any
7378 // signed or scaled indexing is extended to the XLEN value type and scaled
7379 // accordingly.
7380 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerMaskedGather(SDValue Op,
7381  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7382  SDLoc DL(Op);
7383  MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType();
7384 
7385  const auto *MemSD = cast<MemSDNode>(Op.getNode());
7386  EVT MemVT = MemSD->getMemoryVT();
7387  MachineMemOperand *MMO = MemSD->getMemOperand();
7388  SDValue Chain = MemSD->getChain();
7389  SDValue BasePtr = MemSD->getBasePtr();
7390 
7391  ISD::LoadExtType LoadExtType;
7392  SDValue Index, Mask, PassThru, VL;
7393 
7394  if (auto *VPGN = dyn_cast<VPGatherSDNode>(Op.getNode())) {
7395  Index = VPGN->getIndex();
7396  Mask = VPGN->getMask();
7397  PassThru = DAG.getUNDEF(VT);
7398  VL = VPGN->getVectorLength();
7399  // VP doesn't support extending loads.
7400  LoadExtType = ISD::NON_EXTLOAD;
7401  } else {
7402  // Else it must be a MGATHER.
7403  auto *MGN = cast<MaskedGatherSDNode>(Op.getNode());
7404  Index = MGN->getIndex();
7405  Mask = MGN->getMask();
7406  PassThru = MGN->getPassThru();
7407  LoadExtType = MGN->getExtensionType();
7408  }
7409 
7410  MVT IndexVT = Index.getSimpleValueType();
7411  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
7412 
7413  assert(VT.getVectorElementCount() == IndexVT.getVectorElementCount() &&
7414  "Unexpected VTs!");
7415  assert(BasePtr.getSimpleValueType() == XLenVT && "Unexpected pointer type");
7416  // Targets have to explicitly opt-in for extending vector loads.
7417  assert(LoadExtType == ISD::NON_EXTLOAD &&
7418  "Unexpected extending MGATHER/VP_GATHER");
7419  (void)LoadExtType;
7420 
7421  // If the mask is known to be all ones, optimize to an unmasked intrinsic;
7422  // the selection of the masked intrinsics doesn't do this for us.
7423  bool IsUnmasked = ISD::isConstantSplatVectorAllOnes(Mask.getNode());
7424 
7425  MVT ContainerVT = VT;
7426  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
7427  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
7428  IndexVT = MVT::getVectorVT(IndexVT.getVectorElementType(),
7429  ContainerVT.getVectorElementCount());
7430 
7431  Index = convertToScalableVector(IndexVT, Index, DAG, Subtarget);
7432 
7433  if (!IsUnmasked) {
7434  MVT MaskVT = getMaskTypeFor(ContainerVT);
7435  Mask = convertToScalableVector(MaskVT, Mask, DAG, Subtarget);
7436  PassThru = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, PassThru, DAG, Subtarget);
7437  }
7438  }
7439 
7440  if (!VL)
7441  VL = getDefaultVLOps(VT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget).second;
7442 
7443  if (XLenVT == MVT::i32 && IndexVT.getVectorElementType().bitsGT(XLenVT)) {
7444  IndexVT = IndexVT.changeVectorElementType(XLenVT);
7445  SDValue TrueMask = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMSET_VL, DL, Mask.getValueType(),
7446  VL);
7447  Index = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::TRUNCATE_VECTOR_VL, DL, IndexVT, Index,
7448  TrueMask, VL);
7449  }
7450 
7451  unsigned IntID =
7452  IsUnmasked ? Intrinsic::riscv_vluxei : Intrinsic::riscv_vluxei_mask;
7453  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops{Chain, DAG.getTargetConstant(IntID, DL, XLenVT)};
7454  if (IsUnmasked)
7455  Ops.push_back(DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT));
7456  else
7457  Ops.push_back(PassThru);
7458  Ops.push_back(BasePtr);
7459  Ops.push_back(Index);
7460  if (!IsUnmasked)
7461  Ops.push_back(Mask);
7462  Ops.push_back(VL);
7463  if (!IsUnmasked)
7464  Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetConstant(RISCVII::TAIL_AGNOSTIC, DL, XLenVT));
7465 
7466  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList({ContainerVT, MVT::Other});
7467  SDValue Result =
7468  DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN, DL, VTs, Ops, MemVT, MMO);
7469  Chain = Result.getValue(1);
7470 
7471  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector())
7472  Result = convertFromScalableVector(VT, Result, DAG, Subtarget);
7473 
7474  return DAG.getMergeValues({Result, Chain}, DL);
7475 }
7476 
7477 // Custom lower MSCATTER/VP_SCATTER to a legalized form for RVV. It will then be
7478 // matched to a RVV indexed store. The RVV indexed store instructions only
7479 // support the "unsigned unscaled" addressing mode; indices are implicitly
7480 // zero-extended or truncated to XLEN and are treated as byte offsets. Any
7481 // signed or scaled indexing is extended to the XLEN value type and scaled
7482 // accordingly.
7483 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerMaskedScatter(SDValue Op,
7484  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7485  SDLoc DL(Op);
7486  const auto *MemSD = cast<MemSDNode>(Op.getNode());
7487  EVT MemVT = MemSD->getMemoryVT();
7488  MachineMemOperand *MMO = MemSD->getMemOperand();
7489  SDValue Chain = MemSD->getChain();
7490  SDValue BasePtr = MemSD->getBasePtr();
7491 
7492  bool IsTruncatingStore = false;
7493  SDValue Index, Mask, Val, VL;
7494 
7495  if (auto *VPSN = dyn_cast<VPScatterSDNode>(Op.getNode())) {
7496  Index = VPSN->getIndex();
7497  Mask = VPSN->getMask();
7498  Val = VPSN->getValue();
7499  VL = VPSN->getVectorLength();
7500  // VP doesn't support truncating stores.
7501  IsTruncatingStore = false;
7502  } else {
7503  // Else it must be a MSCATTER.
7504  auto *MSN = cast<MaskedScatterSDNode>(Op.getNode());
7505  Index = MSN->getIndex();
7506  Mask = MSN->getMask();
7507  Val = MSN->getValue();
7508  IsTruncatingStore = MSN->isTruncatingStore();
7509  }
7510 
7511  MVT VT = Val.getSimpleValueType();
7512  MVT IndexVT = Index.getSimpleValueType();
7513  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
7514 
7515  assert(VT.getVectorElementCount() == IndexVT.getVectorElementCount() &&
7516  "Unexpected VTs!");
7517  assert(BasePtr.getSimpleValueType() == XLenVT && "Unexpected pointer type");
7518  // Targets have to explicitly opt-in for extending vector loads and
7519  // truncating vector stores.
7520  assert(!IsTruncatingStore && "Unexpected truncating MSCATTER/VP_SCATTER");
7521  (void)IsTruncatingStore;
7522 
7523  // If the mask is known to be all ones, optimize to an unmasked intrinsic;
7524  // the selection of the masked intrinsics doesn't do this for us.
7525  bool IsUnmasked = ISD::isConstantSplatVectorAllOnes(Mask.getNode());
7526 
7527  MVT ContainerVT = VT;
7528  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
7529  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT);
7530  IndexVT = MVT::getVectorVT(IndexVT.getVectorElementType(),
7531  ContainerVT.getVectorElementCount());
7532 
7533  Index = convertToScalableVector(IndexVT, Index, DAG, Subtarget);
7534  Val = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Val, DAG, Subtarget);
7535 
7536  if (!IsUnmasked) {
7537  MVT MaskVT = getMaskTypeFor(ContainerVT);
7538  Mask = convertToScalableVector(MaskVT, Mask, DAG, Subtarget);
7539  }
7540  }
7541 
7542  if (!VL)
7543  VL = getDefaultVLOps(VT, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget).second;
7544 
7545  if (XLenVT == MVT::i32 && IndexVT.getVectorElementType().bitsGT(XLenVT)) {
7546  IndexVT = IndexVT.changeVectorElementType(XLenVT);
7547  SDValue TrueMask = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMSET_VL, DL, Mask.getValueType(),
7548  VL);
7549  Index = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::TRUNCATE_VECTOR_VL, DL, IndexVT, Index,
7550  TrueMask, VL);
7551  }
7552 
7553  unsigned IntID =
7554  IsUnmasked ? Intrinsic::riscv_vsoxei : Intrinsic::riscv_vsoxei_mask;
7555  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops{Chain, DAG.getTargetConstant(IntID, DL, XLenVT)};
7556  Ops.push_back(Val);
7557  Ops.push_back(BasePtr);
7558  Ops.push_back(Index);
7559  if (!IsUnmasked)
7560  Ops.push_back(Mask);
7561  Ops.push_back(VL);
7562 
7563  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID, DL,
7564  DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other), Ops, MemVT, MMO);
7565 }
7566 
7567 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerGET_ROUNDING(SDValue Op,
7568  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7569  const MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
7570  SDLoc DL(Op);
7571  SDValue Chain = Op->getOperand(0);
7572  SDValue SysRegNo = DAG.getTargetConstant(
7573  RISCVSysReg::lookupSysRegByName("FRM")->Encoding, DL, XLenVT);
7574  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(XLenVT, MVT::Other);
7575  SDValue RM = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::READ_CSR, DL, VTs, Chain, SysRegNo);
7576 
7577  // Encoding used for rounding mode in RISCV differs from that used in
7578  // FLT_ROUNDS. To convert it the RISCV rounding mode is used as an index in a
7579  // table, which consists of a sequence of 4-bit fields, each representing
7580  // corresponding FLT_ROUNDS mode.
7581  static const int Table =
7582  (int(RoundingMode::NearestTiesToEven) << 4 * RISCVFPRndMode::RNE) |
7583  (int(RoundingMode::TowardZero) << 4 * RISCVFPRndMode::RTZ) |
7584  (int(RoundingMode::TowardNegative) << 4 * RISCVFPRndMode::RDN) |
7585  (int(RoundingMode::TowardPositive) << 4 * RISCVFPRndMode::RUP) |
7586  (int(RoundingMode::NearestTiesToAway) << 4 * RISCVFPRndMode::RMM);
7587 
7588  SDValue Shift =
7589  DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, XLenVT, RM, DAG.getConstant(2, DL, XLenVT));
7590  SDValue Shifted = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, XLenVT,
7591  DAG.getConstant(Table, DL, XLenVT), Shift);
7592  SDValue Masked = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, XLenVT, Shifted,
7593  DAG.getConstant(7, DL, XLenVT));
7594 
7595  return DAG.getMergeValues({Masked, Chain}, DL);
7596 }
7597 
7598 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerSET_ROUNDING(SDValue Op,
7599  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7600  const MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
7601  SDLoc DL(Op);
7602  SDValue Chain = Op->getOperand(0);
7603  SDValue RMValue = Op->getOperand(1);
7604  SDValue SysRegNo = DAG.getTargetConstant(
7605  RISCVSysReg::lookupSysRegByName("FRM")->Encoding, DL, XLenVT);
7606 
7607  // Encoding used for rounding mode in RISCV differs from that used in
7608  // FLT_ROUNDS. To convert it the C rounding mode is used as an index in
7609  // a table, which consists of a sequence of 4-bit fields, each representing
7610  // corresponding RISCV mode.
7611  static const unsigned Table =
7612  (RISCVFPRndMode::RNE << 4 * int(RoundingMode::NearestTiesToEven)) |
7613  (RISCVFPRndMode::RTZ << 4 * int(RoundingMode::TowardZero)) |
7614  (RISCVFPRndMode::RDN << 4 * int(RoundingMode::TowardNegative)) |
7615  (RISCVFPRndMode::RUP << 4 * int(RoundingMode::TowardPositive)) |
7616  (RISCVFPRndMode::RMM << 4 * int(RoundingMode::NearestTiesToAway));
7617 
7618  SDValue Shift = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, XLenVT, RMValue,
7619  DAG.getConstant(2, DL, XLenVT));
7620  SDValue Shifted = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, XLenVT,
7621  DAG.getConstant(Table, DL, XLenVT), Shift);
7622  RMValue = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, XLenVT, Shifted,
7623  DAG.getConstant(0x7, DL, XLenVT));
7624  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::WRITE_CSR, DL, MVT::Other, Chain, SysRegNo,
7625  RMValue);
7626 }
7627 
7628 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::lowerEH_DWARF_CFA(SDValue Op,
7629  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7630  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
7631 
7632  bool isRISCV64 = Subtarget.is64Bit();
7633  EVT PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
7634 
7635  int FI = MF.getFrameInfo().CreateFixedObject(isRISCV64 ? 8 : 4, 0, false);
7636  return DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, PtrVT);
7637 }
7638 
7639 // Returns the opcode of the target-specific SDNode that implements the 32-bit
7640 // form of the given Opcode.
7641 static RISCVISD::NodeType getRISCVWOpcode(unsigned Opcode) {
7642  switch (Opcode) {
7643  default:
7644  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected opcode");
7645  case ISD::SHL:
7646  return RISCVISD::SLLW;
7647  case ISD::SRA:
7648  return RISCVISD::SRAW;
7649  case ISD::SRL:
7650  return RISCVISD::SRLW;
7651  case ISD::SDIV:
7652  return RISCVISD::DIVW;
7653  case ISD::UDIV:
7654  return RISCVISD::DIVUW;
7655  case ISD::UREM:
7656  return RISCVISD::REMUW;
7657  case ISD::ROTL:
7658  return RISCVISD::ROLW;
7659  case ISD::ROTR:
7660  return RISCVISD::RORW;
7661  }
7662 }
7663 
7664 // Converts the given i8/i16/i32 operation to a target-specific SelectionDAG
7665 // node. Because i8/i16/i32 isn't a legal type for RV64, these operations would
7666 // otherwise be promoted to i64, making it difficult to select the
7667 // SLLW/DIVUW/.../*W later one because the fact the operation was originally of
7668 // type i8/i16/i32 is lost.
7669 static SDValue customLegalizeToWOp(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
7670  unsigned ExtOpc = ISD::ANY_EXTEND) {
7671  SDLoc DL(N);
7672  RISCVISD::NodeType WOpcode = getRISCVWOpcode(N->getOpcode());
7673  SDValue NewOp0 = DAG.getNode(ExtOpc, DL, MVT::i64, N->getOperand(0));
7674  SDValue NewOp1 = DAG.getNode(ExtOpc, DL, MVT::i64, N->getOperand(1));
7675  SDValue NewRes = DAG.getNode(WOpcode, DL, MVT::i64, NewOp0, NewOp1);
7676  // ReplaceNodeResults requires we maintain the same type for the return value.
7677  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, N->getValueType(0), NewRes);
7678 }
7679 
7680 // Converts the given 32-bit operation to a i64 operation with signed extension
7681 // semantic to reduce the signed extension instructions.
7682 static SDValue customLegalizeToWOpWithSExt(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
7683  SDLoc DL(N);
7684  SDValue NewOp0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, N->getOperand(0));
7685  SDValue NewOp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, N->getOperand(1));
7686  SDValue NewWOp = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, MVT::i64, NewOp0, NewOp1);
7687  SDValue NewRes = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, DL, MVT::i64, NewWOp,
7688  DAG.getValueType(MVT::i32));
7689  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, NewRes);
7690 }
7691 
7692 void RISCVTargetLowering::ReplaceNodeResults(SDNode *N,
7693  SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Results,
7694  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7695  SDLoc DL(N);
7696  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
7697  default:
7698  llvm_unreachable("Don't know how to custom type legalize this operation!");
7699  case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT:
7700  case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT:
7701  case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
7702  case ISD::FP_TO_UINT: {
7703  assert(N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i32 && Subtarget.is64Bit() &&
7704  "Unexpected custom legalisation");
7705  bool IsStrict = N->isStrictFPOpcode();
7706  bool IsSigned = N->getOpcode() == ISD::FP_TO_SINT ||
7707  N->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT;
7708  SDValue Op0 = IsStrict ? N->getOperand(1) : N->getOperand(0);
7709  if (getTypeAction(*DAG.getContext(), Op0.getValueType()) !=
7710  TargetLowering::TypeSoftenFloat) {
7711  if (!isTypeLegal(Op0.getValueType()))
7712  return;
7713  if (IsStrict) {
7714  SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0);
7715  // In absense of Zfh, promote f16 to f32, then convert.
7716  if (Op0.getValueType() == MVT::f16 && !Subtarget.hasStdExtZfh()) {
7717  Op0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_FP_EXTEND, DL, {MVT::f32, MVT::Other},
7718  {Chain, Op0});
7719  Chain = Op0.getValue(1);
7720  }
7721  unsigned Opc = IsSigned ? RISCVISD::STRICT_FCVT_W_RV64
7722  : RISCVISD::STRICT_FCVT_WU_RV64;
7723  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(MVT::i64, MVT::Other);
7724  SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(
7725  Opc, DL, VTs, Chain, Op0,
7726  DAG.getTargetConstant(RISCVFPRndMode::RTZ, DL, MVT::i64));
7727  Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, Res));
7728  Results.push_back(Res.getValue(1));
7729  return;
7730  }
7731  // In absense of Zfh, promote f16 to f32, then convert.
7732  if (Op0.getValueType() == MVT::f16 && !Subtarget.hasStdExtZfh())
7733  Op0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, DL, MVT::f32, Op0);
7734 
7735  unsigned Opc = IsSigned ? RISCVISD::FCVT_W_RV64 : RISCVISD::FCVT_WU_RV64;
7736  SDValue Res =
7737  DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, MVT::i64, Op0,
7738  DAG.getTargetConstant(RISCVFPRndMode::RTZ, DL, MVT::i64));
7739  Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, Res));
7740  return;
7741  }
7742  // If the FP type needs to be softened, emit a library call using the 'si'
7743  // version. If we left it to default legalization we'd end up with 'di'. If
7744  // the FP type doesn't need to be softened just let generic type
7745  // legalization promote the result type.
7746  RTLIB::Libcall LC;
7747  if (IsSigned)
7748  LC = RTLIB::getFPTOSINT(Op0.getValueType(), N->getValueType(0));
7749  else
7750  LC = RTLIB::getFPTOUINT(Op0.getValueType(), N->getValueType(0));
7751  MakeLibCallOptions CallOptions;
7752  EVT OpVT = Op0.getValueType();
7753  CallOptions.setTypeListBeforeSoften(OpVT, N->getValueType(0), true);
7754  SDValue Chain = IsStrict ? N->getOperand(0) : SDValue();
7755  SDValue Result;
7756  std::tie(Result, Chain) =
7757  makeLibCall(DAG, LC, N->getValueType(0), Op0, CallOptions, DL, Chain);
7758  Results.push_back(Result);
7759  if (IsStrict)
7760  Results.push_back(Chain);
7761  break;
7762  }
7763  case ISD::READCYCLECOUNTER: {
7764  assert(!Subtarget.is64Bit() &&
7765  "READCYCLECOUNTER only has custom type legalization on riscv32");
7766 
7767  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(MVT::i32, MVT::i32, MVT::Other);
7768  SDValue RCW =
7769  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::READ_CYCLE_WIDE, DL, VTs, N->getOperand(0));
7770 
7771  Results.push_back(
7772  DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_PAIR, DL, MVT::i64, RCW, RCW.getValue(1)));
7773  Results.push_back(RCW.getValue(2));
7774  break;
7775  }
7776  case ISD::LOAD: {
7777  if (!ISD::isNON_EXTLoad(N))
7778  return;
7779 
7780  // Use a SEXTLOAD instead of the default EXTLOAD. Similar to the
7781  // sext_inreg we emit for ADD/SUB/MUL/SLLI.
7782  LoadSDNode *Ld = cast<LoadSDNode>(N);
7783 
7784  SDLoc dl(N);
7785  SDValue Res = DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::SEXTLOAD, dl, MVT::i64, Ld->getChain(),
7786  Ld->getBasePtr(), Ld->getMemoryVT(),
7787  Ld->getMemOperand());
7788  Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, MVT::i32, Res));
7789  Results.push_back(Res.getValue(1));
7790  return;
7791  }
7792  case ISD::MUL: {
7793  unsigned Size = N->getSimpleValueType(0).getSizeInBits();
7794  unsigned XLen = Subtarget.getXLen();
7795  // This multiply needs to be expanded, try to use MULHSU+MUL if possible.
7796  if (Size > XLen) {
7797  assert(Size == (XLen * 2) && "Unexpected custom legalisation");
7798  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
7799  SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
7800  APInt HighMask = APInt::getHighBitsSet(Size, XLen);
7801 
7802  bool LHSIsU = DAG.MaskedValueIsZero(LHS, HighMask);
7803  bool RHSIsU = DAG.MaskedValueIsZero(RHS, HighMask);
7804  // We need exactly one side to be unsigned.
7805  if (LHSIsU == RHSIsU)
7806  return;
7807 
7808  auto MakeMULPair = [&](SDValue S, SDValue U) {
7809  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
7810  S = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, XLenVT, S);
7811  U = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, XLenVT, U);
7812  SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, DL, XLenVT, S, U);
7813  SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::MULHSU, DL, XLenVT, S, U);
7814  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_PAIR, DL, N->getValueType(0), Lo, Hi);
7815  };
7816 
7817  bool LHSIsS = DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(LHS) > XLen;
7818  bool RHSIsS = DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(RHS) > XLen;
7819 
7820  // The other operand should be signed, but still prefer MULH when
7821  // possible.
7822  if (RHSIsU && LHSIsS && !RHSIsS)
7823  Results.push_back(MakeMULPair(LHS, RHS));
7824  else if (LHSIsU && RHSIsS && !LHSIsS)
7825  Results.push_back(MakeMULPair(RHS, LHS));
7826 
7827  return;
7828  }
7829  [[fallthrough]];
7830  }
7831  case ISD::ADD:
7832  case ISD::SUB:
7833  assert(N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i32 && Subtarget.is64Bit() &&
7834  "Unexpected custom legalisation");
7835  Results.push_back(customLegalizeToWOpWithSExt(N, DAG));
7836  break;
7837  case ISD::SHL:
7838  case ISD::SRA:
7839  case ISD::SRL:
7840  assert(N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i32 && Subtarget.is64Bit() &&
7841  "Unexpected custom legalisation");
7842  if (N->getOperand(1).getOpcode() != ISD::Constant) {
7843  // If we can use a BSET instruction, allow default promotion to apply.
7844  if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SHL && Subtarget.hasStdExtZbs() &&
7845  isOneConstant(N->getOperand(0)))
7846  break;
7847  Results.push_back(customLegalizeToWOp(N, DAG));
7848  break;
7849  }
7850 
7851  // Custom legalize ISD::SHL by placing a SIGN_EXTEND_INREG after. This is
7852  // similar to customLegalizeToWOpWithSExt, but we must zero_extend the
7853  // shift amount.
7854  if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) {
7855  SDLoc DL(N);
7856  SDValue NewOp0 =
7857  DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, N->getOperand(0));
7858  SDValue NewOp1 =
7859  DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, N->getOperand(1));
7860  SDValue NewWOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, MVT::i64, NewOp0, NewOp1);
7861  SDValue NewRes = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, DL, MVT::i64, NewWOp,
7862  DAG.getValueType(MVT::i32));
7863  Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, NewRes));
7864  }
7865 
7866  break;
7867  case ISD::ROTL:
7868  case ISD::ROTR:
7869  assert(N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i32 && Subtarget.is64Bit() &&
7870  "Unexpected custom legalisation");
7871  Results.push_back(customLegalizeToWOp(N, DAG));
7872  break;
7873  case ISD::CTTZ:
7874  case ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
7875  case ISD::CTLZ:
7876  case ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF: {
7877  assert(N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i32 && Subtarget.is64Bit() &&
7878  "Unexpected custom legalisation");
7879 
7880  SDValue NewOp0 =
7881  DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, N->getOperand(0));
7882  bool IsCTZ =
7883  N->getOpcode() == ISD::CTTZ || N->getOpcode() == ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF;
7884  unsigned Opc = IsCTZ ? RISCVISD::CTZW : RISCVISD::CLZW;
7885  SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, MVT::i64, NewOp0);
7886  Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, Res));
7887  return;
7888  }
7889  case ISD::SDIV:
7890  case ISD::UDIV:
7891  case ISD::UREM: {
7892  MVT VT = N->getSimpleValueType(0);
7893  assert((VT == MVT::i8 || VT == MVT::i16 || VT == MVT::i32) &&
7894  Subtarget.is64Bit() && Subtarget.hasStdExtM() &&
7895  "Unexpected custom legalisation");
7896  // Don't promote division/remainder by constant since we should expand those
7897  // to multiply by magic constant.
7898  AttributeList Attr = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction().getAttributes();
7899  if (N->getOperand(1).getOpcode() == ISD::Constant &&
7900  !isIntDivCheap(N->getValueType(0), Attr))
7901  return;
7902 
7903  // If the input is i32, use ANY_EXTEND since the W instructions don't read
7904  // the upper 32 bits. For other types we need to sign or zero extend
7905  // based on the opcode.
7906  unsigned ExtOpc = ISD::ANY_EXTEND;
7907  if (VT != MVT::i32)
7908  ExtOpc = N->getOpcode() == ISD::SDIV ? ISD::SIGN_EXTEND
7909  : ISD::ZERO_EXTEND;
7910 
7911  Results.push_back(customLegalizeToWOp(N, DAG, ExtOpc));
7912  break;
7913  }
7914  case ISD::UADDO:
7915  case ISD::USUBO: {
7916  assert(N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i32 && Subtarget.is64Bit() &&
7917  "Unexpected custom legalisation");
7918  bool IsAdd = N->getOpcode() == ISD::UADDO;
7919  // Create an ADDW or SUBW.
7920  SDValue LHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, N->getOperand(0));
7921  SDValue RHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, N->getOperand(1));
7922  SDValue Res =
7923  DAG.getNode(IsAdd ? ISD::ADD : ISD::SUB, DL, MVT::i64, LHS, RHS);
7924  Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, DL, MVT::i64, Res,
7925  DAG.getValueType(MVT::i32));
7926 
7927  SDValue Overflow;
7928  if (IsAdd && isOneConstant(RHS)) {
7929  // Special case uaddo X, 1 overflowed if the addition result is 0.
7930  // The general case (X + C) < C is not necessarily beneficial. Although we
7931  // reduce the live range of X, we may introduce the materialization of
7932  // constant C, especially when the setcc result is used by branch. We have
7933  // no compare with constant and branch instructions.
7934  Overflow = DAG.getSetCC(DL, N->getValueType(1), Res,
7935  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i64), ISD::SETEQ);
7936  } else {
7937  // Sign extend the LHS and perform an unsigned compare with the ADDW
7938  // result. Since the inputs are sign extended from i32, this is equivalent
7939  // to comparing the lower 32 bits.
7940  LHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, N->getOperand(0));
7941  Overflow = DAG.getSetCC(DL, N->getValueType(1), Res, LHS,
7942  IsAdd ? ISD::SETULT : ISD::SETUGT);
7943  }
7944 
7945  Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, Res));
7946  Results.push_back(Overflow);
7947  return;
7948  }
7949  case ISD::UADDSAT:
7950  case ISD::USUBSAT: {
7951  assert(N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i32 && Subtarget.is64Bit() &&
7952  "Unexpected custom legalisation");
7953  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZbb()) {
7954  // With Zbb we can sign extend and let LegalizeDAG use minu/maxu. Using
7955  // sign extend allows overflow of the lower 32 bits to be detected on
7956  // the promoted size.
7957  SDValue LHS =
7958  DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, N->getOperand(0));
7959  SDValue RHS =
7960  DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, N->getOperand(1));
7961  SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, MVT::i64, LHS, RHS);
7962  Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, Res));
7963  return;
7964  }
7965 
7966  // Without Zbb, expand to UADDO/USUBO+select which will trigger our custom
7967  // promotion for UADDO/USUBO.
7968  Results.push_back(expandAddSubSat(N, DAG));
7969  return;
7970  }
7971  case ISD::ABS: {
7972  assert(N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i32 && Subtarget.is64Bit() &&
7973  "Unexpected custom legalisation");
7974 
7975  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZbb()) {
7976  // Emit a special ABSW node that will be expanded to NEGW+MAX at isel.
7977  // This allows us to remember that the result is sign extended. Expanding
7978  // to NEGW+MAX here requires a Freeze which breaks ComputeNumSignBits.
7979  SDValue Src = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64,
7980  N->getOperand(0));
7981  SDValue Abs = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::ABSW, DL, MVT::i64, Src);
7982  Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, Abs));
7983  return;
7984  }
7985 
7986  // Expand abs to Y = (sraiw X, 31); subw(xor(X, Y), Y)
7987  SDValue Src = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, N->getOperand(0));
7988 
7989  // Freeze the source so we can increase it's use count.
7990  Src = DAG.getFreeze(Src);
7991 
7992  // Copy sign bit to all bits using the sraiw pattern.
7993  SDValue SignFill = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, DL, MVT::i64, Src,
7994  DAG.getValueType(MVT::i32));
7995  SignFill = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, DL, MVT::i64, SignFill,
7996  DAG.getConstant(31, DL, MVT::i64));
7997 
7998  SDValue NewRes = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, MVT::i64, Src, SignFill);
7999  NewRes = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, MVT::i64, NewRes, SignFill);
8000 
8001  // NOTE: The result is only required to be anyextended, but sext is
8002  // consistent with type legalization of sub.
8003  NewRes = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, DL, MVT::i64, NewRes,
8004  DAG.getValueType(MVT::i32));
8005  Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, NewRes));
8006  return;
8007  }
8008  case ISD::BITCAST: {
8009  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8010  assert(VT.isInteger() && !VT.isVector() && "Unexpected VT!");
8011  SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
8012  EVT Op0VT = Op0.getValueType();
8013  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
8014  if (VT == MVT::i16 && Op0VT == MVT::f16 &&
8015  Subtarget.hasStdExtZfhOrZfhmin()) {
8016  SDValue FPConv = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FMV_X_ANYEXTH, DL, XLenVT, Op0);
8017  Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i16, FPConv));
8018  } else if (VT == MVT::i32 && Op0VT == MVT::f32 && Subtarget.is64Bit() &&
8019  Subtarget.hasStdExtF()) {
8020  SDValue FPConv =
8021  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FMV_X_ANYEXTW_RV64, DL, MVT::i64, Op0);
8022  Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, FPConv));
8023  } else if (!VT.isVector() && Op0VT.isFixedLengthVector() &&
8024  isTypeLegal(Op0VT)) {
8025  // Custom-legalize bitcasts from fixed-length vector types to illegal
8026  // scalar types in order to improve codegen. Bitcast the vector to a
8027  // one-element vector type whose element type is the same as the result
8028  // type, and extract the first element.
8029  EVT BVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), VT, 1);
8030  if (isTypeLegal(BVT)) {
8031  SDValue BVec = DAG.getBitcast(BVT, Op0);
8032  Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, VT, BVec,
8033  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, XLenVT)));
8034  }
8035  }
8036  break;
8037  }
8038  case RISCVISD::BREV8: {
8039  MVT VT = N->getSimpleValueType(0);
8040  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
8041  assert((VT == MVT::i16 || (VT == MVT::i32 && Subtarget.is64Bit())) &&
8042  "Unexpected custom legalisation");
8043  assert(Subtarget.hasStdExtZbkb() && "Unexpected extension");
8044  SDValue NewOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, XLenVT, N->getOperand(0));
8045  SDValue NewRes = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, XLenVT, NewOp);
8046  // ReplaceNodeResults requires we maintain the same type for the return
8047  // value.
8048  Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VT, NewRes));
8049  break;
8050  }
8051  case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT: {
8052  // Custom-legalize an EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT where XLEN<SEW, as the SEW element
8053  // type is illegal (currently only vXi64 RV32).
8054  // With vmv.x.s, when SEW > XLEN, only the least-significant XLEN bits are
8055  // transferred to the destination register. We issue two of these from the
8056  // upper- and lower- halves of the SEW-bit vector element, slid down to the
8057  // first element.
8058  SDValue Vec = N->getOperand(0);
8059  SDValue Idx = N->getOperand(1);
8060 
8061  // The vector type hasn't been legalized yet so we can't issue target
8062  // specific nodes if it needs legalization.
8063  // FIXME: We would manually legalize if it's important.
8064  if (!isTypeLegal(Vec.getValueType()))
8065  return;
8066 
8067  MVT VecVT = Vec.getSimpleValueType();
8068 
8069  assert(!Subtarget.is64Bit() && N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i64 &&
8070  VecVT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i64 &&
8071  "Unexpected EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT legalization");
8072 
8073  // If this is a fixed vector, we need to convert it to a scalable vector.
8074  MVT ContainerVT = VecVT;
8075  if (VecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
8076  ContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VecVT);
8077  Vec = convertToScalableVector(ContainerVT, Vec, DAG, Subtarget);
8078  }
8079 
8080  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
8081 
8082  // Use a VL of 1 to avoid processing more elements than we need.
8083  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(1, ContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
8084 
8085  // Unless the index is known to be 0, we must slide the vector down to get
8086  // the desired element into index 0.
8087  if (!isNullConstant(Idx)) {
8088  Vec = getVSlidedown(DAG, Subtarget, DL, ContainerVT,
8089  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), Vec, Idx, Mask, VL);
8090  }
8091 
8092  // Extract the lower XLEN bits of the correct vector element.
8093  SDValue EltLo = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_X_S, DL, XLenVT, Vec);
8094 
8095  // To extract the upper XLEN bits of the vector element, shift the first
8096  // element right by 32 bits and re-extract the lower XLEN bits.
8097  SDValue ThirtyTwoV = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, ContainerVT,
8098  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT),
8099  DAG.getConstant(32, DL, XLenVT), VL);
8100  SDValue LShr32 =
8101  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SRL_VL, DL, ContainerVT, Vec, ThirtyTwoV,
8102  DAG.getUNDEF(ContainerVT), Mask, VL);
8103 
8104  SDValue EltHi = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_X_S, DL, XLenVT, LShr32);
8105 
8106  Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_PAIR, DL, MVT::i64, EltLo, EltHi));
8107  break;
8108  }
8109  case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN: {
8110  unsigned IntNo = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(0))->getZExtValue();
8111  switch (IntNo) {
8112  default:
8113  llvm_unreachable(
8114  "Don't know how to custom type legalize this intrinsic!");
8115  case Intrinsic::riscv_orc_b: {
