8116  SDValue NewOp =
8117  DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, N->getOperand(1));
8118  SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::ORC_B, DL, MVT::i64, NewOp);
8119  Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, Res));
8120  return;
8121  }
8122  case Intrinsic::riscv_vmv_x_s: {
8123  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8124  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
8125  if (VT.bitsLT(XLenVT)) {
8126  // Simple case just extract using vmv.x.s and truncate.
8127  SDValue Extract = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_X_S, DL,
8128  Subtarget.getXLenVT(), N->getOperand(1));
8129  Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VT, Extract));
8130  return;
8131  }
8132 
8133  assert(VT == MVT::i64 && !Subtarget.is64Bit() &&
8134  "Unexpected custom legalization");
8135 
8136  // We need to do the move in two steps.
8137  SDValue Vec = N->getOperand(1);
8138  MVT VecVT = Vec.getSimpleValueType();
8139 
8140  // First extract the lower XLEN bits of the element.
8141  SDValue EltLo = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_X_S, DL, XLenVT, Vec);
8142 
8143  // To extract the upper XLEN bits of the vector element, shift the first
8144  // element right by 32 bits and re-extract the lower XLEN bits.
8145  auto [Mask, VL] = getDefaultVLOps(1, VecVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
8146 
8147  SDValue ThirtyTwoV =
8148  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, VecVT, DAG.getUNDEF(VecVT),
8149  DAG.getConstant(32, DL, XLenVT), VL);
8150  SDValue LShr32 = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SRL_VL, DL, VecVT, Vec, ThirtyTwoV,
8151  DAG.getUNDEF(VecVT), Mask, VL);
8152  SDValue EltHi = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_X_S, DL, XLenVT, LShr32);
8153 
8154  Results.push_back(
8155  DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_PAIR, DL, MVT::i64, EltLo, EltHi));
8156  break;
8157  }
8158  }
8159  break;
8160  }
8161  case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD:
8162  case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND:
8163  case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR:
8164  case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR:
8165  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX:
8166  case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX:
8167  case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN:
8168  case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN:
8169  if (SDValue V = lowerVECREDUCE(SDValue(N, 0), DAG))
8170  Results.push_back(V);
8171  break;
8172  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_ADD:
8173  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_AND:
8174  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_OR:
8175  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_XOR:
8176  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SMAX:
8177  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_UMAX:
8178  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_SMIN:
8179  case ISD::VP_REDUCE_UMIN:
8180  if (SDValue V = lowerVPREDUCE(SDValue(N, 0), DAG))
8181  Results.push_back(V);
8182  break;
8183  case ISD::GET_ROUNDING: {
8184  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(Subtarget.getXLenVT(), MVT::Other);
8185  SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::GET_ROUNDING, DL, VTs, N->getOperand(0));
8186  Results.push_back(Res.getValue(0));
8187  Results.push_back(Res.getValue(1));
8188  break;
8189  }
8190  }
8191 }
8192 
8193 // Try to fold (<bop> x, (reduction.<bop> vec, start))
8194 static SDValue combineBinOpToReduce(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
8195  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
8196  auto BinOpToRVVReduce = [](unsigned Opc) {
8197  switch (Opc) {
8198  default:
8199  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled binary to transfrom reduction");
8200  case ISD::ADD:
8201  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_ADD_VL;
8202  case ISD::UMAX:
8203  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX_VL;
8204  case ISD::SMAX:
8205  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX_VL;
8206  case ISD::UMIN:
8207  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN_VL;
8208  case ISD::SMIN:
8209  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN_VL;
8210  case ISD::AND:
8211  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_AND_VL;
8212  case ISD::OR:
8213  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_OR_VL;
8214  case ISD::XOR:
8215  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_XOR_VL;
8216  case ISD::FADD:
8217  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_FADD_VL;
8218  case ISD::FMAXNUM:
8219  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_FMAX_VL;
8220  case ISD::FMINNUM:
8221  return RISCVISD::VECREDUCE_FMIN_VL;
8222  }
8223  };
8224 
8225  auto IsReduction = [&BinOpToRVVReduce](SDValue V, unsigned Opc) {
8226  return V.getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT &&
8227  isNullConstant(V.getOperand(1)) &&
8228  V.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == BinOpToRVVReduce(Opc);
8229  };
8230 
8231  unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode();
8232  unsigned ReduceIdx;
8233  if (IsReduction(N->getOperand(0), Opc))
8234  ReduceIdx = 0;
8235  else if (IsReduction(N->getOperand(1), Opc))
8236  ReduceIdx = 1;
8237  else
8238  return SDValue();
8239 
8240  // Skip if FADD disallows reassociation but the combiner needs.
8241  if (Opc == ISD::FADD && !N->getFlags().hasAllowReassociation())
8242  return SDValue();
8243 
8244  SDValue Extract = N->getOperand(ReduceIdx);
8245  SDValue Reduce = Extract.getOperand(0);
8246  if (!Reduce.hasOneUse())
8247  return SDValue();
8248 
8249  SDValue ScalarV = Reduce.getOperand(2);
8250  EVT ScalarVT = ScalarV.getValueType();
8251  if (ScalarV.getOpcode() == ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR &&
8252  ScalarV.getOperand(0)->isUndef())
8253  ScalarV = ScalarV.getOperand(1);
8254 
8255  // Make sure that ScalarV is a splat with VL=1.
8256  if (ScalarV.getOpcode() != RISCVISD::VFMV_S_F_VL &&
8257  ScalarV.getOpcode() != RISCVISD::VMV_S_X_VL &&
8258  ScalarV.getOpcode() != RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL)
8259  return SDValue();
8260 
8261  if (!hasNonZeroAVL(ScalarV.getOperand(2)))
8262  return SDValue();
8263 
8264  // Check the scalar of ScalarV is neutral element
8265  // TODO: Deal with value other than neutral element.
8266  if (!isNeutralConstant(N->getOpcode(), N->getFlags(), ScalarV.getOperand(1),
8267  0))
8268  return SDValue();
8269 
8270  if (!ScalarV.hasOneUse())
8271  return SDValue();
8272 
8273  SDValue NewStart = N->getOperand(1 - ReduceIdx);
8274 
8275  SDLoc DL(N);
8276  SDValue NewScalarV =
8277  lowerScalarInsert(NewStart, ScalarV.getOperand(2),
8278  ScalarV.getSimpleValueType(), DL, DAG, Subtarget);
8279 
8280  // If we looked through an INSERT_SUBVECTOR we need to restore it.
8281  if (ScalarVT != ScalarV.getValueType())
8282  NewScalarV =
8283  DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, ScalarVT, DAG.getUNDEF(ScalarVT),
8284  NewScalarV, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, Subtarget.getXLenVT()));
8285 
8286  SDValue NewReduce =
8287  DAG.getNode(Reduce.getOpcode(), DL, Reduce.getValueType(),
8288  Reduce.getOperand(0), Reduce.getOperand(1), NewScalarV,
8289  Reduce.getOperand(3), Reduce.getOperand(4));
8290  return DAG.getNode(Extract.getOpcode(), DL, Extract.getValueType(), NewReduce,
8291  Extract.getOperand(1));
8292 }
8293 
8294 // Optimize (add (shl x, c0), (shl y, c1)) ->
8295 // (SLLI (SH*ADD x, y), c0), if c1-c0 equals to [1|2|3].
8296 static SDValue transformAddShlImm(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
8297  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
8298  // Perform this optimization only in the zba extension.
8299  if (!Subtarget.hasStdExtZba())
8300  return SDValue();
8301 
8302  // Skip for vector types and larger types.
8303  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8304  if (VT.isVector() || VT.getSizeInBits() > Subtarget.getXLen())
8305  return SDValue();
8306 
8307  // The two operand nodes must be SHL and have no other use.
8308  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
8309  SDValue N1 = N->getOperand(1);
8310  if (N0->getOpcode() != ISD::SHL || N1->getOpcode() != ISD::SHL ||
8311  !N0->hasOneUse() || !N1->hasOneUse())
8312  return SDValue();
8313 
8314  // Check c0 and c1.
8315  auto *N0C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0->getOperand(1));
8316  auto *N1C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N1->getOperand(1));
8317  if (!N0C || !N1C)
8318  return SDValue();
8319  int64_t C0 = N0C->getSExtValue();
8320  int64_t C1 = N1C->getSExtValue();
8321  if (C0 <= 0 || C1 <= 0)
8322  return SDValue();
8323 
8324  // Skip if SH1ADD/SH2ADD/SH3ADD are not applicable.
8325  int64_t Bits = std::min(C0, C1);
8326  int64_t Diff = std::abs(C0 - C1);
8327  if (Diff != 1 && Diff != 2 && Diff != 3)
8328  return SDValue();
8329 
8330  // Build nodes.
8331  SDLoc DL(N);
8332  SDValue NS = (C0 < C1) ? N0->getOperand(0) : N1->getOperand(0);
8333  SDValue NL = (C0 > C1) ? N0->getOperand(0) : N1->getOperand(0);
8334  SDValue NA0 =
8335  DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, NL, DAG.getConstant(Diff, DL, VT));
8336  SDValue NA1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, NA0, NS);
8337  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, NA1, DAG.getConstant(Bits, DL, VT));
8338 }
8339 
8340 // Combine a constant select operand into its use:
8341 //
8342 // (and (select cond, -1, c), x)
8343 // -> (select cond, x, (and x, c)) [AllOnes=1]
8344 // (or (select cond, 0, c), x)
8345 // -> (select cond, x, (or x, c)) [AllOnes=0]
8346 // (xor (select cond, 0, c), x)
8347 // -> (select cond, x, (xor x, c)) [AllOnes=0]
8348 // (add (select cond, 0, c), x)
8349 // -> (select cond, x, (add x, c)) [AllOnes=0]
8350 // (sub x, (select cond, 0, c))
8351 // -> (select cond, x, (sub x, c)) [AllOnes=0]
8352 static SDValue combineSelectAndUse(SDNode *N, SDValue Slct, SDValue OtherOp,
8353  SelectionDAG &DAG, bool AllOnes,
8354  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
8355  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8356 
8357  // Skip vectors.
8358  if (VT.isVector())
8359  return SDValue();
8360 
8361  if (!Subtarget.hasShortForwardBranchOpt() ||
8362  (Slct.getOpcode() != ISD::SELECT &&
8363  Slct.getOpcode() != RISCVISD::SELECT_CC) ||
8364  !Slct.hasOneUse())
8365  return SDValue();
8366 
8367  auto isZeroOrAllOnes = [](SDValue N, bool AllOnes) {
8368  return AllOnes ? isAllOnesConstant(N) : isNullConstant(N);
8369  };
8370 
8371  bool SwapSelectOps;
8372  unsigned OpOffset = Slct.getOpcode() == RISCVISD::SELECT_CC ? 2 : 0;
8373  SDValue TrueVal = Slct.getOperand(1 + OpOffset);
8374  SDValue FalseVal = Slct.getOperand(2 + OpOffset);
8375  SDValue NonConstantVal;
8376  if (isZeroOrAllOnes(TrueVal, AllOnes)) {
8377  SwapSelectOps = false;
8378  NonConstantVal = FalseVal;
8379  } else if (isZeroOrAllOnes(FalseVal, AllOnes)) {
8380  SwapSelectOps = true;
8381  NonConstantVal = TrueVal;
8382  } else
8383  return SDValue();
8384 
8385  // Slct is now know to be the desired identity constant when CC is true.
8386  TrueVal = OtherOp;
8387  FalseVal = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), SDLoc(N), VT, OtherOp, NonConstantVal);
8388  // Unless SwapSelectOps says the condition should be false.
8389  if (SwapSelectOps)
8390  std::swap(TrueVal, FalseVal);
8391 
8392  if (Slct.getOpcode() == RISCVISD::SELECT_CC)
8393  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SELECT_CC, SDLoc(N), VT,
8394  {Slct.getOperand(0), Slct.getOperand(1),
8395  Slct.getOperand(2), TrueVal, FalseVal});
8396 
8397  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, SDLoc(N), VT,
8398  {Slct.getOperand(0), TrueVal, FalseVal});
8399 }
8400 
8401 // Attempt combineSelectAndUse on each operand of a commutative operator N.
8402 static SDValue combineSelectAndUseCommutative(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
8403  bool AllOnes,
8404  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
8405  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
8406  SDValue N1 = N->getOperand(1);
8407  if (SDValue Result = combineSelectAndUse(N, N0, N1, DAG, AllOnes, Subtarget))
8408  return Result;
8409  if (SDValue Result = combineSelectAndUse(N, N1, N0, DAG, AllOnes, Subtarget))
8410  return Result;
8411  return SDValue();
8412 }
8413 
8414 // Transform (add (mul x, c0), c1) ->
8415 // (add (mul (add x, c1/c0), c0), c1%c0).
8416 // if c1/c0 and c1%c0 are simm12, while c1 is not. A special corner case
8417 // that should be excluded is when c0*(c1/c0) is simm12, which will lead
8418 // to an infinite loop in DAGCombine if transformed.
8419 // Or transform (add (mul x, c0), c1) ->
8420 // (add (mul (add x, c1/c0+1), c0), c1%c0-c0),
8421 // if c1/c0+1 and c1%c0-c0 are simm12, while c1 is not. A special corner
8422 // case that should be excluded is when c0*(c1/c0+1) is simm12, which will
8423 // lead to an infinite loop in DAGCombine if transformed.
8424 // Or transform (add (mul x, c0), c1) ->
8425 // (add (mul (add x, c1/c0-1), c0), c1%c0+c0),
8426 // if c1/c0-1 and c1%c0+c0 are simm12, while c1 is not. A special corner
8427 // case that should be excluded is when c0*(c1/c0-1) is simm12, which will
8428 // lead to an infinite loop in DAGCombine if transformed.
8429 // Or transform (add (mul x, c0), c1) ->
8430 // (mul (add x, c1/c0), c0).
8431 // if c1%c0 is zero, and c1/c0 is simm12 while c1 is not.
8432 static SDValue transformAddImmMulImm(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
8433  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
8434  // Skip for vector types and larger types.
8435  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8436  if (VT.isVector() || VT.getSizeInBits() > Subtarget.getXLen())
8437  return SDValue();
8438  // The first operand node must be a MUL and has no other use.
8439  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
8440  if (!N0->hasOneUse() || N0->getOpcode() != ISD::MUL)
8441  return SDValue();
8442  // Check if c0 and c1 match above conditions.
8443  auto *N0C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0->getOperand(1));
8444  auto *N1C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
8445  if (!N0C || !N1C)
8446  return SDValue();
8447  // If N0C has multiple uses it's possible one of the cases in
8448  // DAGCombiner::isMulAddWithConstProfitable will be true, which would result
8449  // in an infinite loop.
8450  if (!N0C->hasOneUse())
8451  return SDValue();
8452  int64_t C0 = N0C->getSExtValue();
8453  int64_t C1 = N1C->getSExtValue();
8454  int64_t CA, CB;
8455  if (C0 == -1 || C0 == 0 || C0 == 1 || isInt<12>(C1))
8456  return SDValue();
8457  // Search for proper CA (non-zero) and CB that both are simm12.
8458  if ((C1 / C0) != 0 && isInt<12>(C1 / C0) && isInt<12>(C1 % C0) &&
8459  !isInt<12>(C0 * (C1 / C0))) {
8460  CA = C1 / C0;
8461  CB = C1 % C0;
8462  } else if ((C1 / C0 + 1) != 0 && isInt<12>(C1 / C0 + 1) &&
8463  isInt<12>(C1 % C0 - C0) && !isInt<12>(C0 * (C1 / C0 + 1))) {
8464  CA = C1 / C0 + 1;
8465  CB = C1 % C0 - C0;
8466  } else if ((C1 / C0 - 1) != 0 && isInt<12>(C1 / C0 - 1) &&
8467  isInt<12>(C1 % C0 + C0) && !isInt<12>(C0 * (C1 / C0 - 1))) {
8468  CA = C1 / C0 - 1;
8469  CB = C1 % C0 + C0;
8470  } else
8471  return SDValue();
8472  // Build new nodes (add (mul (add x, c1/c0), c0), c1%c0).
8473  SDLoc DL(N);
8474  SDValue New0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, N0->getOperand(0),
8475  DAG.getConstant(CA, DL, VT));
8476  SDValue New1 =
8477  DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, DL, VT, New0, DAG.getConstant(C0, DL, VT));
8478  return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, New1, DAG.getConstant(CB, DL, VT));
8479 }
8480 
8481 static SDValue performADDCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
8482  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
8483  if (SDValue V = transformAddImmMulImm(N, DAG, Subtarget))
8484  return V;
8485  if (SDValue V = transformAddShlImm(N, DAG, Subtarget))
8486  return V;
8487  if (SDValue V = combineBinOpToReduce(N, DAG, Subtarget))
8488  return V;
8489  // fold (add (select lhs, rhs, cc, 0, y), x) ->
8490  // (select lhs, rhs, cc, x, (add x, y))
8491  return combineSelectAndUseCommutative(N, DAG, /*AllOnes*/ false, Subtarget);
8492 }
8493 
8494 // Try to turn a sub boolean RHS and constant LHS into an addi.
8495 static SDValue combineSubOfBoolean(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
8496  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
8497  SDValue N1 = N->getOperand(1);
8498  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8499  SDLoc DL(N);
8500 
8501  // Require a constant LHS.
8502  auto *N0C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0);
8503  if (!N0C)
8504  return SDValue();
8505 
8506  // All our optimizations involve subtracting 1 from the immediate and forming
8507  // an ADDI. Make sure the new immediate is valid for an ADDI.
8508  APInt ImmValMinus1 = N0C->getAPIntValue() - 1;
8509  if (!ImmValMinus1.isSignedIntN(12))
8510  return SDValue();
8511 
8512  SDValue NewLHS;
8513  if (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC && N1.hasOneUse()) {
8514  // (sub constant, (setcc x, y, eq/neq)) ->
8515  // (add (setcc x, y, neq/eq), constant - 1)
8516  ISD::CondCode CCVal = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N1.getOperand(2))->get();
8517  EVT SetCCOpVT = N1.getOperand(0).getValueType();
8518  if (!isIntEqualitySetCC(CCVal) || !SetCCOpVT.isInteger())
8519  return SDValue();
8520  CCVal = ISD::getSetCCInverse(CCVal, SetCCOpVT);
8521  NewLHS =
8522  DAG.getSetCC(SDLoc(N1), VT, N1.getOperand(0), N1.getOperand(1), CCVal);
8523  } else if (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::XOR && isOneConstant(N1.getOperand(1)) &&
8524  N1.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC) {
8525  // (sub C, (xor (setcc), 1)) -> (add (setcc), C-1).
8526  // Since setcc returns a bool the xor is equivalent to 1-setcc.
8527  NewLHS = N1.getOperand(0);
8528  } else
8529  return SDValue();
8530 
8531  SDValue NewRHS = DAG.getConstant(ImmValMinus1, DL, VT);
8532  return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, NewLHS, NewRHS);
8533 }
8534 
8535 static SDValue performSUBCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
8536  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
8537  if (SDValue V = combineSubOfBoolean(N, DAG))
8538  return V;
8539 
8540  // fold (sub x, (select lhs, rhs, cc, 0, y)) ->
8541  // (select lhs, rhs, cc, x, (sub x, y))
8542  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
8543  SDValue N1 = N->getOperand(1);
8544  return combineSelectAndUse(N, N1, N0, DAG, /*AllOnes*/ false, Subtarget);
8545 }
8546 
8547 // Apply DeMorgan's law to (and/or (xor X, 1), (xor Y, 1)) if X and Y are 0/1.
8548 // Legalizing setcc can introduce xors like this. Doing this transform reduces
8549 // the number of xors and may allow the xor to fold into a branch condition.
8550 static SDValue combineDeMorganOfBoolean(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
8551  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
8552  SDValue N1 = N->getOperand(1);
8553  bool IsAnd = N->getOpcode() == ISD::AND;
8554 
8555  if (N0.getOpcode() != ISD::XOR || N1.getOpcode() != ISD::XOR)
8556  return SDValue();
8557 
8558  if (!N0.hasOneUse() || !N1.hasOneUse())
8559  return SDValue();
8560 
8561  SDValue N01 = N0.getOperand(1);
8562  SDValue N11 = N1.getOperand(1);
8563 
8564  // For AND, SimplifyDemandedBits may have turned one of the (xor X, 1) into
8565  // (xor X, -1) based on the upper bits of the other operand being 0. If the
8566  // operation is And, allow one of the Xors to use -1.
8567  if (isOneConstant(N01)) {
8568  if (!isOneConstant(N11) && !(IsAnd && isAllOnesConstant(N11)))
8569  return SDValue();
8570  } else if (isOneConstant(N11)) {
8571  // N01 and N11 being 1 was already handled. Handle N11==1 and N01==-1.
8572  if (!(IsAnd && isAllOnesConstant(N01)))
8573  return SDValue();
8574  } else
8575  return SDValue();
8576 
8577  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8578 
8579  SDValue N00 = N0.getOperand(0);
8580  SDValue N10 = N1.getOperand(0);
8581 
8582  // The LHS of the xors needs to be 0/1.
8583  APInt Mask = APInt::getBitsSetFrom(VT.getSizeInBits(), 1);
8584  if (!DAG.MaskedValueIsZero(N00, Mask) || !DAG.MaskedValueIsZero(N10, Mask))
8585  return SDValue();
8586 
8587  // Invert the opcode and insert a new xor.
8588  SDLoc DL(N);
8589  unsigned Opc = IsAnd ? ISD::OR : ISD::AND;
8590  SDValue Logic = DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, VT, N00, N10);
8591  return DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, VT, Logic, DAG.getConstant(1, DL, VT));
8592 }
8593 
8594 static SDValue performTRUNCATECombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
8595  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
8596  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
8597  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8598 
8599  // Pre-promote (i1 (truncate (srl X, Y))) on RV64 with Zbs without zero
8600  // extending X. This is safe since we only need the LSB after the shift and
8601  // shift amounts larger than 31 would produce poison. If we wait until
8602  // type legalization, we'll create RISCVISD::SRLW and we can't recover it
8603  // to use a BEXT instruction.
8604  if (Subtarget.is64Bit() && Subtarget.hasStdExtZbs() && VT == MVT::i1 &&
8605  N0.getValueType() == MVT::i32 && N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL &&
8606  !isa<ConstantSDNode>(N0.getOperand(1)) && N0.hasOneUse()) {
8607  SDLoc DL(N0);
8608  SDValue Op0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, N0.getOperand(0));
8609  SDValue Op1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, N0.getOperand(1));
8610  SDValue Srl = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, MVT::i64, Op0, Op1);
8611  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SDLoc(N), VT, Srl);
8612  }
8613 
8614  return SDValue();
8615 }
8616 
8617 namespace {
8618 // Helper class contains information about comparison operation.
8619 // The first two operands of this operation are compared values and the
8620 // last one is the operation.
8621 // Compared values are stored in Ops.
8622 // Comparison operation is stored in CCode.
8623 class CmpOpInfo {
8624  static unsigned constexpr Size = 2u;
8625 
8626  // Type for storing operands of compare operation.
8627  using OpsArray = std::array<SDValue, Size>;
8628  OpsArray Ops;
8629 
8630  using const_iterator = OpsArray::const_iterator;
8631  const_iterator begin() const { return Ops.begin(); }
8632  const_iterator end() const { return Ops.end(); }
8633 
8634  ISD::CondCode CCode;
8635 
8636  unsigned CommonPos{Size};
8637  unsigned DifferPos{Size};
8638 
8639  // Sets CommonPos and DifferPos based on incoming position
8640  // of common operand CPos.
8641  void setPositions(const_iterator CPos) {
8642  assert(CPos != Ops.end() && "Common operand has to be in OpsArray.\n");
8643  CommonPos = CPos == Ops.begin() ? 0 : 1;
8644  DifferPos = 1 - CommonPos;
8645  assert((DifferPos == 0 || DifferPos == 1) &&
8646  "Positions can be only 0 or 1.");
8647  }
8648 
8649  // Private constructor of comparison info based on comparison operator.
8650  // It is private because CmpOpInfo only reasonable relative to other
8651  // comparison operator. Therefore, infos about comparison operation
8652  // have to be collected simultaneously via CmpOpInfo::getInfoAbout().
8653  CmpOpInfo(const SDValue &CmpOp)
8654  : Ops{CmpOp.getOperand(0), CmpOp.getOperand(1)},
8655  CCode{cast<CondCodeSDNode>(CmpOp.getOperand(2))->get()} {}
8656 
8657  // Finds common operand of Op1 and Op2 and finishes filling CmpOpInfos.
8658  // Returns true if common operand is found. Otherwise - false.
8659  static bool establishCorrespondence(CmpOpInfo &Op1, CmpOpInfo &Op2) {
8660  const auto CommonOpIt1 =
8661  std::find_first_of(Op1.begin(), Op1.end(), Op2.begin(), Op2.end());
8662  if (CommonOpIt1 == Op1.end())
8663  return false;
8664 
8665  const auto CommonOpIt2 = std::find(Op2.begin(), Op2.end(), *CommonOpIt1);
8666  assert(CommonOpIt2 != Op2.end() &&
8667  "Cannot find common operand in the second comparison operation.");
8668 
8669  Op1.setPositions(CommonOpIt1);
8670  Op2.setPositions(CommonOpIt2);
8671 
8672  return true;
8673  }
8674 
8675 public:
8676  CmpOpInfo(const CmpOpInfo &) = default;
8677  CmpOpInfo(CmpOpInfo &&) = default;
8678 
8679  SDValue const &operator[](unsigned Pos) const {
8680  assert(Pos < Size && "Out of range\n");
8681  return Ops[Pos];
8682  }
8683 
8684  // Creates infos about comparison operations CmpOp0 and CmpOp1.
8685  // If there is no common operand returns None. Otherwise, returns
8686  // correspondence info about comparison operations.
8687  static std::optional<std::pair<CmpOpInfo, CmpOpInfo>>
8688  getInfoAbout(SDValue const &CmpOp0, SDValue const &CmpOp1) {
8689  CmpOpInfo Op0{CmpOp0};
8690  CmpOpInfo Op1{CmpOp1};
8691  if (!establishCorrespondence(Op0, Op1))
8692  return std::nullopt;
8693  return std::make_pair(Op0, Op1);
8694  }
8695 
8696  // Returns position of common operand.
8697  unsigned getCPos() const { return CommonPos; }
8698 
8699  // Returns position of differ operand.
8700  unsigned getDPos() const { return DifferPos; }
8701 
8702  // Returns common operand.
8703  SDValue const &getCOp() const { return operator[](CommonPos); }
8704 
8705  // Returns differ operand.
8706  SDValue const &getDOp() const { return operator[](DifferPos); }
8707 
8708  // Returns consition code of comparison operation.
8709  ISD::CondCode getCondCode() const { return CCode; }
8710 };
8711 } // namespace
8712 
8713 // Verifies conditions to apply an optimization.
8714 // Returns Reference comparison code and three operands A, B, C.
8715 // Conditions for optimization:
8716 // One operand of the compasions has to be common.
8717 // This operand is written to C.
8718 // Two others operands are differend. They are written to A and B.
8719 // Comparisons has to be similar with respect to common operand C.
8720 // e.g. A < C; C > B are similar
8721 // but A < C; B > C are not.
8722 // Reference comparison code is the comparison code if
8723 // common operand is right placed.
8724 // e.g. C > A will be swapped to A < C.
8725 static std::optional<std::tuple<ISD::CondCode, SDValue, SDValue, SDValue>>
8726 verifyCompareConds(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
8727  LLVM_DEBUG(
8728  dbgs() << "Checking conditions for comparison operation combining.\n";);
8729 
8730  SDValue V0 = N->getOperand(0);
8731  SDValue V1 = N->getOperand(1);
8732  assert(V0.getValueType() == V1.getValueType() &&
8733  "Operations must have the same value type.");
8734 
8735  // Condition 1. Operations have to be used only in logic operation.
8736  if (!V0.hasOneUse() || !V1.hasOneUse())
8737  return std::nullopt;
8738 
8739  // Condition 2. Operands have to be comparison operations.
8740  if (V0.getOpcode() != ISD::SETCC || V1.getOpcode() != ISD::SETCC)
8741  return std::nullopt;
8742 
8743  // Condition 3.1. Operations only with integers.
8744  if (!V0.getOperand(0).getValueType().isInteger())
8745  return std::nullopt;
8746 
8747  const auto ComparisonInfo = CmpOpInfo::getInfoAbout(V0, V1);
8748  // Condition 3.2. Common operand has to be in comparison.
8749  if (!ComparisonInfo)
8750  return std::nullopt;
8751 
8752  const auto [Op0, Op1] = ComparisonInfo.value();
8753 
8754  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Shared operands are on positions: " << Op0.getCPos()
8755  << " and " << Op1.getCPos() << '\n';);
8756  // If common operand at the first position then swap operation to convert to
8757  // strict pattern. Common operand has to be right hand side.
8758  ISD::CondCode RefCond = Op0.getCondCode();
8759  ISD::CondCode AssistCode = Op1.getCondCode();
8760  if (!Op0.getCPos())
8761  RefCond = ISD::getSetCCSwappedOperands(RefCond);
8762  if (!Op1.getCPos())
8763  AssistCode = ISD::getSetCCSwappedOperands(AssistCode);
8764  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Reference condition is: " << RefCond << '\n';);
8765  // If there are different comparison operations then do not perform an
8766  // optimization. a < c; c < b -> will be changed to b > c.
8767  if (RefCond != AssistCode)
8768  return std::nullopt;
8769 
8770  // Conditions can be only similar to Less or Greater. (>, >=, <, <=)
8771  // Applying this mask to the operation will determine Less and Greater
8772  // operations.
8773  const unsigned CmpMask = 0b110;
8774  const unsigned MaskedOpcode = CmpMask & RefCond;
8775  // If masking gave 0b110, then this is an operation NE, O or TRUE.
8776  if (MaskedOpcode == CmpMask)
8777  return std::nullopt;
8778  // If masking gave 00000, then this is an operation E, O or FALSE.
8779  if (MaskedOpcode == 0)
8780  return std::nullopt;
8781  // Everything else is similar to Less or Greater.
8782 
8783  SDValue A = Op0.getDOp();
8784  SDValue B = Op1.getDOp();
8785  SDValue C = Op0.getCOp();
8786 
8787  LLVM_DEBUG(
8788  dbgs() << "The conditions for combining comparisons are satisfied.\n";);
8789  return std::make_tuple(RefCond, A, B, C);
8790 }
8791 
8792 static ISD::NodeType getSelectionCode(bool IsUnsigned, bool IsAnd,
8793  bool IsGreaterOp) {
8794  // Codes of selection operation. The first index selects signed or unsigned,
8795  // the second index selects MIN/MAX.
8796  static constexpr ISD::NodeType SelectionCodes[2][2] = {
8797  {ISD::SMIN, ISD::SMAX}, {ISD::UMIN, ISD::UMAX}};
8798  const bool ChooseSelCode = IsAnd ^ IsGreaterOp;
8799  return SelectionCodes[IsUnsigned][ChooseSelCode];
8800 }
8801 
8802 // Combines two comparison operation and logic operation to one selection
8803 // operation(min, max) and logic operation. Returns new constructed Node if
8804 // conditions for optimization are satisfied.
8805 static SDValue combineCmpOp(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
8806  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
8807  if (!Subtarget.hasStdExtZbb())
8808  return SDValue();
8809 
8810  const unsigned BitOpcode = N->getOpcode();
8811  assert((BitOpcode == ISD::AND || BitOpcode == ISD::OR) &&
8812  "This optimization can be used only with AND/OR operations");
8813 
8814  const auto Props = verifyCompareConds(N, DAG);
8815  // If conditions are invalidated then do not perform an optimization.
8816  if (!Props)
8817  return SDValue();
8818 
8819  const auto [RefOpcode, A, B, C] = Props.value();
8820  const EVT CmpOpVT = A.getValueType();
8821 
8822  const bool IsGreaterOp = RefOpcode & 0b10;
8823  const bool IsUnsigned = ISD::isUnsignedIntSetCC(RefOpcode);
8824  assert((IsUnsigned || ISD::isSignedIntSetCC(RefOpcode)) &&
8825  "Operation neither with signed or unsigned integers.");
8826 
8827  const bool IsAnd = BitOpcode == ISD::AND;
8828  const ISD::NodeType PickCode =
8829  getSelectionCode(IsUnsigned, IsAnd, IsGreaterOp);
8830 
8831  SDLoc DL(N);
8832  SDValue Pick = DAG.getNode(PickCode, DL, CmpOpVT, A, B);
8833  SDValue Cmp =
8834  DAG.getSetCC(DL, N->getOperand(0).getValueType(), Pick, C, RefOpcode);
8835 
8836  return Cmp;
8837 }
8838 
8839 static SDValue performANDCombine(SDNode *N,
8840  TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
8841  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
8842  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
8843 
8844  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
8845  // Pre-promote (i32 (and (srl X, Y), 1)) on RV64 with Zbs without zero
8846  // extending X. This is safe since we only need the LSB after the shift and
8847  // shift amounts larger than 31 would produce poison. If we wait until
8848  // type legalization, we'll create RISCVISD::SRLW and we can't recover it
8849  // to use a BEXT instruction.
8850  if (Subtarget.is64Bit() && Subtarget.hasStdExtZbs() &&
8851  N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i32 && isOneConstant(N->getOperand(1)) &&
8852  N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL && !isa<ConstantSDNode>(N0.getOperand(1)) &&
8853  N0.hasOneUse()) {
8854  SDLoc DL(N);
8855  SDValue Op0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, N0.getOperand(0));
8856  SDValue Op1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, N0.getOperand(1));
8857  SDValue Srl = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, MVT::i64, Op0, Op1);
8858  SDValue And = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, MVT::i64, Srl,
8859  DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i64));
8860  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, And);
8861  }
8862 
8863  if (SDValue V = combineCmpOp(N, DAG, Subtarget))
8864  return V;
8865 
8866  if (SDValue V = combineBinOpToReduce(N, DAG, Subtarget))
8867  return V;
8868 
8869  if (DCI.isAfterLegalizeDAG())
8870  if (SDValue V = combineDeMorganOfBoolean(N, DAG))
8871  return V;
8872 
8873  // fold (and (select lhs, rhs, cc, -1, y), x) ->
8874  // (select lhs, rhs, cc, x, (and x, y))
8875  return combineSelectAndUseCommutative(N, DAG, /*AllOnes*/ true, Subtarget);
8876 }
8877 
8878 static SDValue performORCombine(SDNode *N, TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
8879  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
8880  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
8881 
8882  if (SDValue V = combineCmpOp(N, DAG, Subtarget))
8883  return V;
8884 
8885  if (SDValue V = combineBinOpToReduce(N, DAG, Subtarget))
8886  return V;
8887 
8888  if (DCI.isAfterLegalizeDAG())
8889  if (SDValue V = combineDeMorganOfBoolean(N, DAG))
8890  return V;
8891 
8892  // fold (or (select cond, 0, y), x) ->
8893  // (select cond, x, (or x, y))
8894  return combineSelectAndUseCommutative(N, DAG, /*AllOnes*/ false, Subtarget);
8895 }
8896 
8897 static SDValue performXORCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
8898  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
8899  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
8900  SDValue N1 = N->getOperand(1);
8901 
8902  // fold (xor (sllw 1, x), -1) -> (rolw ~1, x)
8903  // NOTE: Assumes ROL being legal means ROLW is legal.
8904  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
8905  if (N0.getOpcode() == RISCVISD::SLLW &&
8906  isAllOnesConstant(N1) && isOneConstant(N0.getOperand(0)) &&
8907  TLI.isOperationLegal(ISD::ROTL, MVT::i64)) {
8908  SDLoc DL(N);
8909  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::ROLW, DL, MVT::i64,
8910  DAG.getConstant(~1, DL, MVT::i64), N0.getOperand(1));
8911  }
8912 
8913  if (SDValue V = combineBinOpToReduce(N, DAG, Subtarget))
8914  return V;
8915  // fold (xor (select cond, 0, y), x) ->
8916  // (select cond, x, (xor x, y))
8917  return combineSelectAndUseCommutative(N, DAG, /*AllOnes*/ false, Subtarget);
8918 }
8919 
8920 // Replace (seteq (i64 (and X, 0xffffffff)), C1) with
8921 // (seteq (i64 (sext_inreg (X, i32)), C1')) where C1' is C1 sign extended from
8922 // bit 31. Same for setne. C1' may be cheaper to materialize and the sext_inreg
8923 // can become a sext.w instead of a shift pair.
8924 static SDValue performSETCCCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
8925  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
8926  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
8927  SDValue N1 = N->getOperand(1);
8928  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8929  EVT OpVT = N0.getValueType();
8930 
8931  if (OpVT != MVT::i64 || !Subtarget.is64Bit())
8932  return SDValue();
8933 
8934  // RHS needs to be a constant.
8935  auto *N1C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N1);
8936  if (!N1C)
8937  return SDValue();
8938 
8939  // LHS needs to be (and X, 0xffffffff).
8940  if (N0.getOpcode() != ISD::AND || !N0.hasOneUse() ||
8941  !isa<ConstantSDNode>(N0.getOperand(1)) ||
8942  N0.getConstantOperandVal(1) != UINT64_C(0xffffffff))
8943  return SDValue();
8944 
8945  // Looking for an equality compare.
8946  ISD::CondCode Cond = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N->getOperand(2))->get();
8947  if (!isIntEqualitySetCC(Cond))
8948  return SDValue();
8949 
8950  // Don't do this if the sign bit is provably zero, it will be turned back into
8951  // an AND.
8952  APInt SignMask = APInt::getOneBitSet(64, 31);
8953  if (DAG.MaskedValueIsZero(N0.getOperand(0), SignMask))
8954  return SDValue();
8955 
8956  const APInt &C1 = N1C->getAPIntValue();
8957 
8958  SDLoc dl(N);
8959  // If the constant is larger than 2^32 - 1 it is impossible for both sides
8960  // to be equal.
8961  if (C1.getActiveBits() > 32)
8962  return DAG.getBoolConstant(Cond == ISD::SETNE, dl, VT, OpVT);
8963 
8964  SDValue SExtOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, N, OpVT,
8965  N0.getOperand(0), DAG.getValueType(MVT::i32));
8966  return DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, SExtOp, DAG.getConstant(C1.trunc(32).sext(64),
8967  dl, OpVT), Cond);
8968 }
8969 
8970 static SDValue
8971 performSIGN_EXTEND_INREGCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
8972  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
8973  SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
8974  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8975 
8976  // Fold (sext_inreg (fmv_x_anyexth X), i16) -> (fmv_x_signexth X)
8977  if (Src.getOpcode() == RISCVISD::FMV_X_ANYEXTH &&
8978  cast<VTSDNode>(N->getOperand(1))->getVT().bitsGE(MVT::i16))
8979  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FMV_X_SIGNEXTH, SDLoc(N), VT,
8980  Src.getOperand(0));
8981 
8982  return SDValue();
8983 }
8984 
8985 namespace {
8986 // Forward declaration of the structure holding the necessary information to
8987 // apply a combine.
8988 struct CombineResult;
8989 
8990 /// Helper class for folding sign/zero extensions.
8991 /// In particular, this class is used for the following combines:
8992 /// add_vl -> vwadd(u) | vwadd(u)_w
8993 /// sub_vl -> vwsub(u) | vwsub(u)_w
8994 /// mul_vl -> vwmul(u) | vwmul_su
8995 ///
8996 /// An object of this class represents an operand of the operation we want to
8997 /// combine.
8998 /// E.g., when trying to combine `mul_vl a, b`, we will have one instance of
8999 /// NodeExtensionHelper for `a` and one for `b`.
9000 ///
9001 /// This class abstracts away how the extension is materialized and
9002 /// how its Mask, VL, number of users affect the combines.
9003 ///
9004 /// In particular:
9005 /// - VWADD_W is conceptually == add(op0, sext(op1))
9006 /// - VWADDU_W == add(op0, zext(op1))
9007 /// - VWSUB_W == sub(op0, sext(op1))
9008 /// - VWSUBU_W == sub(op0, zext(op1))
9009 ///
9010 /// And VMV_V_X_VL, depending on the value, is conceptually equivalent to
9011 /// zext|sext(smaller_value).
9012 struct NodeExtensionHelper {
9013  /// Records if this operand is like being zero extended.
9014  bool SupportsZExt;
9015  /// Records if this operand is like being sign extended.
9016  /// Note: SupportsZExt and SupportsSExt are not mutually exclusive. For
9017  /// instance, a splat constant (e.g., 3), would support being both sign and
9018  /// zero extended.
9019  bool SupportsSExt;
9020  /// This boolean captures whether we care if this operand would still be
9021  /// around after the folding happens.
9022  bool EnforceOneUse;
9023  /// Records if this operand's mask needs to match the mask of the operation
9024  /// that it will fold into.
9025  bool CheckMask;
9026  /// Value of the Mask for this operand.
9027  /// It may be SDValue().
9028  SDValue Mask;
9029  /// Value of the vector length operand.
9030  /// It may be SDValue().
9031  SDValue VL;
9032  /// Original value that this NodeExtensionHelper represents.
9033  SDValue OrigOperand;
9034 
9035  /// Get the value feeding the extension or the value itself.
9036  /// E.g., for zext(a), this would return a.
9037  SDValue getSource() const {
9038  switch (OrigOperand.getOpcode()) {
9039  case RISCVISD::VSEXT_VL:
9040  case RISCVISD::VZEXT_VL:
9041  return OrigOperand.getOperand(0);
9042  default:
9043  return OrigOperand;
9044  }
9045  }
9046 
9047  /// Check if this instance represents a splat.
9048  bool isSplat() const {
9049  return OrigOperand.getOpcode() == RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL;
9050  }
9051 
9052  /// Get or create a value that can feed \p Root with the given extension \p
9053  /// SExt. If \p SExt is None, this returns the source of this operand.
9054  /// \see ::getSource().
9055  SDValue getOrCreateExtendedOp(const SDNode *Root, SelectionDAG &DAG,
9056  std::optional<bool> SExt) const {
9057  if (!SExt.has_value())
9058  return OrigOperand;
9059 
9060  MVT NarrowVT = getNarrowType(Root);
9061 
9062  SDValue Source = getSource();
9063  if (Source.getValueType() == NarrowVT)
9064  return Source;
9065 
9066  unsigned ExtOpc = *SExt ? RISCVISD::VSEXT_VL : RISCVISD::VZEXT_VL;
9067 
9068  // If we need an extension, we should be changing the type.
9069  SDLoc DL(Root);
9070  auto [Mask, VL] = getMaskAndVL(Root);
9071  switch (OrigOperand.getOpcode()) {
9072  case RISCVISD::VSEXT_VL:
9073  case RISCVISD::VZEXT_VL:
9074  return DAG.getNode(ExtOpc, DL, NarrowVT, Source, Mask, VL);
9075  case RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL:
9076  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, NarrowVT,
9077  DAG.getUNDEF(NarrowVT), Source.getOperand(1), VL);
9078  default:
9079  // Other opcodes can only come from the original LHS of VW(ADD|SUB)_W_VL
9080  // and that operand should already have the right NarrowVT so no
9081  // extension should be required at this point.
9082  llvm_unreachable("Unsupported opcode");
9083  }
9084  }
9085 
9086  /// Helper function to get the narrow type for \p Root.
9087  /// The narrow type is the type of \p Root where we divided the size of each
9088  /// element by 2. E.g., if Root's type <2xi16> -> narrow type <2xi8>.
9089  /// \pre The size of the type of the elements of Root must be a multiple of 2
9090  /// and be greater than 16.
9091  static MVT getNarrowType(const SDNode *Root) {
9092  MVT VT = Root->getSimpleValueType(0);
9093 
9094  // Determine the narrow size.
9095  unsigned NarrowSize = VT.getScalarSizeInBits() / 2;
9096  assert(NarrowSize >= 8 && "Trying to extend something we can't represent");
9097  MVT NarrowVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::getIntegerVT(NarrowSize),
9098  VT.getVectorElementCount());
9099  return NarrowVT;
9100  }
9101 
9102  /// Return the opcode required to materialize the folding of the sign
9103  /// extensions (\p IsSExt == true) or zero extensions (IsSExt == false) for
9104  /// both operands for \p Opcode.
9105  /// Put differently, get the opcode to materialize:
9106  /// - ISExt == true: \p Opcode(sext(a), sext(b)) -> newOpcode(a, b)
9107  /// - ISExt == false: \p Opcode(zext(a), zext(b)) -> newOpcode(a, b)
9108  /// \pre \p Opcode represents a supported root (\see ::isSupportedRoot()).
9109  static unsigned getSameExtensionOpcode(unsigned Opcode, bool IsSExt) {
9110  switch (Opcode) {
9111  case RISCVISD::ADD_VL:
9112  case RISCVISD::VWADD_W_VL:
9113  case RISCVISD::VWADDU_W_VL:
9114  return IsSExt ? RISCVISD::VWADD_VL : RISCVISD::VWADDU_VL;
9115  case RISCVISD::MUL_VL:
9116  return IsSExt ? RISCVISD::VWMUL_VL : RISCVISD::VWMULU_VL;
9117  case RISCVISD::SUB_VL:
9118  case RISCVISD::VWSUB_W_VL:
9119  case RISCVISD::VWSUBU_W_VL:
9120  return IsSExt ? RISCVISD::VWSUB_VL : RISCVISD::VWSUBU_VL;
9121  default:
9122  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected opcode");
9123  }
9124  }
9125 
9126  /// Get the opcode to materialize \p Opcode(sext(a), zext(b)) ->
9127  /// newOpcode(a, b).
9128  static unsigned getSUOpcode(unsigned Opcode) {
9129  assert(Opcode == RISCVISD::MUL_VL && "SU is only supported for MUL");
9130  return RISCVISD::VWMULSU_VL;
9131  }
9132 
9133  /// Get the opcode to materialize \p Opcode(a, s|zext(b)) ->
9134  /// newOpcode(a, b).
9135  static unsigned getWOpcode(unsigned Opcode, bool IsSExt) {
9136  switch (Opcode) {
9137  case RISCVISD::ADD_VL:
9138  return IsSExt ? RISCVISD::VWADD_W_VL : RISCVISD::VWADDU_W_VL;
9139  case RISCVISD::SUB_VL:
9140  return IsSExt ? RISCVISD::VWSUB_W_VL : RISCVISD::VWSUBU_W_VL;
9141  default:
9142  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected opcode");
9143  }
9144  }
9145 
9146  using CombineToTry = std::function<std::optional<CombineResult>(
9147  SDNode * /*Root*/, const NodeExtensionHelper & /*LHS*/,
9148  const NodeExtensionHelper & /*RHS*/)>;
9149 
9150  /// Check if this node needs to be fully folded or extended for all users.
9151  bool needToPromoteOtherUsers() const { return EnforceOneUse; }
9152 
9153  /// Helper method to set the various fields of this struct based on the
9154  /// type of \p Root.
9155  void fillUpExtensionSupport(SDNode *Root, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
9156  SupportsZExt = false;
9157  SupportsSExt = false;
9158  EnforceOneUse = true;
9159  CheckMask = true;
9160  switch (OrigOperand.getOpcode()) {
9161  case RISCVISD::VZEXT_VL:
9162  SupportsZExt = true;
9163  Mask = OrigOperand.getOperand(1);
9164  VL = OrigOperand.getOperand(2);
9165  break;
9166  case RISCVISD::VSEXT_VL:
9167  SupportsSExt = true;
9168  Mask = OrigOperand.getOperand(1);
9169  VL = OrigOperand.getOperand(2);
9170  break;
9171  case RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL: {
9172  // Historically, we didn't care about splat values not disappearing during
9173  // combines.
9174  EnforceOneUse = false;
9175  CheckMask = false;
9176  VL = OrigOperand.getOperand(2);
9177 
9178  // The operand is a splat of a scalar.
9179 
9180  // The pasthru must be undef for tail agnostic.
9181  if (!OrigOperand.getOperand(0).isUndef())
9182  break;
9183 
9184  // Get the scalar value.
9185  SDValue Op = OrigOperand.getOperand(1);
9186 
9187  // See if we have enough sign bits or zero bits in the scalar to use a
9188  // widening opcode by splatting to smaller element size.
9189  MVT VT = Root->getSimpleValueType(0);
9190  unsigned EltBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
9191  unsigned ScalarBits = Op.getValueSizeInBits();
9192  // Make sure we're getting all element bits from the scalar register.
9193  // FIXME: Support implicit sign extension of vmv.v.x?
9194  if (ScalarBits < EltBits)
9195  break;
9196 
9197  unsigned NarrowSize = VT.getScalarSizeInBits() / 2;
9198  // If the narrow type cannot be expressed with a legal VMV,
9199  // this is not a valid candidate.
9200  if (NarrowSize < 8)
9201  break;
9202 
9203  if (DAG.ComputeMaxSignificantBits(Op) <= NarrowSize)
9204  SupportsSExt = true;
9205  if (DAG.MaskedValueIsZero(Op,
9206  APInt::getBitsSetFrom(ScalarBits, NarrowSize)))
9207  SupportsZExt = true;
9208  break;
9209  }
9210  default:
9211  break;
9212  }
9213  }
9214 
9215  /// Check if \p Root supports any extension folding combines.
9216  static bool isSupportedRoot(const SDNode *Root) {
9217  switch (Root->getOpcode()) {
9218  case RISCVISD::ADD_VL:
9219  case RISCVISD::MUL_VL:
9220  case RISCVISD::VWADD_W_VL:
9221  case RISCVISD::VWADDU_W_VL:
9222  case RISCVISD::SUB_VL:
9223  case RISCVISD::VWSUB_W_VL:
9224  case RISCVISD::VWSUBU_W_VL:
9225  return true;
9226  default:
9227  return false;
9228  }
9229  }
9230 
9231  /// Build a NodeExtensionHelper for \p Root.getOperand(\p OperandIdx).
9232  NodeExtensionHelper(SDNode *Root, unsigned OperandIdx, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
9233  assert(isSupportedRoot(Root) && "Trying to build an helper with an "
9234  "unsupported root");
9235  assert(OperandIdx < 2 && "Requesting something else than LHS or RHS");
9236  OrigOperand = Root->getOperand(OperandIdx);
9237 
9238  unsigned Opc = Root->getOpcode();
9239  switch (Opc) {
9240  // We consider VW<ADD|SUB>(U)_W(LHS, RHS) as if they were
9241  // <ADD|SUB>(LHS, S|ZEXT(RHS))
9242  case RISCVISD::VWADD_W_VL:
9243  case RISCVISD::VWADDU_W_VL:
9244  case RISCVISD::VWSUB_W_VL:
9245  case RISCVISD::VWSUBU_W_VL:
9246  if (OperandIdx == 1) {
9247  SupportsZExt =
9248  Opc == RISCVISD::VWADDU_W_VL || Opc == RISCVISD::VWSUBU_W_VL;
9249  SupportsSExt = !SupportsZExt;
9250  std::tie(Mask, VL) = getMaskAndVL(Root);
9251  CheckMask = true;
9252  // There's no existing extension here, so we don't have to worry about
9253  // making sure it gets removed.
9254  EnforceOneUse = false;
9255  break;
9256  }
9257  [[fallthrough]];
9258  default:
9259  fillUpExtensionSupport(Root, DAG);
9260  break;
9261  }
9262  }
9263 
9264  /// Check if this operand is compatible with the given vector length \p VL.
9265  bool isVLCompatible(SDValue VL) const {
9266  return this->VL != SDValue() && this->VL == VL;
9267  }
9268 
9269  /// Check if this operand is compatible with the given \p Mask.
9270  bool isMaskCompatible(SDValue Mask) const {
9271  return !CheckMask || (this->Mask != SDValue() && this->Mask == Mask);
9272  }
9273 
9274  /// Helper function to get the Mask and VL from \p Root.
9275  static std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> getMaskAndVL(const SDNode *Root) {
9276  assert(isSupportedRoot(Root) && "Unexpected root");
9277  return std::make_pair(Root->getOperand(3), Root->getOperand(4));
9278  }
9279 
9280  /// Check if the Mask and VL of this operand are compatible with \p Root.
9281  bool areVLAndMaskCompatible(const SDNode *Root) const {
9282  auto [Mask, VL] = getMaskAndVL(Root);
9283  return isMaskCompatible(Mask) && isVLCompatible(VL);
9284  }
9285 
9286  /// Helper function to check if \p N is commutative with respect to the
9287  /// foldings that are supported by this class.
9288  static bool isCommutative(const SDNode *N) {
9289  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
9290  case RISCVISD::ADD_VL:
9291  case RISCVISD::MUL_VL:
9292  case RISCVISD::VWADD_W_VL:
9293  case RISCVISD::VWADDU_W_VL:
9294  return true;
9295  case RISCVISD::SUB_VL:
9296  case RISCVISD::VWSUB_W_VL:
9297  case RISCVISD::VWSUBU_W_VL:
9298  return false;
9299  default:
9300  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected opcode");
9301  }
9302  }
9303 
9304  /// Get a list of combine to try for folding extensions in \p Root.
9305  /// Note that each returned CombineToTry function doesn't actually modify
9306  /// anything. Instead they produce an optional CombineResult that if not None,
9307  /// need to be materialized for the combine to be applied.
9308  /// \see CombineResult::materialize.
9309  /// If the related CombineToTry function returns std::nullopt, that means the
9310  /// combine didn't match.
9311  static SmallVector<CombineToTry> getSupportedFoldings(const SDNode *Root);
9312 };
9313 
9314 /// Helper structure that holds all the necessary information to materialize a
9315 /// combine that does some extension folding.
9316 struct CombineResult {
9317  /// Opcode to be generated when materializing the combine.
9318  unsigned TargetOpcode;
9319  // No value means no extension is needed. If extension is needed, the value
9320  // indicates if it needs to be sign extended.
9321  std::optional<bool> SExtLHS;
9322  std::optional<bool> SExtRHS;
9323  /// Root of the combine.
9324  SDNode *Root;
9325  /// LHS of the TargetOpcode.
9326  NodeExtensionHelper LHS;
9327  /// RHS of the TargetOpcode.
9328  NodeExtensionHelper RHS;
9329 
9330  CombineResult(unsigned TargetOpcode, SDNode *Root,
9331  const NodeExtensionHelper &LHS, std::optional<bool> SExtLHS,
9332  const NodeExtensionHelper &RHS, std::optional<bool> SExtRHS)
9333  : TargetOpcode(TargetOpcode), SExtLHS(SExtLHS), SExtRHS(SExtRHS),
9334  Root(Root), LHS(LHS), RHS(RHS) {}
9335 
9336  /// Return a value that uses TargetOpcode and that can be used to replace
9337  /// Root.
9338  /// The actual replacement is *not* done in that method.
9339  SDValue materialize(SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9340  SDValue Mask, VL, Merge;
9341  std::tie(Mask, VL) = NodeExtensionHelper::getMaskAndVL(Root);
9342  Merge = Root->getOperand(2);
9343  return DAG.getNode(TargetOpcode, SDLoc(Root), Root->getValueType(0),
9344  LHS.getOrCreateExtendedOp(Root, DAG, SExtLHS),
9345  RHS.getOrCreateExtendedOp(Root, DAG, SExtRHS), Merge,
9346  Mask, VL);
9347  }
9348 };
9349 
9350 /// Check if \p Root follows a pattern Root(ext(LHS), ext(RHS))
9351 /// where `ext` is the same for both LHS and RHS (i.e., both are sext or both
9352 /// are zext) and LHS and RHS can be folded into Root.
9353 /// AllowSExt and AllozZExt define which form `ext` can take in this pattern.
9354 ///
9355 /// \note If the pattern can match with both zext and sext, the returned
9356 /// CombineResult will feature the zext result.
9357 ///
9358 /// \returns std::nullopt if the pattern doesn't match or a CombineResult that
9359 /// can be used to apply the pattern.
9360 static std::optional<CombineResult>
9361 canFoldToVWWithSameExtensionImpl(SDNode *Root, const NodeExtensionHelper &LHS,
9362  const NodeExtensionHelper &RHS, bool AllowSExt,
9363  bool AllowZExt) {
9364  assert((AllowSExt || AllowZExt) && "Forgot to set what you want?");
9365  if (!LHS.areVLAndMaskCompatible(Root) || !RHS.areVLAndMaskCompatible(Root))
9366  return std::nullopt;
9367  if (AllowZExt && LHS.SupportsZExt && RHS.SupportsZExt)
9368  return CombineResult(NodeExtensionHelper::getSameExtensionOpcode(
9369  Root->getOpcode(), /*IsSExt=*/false),
9370  Root, LHS, /*SExtLHS=*/false, RHS,
9371  /*SExtRHS=*/false);
9372  if (AllowSExt && LHS.SupportsSExt && RHS.SupportsSExt)
9373  return CombineResult(NodeExtensionHelper::getSameExtensionOpcode(
9374  Root->getOpcode(), /*IsSExt=*/true),
9375  Root, LHS, /*SExtLHS=*/true, RHS,
9376  /*SExtRHS=*/true);
9377  return std::nullopt;
9378 }
9379 
9380 /// Check if \p Root follows a pattern Root(ext(LHS), ext(RHS))
9381 /// where `ext` is the same for both LHS and RHS (i.e., both are sext or both
9382 /// are zext) and LHS and RHS can be folded into Root.
9383 ///
9384 /// \returns std::nullopt if the pattern doesn't match or a CombineResult that
9385 /// can be used to apply the pattern.
9386 static std::optional<CombineResult>
9387 canFoldToVWWithSameExtension(SDNode *Root, const NodeExtensionHelper &LHS,
9388  const NodeExtensionHelper &RHS) {
9389  return canFoldToVWWithSameExtensionImpl(Root, LHS, RHS, /*AllowSExt=*/true,
9390  /*AllowZExt=*/true);
9391 }
9392 
9393 /// Check if \p Root follows a pattern Root(LHS, ext(RHS))
9394 ///
9395 /// \returns std::nullopt if the pattern doesn't match or a CombineResult that
9396 /// can be used to apply the pattern.
9397 static std::optional<CombineResult>
9398 canFoldToVW_W(SDNode *Root, const NodeExtensionHelper &LHS,
9399  const NodeExtensionHelper &RHS) {
9400  if (!RHS.areVLAndMaskCompatible(Root))
9401  return std::nullopt;
9402 
9403  // FIXME: Is it useful to form a vwadd.wx or vwsub.wx if it removes a scalar
9404  // sext/zext?
9405  // Control this behavior behind an option (AllowSplatInVW_W) for testing
9406  // purposes.
9407  if (RHS.SupportsZExt && (!RHS.isSplat() || AllowSplatInVW_W))
9408  return CombineResult(
9409  NodeExtensionHelper::getWOpcode(Root->getOpcode(), /*IsSExt=*/false),
9410  Root, LHS, /*SExtLHS=*/std::nullopt, RHS, /*SExtRHS=*/false);
9411  if (RHS.SupportsSExt && (!RHS.isSplat() || AllowSplatInVW_W))
9412  return CombineResult(
9413  NodeExtensionHelper::getWOpcode(Root->getOpcode(), /*IsSExt=*/true),
9414  Root, LHS, /*SExtLHS=*/std::nullopt, RHS, /*SExtRHS=*/true);
9415  return std::nullopt;
9416 }
9417 
9418 /// Check if \p Root follows a pattern Root(sext(LHS), sext(RHS))
9419 ///
9420 /// \returns std::nullopt if the pattern doesn't match or a CombineResult that
9421 /// can be used to apply the pattern.
9422 static std::optional<CombineResult>
9423 canFoldToVWWithSEXT(SDNode *Root, const NodeExtensionHelper &LHS,
9424  const NodeExtensionHelper &RHS) {
9425  return canFoldToVWWithSameExtensionImpl(Root, LHS, RHS, /*AllowSExt=*/true,
9426  /*AllowZExt=*/false);
9427 }
9428 
9429 /// Check if \p Root follows a pattern Root(zext(LHS), zext(RHS))
9430 ///
9431 /// \returns std::nullopt if the pattern doesn't match or a CombineResult that
9432 /// can be used to apply the pattern.
9433 static std::optional<CombineResult>
9434 canFoldToVWWithZEXT(SDNode *Root, const NodeExtensionHelper &LHS,
9435  const NodeExtensionHelper &RHS) {
9436  return canFoldToVWWithSameExtensionImpl(Root, LHS, RHS, /*AllowSExt=*/false,
9437  /*AllowZExt=*/true);
9438 }
9439 
9440 /// Check if \p Root follows a pattern Root(sext(LHS), zext(RHS))
9441 ///
9442 /// \returns std::nullopt if the pattern doesn't match or a CombineResult that
9443 /// can be used to apply the pattern.
9444 static std::optional<CombineResult>
9445 canFoldToVW_SU(SDNode *Root, const NodeExtensionHelper &LHS,
9446  const NodeExtensionHelper &RHS) {
9447  if (!LHS.SupportsSExt || !RHS.SupportsZExt)
9448  return std::nullopt;
9449  if (!LHS.areVLAndMaskCompatible(Root) || !RHS.areVLAndMaskCompatible(Root))
9450  return std::nullopt;
9451  return CombineResult(NodeExtensionHelper::getSUOpcode(Root->getOpcode()),
9452  Root, LHS, /*SExtLHS=*/true, RHS, /*SExtRHS=*/false);
9453 }
9454 
9455 SmallVector<NodeExtensionHelper::CombineToTry>
9456 NodeExtensionHelper::getSupportedFoldings(const SDNode *Root) {
9457  SmallVector<CombineToTry> Strategies;
9458  switch (Root->getOpcode()) {
9459  case RISCVISD::ADD_VL:
9460  case RISCVISD::SUB_VL:
9461  // add|sub -> vwadd(u)|vwsub(u)
9462  Strategies.push_back(canFoldToVWWithSameExtension);
9463  // add|sub -> vwadd(u)_w|vwsub(u)_w
9464  Strategies.push_back(canFoldToVW_W);
9465  break;
9466  case RISCVISD::MUL_VL:
9467  // mul -> vwmul(u)
9468  Strategies.push_back(canFoldToVWWithSameExtension);
9469  // mul -> vwmulsu
9470  Strategies.push_back(canFoldToVW_SU);
9471  break;
9472  case RISCVISD::VWADD_W_VL:
9473  case RISCVISD::VWSUB_W_VL:
9474  // vwadd_w|vwsub_w -> vwadd|vwsub
9475  Strategies.push_back(canFoldToVWWithSEXT);
9476  break;
9477  case RISCVISD::VWADDU_W_VL:
9478  case RISCVISD::VWSUBU_W_VL:
9479  // vwaddu_w|vwsubu_w -> vwaddu|vwsubu
9480  Strategies.push_back(canFoldToVWWithZEXT);
9481  break;
9482  default:
9483  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected opcode");
9484  }
9485  return Strategies;
9486 }
9487 } // End anonymous namespace.
9488 
9489 /// Combine a binary operation to its equivalent VW or VW_W form.
9490 /// The supported combines are:
9491 /// add_vl -> vwadd(u) | vwadd(u)_w
9492 /// sub_vl -> vwsub(u) | vwsub(u)_w
9493 /// mul_vl -> vwmul(u) | vwmul_su
9494 /// vwadd_w(u) -> vwadd(u)
9495 /// vwub_w(u) -> vwadd(u)
9496 static SDValue
9497 combineBinOp_VLToVWBinOp_VL(SDNode *N, TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) {
9498  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
9499 
9500  assert(NodeExtensionHelper::isSupportedRoot(N) &&
9501  "Shouldn't have called this method");
9502  SmallVector<SDNode *> Worklist;
9503  SmallSet<SDNode *, 8> Inserted;
9504  Worklist.push_back(N);
9505  Inserted.insert(N);
9506  SmallVector<CombineResult> CombinesToApply;
9507 
9508  while (!Worklist.empty()) {
9509  SDNode *Root = Worklist.pop_back_val();
9510  if (!NodeExtensionHelper::isSupportedRoot(Root))
9511  return SDValue();
9512 
9513  NodeExtensionHelper LHS(N, 0, DAG);
9514  NodeExtensionHelper RHS(N, 1, DAG);
9515  auto AppendUsersIfNeeded = [&Worklist,
9516  &Inserted](const NodeExtensionHelper &Op) {
9517  if (Op.needToPromoteOtherUsers()) {
9518  for (SDNode *TheUse : Op.OrigOperand->uses()) {
9519  if (Inserted.insert(TheUse).second)
9520  Worklist.push_back(TheUse);
9521  }
9522  }
9523  };
9524 
9525  // Control the compile time by limiting the number of node we look at in
9526  // total.
9527  if (Inserted.size() > ExtensionMaxWebSize)
9528  return SDValue();
9529 
9530  SmallVector<NodeExtensionHelper::CombineToTry> FoldingStrategies =
9531  NodeExtensionHelper::getSupportedFoldings(N);
9532 
9533  assert(!FoldingStrategies.empty() && "Nothing to be folded");
9534  bool Matched = false;
9535  for (int Attempt = 0;
9536  (Attempt != 1 + NodeExtensionHelper::isCommutative(N)) && !Matched;
9537  ++Attempt) {
9538 
9539  for (NodeExtensionHelper::CombineToTry FoldingStrategy :
9540  FoldingStrategies) {
9541  std::optional<CombineResult> Res = FoldingStrategy(N, LHS, RHS);
9542  if (Res) {
9543  Matched = true;
9544  CombinesToApply.push_back(*Res);
9545  // All the inputs that are extended need to be folded, otherwise
9546  // we would be leaving the old input (since it is may still be used),
9547  // and the new one.
9548  if (Res->SExtLHS.has_value())
9549  AppendUsersIfNeeded(LHS);
9550  if (Res->SExtRHS.has_value())
9551  AppendUsersIfNeeded(RHS);
9552  break;
9553  }
9554  }
9555  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
9556  }
9557  // Right now we do an all or nothing approach.
9558  if (!Matched)
9559  return SDValue();
9560  }
9561  // Store the value for the replacement of the input node separately.
9562  SDValue InputRootReplacement;
9563  // We do the RAUW after we materialize all the combines, because some replaced
9564  // nodes may be feeding some of the yet-to-be-replaced nodes. Put differently,
9565  // some of these nodes may appear in the NodeExtensionHelpers of some of the
9566  // yet-to-be-visited CombinesToApply roots.
9567  SmallVector<std::pair<SDValue, SDValue>> ValuesToReplace;
9568  ValuesToReplace.reserve(CombinesToApply.size());
9569  for (CombineResult Res : CombinesToApply) {
9570  SDValue NewValue = Res.materialize(DAG);
9571  if (!InputRootReplacement) {
9572  assert(Res.Root == N &&
9573  "First element is expected to be the current node");
9574  InputRootReplacement = NewValue;
9575  } else {
9576  ValuesToReplace.emplace_back(SDValue(Res.Root, 0), NewValue);
9577  }
9578  }
9579  for (std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> OldNewValues : ValuesToReplace) {
9580  DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(OldNewValues.first, OldNewValues.second);
9581  DCI.AddToWorklist(OldNewValues.second.getNode());
9582  }
9583  return InputRootReplacement;
9584 }
9585 
9586 // Fold
9587 // (fp_to_int (froundeven X)) -> fcvt X, rne
9588 // (fp_to_int (ftrunc X)) -> fcvt X, rtz
9589 // (fp_to_int (ffloor X)) -> fcvt X, rdn
9590 // (fp_to_int (fceil X)) -> fcvt X, rup
9591 // (fp_to_int (fround X)) -> fcvt X, rmm
9592 static SDValue performFP_TO_INTCombine(SDNode *N,
9593  TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
9594  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
9595  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
9596  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
9597  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
9598 
9599  SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
9600 
9601  // Ensure the FP type is legal.
9602  if (!TLI.isTypeLegal(Src.getValueType()))
9603  return SDValue();
9604 
9605  // Don't do this for f16 with Zfhmin and not Zfh.
9606  if (Src.getValueType() == MVT::f16 && !Subtarget.hasStdExtZfh())
9607  return SDValue();
9608 
9609  RISCVFPRndMode::RoundingMode FRM = matchRoundingOp(Src.getOpcode());
9610  if (FRM == RISCVFPRndMode::Invalid)
9611  return SDValue();
9612 
9613  SDLoc DL(N);
9614  bool IsSigned = N->getOpcode() == ISD::FP_TO_SINT;
9615  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
9616 
9617  if (VT.isVector() && TLI.isTypeLegal(VT)) {
9618  MVT SrcVT = Src.getSimpleValueType();
9619  MVT SrcContainerVT = SrcVT;
9620  MVT ContainerVT = VT.getSimpleVT();
9621  SDValue XVal = Src.getOperand(0);
9622 
9623  // For widening and narrowing conversions we just combine it into a
9624  // VFCVT_..._VL node, as there are no specific VFWCVT/VFNCVT VL nodes. They
9625  // end up getting lowered to their appropriate pseudo instructions based on
9626  // their operand types
9627  if (VT.getScalarSizeInBits() > SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits() * 2 ||
9628  VT.getScalarSizeInBits() * 2 < SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits())
9629  return SDValue();
9630 
9631  // Make fixed-length vectors scalable first
9632  if (SrcVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
9633  SrcContainerVT = getContainerForFixedLengthVector(DAG, SrcVT, Subtarget);
9634  XVal = convertToScalableVector(SrcContainerVT, XVal, DAG, Subtarget);
9635  ContainerVT =
9636  getContainerForFixedLengthVector(DAG, ContainerVT, Subtarget);
9637  }
9638 
9639  auto [Mask, VL] =
9640  getDefaultVLOps(SrcVT, SrcContainerVT, DL, DAG, Subtarget);
9641 
9642  SDValue FpToInt;
9643  if (FRM == RISCVFPRndMode::RTZ) {
9644  // Use the dedicated trunc static rounding mode if we're truncating so we
9645  // don't need to generate calls to fsrmi/fsrm
9646  unsigned Opc =
9647  IsSigned ? RISCVISD::VFCVT_RTZ_X_F_VL : RISCVISD::VFCVT_RTZ_XU_F_VL;
9648  FpToInt = DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, ContainerVT, XVal, Mask, VL);
9649  } else {
9650  unsigned Opc =
9651  IsSigned ? RISCVISD::VFCVT_RM_X_F_VL : RISCVISD::VFCVT_RM_XU_F_VL;
9652  FpToInt = DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, ContainerVT, XVal, Mask,
9653  DAG.getTargetConstant(FRM, DL, XLenVT), VL);
9654  }
9655 
9656  // If converted from fixed-length to scalable, convert back
9657  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector())
9658  FpToInt = convertFromScalableVector(VT, FpToInt, DAG, Subtarget);
9659 
9660  return FpToInt;
9661  }
9662 
9663  // Only handle XLen or i32 types. Other types narrower than XLen will
9664  // eventually be legalized to XLenVT.
9665  if (VT != MVT::i32 && VT != XLenVT)
9666  return SDValue();
9667 
9668  unsigned Opc;
9669  if (VT == XLenVT)
9670  Opc = IsSigned ? RISCVISD::FCVT_X : RISCVISD::FCVT_XU;
9671  else
9672  Opc = IsSigned ? RISCVISD::FCVT_W_RV64 : RISCVISD::FCVT_WU_RV64;
9673 
9674  SDValue FpToInt = DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, XLenVT, Src.getOperand(0),
9675  DAG.getTargetConstant(FRM, DL, XLenVT));
9676  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VT, FpToInt);
9677 }
9678 
9679 // Fold
9680 // (fp_to_int_sat (froundeven X)) -> (select X == nan, 0, (fcvt X, rne))
9681 // (fp_to_int_sat (ftrunc X)) -> (select X == nan, 0, (fcvt X, rtz))
9682 // (fp_to_int_sat (ffloor X)) -> (select X == nan, 0, (fcvt X, rdn))
9683 // (fp_to_int_sat (fceil X)) -> (select X == nan, 0, (fcvt X, rup))
9684 // (fp_to_int_sat (fround X)) -> (select X == nan, 0, (fcvt X, rmm))
9685 static SDValue performFP_TO_INT_SATCombine(SDNode *N,
9686  TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
9687  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
9688  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
9689  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
9690  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
9691 
9692  // Only handle XLen types. Other types narrower than XLen will eventually be
9693  // legalized to XLenVT.
9694  EVT DstVT = N->getValueType(0);
9695  if (DstVT != XLenVT)
9696  return SDValue();
9697 
9698  SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
9699 
9700  // Ensure the FP type is also legal.
9701  if (!TLI.isTypeLegal(Src.getValueType()))
9702  return SDValue();
9703 
9704  // Don't do this for f16 with Zfhmin and not Zfh.
9705  if (Src.getValueType() == MVT::f16 && !Subtarget.hasStdExtZfh())
9706  return SDValue();
9707 
9708  EVT SatVT = cast<VTSDNode>(N->getOperand(1))->getVT();
9709 
9710  RISCVFPRndMode::RoundingMode FRM = matchRoundingOp(Src.getOpcode());
9711  if (FRM == RISCVFPRndMode::Invalid)
9712  return SDValue();
9713 
9714  bool IsSigned = N->getOpcode() == ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT;
9715 
9716  unsigned Opc;
9717  if (SatVT == DstVT)
9718  Opc = IsSigned ? RISCVISD::FCVT_X : RISCVISD::FCVT_XU;
9719  else if (DstVT == MVT::i64 && SatVT == MVT::i32)
9720  Opc = IsSigned ? RISCVISD::FCVT_W_RV64 : RISCVISD::FCVT_WU_RV64;
9721  else
9722  return SDValue();
9723  // FIXME: Support other SatVTs by clamping before or after the conversion.
9724 
9725  Src = Src.getOperand(0);
9726 
9727  SDLoc DL(N);
9728  SDValue FpToInt = DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, XLenVT, Src,
9729  DAG.getTargetConstant(FRM, DL, XLenVT));
9730 
9731  // fcvt.wu.* sign extends bit 31 on RV64. FP_TO_UINT_SAT expects to zero
9732  // extend.
9733  if (Opc == RISCVISD::FCVT_WU_RV64)
9734  FpToInt = DAG.getZeroExtendInReg(FpToInt, DL, MVT::i32);
9735 
9736  // RISCV FP-to-int conversions saturate to the destination register size, but
9737  // don't produce 0 for nan.
9738  SDValue ZeroInt = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, DstVT);
9739  return DAG.getSelectCC(DL, Src, Src, ZeroInt, FpToInt, ISD::CondCode::SETUO);
9740 }
9741 
9742 // Combine (bitreverse (bswap X)) to the BREV8 GREVI encoding if the type is
9743 // smaller than XLenVT.
9744 static SDValue performBITREVERSECombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
9745  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
9746  assert(Subtarget.hasStdExtZbkb() && "Unexpected extension");
9747 
9748  SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
9749  if (Src.getOpcode() != ISD::BSWAP)
9750  return SDValue();
9751 
9752  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
9753  if (!VT.isScalarInteger() || VT.getSizeInBits() >= Subtarget.getXLen() ||
9754  !llvm::has_single_bit<uint32_t>(VT.getSizeInBits()))
9755  return SDValue();
9756 
9757  SDLoc DL(N);
9758  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::BREV8, DL, VT, Src.getOperand(0));
9759 }
9760 
9761 // Convert from one FMA opcode to another based on whether we are negating the
9762 // multiply result and/or the accumulator.
9763 // NOTE: Only supports RVV operations with VL.
9764 static unsigned negateFMAOpcode(unsigned Opcode, bool NegMul, bool NegAcc) {
9765  assert((NegMul || NegAcc) && "Not negating anything?");
9766 
9767  // Negating the multiply result changes ADD<->SUB and toggles 'N'.
9768  if (NegMul) {
9769  // clang-format off
9770  switch (Opcode) {
9771  default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected opcode");
9772  case RISCVISD::VFMADD_VL: Opcode = RISCVISD::VFNMSUB_VL; break;
9773  case RISCVISD::VFNMSUB_VL: Opcode = RISCVISD::VFMADD_VL; break;
9774  case RISCVISD::VFNMADD_VL: Opcode = RISCVISD::VFMSUB_VL; break;
9775  case RISCVISD::VFMSUB_VL: Opcode = RISCVISD::VFNMADD_VL; break;
9776  }
9777  // clang-format on
9778  }
9779 
9780  // Negating the accumulator changes ADD<->SUB.
9781  if (NegAcc) {
9782  // clang-format off
9783  switch (Opcode) {
9784  default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected opcode");
9785  case RISCVISD::VFMADD_VL: Opcode = RISCVISD::VFMSUB_VL; break;
9786  case RISCVISD::VFMSUB_VL: Opcode = RISCVISD::VFMADD_VL; break;
9787  case RISCVISD::VFNMADD_VL: Opcode = RISCVISD::VFNMSUB_VL; break;
9788  case RISCVISD::VFNMSUB_VL: Opcode = RISCVISD::VFNMADD_VL; break;
9789  }
9790  // clang-format on
9791  }
9792 
9793  return Opcode;
9794 }
9795 
9796 static SDValue performSRACombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
9797  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
9798  assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRA && "Unexpected opcode");
9799 
9800  if (N->getValueType(0) != MVT::i64 || !Subtarget.is64Bit())
9801  return SDValue();
9802 
9803  if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1)))
9804  return SDValue();
9805  uint64_t ShAmt = N->getConstantOperandVal(1);
9806  if (ShAmt > 32)
9807  return SDValue();
9808 
9809  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
9810 
9811  // Combine (sra (sext_inreg (shl X, C1), i32), C2) ->
9812  // (sra (shl X, C1+32), C2+32) so it gets selected as SLLI+SRAI instead of
9813  // SLLIW+SRAIW. SLLI+SRAI have compressed forms.
9814  if (ShAmt < 32 &&
9815  N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG && N0.hasOneUse() &&
9816  cast<VTSDNode>(N0.getOperand(1))->getVT() == MVT::i32 &&
9817  N0.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::SHL && N0.getOperand(0).hasOneUse() &&
9818  isa<ConstantSDNode>(N0.getOperand(0).getOperand(1))) {
9819  uint64_t LShAmt = N0.getOperand(0).getConstantOperandVal(1);
9820  if (LShAmt < 32) {
9821  SDLoc ShlDL(N0.getOperand(0));
9822  SDValue Shl = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, ShlDL, MVT::i64,
9823  N0.getOperand(0).getOperand(0),
9824  DAG.getConstant(LShAmt + 32, ShlDL, MVT::i64));
9825  SDLoc DL(N);
9826  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, DL, MVT::i64, Shl,
9827  DAG.getConstant(ShAmt + 32, DL, MVT::i64));
9828  }
9829  }
9830 
9831  // Combine (sra (shl X, 32), 32 - C) -> (shl (sext_inreg X, i32), C)
9832  // FIXME: Should this be a generic combine? There's a similar combine on X86.
9833  //
9834  // Also try these folds where an add or sub is in the middle.
9835  // (sra (add (shl X, 32), C1), 32 - C) -> (shl (sext_inreg (add X, C1), C)
9836  // (sra (sub C1, (shl X, 32)), 32 - C) -> (shl (sext_inreg (sub C1, X), C)
9837  SDValue Shl;
9838  ConstantSDNode *AddC = nullptr;
9839 
9840  // We might have an ADD or SUB between the SRA and SHL.
9841  bool IsAdd = N0.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD;
9842  if ((IsAdd || N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SUB)) {
9843  // Other operand needs to be a constant we can modify.
9844  AddC = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0.getOperand(IsAdd ? 1 : 0));
9845  if (!AddC)
9846  return SDValue();
9847 
9848  // AddC needs to have at least 32 trailing zeros.
9849  if (AddC->getAPIntValue().countTrailingZeros() < 32)
9850  return SDValue();
9851 
9852  // All users should be a shift by constant less than or equal to 32. This
9853  // ensures we'll do this optimization for each of them to produce an
9854  // add/sub+sext_inreg they can all share.
9855  for (SDNode *U : N0->uses()) {
9856  if (U->getOpcode() != ISD::SRA ||
9857  !isa<ConstantSDNode>(U->getOperand(1)) ||
9858  cast<ConstantSDNode>(U->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue() > 32)
9859  return SDValue();
9860  }
9861 
9862  Shl = N0.getOperand(IsAdd ? 0 : 1);
9863  } else {
9864  // Not an ADD or SUB.
9865  Shl = N0;
9866  }
9867 
9868  // Look for a shift left by 32.
9869  if (Shl.getOpcode() != ISD::SHL || !isa<ConstantSDNode>(Shl.getOperand(1)) ||
9870  Shl.getConstantOperandVal(1) != 32)
9871  return SDValue();
9872 
9873  // We if we didn't look through an add/sub, then the shl should have one use.
9874  // If we did look through an add/sub, the sext_inreg we create is free so
9875  // we're only creating 2 new instructions. It's enough to only remove the
9876  // original sra+add/sub.
9877  if (!AddC && !Shl.hasOneUse())
9878  return SDValue();
9879 
9880  SDLoc DL(N);
9881  SDValue In = Shl.getOperand(0);
9882 
9883  // If we looked through an ADD or SUB, we need to rebuild it with the shifted
9884  // constant.
9885  if (AddC) {
9886  SDValue ShiftedAddC =
9887  DAG.getConstant(AddC->getAPIntValue().lshr(32), DL, MVT::i64);
9888  if (IsAdd)
9889  In = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, MVT::i64, In, ShiftedAddC);
9890  else
9891  In = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, MVT::i64, ShiftedAddC, In);
9892  }
9893 
9894  SDValue SExt = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, DL, MVT::i64, In,
9895  DAG.getValueType(MVT::i32));
9896  if (ShAmt == 32)
9897  return SExt;
9898 
9899  return DAG.getNode(
9900  ISD::SHL, DL, MVT::i64, SExt,
9901  DAG.getConstant(32 - ShAmt, DL, MVT::i64));
9902 }
9903 
9904 // Invert (and/or (set cc X, Y), (xor Z, 1)) to (or/and (set !cc X, Y)), Z) if
9905 // the result is used as the conditon of a br_cc or select_cc we can invert,
9906 // inverting the setcc is free, and Z is 0/1. Caller will invert the
9907 // br_cc/select_cc.
9908 static SDValue tryDemorganOfBooleanCondition(SDValue Cond, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
9909  bool IsAnd = Cond.getOpcode() == ISD::AND;
9910  if (!IsAnd && Cond.getOpcode() != ISD::OR)
9911  return SDValue();
9912 
9913  if (!Cond.hasOneUse())
9914  return SDValue();
9915 
9916  SDValue Setcc = Cond.getOperand(0);
9917  SDValue Xor = Cond.getOperand(1);
9918  // Canonicalize setcc to LHS.
9919  if (Setcc.getOpcode() != ISD::SETCC)
9920  std::swap(Setcc, Xor);
9921  // LHS should be a setcc and RHS should be an xor.
9922  if (Setcc.getOpcode() != ISD::SETCC || !Setcc.hasOneUse() ||
9923  Xor.getOpcode() != ISD::XOR || !Xor.hasOneUse())
9924  return SDValue();
9925 
9926  // If the condition is an And, SimplifyDemandedBits may have changed
9927  // (xor Z, 1) to (not Z).
9928  SDValue Xor1 = Xor.getOperand(1);
9929  if (!isOneConstant(Xor1) && !(IsAnd && isAllOnesConstant(Xor1)))
9930  return SDValue();
9931 
9932  EVT VT = Cond.getValueType();
9933  SDValue Xor0 = Xor.getOperand(0);
9934 
9935  // The LHS of the xor needs to be 0/1.
9936  APInt Mask = APInt::getBitsSetFrom(VT.getSizeInBits(), 1);
9937  if (!DAG.MaskedValueIsZero(Xor0, Mask))
9938  return SDValue();
9939 
9940  // We can only invert integer setccs.
9941  EVT SetCCOpVT = Setcc.getOperand(0).getValueType();
9942  if (!SetCCOpVT.isScalarInteger())
9943  return SDValue();
9944 
9945  ISD::CondCode CCVal = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(Setcc.getOperand(2))->get();
9946  if (ISD::isIntEqualitySetCC(CCVal)) {
9947  CCVal = ISD::getSetCCInverse(CCVal, SetCCOpVT);
9948  Setcc = DAG.getSetCC(SDLoc(Setcc), VT, Setcc.getOperand(0),
9949  Setcc.getOperand(1), CCVal);
9950  } else if (CCVal == ISD::SETLT && isNullConstant(Setcc.getOperand(0))) {
9951  // Invert (setlt 0, X) by converting to (setlt X, 1).
9952  Setcc = DAG.getSetCC(SDLoc(Setcc), VT, Setcc.getOperand(1),
9953  DAG.getConstant(1, SDLoc(Setcc), VT), CCVal);
9954  } else if (CCVal == ISD::SETLT && isOneConstant(Setcc.getOperand(1))) {
9955  // (setlt X, 1) by converting to (setlt 0, X).
9956  Setcc = DAG.getSetCC(SDLoc(Setcc), VT,
9957  DAG.getConstant(0, SDLoc(Setcc), VT),
9958  Setcc.getOperand(0), CCVal);
9959  } else
9960  return SDValue();
9961 
9962  unsigned Opc = IsAnd ? ISD::OR : ISD::AND;
9963  return DAG.getNode(Opc, SDLoc(Cond), VT, Setcc, Xor.getOperand(0));
9964 }
9965 
9966 // Perform common combines for BR_CC and SELECT_CC condtions.
9967 static bool combine_CC(SDValue &LHS, SDValue &RHS, SDValue &CC, const SDLoc &DL,
9968  SelectionDAG &DAG, const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
9969  ISD::CondCode CCVal = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(CC)->get();
9970 
9971  // As far as arithmetic right shift always saves the sign,
9972  // shift can be omitted.
9973  // Fold setlt (sra X, N), 0 -> setlt X, 0 and
9974  // setge (sra X, N), 0 -> setge X, 0
9975  if (auto *RHSConst = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS.getNode())) {
9976  if ((CCVal == ISD::SETGE || CCVal == ISD::SETLT) &&
9977  LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SRA && RHSConst->isZero()) {
9978  LHS = LHS.getOperand(0);
9979  return true;
9980  }
9981  }
9982 
9983  if (!ISD::isIntEqualitySetCC(CCVal))
9984  return false;
9985 
9986  // Fold ((setlt X, Y), 0, ne) -> (X, Y, lt)
9987  // Sometimes the setcc is introduced after br_cc/select_cc has been formed.
9988  if (LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC && isNullConstant(RHS) &&
9989  LHS.getOperand(0).getValueType() == Subtarget.getXLenVT()) {
9990  // If we're looking for eq 0 instead of ne 0, we need to invert the
9991  // condition.
9992  bool Invert = CCVal == ISD::SETEQ;
9993  CCVal = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(LHS.getOperand(2))->get();
9994  if (Invert)
9995  CCVal = ISD::getSetCCInverse(CCVal, LHS.getValueType());
9996 
9997  RHS = LHS.getOperand(1);
9998  LHS = LHS.getOperand(0);
9999  translateSetCCForBranch(DL, LHS, RHS, CCVal, DAG);
10000 
10001  CC = DAG.getCondCode(CCVal);
10002  return true;
10003  }
10004 
10005  // Fold ((xor X, Y), 0, eq/ne) -> (X, Y, eq/ne)
10006  if (LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::XOR && isNullConstant(RHS)) {
10007  RHS = LHS.getOperand(1);
10008  LHS = LHS.getOperand(0);
10009  return true;
10010  }
10011 
10012  // Fold ((srl (and X, 1<<C), C), 0, eq/ne) -> ((shl X, XLen-1-C), 0, ge/lt)
10013  if (isNullConstant(RHS) && LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL && LHS.hasOneUse() &&
10014  LHS.getOperand(1).getOpcode() == ISD::Constant) {
10015  SDValue LHS0 = LHS.getOperand(0);
10016  if (LHS0.getOpcode() == ISD::AND &&
10017  LHS0.getOperand(1).getOpcode() == ISD::Constant) {
10018  uint64_t Mask = LHS0.getConstantOperandVal(1);
10019  uint64_t ShAmt = LHS.getConstantOperandVal(1);
10020  if (isPowerOf2_64(Mask) && Log2_64(Mask) == ShAmt) {
10021  CCVal = CCVal == ISD::SETEQ ? ISD::SETGE : ISD::SETLT;
10022  CC = DAG.getCondCode(CCVal);
10023 
10024  ShAmt = LHS.getValueSizeInBits() - 1 - ShAmt;
10025  LHS = LHS0.getOperand(0);
10026  if (ShAmt != 0)
10027  LHS =
10028  DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, LHS.getValueType(), LHS0.getOperand(0),
10029  DAG.getConstant(ShAmt, DL, LHS.getValueType()));
10030  return true;
10031  }
10032  }
10033  }
10034 
10035  // (X, 1, setne) -> // (X, 0, seteq) if we can prove X is 0/1.
10036  // This can occur when legalizing some floating point comparisons.
10037  APInt Mask = APInt::getBitsSetFrom(LHS.getValueSizeInBits(), 1);
10038  if (isOneConstant(RHS) && DAG.MaskedValueIsZero(LHS, Mask)) {
10039  CCVal = ISD::getSetCCInverse(CCVal, LHS.getValueType());
10040  CC = DAG.getCondCode(CCVal);
10041  RHS = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, LHS.getValueType());
10042  return true;
10043  }
10044 
10045  if (isNullConstant(RHS)) {
10046  if (SDValue NewCond = tryDemorganOfBooleanCondition(LHS, DAG)) {
10047  CCVal = ISD::getSetCCInverse(CCVal, LHS.getValueType());
10048  CC = DAG.getCondCode(CCVal);
10049  LHS = NewCond;
10050  return true;
10051  }
10052  }
10053 
10054  return false;
10055 }
10056 
10057 // Fold
10058 // (select C, (add Y, X), Y) -> (add Y, (select C, X, 0)).
10059 // (select C, (sub Y, X), Y) -> (sub Y, (select C, X, 0)).
10060 // (select C, (or Y, X), Y) -> (or Y, (select C, X, 0)).
10061 // (select C, (xor Y, X), Y) -> (xor Y, (select C, X, 0)).
10062 static SDValue tryFoldSelectIntoOp(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
10063  SDValue TrueVal, SDValue FalseVal,
10064  bool Swapped) {
10065  bool Commutative = true;
10066  switch (TrueVal.getOpcode()) {
10067  default:
10068  return SDValue();
10069  case ISD::SUB:
10070  Commutative = false;
10071  break;
10072  case ISD::ADD:
10073  case ISD::OR:
10074  case ISD::XOR:
10075  break;
10076  }
10077 
10078  if (!TrueVal.hasOneUse() || isa<ConstantSDNode>(FalseVal))
10079  return SDValue();
10080 
10081  unsigned OpToFold;
10082  if (FalseVal == TrueVal.getOperand(0))
10083  OpToFold = 0;
10084  else if (Commutative && FalseVal == TrueVal.getOperand(1))
10085  OpToFold = 1;
10086  else
10087  return SDValue();
10088 
10089  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
10090  SDLoc DL(N);
10091  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT);
10092  SDValue OtherOp = TrueVal.getOperand(1 - OpToFold);
10093 
10094  if (Swapped)
10095  std::swap(OtherOp, Zero);
10096  SDValue NewSel = DAG.getSelect(DL, VT, N->getOperand(0), OtherOp, Zero);
10097  return DAG.getNode(TrueVal.getOpcode(), DL, VT, FalseVal, NewSel);
10098 }
10099 
10100 static SDValue performSELECTCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
10101  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
10102  if (Subtarget.hasShortForwardBranchOpt())
10103  return SDValue();
10104 
10105  // Only support XLenVT.
10106  if (N->getValueType(0) != Subtarget.getXLenVT())
10107  return SDValue();
10108 
10109  SDValue TrueVal = N->getOperand(1);
10110  SDValue FalseVal = N->getOperand(2);
10111  if (SDValue V = tryFoldSelectIntoOp(N, DAG, TrueVal, FalseVal, /*Swapped*/false))
10112  return V;
10113  return tryFoldSelectIntoOp(N, DAG, FalseVal, TrueVal, /*Swapped*/true);
10114 }
10115 
10116 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::PerformDAGCombine(SDNode *N,
10117  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
10118  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
10119 
10120  // Helper to call SimplifyDemandedBits on an operand of N where only some low
10121  // bits are demanded. N will be added to the Worklist if it was not deleted.
10122  // Caller should return SDValue(N, 0) if this returns true.
10123  auto SimplifyDemandedLowBitsHelper = [&](unsigned OpNo, unsigned LowBits) {
10124  SDValue Op = N->getOperand(OpNo);
10125  APInt Mask = APInt::getLowBitsSet(Op.getValueSizeInBits(), LowBits);
10126  if (!SimplifyDemandedBits(Op, Mask, DCI))
10127  return false;
10128 
10129  if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::DELETED_NODE)
10130  DCI.AddToWorklist(N);
10131  return true;
10132  };
10133 
10134  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
10135  default:
10136  break;
10137  case RISCVISD::SplitF64: {
10138  SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
10139  // If the input to SplitF64 is just BuildPairF64 then the operation is
