10140  // redundant. Instead, use BuildPairF64's operands directly.
10141  if (Op0->getOpcode() == RISCVISD::BuildPairF64)
10142  return DCI.CombineTo(N, Op0.getOperand(0), Op0.getOperand(1));
10143 
10144  if (Op0->isUndef()) {
10145  SDValue Lo = DAG.getUNDEF(MVT::i32);
10146  SDValue Hi = DAG.getUNDEF(MVT::i32);
10147  return DCI.CombineTo(N, Lo, Hi);
10148  }
10149 
10150  SDLoc DL(N);
10151 
10152  // It's cheaper to materialise two 32-bit integers than to load a double
10153  // from the constant pool and transfer it to integer registers through the
10154  // stack.
10155  if (ConstantFPSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Op0)) {
10156  APInt V = C->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt();
10157  SDValue Lo = DAG.getConstant(V.trunc(32), DL, MVT::i32);
10158  SDValue Hi = DAG.getConstant(V.lshr(32).trunc(32), DL, MVT::i32);
10159  return DCI.CombineTo(N, Lo, Hi);
10160  }
10161 
10162  // This is a target-specific version of a DAGCombine performed in
10163  // DAGCombiner::visitBITCAST. It performs the equivalent of:
10164  // fold (bitconvert (fneg x)) -> (xor (bitconvert x), signbit)
10165  // fold (bitconvert (fabs x)) -> (and (bitconvert x), (not signbit))
10166  if (!(Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FNEG || Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FABS) ||
10167  !Op0.getNode()->hasOneUse())
10168  break;
10169  SDValue NewSplitF64 =
10170  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SplitF64, DL, DAG.getVTList(MVT::i32, MVT::i32),
10171  Op0.getOperand(0));
10172  SDValue Lo = NewSplitF64.getValue(0);
10173  SDValue Hi = NewSplitF64.getValue(1);
10174  APInt SignBit = APInt::getSignMask(32);
10175  if (Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FNEG) {
10176  SDValue NewHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, MVT::i32, Hi,
10177  DAG.getConstant(SignBit, DL, MVT::i32));
10178  return DCI.CombineTo(N, Lo, NewHi);
10179  }
10180  assert(Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FABS);
10181  SDValue NewHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, MVT::i32, Hi,
10182  DAG.getConstant(~SignBit, DL, MVT::i32));
10183  return DCI.CombineTo(N, Lo, NewHi);
10184  }
10185  case RISCVISD::SLLW:
10186  case RISCVISD::SRAW:
10187  case RISCVISD::SRLW:
10188  case RISCVISD::RORW:
10189  case RISCVISD::ROLW: {
10190  // Only the lower 32 bits of LHS and lower 5 bits of RHS are read.
10191  if (SimplifyDemandedLowBitsHelper(0, 32) ||
10192  SimplifyDemandedLowBitsHelper(1, 5))
10193  return SDValue(N, 0);
10194 
10195  break;
10196  }
10197  case RISCVISD::CLZW:
10198  case RISCVISD::CTZW: {
10199  // Only the lower 32 bits of the first operand are read
10200  if (SimplifyDemandedLowBitsHelper(0, 32))
10201  return SDValue(N, 0);
10202  break;
10203  }
10204  case RISCVISD::FMV_X_ANYEXTH:
10205  case RISCVISD::FMV_X_ANYEXTW_RV64: {
10206  SDLoc DL(N);
10207  SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
10208  MVT VT = N->getSimpleValueType(0);
10209  // If the input to FMV_X_ANYEXTW_RV64 is just FMV_W_X_RV64 then the
10210  // conversion is unnecessary and can be replaced with the FMV_W_X_RV64
10211  // operand. Similar for FMV_X_ANYEXTH and FMV_H_X.
10212  if ((N->getOpcode() == RISCVISD::FMV_X_ANYEXTW_RV64 &&
10213  Op0->getOpcode() == RISCVISD::FMV_W_X_RV64) ||
10214  (N->getOpcode() == RISCVISD::FMV_X_ANYEXTH &&
10215  Op0->getOpcode() == RISCVISD::FMV_H_X)) {
10216  assert(Op0.getOperand(0).getValueType() == VT &&
10217  "Unexpected value type!");
10218  return Op0.getOperand(0);
10219  }
10220 
10221  // This is a target-specific version of a DAGCombine performed in
10222  // DAGCombiner::visitBITCAST. It performs the equivalent of:
10223  // fold (bitconvert (fneg x)) -> (xor (bitconvert x), signbit)
10224  // fold (bitconvert (fabs x)) -> (and (bitconvert x), (not signbit))
10225  if (!(Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FNEG || Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FABS) ||
10226  !Op0.getNode()->hasOneUse())
10227  break;
10228  SDValue NewFMV = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, VT, Op0.getOperand(0));
10229  unsigned FPBits = N->getOpcode() == RISCVISD::FMV_X_ANYEXTW_RV64 ? 32 : 16;
10230  APInt SignBit = APInt::getSignMask(FPBits).sext(VT.getSizeInBits());
10231  if (Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FNEG)
10232  return DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, VT, NewFMV,
10233  DAG.getConstant(SignBit, DL, VT));
10234 
10235  assert(Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FABS);
10236  return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, NewFMV,
10237  DAG.getConstant(~SignBit, DL, VT));
10238  }
10239  case ISD::ADD:
10240  return performADDCombine(N, DAG, Subtarget);
10241  case ISD::SUB:
10242  return performSUBCombine(N, DAG, Subtarget);
10243  case ISD::AND:
10244  return performANDCombine(N, DCI, Subtarget);
10245  case ISD::OR:
10246  return performORCombine(N, DCI, Subtarget);
10247  case ISD::XOR:
10248  return performXORCombine(N, DAG, Subtarget);
10249  case ISD::FADD:
10250  case ISD::UMAX:
10251  case ISD::UMIN:
10252  case ISD::SMAX:
10253  case ISD::SMIN:
10254  case ISD::FMAXNUM:
10255  case ISD::FMINNUM:
10256  return combineBinOpToReduce(N, DAG, Subtarget);
10257  case ISD::SETCC:
10258  return performSETCCCombine(N, DAG, Subtarget);
10259  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG:
10260  return performSIGN_EXTEND_INREGCombine(N, DAG, Subtarget);
10261  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
10262  // Fold (zero_extend (fp_to_uint X)) to prevent forming fcvt+zexti32 during
10263  // type legalization. This is safe because fp_to_uint produces poison if
10264  // it overflows.
10265  if (N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i64 && Subtarget.is64Bit()) {
10266  SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
10267  if (Src.getOpcode() == ISD::FP_TO_UINT &&
10268  isTypeLegal(Src.getOperand(0).getValueType()))
10269  return DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_TO_UINT, SDLoc(N), MVT::i64,
10270  Src.getOperand(0));
10271  if (Src.getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT && Src.hasOneUse() &&
10272  isTypeLegal(Src.getOperand(1).getValueType())) {
10273  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(MVT::i64, MVT::Other);
10274  SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT, SDLoc(N), VTs,
10275  Src.getOperand(0), Src.getOperand(1));
10276  DCI.CombineTo(N, Res);
10277  DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(Src.getValue(1), Res.getValue(1));
10278  DCI.recursivelyDeleteUnusedNodes(Src.getNode());
10279  return SDValue(N, 0); // Return N so it doesn't get rechecked.
10280  }
10281  }
10282  return SDValue();
10283  case ISD::TRUNCATE:
10284  return performTRUNCATECombine(N, DAG, Subtarget);
10285  case ISD::SELECT:
10286  return performSELECTCombine(N, DAG, Subtarget);
10287  case RISCVISD::SELECT_CC: {
10288  // Transform
10289  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
10290  SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
10291  SDValue CC = N->getOperand(2);
10292  ISD::CondCode CCVal = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(CC)->get();
10293  SDValue TrueV = N->getOperand(3);
10294  SDValue FalseV = N->getOperand(4);
10295  SDLoc DL(N);
10296  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
10297 
10298  // If the True and False values are the same, we don't need a select_cc.
10299  if (TrueV == FalseV)
10300  return TrueV;
10301 
10302  // (select (x < 0), y, z) -> x >> (XLEN - 1) & (y - z) + z
10303  // (select (x >= 0), y, z) -> x >> (XLEN - 1) & (z - y) + y
10304  if (!Subtarget.hasShortForwardBranchOpt() && isa<ConstantSDNode>(TrueV) &&
10305  isa<ConstantSDNode>(FalseV) && isNullConstant(RHS) &&
10306  (CCVal == ISD::CondCode::SETLT || CCVal == ISD::CondCode::SETGE)) {
10307  if (CCVal == ISD::CondCode::SETGE)
10308  std::swap(TrueV, FalseV);
10309 
10310  int64_t TrueSImm = cast<ConstantSDNode>(TrueV)->getSExtValue();
10311  int64_t FalseSImm = cast<ConstantSDNode>(FalseV)->getSExtValue();
10312  // Only handle simm12, if it is not in this range, it can be considered as
10313  // register.
10314  if (isInt<12>(TrueSImm) && isInt<12>(FalseSImm) &&
10315  isInt<12>(TrueSImm - FalseSImm)) {
10316  SDValue SRA =
10317  DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, DL, VT, LHS,
10318  DAG.getConstant(Subtarget.getXLen() - 1, DL, VT));
10319  SDValue AND =
10320  DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, SRA,
10321  DAG.getConstant(TrueSImm - FalseSImm, DL, VT));
10322  return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, AND, FalseV);
10323  }
10324 
10325  if (CCVal == ISD::CondCode::SETGE)
10326  std::swap(TrueV, FalseV);
10327  }
10328 
10329  if (combine_CC(LHS, RHS, CC, DL, DAG, Subtarget))
10330  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SELECT_CC, DL, N->getValueType(0),
10331  {LHS, RHS, CC, TrueV, FalseV});
10332 
10333  if (!Subtarget.hasShortForwardBranchOpt()) {
10334  // (select c, -1, y) -> -c | y
10335  if (isAllOnesConstant(TrueV)) {
10336  SDValue C = DAG.getSetCC(DL, VT, LHS, RHS, CCVal);
10337  SDValue Neg = DAG.getNegative(C, DL, VT);
10338  return DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, Neg, FalseV);
10339  }
10340  // (select c, y, -1) -> -!c | y
10341  if (isAllOnesConstant(FalseV)) {
10342  SDValue C =
10343  DAG.getSetCC(DL, VT, LHS, RHS, ISD::getSetCCInverse(CCVal, VT));
10344  SDValue Neg = DAG.getNegative(C, DL, VT);
10345  return DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, Neg, TrueV);
10346  }
10347 
10348  // (select c, 0, y) -> -!c & y
10349  if (isNullConstant(TrueV)) {
10350  SDValue C =
10351  DAG.getSetCC(DL, VT, LHS, RHS, ISD::getSetCCInverse(CCVal, VT));
10352  SDValue Neg = DAG.getNegative(C, DL, VT);
10353  return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, Neg, FalseV);
10354  }
10355  // (select c, y, 0) -> -c & y
10356  if (isNullConstant(FalseV)) {
10357  SDValue C = DAG.getSetCC(DL, VT, LHS, RHS, CCVal);
10358  SDValue Neg = DAG.getNegative(C, DL, VT);
10359  return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, Neg, TrueV);
10360  }
10361  }
10362 
10363  return SDValue();
10364  }
10365  case RISCVISD::BR_CC: {
10366  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(1);
10367  SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(2);
10368  SDValue CC = N->getOperand(3);
10369  SDLoc DL(N);
10370 
10371  if (combine_CC(LHS, RHS, CC, DL, DAG, Subtarget))
10372  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::BR_CC, DL, N->getValueType(0),
10373  N->getOperand(0), LHS, RHS, CC, N->getOperand(4));
10374 
10375  return SDValue();
10376  }
10377  case ISD::BITREVERSE:
10378  return performBITREVERSECombine(N, DAG, Subtarget);
10379  case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
10380  case ISD::FP_TO_UINT:
10381  return performFP_TO_INTCombine(N, DCI, Subtarget);
10382  case ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT:
10383  case ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT:
10384  return performFP_TO_INT_SATCombine(N, DCI, Subtarget);
10385  case ISD::FCOPYSIGN: {
10386  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
10387  if (!VT.isVector())
10388  break;
10389  // There is a form of VFSGNJ which injects the negated sign of its second
10390  // operand. Try and bubble any FNEG up after the extend/round to produce
10391  // this optimized pattern. Avoid modifying cases where FP_ROUND and
10392  // TRUNC=1.
10393  SDValue In2 = N->getOperand(1);
10394  // Avoid cases where the extend/round has multiple uses, as duplicating
10395  // those is typically more expensive than removing a fneg.
10396  if (!In2.hasOneUse())
10397  break;
10398  if (In2.getOpcode() != ISD::FP_EXTEND &&
10399  (In2.getOpcode() != ISD::FP_ROUND || In2.getConstantOperandVal(1) != 0))
10400  break;
10401  In2 = In2.getOperand(0);
10402  if (In2.getOpcode() != ISD::FNEG)
10403  break;
10404  SDLoc DL(N);
10405  SDValue NewFPExtRound = DAG.getFPExtendOrRound(In2.getOperand(0), DL, VT);
10406  return DAG.getNode(ISD::FCOPYSIGN, DL, VT, N->getOperand(0),
10407  DAG.getNode(ISD::FNEG, DL, VT, NewFPExtRound));
10408  }
10409  case ISD::MGATHER:
10410  case ISD::MSCATTER:
10411  case ISD::VP_GATHER:
10412  case ISD::VP_SCATTER: {
10413  if (!DCI.isBeforeLegalize())
10414  break;
10415  SDValue Index, ScaleOp;
10416  bool IsIndexSigned = false;
10417  if (const auto *VPGSN = dyn_cast<VPGatherScatterSDNode>(N)) {
10418  Index = VPGSN->getIndex();
10419  ScaleOp = VPGSN->getScale();
10420  IsIndexSigned = VPGSN->isIndexSigned();
10421  assert(!VPGSN->isIndexScaled() &&
10422  "Scaled gather/scatter should not be formed");
10423  } else {
10424  const auto *MGSN = cast<MaskedGatherScatterSDNode>(N);
10425  Index = MGSN->getIndex();
10426  ScaleOp = MGSN->getScale();
10427  IsIndexSigned = MGSN->isIndexSigned();
10428  assert(!MGSN->isIndexScaled() &&
10429  "Scaled gather/scatter should not be formed");
10430 
10431  }
10432  EVT IndexVT = Index.getValueType();
10433  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
10434  // RISCV indexed loads only support the "unsigned unscaled" addressing
10435  // mode, so anything else must be manually legalized.
10436  bool NeedsIdxLegalization =
10437  (IsIndexSigned && IndexVT.getVectorElementType().bitsLT(XLenVT));
10438  if (!NeedsIdxLegalization)
10439  break;
10440 
10441  SDLoc DL(N);
10442 
10443  // Any index legalization should first promote to XLenVT, so we don't lose
10444  // bits when scaling. This may create an illegal index type so we let
10445  // LLVM's legalization take care of the splitting.
10446  // FIXME: LLVM can't split VP_GATHER or VP_SCATTER yet.
10447  if (IndexVT.getVectorElementType().bitsLT(XLenVT)) {
10448  IndexVT = IndexVT.changeVectorElementType(XLenVT);
10449  Index = DAG.getNode(IsIndexSigned ? ISD::SIGN_EXTEND : ISD::ZERO_EXTEND,
10450  DL, IndexVT, Index);
10451  }
10452 
10453  ISD::MemIndexType NewIndexTy = ISD::UNSIGNED_SCALED;
10454  if (const auto *VPGN = dyn_cast<VPGatherSDNode>(N))
10455  return DAG.getGatherVP(N->getVTList(), VPGN->getMemoryVT(), DL,
10456  {VPGN->getChain(), VPGN->getBasePtr(), Index,
10457  ScaleOp, VPGN->getMask(),
10458  VPGN->getVectorLength()},
10459  VPGN->getMemOperand(), NewIndexTy);
10460  if (const auto *VPSN = dyn_cast<VPScatterSDNode>(N))
10461  return DAG.getScatterVP(N->getVTList(), VPSN->getMemoryVT(), DL,
10462  {VPSN->getChain(), VPSN->getValue(),
10463  VPSN->getBasePtr(), Index, ScaleOp,
10464  VPSN->getMask(), VPSN->getVectorLength()},
10465  VPSN->getMemOperand(), NewIndexTy);
10466  if (const auto *MGN = dyn_cast<MaskedGatherSDNode>(N))
10467  return DAG.getMaskedGather(
10468  N->getVTList(), MGN->getMemoryVT(), DL,
10469  {MGN->getChain(), MGN->getPassThru(), MGN->getMask(),
10470  MGN->getBasePtr(), Index, ScaleOp},
10471  MGN->getMemOperand(), NewIndexTy, MGN->getExtensionType());
10472  const auto *MSN = cast<MaskedScatterSDNode>(N);
10473  return DAG.getMaskedScatter(
10474  N->getVTList(), MSN->getMemoryVT(), DL,
10475  {MSN->getChain(), MSN->getValue(), MSN->getMask(), MSN->getBasePtr(),
10476  Index, ScaleOp},
10477  MSN->getMemOperand(), NewIndexTy, MSN->isTruncatingStore());
10478  }
10479  case RISCVISD::SRA_VL:
10480  case RISCVISD::SRL_VL:
10481  case RISCVISD::SHL_VL: {
10482  SDValue ShAmt = N->getOperand(1);
10483  if (ShAmt.getOpcode() == RISCVISD::SPLAT_VECTOR_SPLIT_I64_VL) {
10484  // We don't need the upper 32 bits of a 64-bit element for a shift amount.
10485  SDLoc DL(N);
10486  SDValue VL = N->getOperand(3);
10487  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
10488  ShAmt = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, VT, DAG.getUNDEF(VT),
10489  ShAmt.getOperand(1), VL);
10490  return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, VT, N->getOperand(0), ShAmt,
10491  N->getOperand(2), N->getOperand(3), N->getOperand(4));
10492  }
10493  break;
10494  }
10495  case ISD::SRA:
10496  if (SDValue V = performSRACombine(N, DAG, Subtarget))
10497  return V;
10498  [[fallthrough]];
10499  case ISD::SRL:
10500  case ISD::SHL: {
10501  SDValue ShAmt = N->getOperand(1);
10502  if (ShAmt.getOpcode() == RISCVISD::SPLAT_VECTOR_SPLIT_I64_VL) {
10503  // We don't need the upper 32 bits of a 64-bit element for a shift amount.
10504  SDLoc DL(N);
10505  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
10506  ShAmt = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, VT, DAG.getUNDEF(VT),
10507  ShAmt.getOperand(1),
10508  DAG.getRegister(RISCV::X0, Subtarget.getXLenVT()));
10509  return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, VT, N->getOperand(0), ShAmt);
10510  }
10511  break;
10512  }
10513  case RISCVISD::ADD_VL:
10514  case RISCVISD::SUB_VL:
10515  case RISCVISD::VWADD_W_VL:
10516  case RISCVISD::VWADDU_W_VL:
10517  case RISCVISD::VWSUB_W_VL:
10518  case RISCVISD::VWSUBU_W_VL:
10519  case RISCVISD::MUL_VL:
10520  return combineBinOp_VLToVWBinOp_VL(N, DCI);
10521  case RISCVISD::VFMADD_VL:
10522  case RISCVISD::VFNMADD_VL:
10523  case RISCVISD::VFMSUB_VL:
10524  case RISCVISD::VFNMSUB_VL: {
10525  // Fold FNEG_VL into FMA opcodes.
10526  SDValue A = N->getOperand(0);
10527  SDValue B = N->getOperand(1);
10528  SDValue C = N->getOperand(2);
10529  SDValue Mask = N->getOperand(3);
10530  SDValue VL = N->getOperand(4);
10531 
10532  auto invertIfNegative = [&Mask, &VL](SDValue &V) {
10533  if (V.getOpcode() == RISCVISD::FNEG_VL && V.getOperand(1) == Mask &&
10534  V.getOperand(2) == VL) {
10535  // Return the negated input.
10536  V = V.getOperand(0);
10537  return true;
10538  }
10539 
10540  return false;
10541  };
10542 
10543  bool NegA = invertIfNegative(A);
10544  bool NegB = invertIfNegative(B);
10545  bool NegC = invertIfNegative(C);
10546 
10547  // If no operands are negated, we're done.
10548  if (!NegA && !NegB && !NegC)
10549  return SDValue();
10550 
10551  unsigned NewOpcode = negateFMAOpcode(N->getOpcode(), NegA != NegB, NegC);
10552  return DAG.getNode(NewOpcode, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), A, B, C, Mask,
10553  VL);
10554  }
10555  case ISD::STORE: {
10556  auto *Store = cast<StoreSDNode>(N);
10557  SDValue Val = Store->getValue();
10558  // Combine store of vmv.x.s/vfmv.f.s to vse with VL of 1.
10559  // vfmv.f.s is represented as extract element from 0. Match it late to avoid
10560  // any illegal types.
10561  if (Val.getOpcode() == RISCVISD::VMV_X_S ||
10562  (DCI.isAfterLegalizeDAG() &&
10563  Val.getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT &&
10564  isNullConstant(Val.getOperand(1)))) {
10565  SDValue Src = Val.getOperand(0);
10566  MVT VecVT = Src.getSimpleValueType();
10567  EVT MemVT = Store->getMemoryVT();
10568  // VecVT should be scalable and memory VT should match the element type.
10569  if (VecVT.isScalableVector() &&
10570  MemVT == VecVT.getVectorElementType()) {
10571  SDLoc DL(N);
10572  MVT MaskVT = getMaskTypeFor(VecVT);
10573  return DAG.getStoreVP(
10574  Store->getChain(), DL, Src, Store->getBasePtr(), Store->getOffset(),
10575  DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MaskVT),
10576  DAG.getConstant(1, DL, Subtarget.getXLenVT()), MemVT,
10577  Store->getMemOperand(), Store->getAddressingMode(),
10578  Store->isTruncatingStore(), /*IsCompress*/ false);
10579  }
10580  }
10581 
10582  break;
10583  }
10584  case ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR: {
10585  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
10586  // Only perform this combine on legal MVT types.
10587  if (!isTypeLegal(VT))
10588  break;
10589  if (auto Gather = matchSplatAsGather(N->getOperand(0), VT.getSimpleVT(), N,
10590  DAG, Subtarget))
10591  return Gather;
10592  break;
10593  }
10594  case RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL: {
10595  // Tail agnostic VMV.V.X only demands the vector element bitwidth from the
10596  // scalar input.
10597  unsigned ScalarSize = N->getOperand(1).getValueSizeInBits();
10598  unsigned EltWidth = N->getValueType(0).getScalarSizeInBits();
10599  if (ScalarSize > EltWidth && N->getOperand(0).isUndef())
10600  if (SimplifyDemandedLowBitsHelper(1, EltWidth))
10601  return SDValue(N, 0);
10602 
10603  break;
10604  }
10605  case RISCVISD::VFMV_S_F_VL: {
10606  SDValue Src = N->getOperand(1);
10607  // Try to remove vector->scalar->vector if the scalar->vector is inserting
10608  // into an undef vector.
10609  // TODO: Could use a vslide or vmv.v.v for non-undef.
10610  if (N->getOperand(0).isUndef() &&
10611  Src.getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT &&
10612  isNullConstant(Src.getOperand(1)) &&
10613  Src.getOperand(0).getValueType().isScalableVector()) {
10614  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
10615  EVT SrcVT = Src.getOperand(0).getValueType();
10616  assert(SrcVT.getVectorElementType() == VT.getVectorElementType());
10617  // Widths match, just return the original vector.
10618  if (SrcVT == VT)
10619  return Src.getOperand(0);
10620  // TODO: Use insert_subvector/extract_subvector to change widen/narrow?
10621  }
10622  break;
10623  }
10624  case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN: {
10625  unsigned IntNo = N->getConstantOperandVal(0);
10626  switch (IntNo) {
10627  // By default we do not combine any intrinsic.
10628  default:
10629  return SDValue();
10630  case Intrinsic::riscv_vcpop:
10631  case Intrinsic::riscv_vcpop_mask:
10632  case Intrinsic::riscv_vfirst:
10633  case Intrinsic::riscv_vfirst_mask: {
10634  SDValue VL = N->getOperand(2);
10635  if (IntNo == Intrinsic::riscv_vcpop_mask ||
10636  IntNo == Intrinsic::riscv_vfirst_mask)
10637  VL = N->getOperand(3);
10638  if (!isNullConstant(VL))
10639  return SDValue();
10640  // If VL is 0, vcpop -> li 0, vfirst -> li -1.
10641  SDLoc DL(N);
10642  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
10643  if (IntNo == Intrinsic::riscv_vfirst ||
10644  IntNo == Intrinsic::riscv_vfirst_mask)
10645  return DAG.getConstant(-1, DL, VT);
10646  return DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT);
10647  }
10648  }
10649  }
10650  case ISD::BITCAST: {
10651  assert(Subtarget.useRVVForFixedLengthVectors());
10652  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
10653  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
10654  EVT SrcVT = N0.getValueType();
10655  // If this is a bitcast between a MVT::v4i1/v2i1/v1i1 and an illegal integer
10656  // type, widen both sides to avoid a trip through memory.
10657  if ((SrcVT == MVT::v1i1 || SrcVT == MVT::v2i1 || SrcVT == MVT::v4i1) &&
10658  VT.isScalarInteger()) {
10659  unsigned NumConcats = 8 / SrcVT.getVectorNumElements();
10660  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Ops(NumConcats, DAG.getUNDEF(SrcVT));
10661  Ops[0] = N0;
10662  SDLoc DL(N);
10663  N0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, DL, MVT::v8i1, Ops);
10664  N0 = DAG.getBitcast(MVT::i8, N0);
10665  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VT, N0);
10666  }
10667 
10668  return SDValue();
10669  }
10670  }
10671 
10672  return SDValue();
10673 }
10674 
10675 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isDesirableToCommuteWithShift(
10676  const SDNode *N, CombineLevel Level) const {
10677  assert((N->getOpcode() == ISD::SHL || N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRA ||
10678  N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRL) &&
10679  "Expected shift op");
10680 
10681  // The following folds are only desirable if `(OP _, c1 << c2)` can be
10682  // materialised in fewer instructions than `(OP _, c1)`:
10683  //
10684  // (shl (add x, c1), c2) -> (add (shl x, c2), c1 << c2)
10685  // (shl (or x, c1), c2) -> (or (shl x, c2), c1 << c2)
10686  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
10687  EVT Ty = N0.getValueType();
10688  if (Ty.isScalarInteger() &&
10689  (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD || N0.getOpcode() == ISD::OR)) {
10690  auto *C1 = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0->getOperand(1));
10691  auto *C2 = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
10692  if (C1 && C2) {
10693  const APInt &C1Int = C1->getAPIntValue();
10694  APInt ShiftedC1Int = C1Int << C2->getAPIntValue();
10695 
10696  // We can materialise `c1 << c2` into an add immediate, so it's "free",
10697  // and the combine should happen, to potentially allow further combines
10698  // later.
10699  if (ShiftedC1Int.getMinSignedBits() <= 64 &&
10700  isLegalAddImmediate(ShiftedC1Int.getSExtValue()))
10701  return true;
10702 
10703  // We can materialise `c1` in an add immediate, so it's "free", and the
10704  // combine should be prevented.
10705  if (C1Int.getMinSignedBits() <= 64 &&
10706  isLegalAddImmediate(C1Int.getSExtValue()))
10707  return false;
10708 
10709  // Neither constant will fit into an immediate, so find materialisation
10710  // costs.
10711  int C1Cost = RISCVMatInt::getIntMatCost(C1Int, Ty.getSizeInBits(),
10712  Subtarget.getFeatureBits(),
10713  /*CompressionCost*/true);
10714  int ShiftedC1Cost = RISCVMatInt::getIntMatCost(
10715  ShiftedC1Int, Ty.getSizeInBits(), Subtarget.getFeatureBits(),
10716  /*CompressionCost*/true);
10717 
10718  // Materialising `c1` is cheaper than materialising `c1 << c2`, so the
10719  // combine should be prevented.
10720  if (C1Cost < ShiftedC1Cost)
10721  return false;
10722  }
10723  }
10724  return true;
10725 }
10726 
10727 bool RISCVTargetLowering::targetShrinkDemandedConstant(
10728  SDValue Op, const APInt &DemandedBits, const APInt &DemandedElts,
10729  TargetLoweringOpt &TLO) const {
10730  // Delay this optimization as late as possible.
10731  if (!TLO.LegalOps)
10732  return false;
10733 
10734  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
10735  if (VT.isVector())
10736  return false;
10737 
10738  unsigned Opcode = Op.getOpcode();
10739  if (Opcode != ISD::AND && Opcode != ISD::OR && Opcode != ISD::XOR)
10740  return false;
10741 
10742  ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1));
10743  if (!C)
10744  return false;
10745 
10746  const APInt &Mask = C->getAPIntValue();
10747 
10748  // Clear all non-demanded bits initially.
10749  APInt ShrunkMask = Mask & DemandedBits;
10750 
10751  // Try to make a smaller immediate by setting undemanded bits.
10752 
10753  APInt ExpandedMask = Mask | ~DemandedBits;
10754 
10755  auto IsLegalMask = [ShrunkMask, ExpandedMask](const APInt &Mask) -> bool {
10756  return ShrunkMask.isSubsetOf(Mask) && Mask.isSubsetOf(ExpandedMask);
10757  };
10758  auto UseMask = [Mask, Op, &TLO](const APInt &NewMask) -> bool {
10759  if (NewMask == Mask)
10760  return true;
10761  SDLoc DL(Op);
10762  SDValue NewC = TLO.DAG.getConstant(NewMask, DL, Op.getValueType());
10763  SDValue NewOp = TLO.DAG.getNode(Op.getOpcode(), DL, Op.getValueType(),
10764  Op.getOperand(0), NewC);
10765  return TLO.CombineTo(Op, NewOp);
10766  };
10767 
10768  // If the shrunk mask fits in sign extended 12 bits, let the target
10769  // independent code apply it.
10770  if (ShrunkMask.isSignedIntN(12))
10771  return false;
10772 
10773  // And has a few special cases for zext.
10774  if (Opcode == ISD::AND) {
10775  // Preserve (and X, 0xffff), if zext.h exists use zext.h,
10776  // otherwise use SLLI + SRLI.
10777  APInt NewMask = APInt(Mask.getBitWidth(), 0xffff);
10778  if (IsLegalMask(NewMask))
10779  return UseMask(NewMask);
10780 
10781  // Try to preserve (and X, 0xffffffff), the (zext_inreg X, i32) pattern.
10782  if (VT == MVT::i64) {
10783  APInt NewMask = APInt(64, 0xffffffff);
10784  if (IsLegalMask(NewMask))
10785  return UseMask(NewMask);
10786  }
10787  }
10788 
10789  // For the remaining optimizations, we need to be able to make a negative
10790  // number through a combination of mask and undemanded bits.
10791  if (!ExpandedMask.isNegative())
10792  return false;
10793 
10794  // What is the fewest number of bits we need to represent the negative number.
10795  unsigned MinSignedBits = ExpandedMask.getMinSignedBits();
10796 
10797  // Try to make a 12 bit negative immediate. If that fails try to make a 32
10798  // bit negative immediate unless the shrunk immediate already fits in 32 bits.
10799  // If we can't create a simm12, we shouldn't change opaque constants.
10800  APInt NewMask = ShrunkMask;
10801  if (MinSignedBits <= 12)
10802  NewMask.setBitsFrom(11);
10803  else if (!C->isOpaque() && MinSignedBits <= 32 && !ShrunkMask.isSignedIntN(32))
10804  NewMask.setBitsFrom(31);
10805  else
10806  return false;
10807 
10808  // Check that our new mask is a subset of the demanded mask.
10809  assert(IsLegalMask(NewMask));
10810  return UseMask(NewMask);
10811 }
10812 
10813 static uint64_t computeGREVOrGORC(uint64_t x, unsigned ShAmt, bool IsGORC) {
10814  static const uint64_t GREVMasks[] = {
10815  0x5555555555555555ULL, 0x3333333333333333ULL, 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0FULL,
10816  0x00FF00FF00FF00FFULL, 0x0000FFFF0000FFFFULL, 0x00000000FFFFFFFFULL};
10817 
10818  for (unsigned Stage = 0; Stage != 6; ++Stage) {
10819  unsigned Shift = 1 << Stage;
10820  if (ShAmt & Shift) {
10821  uint64_t Mask = GREVMasks[Stage];
10822  uint64_t Res = ((x & Mask) << Shift) | ((x >> Shift) & Mask);
10823  if (IsGORC)
10824  Res |= x;
10825  x = Res;
10826  }
10827  }
10828 
10829  return x;
10830 }
10831 
10832 void RISCVTargetLowering::computeKnownBitsForTargetNode(const SDValue Op,
10833  KnownBits &Known,
10834  const APInt &DemandedElts,
10835  const SelectionDAG &DAG,
10836  unsigned Depth) const {
10837  unsigned BitWidth = Known.getBitWidth();
10838  unsigned Opc = Op.getOpcode();
10839  assert((Opc >= ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END ||
10840  Opc == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN ||
10841  Opc == ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN ||
10842  Opc == ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID) &&
10843  "Should use MaskedValueIsZero if you don't know whether Op"
10844  " is a target node!");
10845 
10846  Known.resetAll();
10847  switch (Opc) {
10848  default: break;
10849  case RISCVISD::SELECT_CC: {
10850  Known = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(4), Depth + 1);
10851  // If we don't know any bits, early out.
10852  if (Known.isUnknown())
10853  break;
10854  KnownBits Known2 = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(3), Depth + 1);
10855 
10856  // Only known if known in both the LHS and RHS.
10857  Known = KnownBits::commonBits(Known, Known2);
10858  break;
10859  }
10860  case RISCVISD::REMUW: {
10861  KnownBits Known2;
10862  Known = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
10863  Known2 = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
10864  // We only care about the lower 32 bits.
10865  Known = KnownBits::urem(Known.trunc(32), Known2.trunc(32));
10866  // Restore the original width by sign extending.
10867  Known = Known.sext(BitWidth);
10868  break;
10869  }
10870  case RISCVISD::DIVUW: {
10871  KnownBits Known2;
10872  Known = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
10873  Known2 = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
10874  // We only care about the lower 32 bits.
10875  Known = KnownBits::udiv(Known.trunc(32), Known2.trunc(32));
10876  // Restore the original width by sign extending.
10877  Known = Known.sext(BitWidth);
10878  break;
10879  }
10880  case RISCVISD::CTZW: {
10881  KnownBits Known2 = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), Depth + 1);
10882  unsigned PossibleTZ = Known2.trunc(32).countMaxTrailingZeros();
10883  unsigned LowBits = llvm::bit_width(PossibleTZ);
10884  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(LowBits);
10885  break;
10886  }
10887  case RISCVISD::CLZW: {
10888  KnownBits Known2 = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), Depth + 1);
10889  unsigned PossibleLZ = Known2.trunc(32).countMaxLeadingZeros();
10890  unsigned LowBits = llvm::bit_width(PossibleLZ);
10891  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(LowBits);
10892  break;
10893  }
10894  case RISCVISD::BREV8:
10895  case RISCVISD::ORC_B: {
10896  // FIXME: This is based on the non-ratified Zbp GREV and GORC where a
10897  // control value of 7 is equivalent to brev8 and orc.b.
10898  Known = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), Depth + 1);
10899  bool IsGORC = Op.getOpcode() == RISCVISD::ORC_B;
10900  // To compute zeros, we need to invert the value and invert it back after.
10901  Known.Zero =
10902  ~computeGREVOrGORC(~Known.Zero.getZExtValue(), 7, IsGORC);
10903  Known.One = computeGREVOrGORC(Known.One.getZExtValue(), 7, IsGORC);
10904  break;
10905  }
10906  case RISCVISD::READ_VLENB: {
10907  // We can use the minimum and maximum VLEN values to bound VLENB. We
10908  // know VLEN must be a power of two.
10909  const unsigned MinVLenB = Subtarget.getRealMinVLen() / 8;
10910  const unsigned MaxVLenB = Subtarget.getRealMaxVLen() / 8;
10911  assert(MinVLenB > 0 && "READ_VLENB without vector extension enabled?");
10912  Known.Zero.setLowBits(Log2_32(MinVLenB));
10913  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(Log2_32(MaxVLenB)+1);
10914  if (MaxVLenB == MinVLenB)
10915  Known.One.setBit(Log2_32(MinVLenB));
10916  break;
10917  }
10918  case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN:
10919  case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN: {
10920  unsigned IntNo =
10921  Op.getConstantOperandVal(Opc == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN ? 0 : 1);
10922  switch (IntNo) {
10923  default:
10924  // We can't do anything for most intrinsics.
10925  break;
10926  case Intrinsic::riscv_vsetvli:
10927  case Intrinsic::riscv_vsetvlimax:
10928  // Assume that VL output is >= 65536.
10929  // TODO: Take SEW and LMUL into account.
10930  if (BitWidth > 17)
10931  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(17);
10932  break;
10933  }
10934  break;
10935  }
10936  }
10937 }
10938 
10939 unsigned RISCVTargetLowering::ComputeNumSignBitsForTargetNode(
10940  SDValue Op, const APInt &DemandedElts, const SelectionDAG &DAG,
10941  unsigned Depth) const {
10942  switch (Op.getOpcode()) {
10943  default:
10944  break;
10945  case RISCVISD::SELECT_CC: {
10946  unsigned Tmp =
10947  DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(3), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
10948  if (Tmp == 1) return 1; // Early out.
10949  unsigned Tmp2 =
10950  DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(4), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
10951  return std::min(Tmp, Tmp2);
10952  }
10953  case RISCVISD::ABSW: {
10954  // We expand this at isel to negw+max. The result will have 33 sign bits
10955  // if the input has at least 33 sign bits.
10956  unsigned Tmp =
10957  DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
10958  if (Tmp < 33) return 1;
10959  return 33;
10960  }
10961  case RISCVISD::SLLW:
10962  case RISCVISD::SRAW:
10963  case RISCVISD::SRLW:
10964  case RISCVISD::DIVW:
10965  case RISCVISD::DIVUW:
10966  case RISCVISD::REMUW:
10967  case RISCVISD::ROLW:
10968  case RISCVISD::RORW:
10969  case RISCVISD::FCVT_W_RV64:
10970  case RISCVISD::FCVT_WU_RV64:
10971  case RISCVISD::STRICT_FCVT_W_RV64:
10972  case RISCVISD::STRICT_FCVT_WU_RV64:
10973  // TODO: As the result is sign-extended, this is conservatively correct. A
10974  // more precise answer could be calculated for SRAW depending on known
10975  // bits in the shift amount.
10976  return 33;
10977  case RISCVISD::VMV_X_S: {
10978  // The number of sign bits of the scalar result is computed by obtaining the
10979  // element type of the input vector operand, subtracting its width from the
10980  // XLEN, and then adding one (sign bit within the element type). If the
10981  // element type is wider than XLen, the least-significant XLEN bits are
10982  // taken.
10983  unsigned XLen = Subtarget.getXLen();
10984  unsigned EltBits = Op.getOperand(0).getScalarValueSizeInBits();
10985  if (EltBits <= XLen)
10986  return XLen - EltBits + 1;
10987  break;
10988  }
10989  case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN: {
10990  unsigned IntNo = Op.getConstantOperandVal(1);
10991  switch (IntNo) {
10992  default:
10993  break;
10994  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_xchg_i64:
10995  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_add_i64:
10996  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_sub_i64:
10997  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_nand_i64:
10998  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_max_i64:
10999  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_min_i64:
11000  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_umax_i64:
11001  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_umin_i64:
11002  case Intrinsic::riscv_masked_cmpxchg_i64:
11003  // riscv_masked_{atomicrmw_*,cmpxchg} intrinsics represent an emulated
11004  // narrow atomic operation. These are implemented using atomic
11005  // operations at the minimum supported atomicrmw/cmpxchg width whose
11006  // result is then sign extended to XLEN. With +A, the minimum width is
11007  // 32 for both 64 and 32.
11008  assert(Subtarget.getXLen() == 64);
11009  assert(getMinCmpXchgSizeInBits() == 32);
11010  assert(Subtarget.hasStdExtA());
11011  return 33;
11012  }
11013  }
11014  }
11015 
11016  return 1;
11017 }
11018 
11019 const Constant *
11020 RISCVTargetLowering::getTargetConstantFromLoad(LoadSDNode *Ld) const {
11021  assert(Ld && "Unexpected null LoadSDNode");
11022  if (!ISD::isNormalLoad(Ld))
11023  return nullptr;
11024 
11025  SDValue Ptr = Ld->getBasePtr();
11026 
11027  // Only constant pools with no offset are supported.
11028  auto GetSupportedConstantPool = [](SDValue Ptr) -> ConstantPoolSDNode * {
11029  auto *CNode = dyn_cast<ConstantPoolSDNode>(Ptr);
11030  if (!CNode || CNode->isMachineConstantPoolEntry() ||
11031  CNode->getOffset() != 0)
11032  return nullptr;
11033 
11034  return CNode;
11035  };
11036 
11037  // Simple case, LLA.
11038  if (Ptr.getOpcode() == RISCVISD::LLA) {
11039  auto *CNode = GetSupportedConstantPool(Ptr);
11040  if (!CNode || CNode->getTargetFlags() != 0)
11041  return nullptr;
11042 
11043  return CNode->getConstVal();
11044  }
11045 
11046  // Look for a HI and ADD_LO pair.
11047  if (Ptr.getOpcode() != RISCVISD::ADD_LO ||
11048  Ptr.getOperand(0).getOpcode() != RISCVISD::HI)
11049  return nullptr;
11050 
11051  auto *CNodeLo = GetSupportedConstantPool(Ptr.getOperand(1));
11052  auto *CNodeHi = GetSupportedConstantPool(Ptr.getOperand(0).getOperand(0));
11053 
11054  if (!CNodeLo || CNodeLo->getTargetFlags() != RISCVII::MO_LO ||
11055  !CNodeHi || CNodeHi->getTargetFlags() != RISCVII::MO_HI)
11056  return nullptr;
11057 
11058  if (CNodeLo->getConstVal() != CNodeHi->getConstVal())
11059  return nullptr;
11060 
11061  return CNodeLo->getConstVal();
11062 }
11063 
11064 static MachineBasicBlock *emitReadCycleWidePseudo(MachineInstr &MI,
11065  MachineBasicBlock *BB) {
11066  assert(MI.getOpcode() == RISCV::ReadCycleWide && "Unexpected instruction");
11067 
11068  // To read the 64-bit cycle CSR on a 32-bit target, we read the two halves.
11069  // Should the count have wrapped while it was being read, we need to try
11070  // again.
11071  // ...
11072  // read:
11073  // rdcycleh x3 # load high word of cycle
11074  // rdcycle x2 # load low word of cycle
11075  // rdcycleh x4 # load high word of cycle
11076  // bne x3, x4, read # check if high word reads match, otherwise try again
11077  // ...
11078 
11079  MachineFunction &MF = *BB->getParent();
11080  const BasicBlock *LLVM_BB = BB->getBasicBlock();
11081  MachineFunction::iterator It = ++BB->getIterator();
11082 
11083  MachineBasicBlock *LoopMBB = MF.CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
11084  MF.insert(It, LoopMBB);
11085 
11086  MachineBasicBlock *DoneMBB = MF.CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
11087  MF.insert(It, DoneMBB);
11088 
11089  // Transfer the remainder of BB and its successor edges to DoneMBB.
11090  DoneMBB->splice(DoneMBB->begin(), BB,
11091  std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)), BB->end());
11092  DoneMBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(BB);
11093 
11094  BB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
11095 
11096  MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF.getRegInfo();
11097  Register ReadAgainReg = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&RISCV::GPRRegClass);
11098  Register LoReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
11099  Register HiReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
11100  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
11101 
11102  const TargetInstrInfo *TII = MF.getSubtarget().getInstrInfo();
11103  BuildMI(LoopMBB, DL, TII->get(RISCV::CSRRS), HiReg)
11104  .addImm(RISCVSysReg::lookupSysRegByName("CYCLEH")->Encoding)
11105  .addReg(RISCV::X0);
11106  BuildMI(LoopMBB, DL, TII->get(RISCV::CSRRS), LoReg)
11107  .addImm(RISCVSysReg::lookupSysRegByName("CYCLE")->Encoding)
11108  .addReg(RISCV::X0);
11109  BuildMI(LoopMBB, DL, TII->get(RISCV::CSRRS), ReadAgainReg)
11110  .addImm(RISCVSysReg::lookupSysRegByName("CYCLEH")->Encoding)
11111  .addReg(RISCV::X0);
11112 
11113  BuildMI(LoopMBB, DL, TII->get(RISCV::BNE))
11114  .addReg(HiReg)
11115  .addReg(ReadAgainReg)
11116  .addMBB(LoopMBB);
11117 
11118  LoopMBB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
11119  LoopMBB->addSuccessor(DoneMBB);
11120 
11121  MI.eraseFromParent();
11122 
11123  return DoneMBB;
11124 }
11125 
11126 static MachineBasicBlock *emitSplitF64Pseudo(MachineInstr &MI,
11127  MachineBasicBlock *BB) {
11128  assert(MI.getOpcode() == RISCV::SplitF64Pseudo && "Unexpected instruction");
11129 
11130  MachineFunction &MF = *BB->getParent();
11131  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
11132  const TargetInstrInfo &TII = *MF.getSubtarget().getInstrInfo();
11133  const TargetRegisterInfo *RI = MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo();
11134  Register LoReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
11135  Register HiReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
11136  Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
11137  const TargetRegisterClass *SrcRC = &RISCV::FPR64RegClass;
11138  int FI = MF.getInfo<RISCVMachineFunctionInfo>()->getMoveF64FrameIndex(MF);
11139 
11140  TII.storeRegToStackSlot(*BB, MI, SrcReg, MI.getOperand(2).isKill(), FI, SrcRC,
11141  RI, Register());
11142  MachinePointerInfo MPI = MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI);
11143  MachineMemOperand *MMOLo =
11144  MF.getMachineMemOperand(MPI, MachineMemOperand::MOLoad, 4, Align(8));
11145  MachineMemOperand *MMOHi = MF.getMachineMemOperand(
11146  MPI.getWithOffset(4), MachineMemOperand::MOLoad, 4, Align(8));
11147  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RISCV::LW), LoReg)
11148  .addFrameIndex(FI)
11149  .addImm(0)
11150  .addMemOperand(MMOLo);
11151  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RISCV::LW), HiReg)
11152  .addFrameIndex(FI)
11153  .addImm(4)
11154  .addMemOperand(MMOHi);
11155  MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now.
11156  return BB;
11157 }
11158 
11159 static MachineBasicBlock *emitBuildPairF64Pseudo(MachineInstr &MI,
11160  MachineBasicBlock *BB) {
11161  assert(MI.getOpcode() == RISCV::BuildPairF64Pseudo &&
11162  "Unexpected instruction");
11163 
11164  MachineFunction &MF = *BB->getParent();
11165  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
11166  const TargetInstrInfo &TII = *MF.getSubtarget().getInstrInfo();
11167  const TargetRegisterInfo *RI = MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo();
11168  Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
11169  Register LoReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
11170  Register HiReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
11171  const TargetRegisterClass *DstRC = &RISCV::FPR64RegClass;
11172  int FI = MF.getInfo<RISCVMachineFunctionInfo>()->getMoveF64FrameIndex(MF);
11173 
11174  MachinePointerInfo MPI = MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI);
11175  MachineMemOperand *MMOLo =
11176  MF.getMachineMemOperand(MPI, MachineMemOperand::MOStore, 4, Align(8));
11177  MachineMemOperand *MMOHi = MF.getMachineMemOperand(
11178  MPI.getWithOffset(4), MachineMemOperand::MOStore, 4, Align(8));
11179  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RISCV::SW))
11180  .addReg(LoReg, getKillRegState(MI.getOperand(1).isKill()))
11181  .addFrameIndex(FI)
11182  .addImm(0)
11183  .addMemOperand(MMOLo);
11184  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RISCV::SW))
11185  .addReg(HiReg, getKillRegState(MI.getOperand(2).isKill()))
11186  .addFrameIndex(FI)
11187  .addImm(4)
11188  .addMemOperand(MMOHi);
11189  TII.loadRegFromStackSlot(*BB, MI, DstReg, FI, DstRC, RI, Register());
11190  MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now.
11191  return BB;
11192 }
11193 
11194 static bool isSelectPseudo(MachineInstr &MI) {
11195  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
11196  default:
11197  return false;
11198  case RISCV::Select_GPR_Using_CC_GPR:
11199  case RISCV::Select_FPR16_Using_CC_GPR:
11200  case RISCV::Select_FPR32_Using_CC_GPR:
11201  case RISCV::Select_FPR64_Using_CC_GPR:
11202  return true;
11203  }
11204 }

11206 static MachineBasicBlock *emitQuietFCMP(MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *BB,
11207  unsigned RelOpcode, unsigned EqOpcode,
11208  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
11209  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
11210  Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
11211  Register Src1Reg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
11212  Register Src2Reg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
11213  MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
11214  Register SavedFFlags = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&RISCV::GPRRegClass);
11215  const TargetInstrInfo &TII = *BB->getParent()->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo();
11216 
11217  // Save the current FFLAGS.
11218  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RISCV::ReadFFLAGS), SavedFFlags);
11219 
11220  auto MIB = BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RelOpcode), DstReg)
11221  .addReg(Src1Reg)
11222  .addReg(Src2Reg);
11223  if (MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::NoFPExcept))
11224  MIB->setFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::NoFPExcept);
11225 
11226  // Restore the FFLAGS.
11227  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RISCV::WriteFFLAGS))
11228  .addReg(SavedFFlags, RegState::Kill);
11229 
11230  // Issue a dummy FEQ opcode to raise exception for signaling NaNs.
11231  auto MIB2 = BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(EqOpcode), RISCV::X0)
11232  .addReg(Src1Reg, getKillRegState(MI.getOperand(1).isKill()))
11233  .addReg(Src2Reg, getKillRegState(MI.getOperand(2).isKill()));
11234  if (MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::NoFPExcept))
11235  MIB2->setFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::NoFPExcept);
11236 
11237  // Erase the pseudoinstruction.
11238  MI.eraseFromParent();
11239  return BB;
11240 }
11241 
11242 static MachineBasicBlock *
11243 EmitLoweredCascadedSelect(MachineInstr &First, MachineInstr &Second,
11244  MachineBasicBlock *ThisMBB,
11245  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
11246  // Select_FPRX_ (rs1, rs2, imm, rs4, (Select_FPRX_ rs1, rs2, imm, rs4, rs5)
11247  // Without this, custom-inserter would have generated:
11248  //
11249  // A
11250  // | \
11251  // | B
11252  // | /
11253  // C
11254  // | \
11255  // | D
11256  // | /
11257  // E
11258  //
11259  // A: X = ...; Y = ...
11260  // B: empty
11261  // C: Z = PHI [X, A], [Y, B]
11262  // D: empty
11263  // E: PHI [X, C], [Z, D]
11264  //
11265  // If we lower both Select_FPRX_ in a single step, we can instead generate:
11266  //
11267  // A
11268  // | \
11269  // | C
11270  // | /|
11271  // |/ |
11272  // | |
11273  // | D
11274  // | /
11275  // E
11276  //
11277  // A: X = ...; Y = ...
11278  // D: empty
11279  // E: PHI [X, A], [X, C], [Y, D]
11280 
11281  const RISCVInstrInfo &TII = *Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
11282  const DebugLoc &DL = First.getDebugLoc();
11283  const BasicBlock *LLVM_BB = ThisMBB->getBasicBlock();
11284  MachineFunction *F = ThisMBB->getParent();
11285  MachineBasicBlock *FirstMBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
11286  MachineBasicBlock *SecondMBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
11287  MachineBasicBlock *SinkMBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
11288  MachineFunction::iterator It = ++ThisMBB->getIterator();
11289  F->insert(It, FirstMBB);
11290  F->insert(It, SecondMBB);
11291  F->insert(It, SinkMBB);
11292 
11293  // Transfer the remainder of ThisMBB and its successor edges to SinkMBB.
11294  SinkMBB->splice(SinkMBB->begin(), ThisMBB,
11295  std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(First)),
11296  ThisMBB->end());
11297  SinkMBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(ThisMBB);
11298 
11299  // Fallthrough block for ThisMBB.
11300  ThisMBB->addSuccessor(FirstMBB);
11301  // Fallthrough block for FirstMBB.
11302  FirstMBB->addSuccessor(SecondMBB);
11303  ThisMBB->addSuccessor(SinkMBB);
11304  FirstMBB->addSuccessor(SinkMBB);
11305  // This is fallthrough.
11306  SecondMBB->addSuccessor(SinkMBB);
11307 
11308  auto FirstCC = static_cast<RISCVCC::CondCode>(First.getOperand(3).getImm());
11309  Register FLHS = First.getOperand(1).getReg();
11310  Register FRHS = First.getOperand(2).getReg();
11311  // Insert appropriate branch.
11312  BuildMI(FirstMBB, DL, TII.getBrCond(FirstCC))
11313  .addReg(FLHS)
11314  .addReg(FRHS)
11315  .addMBB(SinkMBB);
11316 
11317  Register SLHS = Second.getOperand(1).getReg();
11318  Register SRHS = Second.getOperand(2).getReg();
11319  Register Op1Reg4 = First.getOperand(4).getReg();
11320  Register Op1Reg5 = First.getOperand(5).getReg();
11321 
11322  auto SecondCC = static_cast<RISCVCC::CondCode>(Second.getOperand(3).getImm());
11323  // Insert appropriate branch.
11324  BuildMI(ThisMBB, DL, TII.getBrCond(SecondCC))
11325  .addReg(SLHS)
11326  .addReg(SRHS)
11327  .addMBB(SinkMBB);
11328 
11329  Register DestReg = Second.getOperand(0).getReg();
11330  Register Op2Reg4 = Second.getOperand(4).getReg();
11331  BuildMI(*SinkMBB, SinkMBB->begin(), DL, TII.get(RISCV::PHI), DestReg)
11332  .addReg(Op2Reg4)
11333  .addMBB(ThisMBB)
11334  .addReg(Op1Reg4)
11335  .addMBB(FirstMBB)
11336  .addReg(Op1Reg5)
11337  .addMBB(SecondMBB);
11338 
11339  // Now remove the Select_FPRX_s.
11340  First.eraseFromParent();
11341  Second.eraseFromParent();
11342  return SinkMBB;
11343 }
11344 
11345 static MachineBasicBlock *emitSelectPseudo(MachineInstr &MI,
11346  MachineBasicBlock *BB,
11347  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
11348  // To "insert" Select_* instructions, we actually have to insert the triangle
11349  // control-flow pattern. The incoming instructions know the destination vreg
11350  // to set, the condition code register to branch on, the true/false values to
11351  // select between, and the condcode to use to select the appropriate branch.
11352  //
11353  // We produce the following control flow:
11354  // HeadMBB
11355  // | \
11356  // | IfFalseMBB
11357  // | /
11358  // TailMBB
11359  //
11360  // When we find a sequence of selects we attempt to optimize their emission
11361  // by sharing the control flow. Currently we only handle cases where we have
11362  // multiple selects with the exact same condition (same LHS, RHS and CC).
11363  // The selects may be interleaved with other instructions if the other
11364  // instructions meet some requirements we deem safe:
11365  // - They are not pseudo instructions.
11366  // - They are debug instructions. Otherwise,
11367  // - They do not have side-effects, do not access memory and their inputs do
11368  // not depend on the results of the select pseudo-instructions.
11369  // The TrueV/FalseV operands of the selects cannot depend on the result of
11370  // previous selects in the sequence.
11371  // These conditions could be further relaxed. See the X86 target for a
11372  // related approach and more information.
11373  //
11374  // Select_FPRX_ (rs1, rs2, imm, rs4, (Select_FPRX_ rs1, rs2, imm, rs4, rs5))
11375  // is checked here and handled by a separate function -
11376  // EmitLoweredCascadedSelect.
11377  Register LHS = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
11378  Register RHS = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
11379  auto CC = static_cast<RISCVCC::CondCode>(MI.getOperand(3).getImm());
11380 
11381  SmallVector<MachineInstr *, 4> SelectDebugValues;
11382  SmallSet<Register, 4> SelectDests;
11383  SelectDests.insert(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
11384 
11385  MachineInstr *LastSelectPseudo = &MI;
11386  auto Next = next_nodbg(MI.getIterator(), BB->instr_end());
11387  if (MI.getOpcode() != RISCV::Select_GPR_Using_CC_GPR && Next != BB->end() &&
11388  Next->getOpcode() == MI.getOpcode() &&
11389  Next->getOperand(5).getReg() == MI.getOperand(0).getReg() &&
11390  Next->getOperand(5).isKill()) {
11391  return EmitLoweredCascadedSelect(MI, *Next, BB, Subtarget);
11392  }
11393 
11394  for (auto E = BB->end(), SequenceMBBI = MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI);
11395  SequenceMBBI != E; ++SequenceMBBI) {
11396  if (SequenceMBBI->isDebugInstr())
11397  continue;
11398  if (isSelectPseudo(*SequenceMBBI)) {
11399  if (SequenceMBBI->getOperand(1).getReg() != LHS ||
11400  SequenceMBBI->getOperand(2).getReg() != RHS ||
11401  SequenceMBBI->getOperand(3).getImm() != CC ||
11402  SelectDests.count(SequenceMBBI->getOperand(4).getReg()) ||
11403  SelectDests.count(SequenceMBBI->getOperand(5).getReg()))
11404  break;
11405  LastSelectPseudo = &*SequenceMBBI;
11406  SequenceMBBI->collectDebugValues(SelectDebugValues);
11407  SelectDests.insert(SequenceMBBI->getOperand(0).getReg());
11408  continue;
11409  }
11410  if (SequenceMBBI->hasUnmodeledSideEffects() ||
11411  SequenceMBBI->mayLoadOrStore() ||
11412  SequenceMBBI->usesCustomInsertionHook())
11413  break;
11414  if (llvm::any_of(SequenceMBBI->operands(), [&](MachineOperand &MO) {
11415  return MO.isReg() && MO.isUse() && SelectDests.count(MO.getReg());
11416  }))
11417  break;
11418  }
11419 
11420  const RISCVInstrInfo &TII = *Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
11421  const BasicBlock *LLVM_BB = BB->getBasicBlock();
11422  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
11423  MachineFunction::iterator I = ++BB->getIterator();
11424 
11425  MachineBasicBlock *HeadMBB = BB;
11426  MachineFunction *F = BB->getParent();
11427  MachineBasicBlock *TailMBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
11428  MachineBasicBlock *IfFalseMBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
11429 
11430  F->insert(I, IfFalseMBB);
11431  F->insert(I, TailMBB);
11432 
11433  // Transfer debug instructions associated with the selects to TailMBB.
11434  for (MachineInstr *DebugInstr : SelectDebugValues) {
11435  TailMBB->push_back(DebugInstr->removeFromParent());
11436  }
11437 
11438  // Move all instructions after the sequence to TailMBB.
11439  TailMBB->splice(TailMBB->end(), HeadMBB,
11440  std::next(LastSelectPseudo->getIterator()), HeadMBB->end());
11441  // Update machine-CFG edges by transferring all successors of the current
11442  // block to the new block which will contain the Phi nodes for the selects.
11443  TailMBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(HeadMBB);
11444  // Set the successors for HeadMBB.
11445  HeadMBB->addSuccessor(IfFalseMBB);
11446  HeadMBB->addSuccessor(TailMBB);
11447 
11448  // Insert appropriate branch.
11449  BuildMI(HeadMBB, DL, TII.getBrCond(CC))
11450  .addReg(LHS)
11451  .addReg(RHS)
11452  .addMBB(TailMBB);
11453 
11454  // IfFalseMBB just falls through to TailMBB.
11455  IfFalseMBB->addSuccessor(TailMBB);
11456 
11457  // Create PHIs for all of the select pseudo-instructions.
11458  auto SelectMBBI = MI.getIterator();
11459  auto SelectEnd = std::next(LastSelectPseudo->getIterator());
11460  auto InsertionPoint = TailMBB->begin();
11461  while (SelectMBBI != SelectEnd) {
11462  auto Next = std::next(SelectMBBI);
11463  if (isSelectPseudo(*SelectMBBI)) {
11464  // %Result = phi [ %TrueValue, HeadMBB ], [ %FalseValue, IfFalseMBB ]
11465  BuildMI(*TailMBB, InsertionPoint, SelectMBBI->getDebugLoc(),
11466  TII.get(RISCV::PHI), SelectMBBI->getOperand(0).getReg())
11467  .addReg(SelectMBBI->getOperand(4).getReg())
11468  .addMBB(HeadMBB)
11469  .addReg(SelectMBBI->getOperand(5).getReg())
11470  .addMBB(IfFalseMBB);
11471  SelectMBBI->eraseFromParent();
11472  }
11473  SelectMBBI = Next;
11474  }
11475 
11476  F->getProperties().reset(MachineFunctionProperties::Property::NoPHIs);
11477  return TailMBB;
11478 }
11479 
11480 static MachineBasicBlock *
11481 emitVFCVT_RM_MASK(MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *BB, unsigned Opcode) {
11482  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
11483 
11484  const TargetInstrInfo &TII = *BB->getParent()->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo();
11485 
11486  MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
11487  Register SavedFRM = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&RISCV::GPRRegClass);
11488 
11489  // Update FRM and save the old value.
11490  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RISCV::SwapFRMImm), SavedFRM)
11491  .addImm(MI.getOperand(4).getImm());
11492 
11493  // Emit an VFCVT without the FRM operand.
11494  assert(MI.getNumOperands() == 8);
11495  auto MIB = BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(Opcode))
11496  .add(MI.getOperand(0))
11497  .add(MI.getOperand(1))
11498  .add(MI.getOperand(2))
11499  .add(MI.getOperand(3))
11500  .add(MI.getOperand(5))
11501  .add(MI.getOperand(6))
11502  .add(MI.getOperand(7));
11503  if (MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::NoFPExcept))
11504  MIB->setFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::NoFPExcept);
11505 
11506  // Restore FRM.
11507  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RISCV::WriteFRM))
11508  .addReg(SavedFRM, RegState::Kill);
11509 
11510  // Erase the pseudoinstruction.
11511  MI.eraseFromParent();
11512  return BB;
11513 }
11514 
11515 static MachineBasicBlock *emitVFROUND_NOEXCEPT_MASK(MachineInstr &MI,
11516  MachineBasicBlock *BB,
11517  unsigned CVTXOpc,
11518  unsigned CVTFOpc) {
11519  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
11520 
11521  const TargetInstrInfo &TII = *BB->getParent()->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo();
11522 
11523  MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
11524  Register SavedFFLAGS = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&RISCV::GPRRegClass);
11525 
11526  // Save the old value of FFLAGS.
11527  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RISCV::ReadFFLAGS), SavedFFLAGS);
11528 
11529  assert(MI.getNumOperands() == 7);
11530 
11531  // Emit a VFCVT_X_F
11532  const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI =
11533  BB->getParent()->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo();
11534  const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MI.getRegClassConstraint(0, &TII, TRI);
11535  Register Tmp = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
11536  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(CVTXOpc), Tmp)
11537  .add(MI.getOperand(1))
11538  .add(MI.getOperand(2))
11539  .add(MI.getOperand(3))
11540  .add(MI.getOperand(4))
11541  .add(MI.getOperand(5))
11542  .add(MI.getOperand(6));
11543 
11544  // Emit a VFCVT_F_X
11545  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(CVTFOpc))
11546  .add(MI.getOperand(0))
11547  .add(MI.getOperand(1))
11548  .addReg(Tmp)
11549  .add(MI.getOperand(3))
11550  .add(MI.getOperand(4))
11551  .add(MI.getOperand(5))
11552  .add(MI.getOperand(6));
11553 
11554  // Restore FFLAGS.
11555  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RISCV::WriteFFLAGS))
11556  .addReg(SavedFFLAGS, RegState::Kill);
11557 
11558  // Erase the pseudoinstruction.
11559  MI.eraseFromParent();
11560  return BB;
11561 }
11562 
11563 static MachineBasicBlock *emitFROUND(MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *MBB,
11564  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
11565  unsigned CmpOpc, F2IOpc, I2FOpc, FSGNJOpc, FSGNJXOpc;
11566  const TargetRegisterClass *RC;
11567  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
11568  default:
11569  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected opcode");
11570  case RISCV::PseudoFROUND_H:
11571  CmpOpc = RISCV::FLT_H;
11572  F2IOpc = RISCV::FCVT_W_H;
11573  I2FOpc = RISCV::FCVT_H_W;
11574  FSGNJOpc = RISCV::FSGNJ_H;
11575  FSGNJXOpc = RISCV::FSGNJX_H;
11576  RC = &RISCV::FPR16RegClass;
11577  break;
11578  case RISCV::PseudoFROUND_S:
11579  CmpOpc = RISCV::FLT_S;
11580  F2IOpc = RISCV::FCVT_W_S;
11581  I2FOpc = RISCV::FCVT_S_W;
11582  FSGNJOpc = RISCV::FSGNJ_S;
11583  FSGNJXOpc = RISCV::FSGNJX_S;
11584  RC = &RISCV::FPR32RegClass;
11585  break;
11586  case RISCV::PseudoFROUND_D:
11587  assert(Subtarget.is64Bit() && "Expected 64-bit GPR.");
11588  CmpOpc = RISCV::FLT_D;
11589  F2IOpc = RISCV::FCVT_L_D;
11590  I2FOpc = RISCV::FCVT_D_L;
11591  FSGNJOpc = RISCV::FSGNJ_D;
11592  FSGNJXOpc = RISCV::FSGNJX_D;
11593  RC = &RISCV::FPR64RegClass;
11594  break;
11595  }
11596 
11597  const BasicBlock *BB = MBB->getBasicBlock();
11598  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
11599  MachineFunction::iterator I = ++MBB->getIterator();
11600 
11601  MachineFunction *F = MBB->getParent();
11602  MachineBasicBlock *CvtMBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(BB);
11603  MachineBasicBlock *DoneMBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(BB);
11604 
11605  F->insert(I, CvtMBB);
11606  F->insert(I, DoneMBB);
11607  // Move all instructions after the sequence to DoneMBB.
11608  DoneMBB->splice(DoneMBB->end(), MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI),
11609  MBB->end());
11610  // Update machine-CFG edges by transferring all successors of the current
11611  // block to the new block which will contain the Phi nodes for the selects.
11612  DoneMBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(MBB);
11613  // Set the successors for MBB.
11614  MBB->addSuccessor(CvtMBB);
11615  MBB->addSuccessor(DoneMBB);
11616 
11617  Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
11618  Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
11619  Register MaxReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
11620  int64_t FRM = MI.getOperand(3).getImm();
11621 
11622  const RISCVInstrInfo &TII = *Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
11623  MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MBB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
11624 
11625  Register FabsReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
11626  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII.get(FSGNJXOpc), FabsReg).addReg(SrcReg).addReg(SrcReg);
11627 
11628  // Compare the FP value to the max value.
11629  Register CmpReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&RISCV::GPRRegClass);
11630  auto MIB =
11631  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII.get(CmpOpc), CmpReg).addReg(FabsReg).addReg(MaxReg);
11632  if (MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::NoFPExcept))
11633  MIB->setFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::NoFPExcept);
11634 
11635  // Insert branch.
11636  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII.get(RISCV::BEQ))
11637  .addReg(CmpReg)
11638  .addReg(RISCV::X0)
11639  .addMBB(DoneMBB);
11640 
11641  CvtMBB->addSuccessor(DoneMBB);
11642 
11643  // Convert to integer.
11644  Register F2IReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&RISCV::GPRRegClass);
11645  MIB = BuildMI(CvtMBB, DL, TII.get(F2IOpc), F2IReg).addReg(SrcReg).addImm(FRM);
11646  if (MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::NoFPExcept))
11647  MIB->setFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::NoFPExcept);
11648 
11649  // Convert back to FP.
11650  Register I2FReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
11651  MIB = BuildMI(CvtMBB, DL, TII.get(I2FOpc), I2FReg).addReg(F2IReg).addImm(FRM);
11652  if (MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::NoFPExcept))
11653  MIB->setFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::NoFPExcept);
11654 
11655  // Restore the sign bit.
11656  Register CvtReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
11657  BuildMI(CvtMBB, DL, TII.get(FSGNJOpc), CvtReg).addReg(I2FReg).addReg(SrcReg);
11658 
11659  // Merge the results.
11660  BuildMI(*DoneMBB, DoneMBB->begin(), DL, TII.get(RISCV::PHI), DstReg)
11661  .addReg(SrcReg)
11662  .addMBB(MBB)
11663  .addReg(CvtReg)
11664  .addMBB(CvtMBB);
11665 
11666  MI.eraseFromParent();
11667  return DoneMBB;
11668 }
11669 
11670 MachineBasicBlock *
11671 RISCVTargetLowering::EmitInstrWithCustomInserter(MachineInstr &MI,
11672  MachineBasicBlock *BB) const {
11673  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
11674  default:
11675  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected instr type to insert");
11676  case RISCV::ReadCycleWide:
11677  assert(!Subtarget.is64Bit() &&
11678  "ReadCycleWrite is only to be used on riscv32");
11679  return emitReadCycleWidePseudo(MI, BB);
11680  case RISCV::Select_GPR_Using_CC_GPR:
11681  case RISCV::Select_FPR16_Using_CC_GPR:
11682  case RISCV::Select_FPR32_Using_CC_GPR:
11683  case RISCV::Select_FPR64_Using_CC_GPR:

11685  case RISCV::BuildPairF64Pseudo:

11870  RISCV::PseudoVFCVT_F_X_V_M4_MASK);
11871  case RISCV::PseudoVFROUND_NOEXCEPT_V_M8_MASK:
11872  return emitVFROUND_NOEXCEPT_MASK(MI, BB, RISCV::PseudoVFCVT_X_F_V_M8_MASK,
11873  RISCV::PseudoVFCVT_F_X_V_M8_MASK);
