11875  return emitVFROUND_NOEXCEPT_MASK(MI, BB, RISCV::PseudoVFCVT_X_F_V_MF2_MASK,
11876  RISCV::PseudoVFCVT_F_X_V_MF2_MASK);
11877  case RISCV::PseudoVFROUND_NOEXCEPT_V_MF4_MASK:
11878  return emitVFROUND_NOEXCEPT_MASK(MI, BB, RISCV::PseudoVFCVT_X_F_V_MF4_MASK,
11879  RISCV::PseudoVFCVT_F_X_V_MF4_MASK);
11880  case RISCV::PseudoFROUND_H:
11881  case RISCV::PseudoFROUND_S:
11882  case RISCV::PseudoFROUND_D:
11883  return emitFROUND(MI, BB, Subtarget);
11884  }
11885 }
11886 
11887 void RISCVTargetLowering::AdjustInstrPostInstrSelection(MachineInstr &MI,
11888  SDNode *Node) const {
11889  // Add FRM dependency to any instructions with dynamic rounding mode.
11890  unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode();
11891  auto Idx = RISCV::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, RISCV::OpName::frm);
11892  if (Idx < 0)
11893  return;
11894  if (MI.getOperand(Idx).getImm() != RISCVFPRndMode::DYN)
11895  return;
11896  // If the instruction already reads FRM, don't add another read.
11897  if (MI.readsRegister(RISCV::FRM))
11898  return;
11899  MI.addOperand(
11900  MachineOperand::CreateReg(RISCV::FRM, /*isDef*/ false, /*isImp*/ true));
11901 }
11902 
11903 // Calling Convention Implementation.
11904 // The expectations for frontend ABI lowering vary from target to target.
11905 // Ideally, an LLVM frontend would be able to avoid worrying about many ABI
11906 // details, but this is a longer term goal. For now, we simply try to keep the
11907 // role of the frontend as simple and well-defined as possible. The rules can
11908 // be summarised as:
11909 // * Never split up large scalar arguments. We handle them here.
11910 // * If a hardfloat calling convention is being used, and the struct may be
11911 // passed in a pair of registers (fp+fp, int+fp), and both registers are
11912 // available, then pass as two separate arguments. If either the GPRs or FPRs
11913 // are exhausted, then pass according to the rule below.
11914 // * If a struct could never be passed in registers or directly in a stack
11915 // slot (as it is larger than 2*XLEN and the floating point rules don't
11916 // apply), then pass it using a pointer with the byval attribute.
11917 // * If a struct is less than 2*XLEN, then coerce to either a two-element
11918 // word-sized array or a 2*XLEN scalar (depending on alignment).
11919 // * The frontend can determine whether a struct is returned by reference or
11920 // not based on its size and fields. If it will be returned by reference, the
11921 // frontend must modify the prototype so a pointer with the sret annotation is
11922 // passed as the first argument. This is not necessary for large scalar
11923 // returns.
11924 // * Struct return values and varargs should be coerced to structs containing
11925 // register-size fields in the same situations they would be for fixed
11926 // arguments.
11927 
11928 static const MCPhysReg ArgGPRs[] = {
11929  RISCV::X10, RISCV::X11, RISCV::X12, RISCV::X13,
11930  RISCV::X14, RISCV::X15, RISCV::X16, RISCV::X17
11931 };
11932 static const MCPhysReg ArgFPR16s[] = {
11933  RISCV::F10_H, RISCV::F11_H, RISCV::F12_H, RISCV::F13_H,
11934  RISCV::F14_H, RISCV::F15_H, RISCV::F16_H, RISCV::F17_H
11935 };
11936 static const MCPhysReg ArgFPR32s[] = {
11937  RISCV::F10_F, RISCV::F11_F, RISCV::F12_F, RISCV::F13_F,
11938  RISCV::F14_F, RISCV::F15_F, RISCV::F16_F, RISCV::F17_F
11939 };
11940 static const MCPhysReg ArgFPR64s[] = {
11941  RISCV::F10_D, RISCV::F11_D, RISCV::F12_D, RISCV::F13_D,
11942  RISCV::F14_D, RISCV::F15_D, RISCV::F16_D, RISCV::F17_D
11943 };
11944 // This is an interim calling convention and it may be changed in the future.
11945 static const MCPhysReg ArgVRs[] = {
11946  RISCV::V8, RISCV::V9, RISCV::V10, RISCV::V11, RISCV::V12, RISCV::V13,
11947  RISCV::V14, RISCV::V15, RISCV::V16, RISCV::V17, RISCV::V18, RISCV::V19,
11948  RISCV::V20, RISCV::V21, RISCV::V22, RISCV::V23};
11949 static const MCPhysReg ArgVRM2s[] = {RISCV::V8M2, RISCV::V10M2, RISCV::V12M2,
11950  RISCV::V14M2, RISCV::V16M2, RISCV::V18M2,
11951  RISCV::V20M2, RISCV::V22M2};
11952 static const MCPhysReg ArgVRM4s[] = {RISCV::V8M4, RISCV::V12M4, RISCV::V16M4,
11953  RISCV::V20M4};
11954 static const MCPhysReg ArgVRM8s[] = {RISCV::V8M8, RISCV::V16M8};
11955 
11956 // Pass a 2*XLEN argument that has been split into two XLEN values through
11957 // registers or the stack as necessary.
11958 static bool CC_RISCVAssign2XLen(unsigned XLen, CCState &State, CCValAssign VA1,
11959  ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags1, unsigned ValNo2,
11960  MVT ValVT2, MVT LocVT2,
11961  ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags2) {
11962  unsigned XLenInBytes = XLen / 8;
11963  if (Register Reg = State.AllocateReg(ArgGPRs)) {
11964  // At least one half can be passed via register.
11965  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(VA1.getValNo(), VA1.getValVT(), Reg,
11966  VA1.getLocVT(), CCValAssign::Full));
11967  } else {
11968  // Both halves must be passed on the stack, with proper alignment.
11969  Align StackAlign =
11970  std::max(Align(XLenInBytes), ArgFlags1.getNonZeroOrigAlign());
11971  State.addLoc(
11972  CCValAssign::getMem(VA1.getValNo(), VA1.getValVT(),
11973  State.AllocateStack(XLenInBytes, StackAlign),
11974  VA1.getLocVT(), CCValAssign::Full));
11975  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getMem(
11976  ValNo2, ValVT2, State.AllocateStack(XLenInBytes, Align(XLenInBytes)),
11977  LocVT2, CCValAssign::Full));
11978  return false;
11979  }
11980 
11981  if (Register Reg = State.AllocateReg(ArgGPRs)) {
11982  // The second half can also be passed via register.
11983  State.addLoc(
11984  CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo2, ValVT2, Reg, LocVT2, CCValAssign::Full));
11985  } else {
11986  // The second half is passed via the stack, without additional alignment.
11987  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getMem(
11988  ValNo2, ValVT2, State.AllocateStack(XLenInBytes, Align(XLenInBytes)),
11989  LocVT2, CCValAssign::Full));
11990  }
11991 
11992  return false;
11993 }
11994 
11995 static unsigned allocateRVVReg(MVT ValVT, unsigned ValNo,
11996  std::optional<unsigned> FirstMaskArgument,
11997  CCState &State, const RISCVTargetLowering &TLI) {
11998  const TargetRegisterClass *RC = TLI.getRegClassFor(ValVT);
11999  if (RC == &RISCV::VRRegClass) {
12000  // Assign the first mask argument to V0.
12001  // This is an interim calling convention and it may be changed in the
12002  // future.
12003  if (FirstMaskArgument && ValNo == *FirstMaskArgument)
12004  return State.AllocateReg(RISCV::V0);
12005  return State.AllocateReg(ArgVRs);
12006  }
12007  if (RC == &RISCV::VRM2RegClass)
12008  return State.AllocateReg(ArgVRM2s);
12009  if (RC == &RISCV::VRM4RegClass)
12010  return State.AllocateReg(ArgVRM4s);
12011  if (RC == &RISCV::VRM8RegClass)
12012  return State.AllocateReg(ArgVRM8s);
12013  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled register class for ValueType");
12014 }
12015 
12016 // Implements the RISC-V calling convention. Returns true upon failure.
12017 static bool CC_RISCV(const DataLayout &DL, RISCVABI::ABI ABI, unsigned ValNo,
12018  MVT ValVT, MVT LocVT, CCValAssign::LocInfo LocInfo,
12019  ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags, CCState &State, bool IsFixed,
12020  bool IsRet, Type *OrigTy, const RISCVTargetLowering &TLI,
12021  std::optional<unsigned> FirstMaskArgument) {
12022  unsigned XLen = DL.getLargestLegalIntTypeSizeInBits();
12023  assert(XLen == 32 || XLen == 64);
12024  MVT XLenVT = XLen == 32 ? MVT::i32 : MVT::i64;
12025 
12026  // Static chain parameter must not be passed in normal argument registers,
12027  // so we assign t2 for it as done in GCC's __builtin_call_with_static_chain
12028  if (ArgFlags.isNest()) {
12029  if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(RISCV::X7)) {
12030  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
12031  return false;
12032  }
12033  }
12034 
12035  // Any return value split in to more than two values can't be returned
12036  // directly. Vectors are returned via the available vector registers.
12037  if (!LocVT.isVector() && IsRet && ValNo > 1)
12038  return true;
12039 
12040  // UseGPRForF16_F32 if targeting one of the soft-float ABIs, if passing a
12041  // variadic argument, or if no F16/F32 argument registers are available.
12042  bool UseGPRForF16_F32 = true;
12043  // UseGPRForF64 if targeting soft-float ABIs or an FLEN=32 ABI, if passing a
12044  // variadic argument, or if no F64 argument registers are available.
12045  bool UseGPRForF64 = true;
12046 
12047  switch (ABI) {
12048  default:
12049  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected ABI");
12050  case RISCVABI::ABI_ILP32:
12051  case RISCVABI::ABI_LP64:
12052  break;
12053  case RISCVABI::ABI_ILP32F:
12054  case RISCVABI::ABI_LP64F:
12055  UseGPRForF16_F32 = !IsFixed;
12056  break;
12057  case RISCVABI::ABI_ILP32D:
12058  case RISCVABI::ABI_LP64D:
12059  UseGPRForF16_F32 = !IsFixed;
12060  UseGPRForF64 = !IsFixed;
12061  break;
12062  }
12063 
12064  // FPR16, FPR32, and FPR64 alias each other.
12065  if (State.getFirstUnallocated(ArgFPR32s) == std::size(ArgFPR32s)) {
12066  UseGPRForF16_F32 = true;
12067  UseGPRForF64 = true;
12068  }
12069 
12070  // From this point on, rely on UseGPRForF16_F32, UseGPRForF64 and
12071  // similar local variables rather than directly checking against the target
12072  // ABI.
12073 
12074  if (UseGPRForF16_F32 && (ValVT == MVT::f16 || ValVT == MVT::f32)) {
12075  LocVT = XLenVT;
12076  LocInfo = CCValAssign::BCvt;
12077  } else if (UseGPRForF64 && XLen == 64 && ValVT == MVT::f64) {
12078  LocVT = MVT::i64;
12079  LocInfo = CCValAssign::BCvt;
12080  }
12081 
12082  // If this is a variadic argument, the RISC-V calling convention requires
12083  // that it is assigned an 'even' or 'aligned' register if it has 8-byte
12084  // alignment (RV32) or 16-byte alignment (RV64). An aligned register should
12085  // be used regardless of whether the original argument was split during
12086  // legalisation or not. The argument will not be passed by registers if the
12087  // original type is larger than 2*XLEN, so the register alignment rule does
12088  // not apply.
12089  unsigned TwoXLenInBytes = (2 * XLen) / 8;
12090  if (!IsFixed && ArgFlags.getNonZeroOrigAlign() == TwoXLenInBytes &&
12091  DL.getTypeAllocSize(OrigTy) == TwoXLenInBytes) {
12092  unsigned RegIdx = State.getFirstUnallocated(ArgGPRs);
12093  // Skip 'odd' register if necessary.
12094  if (RegIdx != std::size(ArgGPRs) && RegIdx % 2 == 1)
12095  State.AllocateReg(ArgGPRs);
12096  }
12097 
12098  SmallVectorImpl<CCValAssign> &PendingLocs = State.getPendingLocs();
12099  SmallVectorImpl<ISD::ArgFlagsTy> &PendingArgFlags =
12100  State.getPendingArgFlags();
12101 
12102  assert(PendingLocs.size() == PendingArgFlags.size() &&
12103  "PendingLocs and PendingArgFlags out of sync");
12104 
12105  // Handle passing f64 on RV32D with a soft float ABI or when floating point
12106  // registers are exhausted.
12107  if (UseGPRForF64 && XLen == 32 && ValVT == MVT::f64) {
12108  assert(!ArgFlags.isSplit() && PendingLocs.empty() &&
12109  "Can't lower f64 if it is split");
12110  // Depending on available argument GPRS, f64 may be passed in a pair of
12111  // GPRs, split between a GPR and the stack, or passed completely on the
12112  // stack. LowerCall/LowerFormalArguments/LowerReturn must recognise these
12113  // cases.
12114  Register Reg = State.AllocateReg(ArgGPRs);
12115  LocVT = MVT::i32;
12116  if (!Reg) {
12117  unsigned StackOffset = State.AllocateStack(8, Align(8));
12118  State.addLoc(
12119  CCValAssign::getMem(ValNo, ValVT, StackOffset, LocVT, LocInfo));
12120  return false;
12121  }
12122  if (!State.AllocateReg(ArgGPRs))
12123  State.AllocateStack(4, Align(4));
12124  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
12125  return false;
12126  }
12127 
12128  // Fixed-length vectors are located in the corresponding scalable-vector
12129  // container types.
12130  if (ValVT.isFixedLengthVector())
12131  LocVT = TLI.getContainerForFixedLengthVector(LocVT);
12132 
12133  // Split arguments might be passed indirectly, so keep track of the pending
12134  // values. Split vectors are passed via a mix of registers and indirectly, so
12135  // treat them as we would any other argument.
12136  if (ValVT.isScalarInteger() && (ArgFlags.isSplit() || !PendingLocs.empty())) {
12137  LocVT = XLenVT;
12138  LocInfo = CCValAssign::Indirect;
12139  PendingLocs.push_back(
12140  CCValAssign::getPending(ValNo, ValVT, LocVT, LocInfo));
12141  PendingArgFlags.push_back(ArgFlags);
12142  if (!ArgFlags.isSplitEnd()) {
12143  return false;
12144  }
12145  }
12146 
12147  // If the split argument only had two elements, it should be passed directly
12148  // in registers or on the stack.
12149  if (ValVT.isScalarInteger() && ArgFlags.isSplitEnd() &&
12150  PendingLocs.size() <= 2) {
12151  assert(PendingLocs.size() == 2 && "Unexpected PendingLocs.size()");
12152  // Apply the normal calling convention rules to the first half of the
12153  // split argument.
12154  CCValAssign VA = PendingLocs[0];
12155  ISD::ArgFlagsTy AF = PendingArgFlags[0];
12156  PendingLocs.clear();
12157  PendingArgFlags.clear();
12158  return CC_RISCVAssign2XLen(XLen, State, VA, AF, ValNo, ValVT, LocVT,
12159  ArgFlags);
12160  }
12161 
12162  // Allocate to a register if possible, or else a stack slot.
12163  Register Reg;
12164  unsigned StoreSizeBytes = XLen / 8;
12165  Align StackAlign = Align(XLen / 8);
12166 
12167  if (ValVT == MVT::f16 && !UseGPRForF16_F32)
12168  Reg = State.AllocateReg(ArgFPR16s);
12169  else if (ValVT == MVT::f32 && !UseGPRForF16_F32)
12170  Reg = State.AllocateReg(ArgFPR32s);
12171  else if (ValVT == MVT::f64 && !UseGPRForF64)
12172  Reg = State.AllocateReg(ArgFPR64s);
12173  else if (ValVT.isVector()) {
12174  Reg = allocateRVVReg(ValVT, ValNo, FirstMaskArgument, State, TLI);
12175  if (!Reg) {
12176  // For return values, the vector must be passed fully via registers or
12177  // via the stack.
12178  // FIXME: The proposed vector ABI only mandates v8-v15 for return values,
12179  // but we're using all of them.
12180  if (IsRet)
12181  return true;
12182  // Try using a GPR to pass the address
12183  if ((Reg = State.AllocateReg(ArgGPRs))) {
12184  LocVT = XLenVT;
12185  LocInfo = CCValAssign::Indirect;
12186  } else if (ValVT.isScalableVector()) {
12187  LocVT = XLenVT;
12188  LocInfo = CCValAssign::Indirect;
12189  } else {
12190  // Pass fixed-length vectors on the stack.
12191  LocVT = ValVT;
12192  StoreSizeBytes = ValVT.getStoreSize();
12193  // Align vectors to their element sizes, being careful for vXi1
12194  // vectors.
12195  StackAlign = MaybeAlign(ValVT.getScalarSizeInBits() / 8).valueOrOne();
12196  }
12197  }
12198  } else {
12199  Reg = State.AllocateReg(ArgGPRs);
12200  }
12201 
12202  unsigned StackOffset =
12203  Reg ? 0 : State.AllocateStack(StoreSizeBytes, StackAlign);
12204 
12205  // If we reach this point and PendingLocs is non-empty, we must be at the
12206  // end of a split argument that must be passed indirectly.
12207  if (!PendingLocs.empty()) {
12208  assert(ArgFlags.isSplitEnd() && "Expected ArgFlags.isSplitEnd()");
12209  assert(PendingLocs.size() > 2 && "Unexpected PendingLocs.size()");
12210 
12211  for (auto &It : PendingLocs) {
12212  if (Reg)
12213  It.convertToReg(Reg);
12214  else
12215  It.convertToMem(StackOffset);
12216  State.addLoc(It);
12217  }
12218  PendingLocs.clear();
12219  PendingArgFlags.clear();
12220  return false;
12221  }
12222 
12223  assert((!UseGPRForF16_F32 || !UseGPRForF64 || LocVT == XLenVT ||
12224  (TLI.getSubtarget().hasVInstructions() && ValVT.isVector())) &&
12225  "Expected an XLenVT or vector types at this stage");
12226 
12227  if (Reg) {
12228  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
12229  return false;
12230  }
12231 
12232  // When a floating-point value is passed on the stack, no bit-conversion is
12233  // needed.
12234  if (ValVT.isFloatingPoint()) {
12235  LocVT = ValVT;
12236  LocInfo = CCValAssign::Full;
12237  }
12238  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getMem(ValNo, ValVT, StackOffset, LocVT, LocInfo));
12239  return false;
12240 }
12241 
12242 template <typename ArgTy>
12243 static std::optional<unsigned> preAssignMask(const ArgTy &Args) {
12244  for (const auto &ArgIdx : enumerate(Args)) {
12245  MVT ArgVT = ArgIdx.value().VT;
12246  if (ArgVT.isVector() && ArgVT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
12247  return ArgIdx.index();
12248  }
12249  return std::nullopt;
12250 }
12251 
12252 void RISCVTargetLowering::analyzeInputArgs(
12253  MachineFunction &MF, CCState &CCInfo,
12254  const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins, bool IsRet,
12255  RISCVCCAssignFn Fn) const {
12256  unsigned NumArgs = Ins.size();
12257  FunctionType *FType = MF.getFunction().getFunctionType();
12258 
12259  std::optional<unsigned> FirstMaskArgument;
12260  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructions())
12261  FirstMaskArgument = preAssignMask(Ins);
12262 
12263  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumArgs; ++i) {
12264  MVT ArgVT = Ins[i].VT;
12265  ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags = Ins[i].Flags;
12266 
12267  Type *ArgTy = nullptr;
12268  if (IsRet)
12269  ArgTy = FType->getReturnType();
12270  else if (Ins[i].isOrigArg())
12271  ArgTy = FType->getParamType(Ins[i].getOrigArgIndex());
12272 
12273  RISCVABI::ABI ABI = MF.getSubtarget<RISCVSubtarget>().getTargetABI();
12274  if (Fn(MF.getDataLayout(), ABI, i, ArgVT, ArgVT, CCValAssign::Full,
12275  ArgFlags, CCInfo, /*IsFixed=*/true, IsRet, ArgTy, *this,
12276  FirstMaskArgument)) {
12277  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "InputArg #" << i << " has unhandled type "
12278  << ArgVT << '\n');
12279  llvm_unreachable(nullptr);
12280  }
12281  }
12282 }
12283 
12284 void RISCVTargetLowering::analyzeOutputArgs(
12285  MachineFunction &MF, CCState &CCInfo,
12286  const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs, bool IsRet,
12287  CallLoweringInfo *CLI, RISCVCCAssignFn Fn) const {
12288  unsigned NumArgs = Outs.size();
12289 
12290  std::optional<unsigned> FirstMaskArgument;
12291  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructions())
12292  FirstMaskArgument = preAssignMask(Outs);
12293 
12294  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumArgs; i++) {
12295  MVT ArgVT = Outs[i].VT;
12296  ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags = Outs[i].Flags;
12297  Type *OrigTy = CLI ? CLI->getArgs()[Outs[i].OrigArgIndex].Ty : nullptr;
12298 
12299  RISCVABI::ABI ABI = MF.getSubtarget<RISCVSubtarget>().getTargetABI();
12300  if (Fn(MF.getDataLayout(), ABI, i, ArgVT, ArgVT, CCValAssign::Full,
12301  ArgFlags, CCInfo, Outs[i].IsFixed, IsRet, OrigTy, *this,
12302  FirstMaskArgument)) {
12303  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "OutputArg #" << i << " has unhandled type "
12304  << ArgVT << "\n");
12305  llvm_unreachable(nullptr);
12306  }
12307  }
12308 }
12309 
12310 // Convert Val to a ValVT. Should not be called for CCValAssign::Indirect
12311 // values.
12312 static SDValue convertLocVTToValVT(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Val,
12313  const CCValAssign &VA, const SDLoc &DL,
12314  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
12315  switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
12316  default:
12317  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected CCValAssign::LocInfo");
12318  case CCValAssign::Full:
12319  if (VA.getValVT().isFixedLengthVector() && VA.getLocVT().isScalableVector())
12320  Val = convertFromScalableVector(VA.getValVT(), Val, DAG, Subtarget);
12321  break;
12322  case CCValAssign::BCvt:
12323  if (VA.getLocVT().isInteger() && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f16)
12324  Val = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FMV_H_X, DL, MVT::f16, Val);
12325  else if (VA.getLocVT() == MVT::i64 && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f32)
12326  Val = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FMV_W_X_RV64, DL, MVT::f32, Val);
12327  else
12328  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VA.getValVT(), Val);
12329  break;
12330  }
12331  return Val;
12332 }
12333 
12334 // The caller is responsible for loading the full value if the argument is
12335 // passed with CCValAssign::Indirect.
12336 static SDValue unpackFromRegLoc(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Chain,
12337  const CCValAssign &VA, const SDLoc &DL,
12338  const ISD::InputArg &In,
12339  const RISCVTargetLowering &TLI) {
12340  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
12341  MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF.getRegInfo();
12342  EVT LocVT = VA.getLocVT();
12343  SDValue Val;
12344  const TargetRegisterClass *RC = TLI.getRegClassFor(LocVT.getSimpleVT());
12345  Register VReg = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
12346  RegInfo.addLiveIn(VA.getLocReg(), VReg);
12347  Val = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, VReg, LocVT);
12348 
12349  // If input is sign extended from 32 bits, note it for the SExtWRemoval pass.
12350  if (In.isOrigArg()) {
12351  Argument *OrigArg = MF.getFunction().getArg(In.getOrigArgIndex());
12352  if (OrigArg->getType()->isIntegerTy()) {
12353  unsigned BitWidth = OrigArg->getType()->getIntegerBitWidth();
12354  // An input zero extended from i31 can also be considered sign extended.
12355  if ((BitWidth <= 32 && In.Flags.isSExt()) ||
12356  (BitWidth < 32 && In.Flags.isZExt())) {
12357  RISCVMachineFunctionInfo *RVFI = MF.getInfo<RISCVMachineFunctionInfo>();
12358  RVFI->addSExt32Register(VReg);
12359  }
12360  }
12361  }
12362 
12363  if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::Indirect)
12364  return Val;
12365 
12366  return convertLocVTToValVT(DAG, Val, VA, DL, TLI.getSubtarget());
12367 }
12368 
12369 static SDValue convertValVTToLocVT(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Val,
12370  const CCValAssign &VA, const SDLoc &DL,
12371  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
12372  EVT LocVT = VA.getLocVT();
12373 
12374  switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
12375  default:
12376  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected CCValAssign::LocInfo");
12377  case CCValAssign::Full:
12378  if (VA.getValVT().isFixedLengthVector() && LocVT.isScalableVector())
12379  Val = convertToScalableVector(LocVT, Val, DAG, Subtarget);
12380  break;
12381  case CCValAssign::BCvt:
12382  if (VA.getLocVT().isInteger() && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f16)
12383  Val = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FMV_X_ANYEXTH, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Val);
12384  else if (VA.getLocVT() == MVT::i64 && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f32)
12385  Val = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FMV_X_ANYEXTW_RV64, DL, MVT::i64, Val);
12386  else
12387  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, LocVT, Val);
12388  break;
12389  }
12390  return Val;
12391 }
12392 
12393 // The caller is responsible for loading the full value if the argument is
12394 // passed with CCValAssign::Indirect.
12395 static SDValue unpackFromMemLoc(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Chain,
12396  const CCValAssign &VA, const SDLoc &DL) {
12397  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
12398  MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
12399  EVT LocVT = VA.getLocVT();
12400  EVT ValVT = VA.getValVT();
12401  EVT PtrVT = MVT::getIntegerVT(DAG.getDataLayout().getPointerSizeInBits(0));
12402  if (ValVT.isScalableVector()) {
12403  // When the value is a scalable vector, we save the pointer which points to
12404  // the scalable vector value in the stack. The ValVT will be the pointer
12405  // type, instead of the scalable vector type.
12406  ValVT = LocVT;
12407  }
12408  int FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(ValVT.getStoreSize(), VA.getLocMemOffset(),
12409  /*IsImmutable=*/true);
12410  SDValue FIN = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, PtrVT);
12411  SDValue Val;
12412 
12413  ISD::LoadExtType ExtType;
12414  switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
12415  default:
12416  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected CCValAssign::LocInfo");
12417  case CCValAssign::Full:
12418  case CCValAssign::Indirect:
12419  case CCValAssign::BCvt:
12420  ExtType = ISD::NON_EXTLOAD;
12421  break;
12422  }
12423  Val = DAG.getExtLoad(
12424  ExtType, DL, LocVT, Chain, FIN,
12425  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), FI), ValVT);
12426  return Val;
12427 }
12428 
12429 static SDValue unpackF64OnRV32DSoftABI(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Chain,
12430  const CCValAssign &VA, const SDLoc &DL) {
12431  assert(VA.getLocVT() == MVT::i32 && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f64 &&
12432  "Unexpected VA");
12433  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
12434  MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
12435  MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF.getRegInfo();
12436 
12437  if (VA.isMemLoc()) {
12438  // f64 is passed on the stack.
12439  int FI =
12440  MFI.CreateFixedObject(8, VA.getLocMemOffset(), /*IsImmutable=*/true);
12441  SDValue FIN = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, MVT::i32);
12442  return DAG.getLoad(MVT::f64, DL, Chain, FIN,
12443  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI));
12444  }
12445 
12446  assert(VA.isRegLoc() && "Expected register VA assignment");
12447 
12448  Register LoVReg = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&RISCV::GPRRegClass);
12449  RegInfo.addLiveIn(VA.getLocReg(), LoVReg);
12450  SDValue Lo = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, LoVReg, MVT::i32);
12451  SDValue Hi;
12452  if (VA.getLocReg() == RISCV::X17) {
12453  // Second half of f64 is passed on the stack.
12454  int FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(4, 0, /*IsImmutable=*/true);
12455  SDValue FIN = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, MVT::i32);
12456  Hi = DAG.getLoad(MVT::i32, DL, Chain, FIN,
12457  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI));
12458  } else {
12459  // Second half of f64 is passed in another GPR.
12460  Register HiVReg = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&RISCV::GPRRegClass);
12461  RegInfo.addLiveIn(VA.getLocReg() + 1, HiVReg);
12462  Hi = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, HiVReg, MVT::i32);
12463  }
12464  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::BuildPairF64, DL, MVT::f64, Lo, Hi);
12465 }
12466 
12467 // FastCC has less than 1% performance improvement for some particular
12468 // benchmark. But theoretically, it may has benenfit for some cases.
12469 static bool CC_RISCV_FastCC(const DataLayout &DL, RISCVABI::ABI ABI,
12470  unsigned ValNo, MVT ValVT, MVT LocVT,
12471  CCValAssign::LocInfo LocInfo,
12472  ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags, CCState &State,
12473  bool IsFixed, bool IsRet, Type *OrigTy,
12474  const RISCVTargetLowering &TLI,
12475  std::optional<unsigned> FirstMaskArgument) {
12476 
12477  // X5 and X6 might be used for save-restore libcall.
12478  static const MCPhysReg GPRList[] = {
12479  RISCV::X10, RISCV::X11, RISCV::X12, RISCV::X13, RISCV::X14,
12480  RISCV::X15, RISCV::X16, RISCV::X17, RISCV::X7, RISCV::X28,
12481  RISCV::X29, RISCV::X30, RISCV::X31};
12482 
12483  if (LocVT == MVT::i32 || LocVT == MVT::i64) {
12484  if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(GPRList)) {
12485  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
12486  return false;
12487  }
12488  }
12489 
12490  if (LocVT == MVT::f16) {
12491  static const MCPhysReg FPR16List[] = {
12492  RISCV::F10_H, RISCV::F11_H, RISCV::F12_H, RISCV::F13_H, RISCV::F14_H,
12493  RISCV::F15_H, RISCV::F16_H, RISCV::F17_H, RISCV::F0_H, RISCV::F1_H,
12494  RISCV::F2_H, RISCV::F3_H, RISCV::F4_H, RISCV::F5_H, RISCV::F6_H,
12495  RISCV::F7_H, RISCV::F28_H, RISCV::F29_H, RISCV::F30_H, RISCV::F31_H};
12496  if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(FPR16List)) {
12497  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
12498  return false;
12499  }
12500  }
12501 
12502  if (LocVT == MVT::f32) {
12503  static const MCPhysReg FPR32List[] = {
12504  RISCV::F10_F, RISCV::F11_F, RISCV::F12_F, RISCV::F13_F, RISCV::F14_F,
12505  RISCV::F15_F, RISCV::F16_F, RISCV::F17_F, RISCV::F0_F, RISCV::F1_F,
12506  RISCV::F2_F, RISCV::F3_F, RISCV::F4_F, RISCV::F5_F, RISCV::F6_F,
12507  RISCV::F7_F, RISCV::F28_F, RISCV::F29_F, RISCV::F30_F, RISCV::F31_F};
12508  if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(FPR32List)) {
12509  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
12510  return false;
12511  }
12512  }
12513 
12514  if (LocVT == MVT::f64) {
12515  static const MCPhysReg FPR64List[] = {
12516  RISCV::F10_D, RISCV::F11_D, RISCV::F12_D, RISCV::F13_D, RISCV::F14_D,
12517  RISCV::F15_D, RISCV::F16_D, RISCV::F17_D, RISCV::F0_D, RISCV::F1_D,
12518  RISCV::F2_D, RISCV::F3_D, RISCV::F4_D, RISCV::F5_D, RISCV::F6_D,
12519  RISCV::F7_D, RISCV::F28_D, RISCV::F29_D, RISCV::F30_D, RISCV::F31_D};
12520  if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(FPR64List)) {
12521  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
12522  return false;
12523  }
12524  }
12525 
12526  if (LocVT == MVT::i32 || LocVT == MVT::f32) {
12527  unsigned Offset4 = State.AllocateStack(4, Align(4));
12528  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getMem(ValNo, ValVT, Offset4, LocVT, LocInfo));
12529  return false;
12530  }
12531 
12532  if (LocVT == MVT::i64 || LocVT == MVT::f64) {
12533  unsigned Offset5 = State.AllocateStack(8, Align(8));
12534  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getMem(ValNo, ValVT, Offset5, LocVT, LocInfo));
12535  return false;
12536  }
12537 
12538  if (LocVT.isVector()) {
12539  if (unsigned Reg =
12540  allocateRVVReg(ValVT, ValNo, FirstMaskArgument, State, TLI)) {
12541  // Fixed-length vectors are located in the corresponding scalable-vector
12542  // container types.
12543  if (ValVT.isFixedLengthVector())
12544  LocVT = TLI.getContainerForFixedLengthVector(LocVT);
12545  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
12546  } else {
12547  // Try and pass the address via a "fast" GPR.
12548  if (unsigned GPRReg = State.AllocateReg(GPRList)) {
12549  LocInfo = CCValAssign::Indirect;
12550  LocVT = TLI.getSubtarget().getXLenVT();
12551  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, GPRReg, LocVT, LocInfo));
12552  } else if (ValVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
12553  auto StackAlign =
12554  MaybeAlign(ValVT.getScalarSizeInBits() / 8).valueOrOne();
12555  unsigned StackOffset =
12556  State.AllocateStack(ValVT.getStoreSize(), StackAlign);
12557  State.addLoc(
12558  CCValAssign::getMem(ValNo, ValVT, StackOffset, LocVT, LocInfo));
12559  } else {
12560  // Can't pass scalable vectors on the stack.
12561  return true;
12562  }
12563  }
12564 
12565  return false;
12566  }
12567 
12568  return true; // CC didn't match.
12569 }
12570 
12571 static bool CC_RISCV_GHC(unsigned ValNo, MVT ValVT, MVT LocVT,
12572  CCValAssign::LocInfo LocInfo,
12573  ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags, CCState &State) {
12574 
12575  if (ArgFlags.isNest()) {
12576  report_fatal_error(
12577  "Attribute 'nest' is not supported in GHC calling convention");
12578  }
12579 
12580  if (LocVT == MVT::i32 || LocVT == MVT::i64) {
12581  // Pass in STG registers: Base, Sp, Hp, R1, R2, R3, R4, R5, R6, R7, SpLim
12582  // s1 s2 s3 s4 s5 s6 s7 s8 s9 s10 s11
12583  static const MCPhysReg GPRList[] = {
12584  RISCV::X9, RISCV::X18, RISCV::X19, RISCV::X20, RISCV::X21, RISCV::X22,
12585  RISCV::X23, RISCV::X24, RISCV::X25, RISCV::X26, RISCV::X27};
12586  if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(GPRList)) {
12587  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
12588  return false;
12589  }
12590  }
12591 
12592  if (LocVT == MVT::f32) {
12593  // Pass in STG registers: F1, ..., F6
12594  // fs0 ... fs5
12595  static const MCPhysReg FPR32List[] = {RISCV::F8_F, RISCV::F9_F,
12596  RISCV::F18_F, RISCV::F19_F,
12597  RISCV::F20_F, RISCV::F21_F};
12598  if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(FPR32List)) {
12599  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
12600  return false;
12601  }
12602  }
12603 
12604  if (LocVT == MVT::f64) {
12605  // Pass in STG registers: D1, ..., D6
12606  // fs6 ... fs11
12607  static const MCPhysReg FPR64List[] = {RISCV::F22_D, RISCV::F23_D,
12608  RISCV::F24_D, RISCV::F25_D,
12609  RISCV::F26_D, RISCV::F27_D};
12610  if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(FPR64List)) {
12611  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
12612  return false;
12613  }
12614  }
12615 
12616  report_fatal_error("No registers left in GHC calling convention");
12617  return true;
12618 }
12619 
12620 // Transform physical registers into virtual registers.
12621 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::LowerFormalArguments(
12622  SDValue Chain, CallingConv::ID CallConv, bool IsVarArg,
12623  const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins, const SDLoc &DL,
12624  SelectionDAG &DAG, SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals) const {
12625 
12626  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
12627 
12628  switch (CallConv) {
12629  default:
12630  report_fatal_error("Unsupported calling convention");
12631  case CallingConv::C:
12632  case CallingConv::Fast:
12633  break;
12634  case CallingConv::GHC:
12635  if (!MF.getSubtarget().getFeatureBits()[RISCV::FeatureStdExtF] ||
12636  !MF.getSubtarget().getFeatureBits()[RISCV::FeatureStdExtD])
12637  report_fatal_error(
12638  "GHC calling convention requires the F and D instruction set extensions");
12639  }
12640 
12641  const Function &Func = MF.getFunction();
12642  if (Func.hasFnAttribute("interrupt")) {
12643  if (!Func.arg_empty())
12644  report_fatal_error(
12645  "Functions with the interrupt attribute cannot have arguments!");
12646 
12647  StringRef Kind =
12648  MF.getFunction().getFnAttribute("interrupt").getValueAsString();
12649 
12650  if (!(Kind == "user" || Kind == "supervisor" || Kind == "machine"))
12651  report_fatal_error(
12652  "Function interrupt attribute argument not supported!");
12653  }
12654 
12655  EVT PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
12656  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
12657  unsigned XLenInBytes = Subtarget.getXLen() / 8;
12658  // Used with vargs to acumulate store chains.
12659  std::vector<SDValue> OutChains;
12660 
12661  // Assign locations to all of the incoming arguments.
12662  SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> ArgLocs;
12663  CCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, MF, ArgLocs, *DAG.getContext());
12664 
12665  if (CallConv == CallingConv::GHC)
12666  CCInfo.AnalyzeFormalArguments(Ins, CC_RISCV_GHC);
12667  else
12668  analyzeInputArgs(MF, CCInfo, Ins, /*IsRet=*/false,
12669  CallConv == CallingConv::Fast ? CC_RISCV_FastCC
12670  : CC_RISCV);
12671 
12672  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
12673  CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
12674  SDValue ArgValue;
12675  // Passing f64 on RV32D with a soft float ABI must be handled as a special
12676  // case.
12677  if (VA.getLocVT() == MVT::i32 && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f64)
12678  ArgValue = unpackF64OnRV32DSoftABI(DAG, Chain, VA, DL);
12679  else if (VA.isRegLoc())
12680  ArgValue = unpackFromRegLoc(DAG, Chain, VA, DL, Ins[i], *this);
12681  else
12682  ArgValue = unpackFromMemLoc(DAG, Chain, VA, DL);
12683 
12684  if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::Indirect) {
12685  // If the original argument was split and passed by reference (e.g. i128
12686  // on RV32), we need to load all parts of it here (using the same
12687  // address). Vectors may be partly split to registers and partly to the
12688  // stack, in which case the base address is partly offset and subsequent
12689  // stores are relative to that.
12690  InVals.push_back(DAG.getLoad(VA.getValVT(), DL, Chain, ArgValue,
12691  MachinePointerInfo()));
12692  unsigned ArgIndex = Ins[i].OrigArgIndex;
12693  unsigned ArgPartOffset = Ins[i].PartOffset;
12694  assert(VA.getValVT().isVector() || ArgPartOffset == 0);
12695  while (i + 1 != e && Ins[i + 1].OrigArgIndex == ArgIndex) {
12696  CCValAssign &PartVA = ArgLocs[i + 1];
12697  unsigned PartOffset = Ins[i + 1].PartOffset - ArgPartOffset;
12698  SDValue Offset = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(PartOffset, DL);
12699  if (PartVA.getValVT().isScalableVector())
12700  Offset = DAG.getNode(ISD::VSCALE, DL, XLenVT, Offset);
12701  SDValue Address = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, ArgValue, Offset);
12702  InVals.push_back(DAG.getLoad(PartVA.getValVT(), DL, Chain, Address,
12703  MachinePointerInfo()));
12704  ++i;
12705  }
12706  continue;
12707  }
12708  InVals.push_back(ArgValue);
12709  }
12710 
12711  if (any_of(ArgLocs,
12712  [](CCValAssign &VA) { return VA.getLocVT().isScalableVector(); }))
12713  MF.getInfo<RISCVMachineFunctionInfo>()->setIsVectorCall();
12714 
12715  if (IsVarArg) {
12716  ArrayRef<MCPhysReg> ArgRegs = ArrayRef(ArgGPRs);
12717  unsigned Idx = CCInfo.getFirstUnallocated(ArgRegs);
12718  const TargetRegisterClass *RC = &RISCV::GPRRegClass;
12719  MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
12720  MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF.getRegInfo();
12721  RISCVMachineFunctionInfo *RVFI = MF.getInfo<RISCVMachineFunctionInfo>();
12722 
12723  // Offset of the first variable argument from stack pointer, and size of
12724  // the vararg save area. For now, the varargs save area is either zero or
12725  // large enough to hold a0-a7.
12726  int VaArgOffset, VarArgsSaveSize;
12727 
12728  // If all registers are allocated, then all varargs must be passed on the
12729  // stack and we don't need to save any argregs.
12730  if (ArgRegs.size() == Idx) {
12731  VaArgOffset = CCInfo.getNextStackOffset();
12732  VarArgsSaveSize = 0;
12733  } else {
12734  VarArgsSaveSize = XLenInBytes * (ArgRegs.size() - Idx);
12735  VaArgOffset = -VarArgsSaveSize;
12736  }
12737 
12738  // Record the frame index of the first variable argument
12739  // which is a value necessary to VASTART.
12740  int FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(XLenInBytes, VaArgOffset, true);
12741  RVFI->setVarArgsFrameIndex(FI);
12742 
12743  // If saving an odd number of registers then create an extra stack slot to
12744  // ensure that the frame pointer is 2*XLEN-aligned, which in turn ensures
12745  // offsets to even-numbered registered remain 2*XLEN-aligned.
12746  if (Idx % 2) {
12747  MFI.CreateFixedObject(XLenInBytes, VaArgOffset - (int)XLenInBytes, true);
12748  VarArgsSaveSize += XLenInBytes;
12749  }
12750 
12751  // Copy the integer registers that may have been used for passing varargs
12752  // to the vararg save area.
12753  for (unsigned I = Idx; I < ArgRegs.size();
12754  ++I, VaArgOffset += XLenInBytes) {
12755  const Register Reg = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
12756  RegInfo.addLiveIn(ArgRegs[I], Reg);
12757  SDValue ArgValue = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, Reg, XLenVT);
12758  FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(XLenInBytes, VaArgOffset, true);
12759  SDValue PtrOff = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
12760  SDValue Store = DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, ArgValue, PtrOff,
12761  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI));
12762  cast<StoreSDNode>(Store.getNode())
12763  ->getMemOperand()
12764  ->setValue((Value *)nullptr);
12765  OutChains.push_back(Store);
12766  }
12767  RVFI->setVarArgsSaveSize(VarArgsSaveSize);
12768  }
12769 
12770  // All stores are grouped in one node to allow the matching between
12771  // the size of Ins and InVals. This only happens for vararg functions.
12772  if (!OutChains.empty()) {
12773  OutChains.push_back(Chain);
12774  Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, OutChains);
12775  }
12776 
12777  return Chain;
12778 }
12779 
12780 /// isEligibleForTailCallOptimization - Check whether the call is eligible
12781 /// for tail call optimization.
12782 /// Note: This is modelled after ARM's IsEligibleForTailCallOptimization.
12783 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isEligibleForTailCallOptimization(
12784  CCState &CCInfo, CallLoweringInfo &CLI, MachineFunction &MF,
12785  const SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> &ArgLocs) const {
12786 
12787  auto CalleeCC = CLI.CallConv;
12788  auto &Outs = CLI.Outs;
12789  auto &Caller = MF.getFunction();
12790  auto CallerCC = Caller.getCallingConv();
12791 
12792  // Exception-handling functions need a special set of instructions to
12793  // indicate a return to the hardware. Tail-calling another function would
12794  // probably break this.
12795  // TODO: The "interrupt" attribute isn't currently defined by RISC-V. This
12796  // should be expanded as new function attributes are introduced.
12797  if (Caller.hasFnAttribute("interrupt"))
12798  return false;
12799 
12800  // Do not tail call opt if the stack is used to pass parameters.
12801  if (CCInfo.getNextStackOffset() != 0)
12802  return false;
12803 
12804  // Do not tail call opt if any parameters need to be passed indirectly.
12805  // Since long doubles (fp128) and i128 are larger than 2*XLEN, they are
12806  // passed indirectly. So the address of the value will be passed in a
12807  // register, or if not available, then the address is put on the stack. In
12808  // order to pass indirectly, space on the stack often needs to be allocated
12809  // in order to store the value. In this case the CCInfo.getNextStackOffset()
12810  // != 0 check is not enough and we need to check if any CCValAssign ArgsLocs
12811  // are passed CCValAssign::Indirect.
12812  for (auto &VA : ArgLocs)
12813  if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::Indirect)
12814  return false;
12815 
12816  // Do not tail call opt if either caller or callee uses struct return
12817  // semantics.
12818  auto IsCallerStructRet = Caller.hasStructRetAttr();
12819  auto IsCalleeStructRet = Outs.empty() ? false : Outs[0].Flags.isSRet();
12820  if (IsCallerStructRet || IsCalleeStructRet)
12821  return false;
12822 
12823  // The callee has to preserve all registers the caller needs to preserve.
12824  const RISCVRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
12825  const uint32_t *CallerPreserved = TRI->getCallPreservedMask(MF, CallerCC);
12826  if (CalleeCC != CallerCC) {
12827  const uint32_t *CalleePreserved = TRI->getCallPreservedMask(MF, CalleeCC);
12828  if (!TRI->regmaskSubsetEqual(CallerPreserved, CalleePreserved))
12829  return false;
12830  }
12831 
12832  // Byval parameters hand the function a pointer directly into the stack area
12833  // we want to reuse during a tail call. Working around this *is* possible
12834  // but less efficient and uglier in LowerCall.
12835  for (auto &Arg : Outs)
12836  if (Arg.Flags.isByVal())
12837  return false;
12838 
12839  return true;
12840 }
12841 
12842 static Align getPrefTypeAlign(EVT VT, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
12843  return DAG.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlign(
12844  VT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()));
12845 }
12846 
12847 // Lower a call to a callseq_start + CALL + callseq_end chain, and add input
12848 // and output parameter nodes.
12849 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::LowerCall(CallLoweringInfo &CLI,
12850  SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals) const {
12851  SelectionDAG &DAG = CLI.DAG;
12852  SDLoc &DL = CLI.DL;
12853  SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs = CLI.Outs;
12854  SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals = CLI.OutVals;
12855  SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins = CLI.Ins;
12856  SDValue Chain = CLI.Chain;
12857  SDValue Callee = CLI.Callee;
12858  bool &IsTailCall = CLI.IsTailCall;
12859  CallingConv::ID CallConv = CLI.CallConv;
12860  bool IsVarArg = CLI.IsVarArg;
12861  EVT PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
12862  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
12863 
12864  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
12865 
12866  // Analyze the operands of the call, assigning locations to each operand.
12867  SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> ArgLocs;
12868  CCState ArgCCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, MF, ArgLocs, *DAG.getContext());
12869 
12870  if (CallConv == CallingConv::GHC)
12871  ArgCCInfo.AnalyzeCallOperands(Outs, CC_RISCV_GHC);
12872  else
12873  analyzeOutputArgs(MF, ArgCCInfo, Outs, /*IsRet=*/false, &CLI,
12874  CallConv == CallingConv::Fast ? CC_RISCV_FastCC
12875  : CC_RISCV);
12876 
12877  // Check if it's really possible to do a tail call.
12878  if (IsTailCall)
12879  IsTailCall = isEligibleForTailCallOptimization(ArgCCInfo, CLI, MF, ArgLocs);
12880 
12881  if (IsTailCall)
12882  ++NumTailCalls;
12883  else if (CLI.CB && CLI.CB->isMustTailCall())
12884  report_fatal_error("failed to perform tail call elimination on a call "
12885  "site marked musttail");
12886 
12887  // Get a count of how many bytes are to be pushed on the stack.
12888  unsigned NumBytes = ArgCCInfo.getNextStackOffset();
12889 
12890  // Create local copies for byval args
12891  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> ByValArgs;
12892  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Outs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
12893  ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags = Outs[i].Flags;
12894  if (!Flags.isByVal())
12895  continue;
12896 
12897  SDValue Arg = OutVals[i];
12898  unsigned Size = Flags.getByValSize();
12899  Align Alignment = Flags.getNonZeroByValAlign();
12900 
12901  int FI =
12902  MF.getFrameInfo().CreateStackObject(Size, Alignment, /*isSS=*/false);
12903  SDValue FIPtr = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
12904  SDValue SizeNode = DAG.getConstant(Size, DL, XLenVT);
12905 
12906  Chain = DAG.getMemcpy(Chain, DL, FIPtr, Arg, SizeNode, Alignment,
12907  /*IsVolatile=*/false,
12908  /*AlwaysInline=*/false, IsTailCall,
12909  MachinePointerInfo(), MachinePointerInfo());
12910  ByValArgs.push_back(FIPtr);
12911  }
12912 
12913  if (!IsTailCall)
12914  Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_START(Chain, NumBytes, 0, CLI.DL);
12915 
12916  // Copy argument values to their designated locations.
12917  SmallVector<std::pair<Register, SDValue>, 8> RegsToPass;
12918  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> MemOpChains;
12919  SDValue StackPtr;
12920  for (unsigned i = 0, j = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
12921  CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
12922  SDValue ArgValue = OutVals[i];
12923  ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags = Outs[i].Flags;
12924 
12925  // Handle passing f64 on RV32D with a soft float ABI as a special case.
12926  bool IsF64OnRV32DSoftABI =
12927  VA.getLocVT() == MVT::i32 && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f64;
12928  if (IsF64OnRV32DSoftABI && VA.isRegLoc()) {
12929  SDValue SplitF64 = DAG.getNode(
12930  RISCVISD::SplitF64, DL, DAG.getVTList(MVT::i32, MVT::i32), ArgValue);
12931  SDValue Lo = SplitF64.getValue(0);
12932  SDValue Hi = SplitF64.getValue(1);
12933 
12934  Register RegLo = VA.getLocReg();
12935  RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(RegLo, Lo));
12936 
12937  if (RegLo == RISCV::X17) {
12938  // Second half of f64 is passed on the stack.
12939  // Work out the address of the stack slot.
12940  if (!StackPtr.getNode())
12941  StackPtr = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, RISCV::X2, PtrVT);
12942  // Emit the store.
12943  MemOpChains.push_back(
12944  DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, Hi, StackPtr, MachinePointerInfo()));
12945  } else {
12946  // Second half of f64 is passed in another GPR.
12947  assert(RegLo < RISCV::X31 && "Invalid register pair");
12948  Register RegHigh = RegLo + 1;
12949  RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(RegHigh, Hi));
12950  }
12951  continue;
12952  }
12953 
12954  // IsF64OnRV32DSoftABI && VA.isMemLoc() is handled below in the same way
12955  // as any other MemLoc.
12956 
12957  // Promote the value if needed.
12958  // For now, only handle fully promoted and indirect arguments.
12959  if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::Indirect) {
12960  // Store the argument in a stack slot and pass its address.
12961  Align StackAlign =
12962  std::max(getPrefTypeAlign(Outs[i].ArgVT, DAG),
12963  getPrefTypeAlign(ArgValue.getValueType(), DAG));
12964  TypeSize StoredSize = ArgValue.getValueType().getStoreSize();
12965  // If the original argument was split (e.g. i128), we need
12966  // to store the required parts of it here (and pass just one address).
12967  // Vectors may be partly split to registers and partly to the stack, in
12968  // which case the base address is partly offset and subsequent stores are
12969  // relative to that.
12970  unsigned ArgIndex = Outs[i].OrigArgIndex;
12971  unsigned ArgPartOffset = Outs[i].PartOffset;
12972  assert(VA.getValVT().isVector() || ArgPartOffset == 0);
12973  // Calculate the total size to store. We don't have access to what we're
12974  // actually storing other than performing the loop and collecting the
12975  // info.
12976  SmallVector<std::pair<SDValue, SDValue>> Parts;
12977  while (i + 1 != e && Outs[i + 1].OrigArgIndex == ArgIndex) {
12978  SDValue PartValue = OutVals[i + 1];
12979  unsigned PartOffset = Outs[i + 1].PartOffset - ArgPartOffset;
12980  SDValue Offset = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(PartOffset, DL);
12981  EVT PartVT = PartValue.getValueType();
12982  if (PartVT.isScalableVector())
12983  Offset = DAG.getNode(ISD::VSCALE, DL, XLenVT, Offset);
12984  StoredSize += PartVT.getStoreSize();
12985  StackAlign = std::max(StackAlign, getPrefTypeAlign(PartVT, DAG));
12986  Parts.push_back(std::make_pair(PartValue, Offset));
12987  ++i;
12988  }
12989  SDValue SpillSlot = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(StoredSize, StackAlign);
12990  int FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(SpillSlot)->getIndex();
12991  MemOpChains.push_back(
12992  DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, ArgValue, SpillSlot,
12993  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI)));
12994  for (const auto &Part : Parts) {
12995  SDValue PartValue = Part.first;
12996  SDValue PartOffset = Part.second;
12997  SDValue Address =
12998  DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, SpillSlot, PartOffset);
12999  MemOpChains.push_back(
13000  DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, PartValue, Address,
13001  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI)));
13002  }
13003  ArgValue = SpillSlot;
13004  } else {
13005  ArgValue = convertValVTToLocVT(DAG, ArgValue, VA, DL, Subtarget);
13006  }
13007 
13008  // Use local copy if it is a byval arg.
13009  if (Flags.isByVal())
13010  ArgValue = ByValArgs[j++];
13011 
13012  if (VA.isRegLoc()) {
13013  // Queue up the argument copies and emit them at the end.
13014  RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(VA.getLocReg(), ArgValue));
13015  } else {
13016  assert(VA.isMemLoc() && "Argument not register or memory");
13017  assert(!IsTailCall && "Tail call not allowed if stack is used "
13018  "for passing parameters");
13019 
13020  // Work out the address of the stack slot.
13021  if (!StackPtr.getNode())
13022  StackPtr = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, RISCV::X2, PtrVT);
13023  SDValue Address =
13024  DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, StackPtr,
13025  DAG.getIntPtrConstant(VA.getLocMemOffset(), DL));
13026 
13027  // Emit the store.
13028  MemOpChains.push_back(
13029  DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, ArgValue, Address, MachinePointerInfo()));
13030  }
13031  }
13032 
13033  // Join the stores, which are independent of one another.
13034  if (!MemOpChains.empty())
13035  Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, MemOpChains);
13036 
13037  SDValue Glue;
13038 
13039  // Build a sequence of copy-to-reg nodes, chained and glued together.
13040  for (auto &Reg : RegsToPass) {
13041  Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, Reg.first, Reg.second, Glue);
13042  Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
13043  }
13044 
13045  // Validate that none of the argument registers have been marked as
13046  // reserved, if so report an error. Do the same for the return address if this
13047  // is not a tailcall.
13048  validateCCReservedRegs(RegsToPass, MF);
13049  if (!IsTailCall &&
13050  MF.getSubtarget<RISCVSubtarget>().isRegisterReservedByUser(RISCV::X1))
13051  MF.getFunction().getContext().diagnose(DiagnosticInfoUnsupported{
13052  MF.getFunction(),
13053  "Return address register required, but has been reserved."});
13054 
13055  // If the callee is a GlobalAddress/ExternalSymbol node, turn it into a
13056  // TargetGlobalAddress/TargetExternalSymbol node so that legalize won't
13057  // split it and then direct call can be matched by PseudoCALL.
13058  if (GlobalAddressSDNode *S = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Callee)) {
13059  const GlobalValue *GV = S->getGlobal();
13060 
13061  unsigned OpFlags = RISCVII::MO_CALL;
13062  if (!getTargetMachine().shouldAssumeDSOLocal(*GV->getParent(), GV))
13063  OpFlags = RISCVII::MO_PLT;
13064 
13065  Callee = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, PtrVT, 0, OpFlags);
13066  } else if (ExternalSymbolSDNode *S = dyn_cast<ExternalSymbolSDNode>(Callee)) {
13067  unsigned OpFlags = RISCVII::MO_CALL;
13068 
13069  if (!getTargetMachine().shouldAssumeDSOLocal(*MF.getFunction().getParent(),
13070  nullptr))
13071  OpFlags = RISCVII::MO_PLT;
13072 
13073  Callee = DAG.getTargetExternalSymbol(S->getSymbol(), PtrVT, OpFlags);
13074  }
13075 
13076  // The first call operand is the chain and the second is the target address.
13077  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
13078  Ops.push_back(Chain);
13079  Ops.push_back(Callee);
13080 
13081  // Add argument registers to the end of the list so that they are
13082  // known live into the call.
13083  for (auto &Reg : RegsToPass)
13084  Ops.push_back(DAG.getRegister(Reg.first, Reg.second.getValueType()));
13085 
13086  if (!IsTailCall) {
13087  // Add a register mask operand representing the call-preserved registers.
13088  const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
13089  const uint32_t *Mask = TRI->getCallPreservedMask(MF, CallConv);
13090  assert(Mask && "Missing call preserved mask for calling convention");
13091  Ops.push_back(DAG.getRegisterMask(Mask));
13092  }
13093 
13094  // Glue the call to the argument copies, if any.
13095  if (Glue.getNode())
13096  Ops.push_back(Glue);
13097 
13098  // Emit the call.
13099  SDVTList NodeTys = DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other, MVT::Glue);
13100 
13101  if (IsTailCall) {
13102  MF.getFrameInfo().setHasTailCall();
13103  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::TAIL, DL, NodeTys, Ops);
13104  }
13105 
13106  Chain = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::CALL, DL, NodeTys, Ops);
13107  DAG.addNoMergeSiteInfo(Chain.getNode(), CLI.NoMerge);
13108  Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
13109 
13110  // Mark the end of the call, which is glued to the call itself.
13111  Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_END(Chain, NumBytes, 0, Glue, DL);
13112  Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
13113 
13114  // Assign locations to each value returned by this call.
13115  SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> RVLocs;
13116  CCState RetCCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, MF, RVLocs, *DAG.getContext());
13117  analyzeInputArgs(MF, RetCCInfo, Ins, /*IsRet=*/true, CC_RISCV);
13118 
13119  // Copy all of the result registers out of their specified physreg.
13120  for (auto &VA : RVLocs) {
13121  // Copy the value out
13122  SDValue RetValue =
13123  DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, VA.getLocReg(), VA.getLocVT(), Glue);
13124  // Glue the RetValue to the end of the call sequence
13125  Chain = RetValue.getValue(1);
13126  Glue = RetValue.getValue(2);
13127 
13128  if (VA.getLocVT() == MVT::i32 && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f64) {
13129  assert(VA.getLocReg() == ArgGPRs[0] && "Unexpected reg assignment");
13130  SDValue RetValue2 =
13131  DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, ArgGPRs[1], MVT::i32, Glue);
13132  Chain = RetValue2.getValue(1);
13133  Glue = RetValue2.getValue(2);
13134  RetValue = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::BuildPairF64, DL, MVT::f64, RetValue,
13135  RetValue2);
13136  }
13137 
13138  RetValue = convertLocVTToValVT(DAG, RetValue, VA, DL, Subtarget);
13139 
13140  InVals.push_back(RetValue);
13141  }
13142 
13143  return Chain;
13144 }
13145 
13146 bool RISCVTargetLowering::CanLowerReturn(
13147  CallingConv::ID CallConv, MachineFunction &MF, bool IsVarArg,
13148  const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs, LLVMContext &Context) const {
13149  SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> RVLocs;
13150  CCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, MF, RVLocs, Context);
13151 
13152  std::optional<unsigned> FirstMaskArgument;
13153  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructions())
13154  FirstMaskArgument = preAssignMask(Outs);
13155 
13156  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Outs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
13157  MVT VT = Outs[i].VT;
13158  ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags = Outs[i].Flags;
13159  RISCVABI::ABI ABI = MF.getSubtarget<RISCVSubtarget>().getTargetABI();
13160  if (CC_RISCV(MF.getDataLayout(), ABI, i, VT, VT, CCValAssign::Full,
13161  ArgFlags, CCInfo, /*IsFixed=*/true, /*IsRet=*/true, nullptr,
13162  *this, FirstMaskArgument))
13163  return false;
13164  }
13165  return true;
13166 }
13167 
13168 SDValue
13169 RISCVTargetLowering::LowerReturn(SDValue Chain, CallingConv::ID CallConv,
13170  bool IsVarArg,
13171  const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs,
13172  const SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals,
13173  const SDLoc &DL, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
13174  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
13175  const RISCVSubtarget &STI = MF.getSubtarget<RISCVSubtarget>();
13176 
13177  // Stores the assignment of the return value to a location.
13178  SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> RVLocs;
13179 
13180  // Info about the registers and stack slot.
13181  CCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), RVLocs,
13182  *DAG.getContext());
13183 
13184  analyzeOutputArgs(DAG.getMachineFunction(), CCInfo, Outs, /*IsRet=*/true,
13185  nullptr, CC_RISCV);
13186 
13187  if (CallConv == CallingConv::GHC && !RVLocs.empty())
13188  report_fatal_error("GHC functions return void only");
13189 
13190  SDValue Glue;
13191  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> RetOps(1, Chain);
13192 
13193  // Copy the result values into the output registers.
13194  for (unsigned i = 0, e = RVLocs.size(); i < e; ++i) {
13195  SDValue Val = OutVals[i];
13196  CCValAssign &VA = RVLocs[i];
13197  assert(VA.isRegLoc() && "Can only return in registers!");
13198 
13199  if (VA.getLocVT() == MVT::i32 && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f64) {
13200  // Handle returning f64 on RV32D with a soft float ABI.
13201  assert(VA.isRegLoc() && "Expected return via registers");
13202  SDValue SplitF64 = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SplitF64, DL,
13203  DAG.getVTList(MVT::i32, MVT::i32), Val);
13204  SDValue Lo = SplitF64.getValue(0);
13205  SDValue Hi = SplitF64.getValue(1);
13206  Register RegLo = VA.getLocReg();
13207  assert(RegLo < RISCV::X31 && "Invalid register pair");
13208  Register RegHi = RegLo + 1;
13209 
13210  if (STI.isRegisterReservedByUser(RegLo) ||
13211  STI.isRegisterReservedByUser(RegHi))
13212  MF.getFunction().getContext().diagnose(DiagnosticInfoUnsupported{
13213  MF.getFunction(),
13214  "Return value register required, but has been reserved."});
13215 
13216  Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, RegLo, Lo, Glue);
13217  Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
13218  RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(RegLo, MVT::i32));
13219  Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, RegHi, Hi, Glue);
13220  Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
13221  RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(RegHi, MVT::i32));
13222  } else {
13223  // Handle a 'normal' return.
13224  Val = convertValVTToLocVT(DAG, Val, VA, DL, Subtarget);
13225  Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, VA.getLocReg(), Val, Glue);
13226 
13227  if (STI.isRegisterReservedByUser(VA.getLocReg()))
13228  MF.getFunction().getContext().diagnose(DiagnosticInfoUnsupported{
13229  MF.getFunction(),
13230  "Return value register required, but has been reserved."});
13231 
13232  // Guarantee that all emitted copies are stuck together.
13233  Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
13234  RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(VA.getLocReg(), VA.getLocVT()));
13235  }
13236  }
13237 
13238  RetOps[0] = Chain; // Update chain.
13239 
13240  // Add the glue node if we have it.
13241  if (Glue.getNode()) {
13242  RetOps.push_back(Glue);
13243  }
13244 
13245  if (any_of(RVLocs,
13246  [](CCValAssign &VA) { return VA.getLocVT().isScalableVector(); }))
13247  MF.getInfo<RISCVMachineFunctionInfo>()->setIsVectorCall();
13248 
13249  unsigned RetOpc = RISCVISD::RET_FLAG;
13250  // Interrupt service routines use different return instructions.
13251  const Function &Func = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction();
13252  if (Func.hasFnAttribute("interrupt")) {
13253  if (!Func.getReturnType()->isVoidTy())
13254  report_fatal_error(
13255  "Functions with the interrupt attribute must have void return type!");
13256 
13257  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
13258  StringRef Kind =
13259  MF.getFunction().getFnAttribute("interrupt").getValueAsString();
13260 
13261  if (Kind == "user")
13262  RetOpc = RISCVISD::URET_FLAG;
13263  else if (Kind == "supervisor")
13264  RetOpc = RISCVISD::SRET_FLAG;
13265  else
13266  RetOpc = RISCVISD::MRET_FLAG;
13267  }
13268 
13269  return DAG.getNode(RetOpc, DL, MVT::Other, RetOps);
13270 }
13271 
13272 void RISCVTargetLowering::validateCCReservedRegs(
13273  const SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<llvm::Register, llvm::SDValue>> &Regs,
13274  MachineFunction &MF) const {
13275  const Function &F = MF.getFunction();
13276  const RISCVSubtarget &STI = MF.getSubtarget<RISCVSubtarget>();
13277 
13278  if (llvm::any_of(Regs, [&STI](auto Reg) {
13279  return STI.isRegisterReservedByUser(Reg.first);
13280  }))
13281  F.getContext().diagnose(DiagnosticInfoUnsupported{
13282  F, "Argument register required, but has been reserved."});
13283 }
13284 
13285 // Check if the result of the node is only used as a return value, as
13286 // otherwise we can't perform a tail-call.
13287 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isUsedByReturnOnly(SDNode *N, SDValue &Chain) const {
13288  if (N->getNumValues() != 1)
13289  return false;
13290  if (!N->hasNUsesOfValue(1, 0))
13291  return false;
13292 
13293  SDNode *Copy = *N->use_begin();
13294 
13295  if (Copy->getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST) {
13296  return isUsedByReturnOnly(Copy, Chain);
13297  }
13298 
13299  // TODO: Handle additional opcodes in order to support tail-calling libcalls
13300  // with soft float ABIs.
13301  if (Copy->getOpcode() != ISD::CopyToReg) {
13302  return false;
13303  }
13304 
13305  // If the ISD::CopyToReg has a glue operand, we conservatively assume it
13306  // isn't safe to perform a tail call.
13307  if (Copy->getOperand(Copy->getNumOperands() - 1).getValueType() == MVT::Glue)
13308  return false;
13309 
13310  // The copy must be used by a RISCVISD::RET_FLAG, and nothing else.
13311  bool HasRet = false;
13312  for (SDNode *Node : Copy->uses()) {
13313  if (Node->getOpcode() != RISCVISD::RET_FLAG)
13314  return false;
13315  HasRet = true;
13316  }
13317  if (!HasRet)
13318  return false;
13319 
13320  Chain = Copy->getOperand(0);
13321  return true;
13322 }
13323 
13324 bool RISCVTargetLowering::mayBeEmittedAsTailCall(const CallInst *CI) const {
13325  return CI->isTailCall();
13326 }

13328 const char *RISCVTargetLowering::getTargetNodeName(unsigned Opcode) const {
13329 #define NODE_NAME_CASE(NODE) \
13330  case RISCVISD::NODE: \
13331  return "RISCVISD::" #NODE;
13332  // clang-format off
13333  switch ((RISCVISD::NodeType)Opcode) {
13334  case RISCVISD::FIRST_NUMBER:
13335  break;
13336  NODE_NAME_CASE(RET_FLAG)
13337  NODE_NAME_CASE(URET_FLAG)
13338  NODE_NAME_CASE(SRET_FLAG)
13339  NODE_NAME_CASE(MRET_FLAG)
13340  NODE_NAME_CASE(CALL)
13341  NODE_NAME_CASE(SELECT_CC)
13342  NODE_NAME_CASE(BR_CC)
13343  NODE_NAME_CASE(BuildPairF64)
13344  NODE_NAME_CASE(SplitF64)
13345  NODE_NAME_CASE(TAIL)
13346  NODE_NAME_CASE(ADD_LO)
13347  NODE_NAME_CASE(HI)
13348  NODE_NAME_CASE(LLA)
13349  NODE_NAME_CASE(ADD_TPREL)
13350  NODE_NAME_CASE(LA)
13351  NODE_NAME_CASE(LA_TLS_IE)
13352  NODE_NAME_CASE(LA_TLS_GD)
13353  NODE_NAME_CASE(MULHSU)
13354  NODE_NAME_CASE(SLLW)
13355  NODE_NAME_CASE(SRAW)
13356  NODE_NAME_CASE(SRLW)
13357  NODE_NAME_CASE(DIVW)
13358  NODE_NAME_CASE(DIVUW)
13359  NODE_NAME_CASE(REMUW)
13360  NODE_NAME_CASE(ROLW)
13361  NODE_NAME_CASE(RORW)
13362  NODE_NAME_CASE(CLZW)
13363  NODE_NAME_CASE(CTZW)
13364  NODE_NAME_CASE(ABSW)
13365  NODE_NAME_CASE(FMV_H_X)
13366  NODE_NAME_CASE(FMV_X_ANYEXTH)
13367  NODE_NAME_CASE(FMV_X_SIGNEXTH)
13368  NODE_NAME_CASE(FMV_W_X_RV64)
13369  NODE_NAME_CASE(FMV_X_ANYEXTW_RV64)
13370  NODE_NAME_CASE(FCVT_X)
13371  NODE_NAME_CASE(FCVT_XU)
13372  NODE_NAME_CASE(FCVT_W_RV64)
13373  NODE_NAME_CASE(FCVT_WU_RV64)
13374  NODE_NAME_CASE(STRICT_FCVT_W_RV64)
13375  NODE_NAME_CASE(STRICT_FCVT_WU_RV64)
13376  NODE_NAME_CASE(FROUND)
13377  NODE_NAME_CASE(READ_CYCLE_WIDE)
13378  NODE_NAME_CASE(BREV8)
13379  NODE_NAME_CASE(ORC_B)
13380  NODE_NAME_CASE(ZIP)
13381  NODE_NAME_CASE(UNZIP)
13382  NODE_NAME_CASE(VMV_V_X_VL)
13383  NODE_NAME_CASE(VFMV_V_F_VL)
13384  NODE_NAME_CASE(VMV_X_S)
13385  NODE_NAME_CASE(VMV_S_X_VL)
13386  NODE_NAME_CASE(VFMV_S_F_VL)
13387  NODE_NAME_CASE(SPLAT_VECTOR_SPLIT_I64_VL)
13388  NODE_NAME_CASE(READ_VLENB)
13389  NODE_NAME_CASE(TRUNCATE_VECTOR_VL)
13390  NODE_NAME_CASE(VSLIDEUP_VL)
13391  NODE_NAME_CASE(VSLIDE1UP_VL)
13392  NODE_NAME_CASE(VSLIDEDOWN_VL)
