13493 
13494 /// getConstraintType - Given a constraint letter, return the type of
13495 /// constraint it is for this target.
13496 RISCVTargetLowering::ConstraintType
13497 RISCVTargetLowering::getConstraintType(StringRef Constraint) const {
13498  if (Constraint.size() == 1) {
13499  switch (Constraint[0]) {
13500  default:
13501  break;
13502  case 'f':
13503  return C_RegisterClass;
13504  case 'I':
13505  case 'J':
13506  case 'K':
13507  return C_Immediate;
13508  case 'A':
13509  return C_Memory;
13510  case 'S': // A symbolic address
13511  return C_Other;
13512  }
13513  } else {
13514  if (Constraint == "vr" || Constraint == "vm")
13515  return C_RegisterClass;
13516  }
13517  return TargetLowering::getConstraintType(Constraint);
13518 }
13519 
13520 std::pair<unsigned, const TargetRegisterClass *>
13521 RISCVTargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI,
13522  StringRef Constraint,
13523  MVT VT) const {
13524  // First, see if this is a constraint that directly corresponds to a
13525  // RISCV register class.
13526  if (Constraint.size() == 1) {
13527  switch (Constraint[0]) {
13528  case 'r':
13529  // TODO: Support fixed vectors up to XLen for P extension?
13530  if (VT.isVector())
13531  break;
13532  return std::make_pair(0U, &RISCV::GPRRegClass);
13533  case 'f':
13534  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZfhOrZfhmin() && VT == MVT::f16)
13535  return std::make_pair(0U, &RISCV::FPR16RegClass);
13536  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtF() && VT == MVT::f32)
13537  return std::make_pair(0U, &RISCV::FPR32RegClass);
13538  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtD() && VT == MVT::f64)
13539  return std::make_pair(0U, &RISCV::FPR64RegClass);
13540  break;
13541  default:
13542  break;
13543  }
13544  } else if (Constraint == "vr") {
13545  for (const auto *RC : {&RISCV::VRRegClass, &RISCV::VRM2RegClass,
13546  &RISCV::VRM4RegClass, &RISCV::VRM8RegClass}) {
13547  if (TRI->isTypeLegalForClass(*RC, VT.SimpleTy))
13548  return std::make_pair(0U, RC);
13549  }
13550  } else if (Constraint == "vm") {
13551  if (TRI->isTypeLegalForClass(RISCV::VMV0RegClass, VT.SimpleTy))
13552  return std::make_pair(0U, &RISCV::VMV0RegClass);
13553  }
13554 
13555  // Clang will correctly decode the usage of register name aliases into their
13556  // official names. However, other frontends like `rustc` do not. This allows
13557  // users of these frontends to use the ABI names for registers in LLVM-style
13558  // register constraints.
13559  unsigned XRegFromAlias = StringSwitch<unsigned>(Constraint.lower())
13560  .Case("{zero}", RISCV::X0)
13561  .Case("{ra}", RISCV::X1)
13562  .Case("{sp}", RISCV::X2)
13563  .Case("{gp}", RISCV::X3)
13564  .Case("{tp}", RISCV::X4)
13565  .Case("{t0}", RISCV::X5)
13566  .Case("{t1}", RISCV::X6)
13567  .Case("{t2}", RISCV::X7)
13568  .Cases("{s0}", "{fp}", RISCV::X8)
13569  .Case("{s1}", RISCV::X9)
13570  .Case("{a0}", RISCV::X10)
13571  .Case("{a1}", RISCV::X11)
13572  .Case("{a2}", RISCV::X12)
13573  .Case("{a3}", RISCV::X13)
13574  .Case("{a4}", RISCV::X14)
13575  .Case("{a5}", RISCV::X15)
13576  .Case("{a6}", RISCV::X16)
13577  .Case("{a7}", RISCV::X17)
13578  .Case("{s2}", RISCV::X18)
13579  .Case("{s3}", RISCV::X19)
13580  .Case("{s4}", RISCV::X20)
13581  .Case("{s5}", RISCV::X21)
13582  .Case("{s6}", RISCV::X22)
13583  .Case("{s7}", RISCV::X23)
13584  .Case("{s8}", RISCV::X24)
13585  .Case("{s9}", RISCV::X25)
13586  .Case("{s10}", RISCV::X26)
13587  .Case("{s11}", RISCV::X27)
13588  .Case("{t3}", RISCV::X28)
13589  .Case("{t4}", RISCV::X29)
13590  .Case("{t5}", RISCV::X30)
13591  .Case("{t6}", RISCV::X31)
13592  .Default(RISCV::NoRegister);
13593  if (XRegFromAlias != RISCV::NoRegister)
13594  return std::make_pair(XRegFromAlias, &RISCV::GPRRegClass);
13595 
13596  // Since TargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint uses the name of the
13597  // TableGen record rather than the AsmName to choose registers for InlineAsm
13598  // constraints, plus we want to match those names to the widest floating point
13599  // register type available, manually select floating point registers here.
13600  //
13601  // The second case is the ABI name of the register, so that frontends can also
13602  // use the ABI names in register constraint lists.
13603  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtF()) {
13604  unsigned FReg = StringSwitch<unsigned>(Constraint.lower())
13605  .Cases("{f0}", "{ft0}", RISCV::F0_F)
13606  .Cases("{f1}", "{ft1}", RISCV::F1_F)
13607  .Cases("{f2}", "{ft2}", RISCV::F2_F)
13608  .Cases("{f3}", "{ft3}", RISCV::F3_F)
13609  .Cases("{f4}", "{ft4}", RISCV::F4_F)
13610  .Cases("{f5}", "{ft5}", RISCV::F5_F)
13611  .Cases("{f6}", "{ft6}", RISCV::F6_F)
13612  .Cases("{f7}", "{ft7}", RISCV::F7_F)
13613  .Cases("{f8}", "{fs0}", RISCV::F8_F)
13614  .Cases("{f9}", "{fs1}", RISCV::F9_F)
13615  .Cases("{f10}", "{fa0}", RISCV::F10_F)
13616  .Cases("{f11}", "{fa1}", RISCV::F11_F)
13617  .Cases("{f12}", "{fa2}", RISCV::F12_F)
13618  .Cases("{f13}", "{fa3}", RISCV::F13_F)
13619  .Cases("{f14}", "{fa4}", RISCV::F14_F)
13620  .Cases("{f15}", "{fa5}", RISCV::F15_F)
13621  .Cases("{f16}", "{fa6}", RISCV::F16_F)
13622  .Cases("{f17}", "{fa7}", RISCV::F17_F)
13623  .Cases("{f18}", "{fs2}", RISCV::F18_F)
13624  .Cases("{f19}", "{fs3}", RISCV::F19_F)
13625  .Cases("{f20}", "{fs4}", RISCV::F20_F)
13626  .Cases("{f21}", "{fs5}", RISCV::F21_F)
13627  .Cases("{f22}", "{fs6}", RISCV::F22_F)
13628  .Cases("{f23}", "{fs7}", RISCV::F23_F)
13629  .Cases("{f24}", "{fs8}", RISCV::F24_F)
13630  .Cases("{f25}", "{fs9}", RISCV::F25_F)
13631  .Cases("{f26}", "{fs10}", RISCV::F26_F)
13632  .Cases("{f27}", "{fs11}", RISCV::F27_F)
13633  .Cases("{f28}", "{ft8}", RISCV::F28_F)
13634  .Cases("{f29}", "{ft9}", RISCV::F29_F)
13635  .Cases("{f30}", "{ft10}", RISCV::F30_F)
13636  .Cases("{f31}", "{ft11}", RISCV::F31_F)
13637  .Default(RISCV::NoRegister);
13638  if (FReg != RISCV::NoRegister) {
13639  assert(RISCV::F0_F <= FReg && FReg <= RISCV::F31_F && "Unknown fp-reg");
13640  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtD() && (VT == MVT::f64 || VT == MVT::Other)) {
13641  unsigned RegNo = FReg - RISCV::F0_F;
13642  unsigned DReg = RISCV::F0_D + RegNo;
13643  return std::make_pair(DReg, &RISCV::FPR64RegClass);
13644  }
13645  if (VT == MVT::f32 || VT == MVT::Other)
13646  return std::make_pair(FReg, &RISCV::FPR32RegClass);
13647  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZfhOrZfhmin() && VT == MVT::f16) {
13648  unsigned RegNo = FReg - RISCV::F0_F;
13649  unsigned HReg = RISCV::F0_H + RegNo;
13650  return std::make_pair(HReg, &RISCV::FPR16RegClass);
13651  }
13652  }
13653  }
13654 
13655  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructions()) {
13656  Register VReg = StringSwitch<Register>(Constraint.lower())
13657  .Case("{v0}", RISCV::V0)
13658  .Case("{v1}", RISCV::V1)
13659  .Case("{v2}", RISCV::V2)
13660  .Case("{v3}", RISCV::V3)
13661  .Case("{v4}", RISCV::V4)
13662  .Case("{v5}", RISCV::V5)
13663  .Case("{v6}", RISCV::V6)
13664  .Case("{v7}", RISCV::V7)
13665  .Case("{v8}", RISCV::V8)
13666  .Case("{v9}", RISCV::V9)
13667  .Case("{v10}", RISCV::V10)
13668  .Case("{v11}", RISCV::V11)
13669  .Case("{v12}", RISCV::V12)
13670  .Case("{v13}", RISCV::V13)
13671  .Case("{v14}", RISCV::V14)
13672  .Case("{v15}", RISCV::V15)
13673  .Case("{v16}", RISCV::V16)
13674  .Case("{v17}", RISCV::V17)
13675  .Case("{v18}", RISCV::V18)
13676  .Case("{v19}", RISCV::V19)
13677  .Case("{v20}", RISCV::V20)
13678  .Case("{v21}", RISCV::V21)
13679  .Case("{v22}", RISCV::V22)
13680  .Case("{v23}", RISCV::V23)
13681  .Case("{v24}", RISCV::V24)
13682  .Case("{v25}", RISCV::V25)
13683  .Case("{v26}", RISCV::V26)
13684  .Case("{v27}", RISCV::V27)
13685  .Case("{v28}", RISCV::V28)
13686  .Case("{v29}", RISCV::V29)
13687  .Case("{v30}", RISCV::V30)
13688  .Case("{v31}", RISCV::V31)
13689  .Default(RISCV::NoRegister);
13690  if (VReg != RISCV::NoRegister) {
13691  if (TRI->isTypeLegalForClass(RISCV::VMRegClass, VT.SimpleTy))
13692  return std::make_pair(VReg, &RISCV::VMRegClass);
13693  if (TRI->isTypeLegalForClass(RISCV::VRRegClass, VT.SimpleTy))
13694  return std::make_pair(VReg, &RISCV::VRRegClass);
13695  for (const auto *RC :
13696  {&RISCV::VRM2RegClass, &RISCV::VRM4RegClass, &RISCV::VRM8RegClass}) {
13697  if (TRI->isTypeLegalForClass(*RC, VT.SimpleTy)) {
13698  VReg = TRI->getMatchingSuperReg(VReg, RISCV::sub_vrm1_0, RC);
13699  return std::make_pair(VReg, RC);
13700  }
13701  }
13702  }
13703  }
13704 
13705  std::pair<Register, const TargetRegisterClass *> Res =
13706  TargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(TRI, Constraint, VT);
13707 
13708  // If we picked one of the Zfinx register classes, remap it to the GPR class.
13709  // FIXME: When Zfinx is supported in CodeGen this will need to take the
13710  // Subtarget into account.
13711  if (Res.second == &RISCV::GPRF16RegClass ||
13712  Res.second == &RISCV::GPRF32RegClass ||
13713  Res.second == &RISCV::GPRF64RegClass)
13714  return std::make_pair(Res.first, &RISCV::GPRRegClass);
13715 
13716  return Res;
13717 }
13718 
13719 unsigned
13720 RISCVTargetLowering::getInlineAsmMemConstraint(StringRef ConstraintCode) const {
13721  // Currently only support length 1 constraints.
13722  if (ConstraintCode.size() == 1) {
13723  switch (ConstraintCode[0]) {
13724  case 'A':
13725  return InlineAsm::Constraint_A;
13726  default:
13727  break;
13728  }
13729  }
13730 
13731  return TargetLowering::getInlineAsmMemConstraint(ConstraintCode);
13732 }
13733 
13734 void RISCVTargetLowering::LowerAsmOperandForConstraint(
13735  SDValue Op, std::string &Constraint, std::vector<SDValue> &Ops,
13736  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
13737  // Currently only support length 1 constraints.
13738  if (Constraint.length() == 1) {
13739  switch (Constraint[0]) {
13740  case 'I':
13741  // Validate & create a 12-bit signed immediate operand.
13742  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)) {
13743  uint64_t CVal = C->getSExtValue();
13744  if (isInt<12>(CVal))
13745  Ops.push_back(
13746  DAG.getTargetConstant(CVal, SDLoc(Op), Subtarget.getXLenVT()));
13747  }
13748  return;
13749  case 'J':
13750  // Validate & create an integer zero operand.
13751  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op))
13752  if (C->getZExtValue() == 0)
13753  Ops.push_back(
13754  DAG.getTargetConstant(0, SDLoc(Op), Subtarget.getXLenVT()));
13755  return;
13756  case 'K':
13757  // Validate & create a 5-bit unsigned immediate operand.
13758  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)) {
13759  uint64_t CVal = C->getZExtValue();
13760  if (isUInt<5>(CVal))
13761  Ops.push_back(
13762  DAG.getTargetConstant(CVal, SDLoc(Op), Subtarget.getXLenVT()));
13763  }
13764  return;
13765  case 'S':
13766  if (const auto *GA = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Op)) {
13767  Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GA->getGlobal(), SDLoc(Op),
13768  GA->getValueType(0)));
13769  } else if (const auto *BA = dyn_cast<BlockAddressSDNode>(Op)) {
13770  Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetBlockAddress(BA->getBlockAddress(),
13771  BA->getValueType(0)));
13772  }
13773  return;
13774  default:
13775  break;
13776  }
13777  }
13778  TargetLowering::LowerAsmOperandForConstraint(Op, Constraint, Ops, DAG);
13779 }
13780 
13781 Instruction *RISCVTargetLowering::emitLeadingFence(IRBuilderBase &Builder,
13782  Instruction *Inst,
13783  AtomicOrdering Ord) const {
13784  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZtso()) {
13785  if (isa<LoadInst>(Inst) && Ord == AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent)
13786  return Builder.CreateFence(Ord);
13787  return nullptr;
13788  }
13789 
13790  if (isa<LoadInst>(Inst) && Ord == AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent)
13791  return Builder.CreateFence(Ord);
13792  if (isa<StoreInst>(Inst) && isReleaseOrStronger(Ord))
13793  return Builder.CreateFence(AtomicOrdering::Release);
13794  return nullptr;
13795 }
13796 
13797 Instruction *RISCVTargetLowering::emitTrailingFence(IRBuilderBase &Builder,
13798  Instruction *Inst,
13799  AtomicOrdering Ord) const {
13800  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZtso())
13801  return nullptr;
13802 
13803  if (isa<LoadInst>(Inst) && isAcquireOrStronger(Ord))
13804  return Builder.CreateFence(AtomicOrdering::Acquire);
13805  return nullptr;
13806 }
13807 
13808 TargetLowering::AtomicExpansionKind
13809 RISCVTargetLowering::shouldExpandAtomicRMWInIR(AtomicRMWInst *AI) const {
13810  // atomicrmw {fadd,fsub} must be expanded to use compare-exchange, as floating
13811  // point operations can't be used in an lr/sc sequence without breaking the
13812  // forward-progress guarantee.
13813  if (AI->isFloatingPointOperation() ||
13814  AI->getOperation() == AtomicRMWInst::UIncWrap ||
13815  AI->getOperation() == AtomicRMWInst::UDecWrap)
13816  return AtomicExpansionKind::CmpXChg;
13817 
13818  // Don't expand forced atomics, we want to have __sync libcalls instead.
13819  if (Subtarget.hasForcedAtomics())
13820  return AtomicExpansionKind::None;
13821 
13822  unsigned Size = AI->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
13823  if (Size == 8 || Size == 16)
13824  return AtomicExpansionKind::MaskedIntrinsic;
13825  return AtomicExpansionKind::None;
13826 }
13827 
13828 static Intrinsic::ID
13829 getIntrinsicForMaskedAtomicRMWBinOp(unsigned XLen, AtomicRMWInst::BinOp BinOp) {
13830  if (XLen == 32) {
13831  switch (BinOp) {
13832  default:
13833  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected AtomicRMW BinOp");
13834  case AtomicRMWInst::Xchg:
13835  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_xchg_i32;
13836  case AtomicRMWInst::Add:
13837  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_add_i32;
13838  case AtomicRMWInst::Sub:
13839  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_sub_i32;
13840  case AtomicRMWInst::Nand:
13841  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_nand_i32;
13842  case AtomicRMWInst::Max:
13843  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_max_i32;
13844  case AtomicRMWInst::Min:
13845  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_min_i32;
13846  case AtomicRMWInst::UMax:
13847  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_umax_i32;
13848  case AtomicRMWInst::UMin:
13849  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_umin_i32;
13850  }
13851  }
13852 
13853  if (XLen == 64) {
13854  switch (BinOp) {
13855  default:
13856  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected AtomicRMW BinOp");
13857  case AtomicRMWInst::Xchg:
13858  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_xchg_i64;
13859  case AtomicRMWInst::Add:
13860  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_add_i64;
13861  case AtomicRMWInst::Sub:
13862  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_sub_i64;
13863  case AtomicRMWInst::Nand:
13864  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_nand_i64;
13865  case AtomicRMWInst::Max:
13866  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_max_i64;
13867  case AtomicRMWInst::Min:
13868  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_min_i64;
13869  case AtomicRMWInst::UMax:
13870  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_umax_i64;
13871  case AtomicRMWInst::UMin:
13872  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_umin_i64;
13873  }
13874  }
13875 
13876  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected XLen\n");
13877 }
13878 
13879 Value *RISCVTargetLowering::emitMaskedAtomicRMWIntrinsic(
13880  IRBuilderBase &Builder, AtomicRMWInst *AI, Value *AlignedAddr, Value *Incr,
13881  Value *Mask, Value *ShiftAmt, AtomicOrdering Ord) const {
13882  unsigned XLen = Subtarget.getXLen();
13883  Value *Ordering =
13884  Builder.getIntN(XLen, static_cast<uint64_t>(AI->getOrdering()));
13885  Type *Tys[] = {AlignedAddr->getType()};
13886  Function *LrwOpScwLoop = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(
13887  AI->getModule(),
13888  getIntrinsicForMaskedAtomicRMWBinOp(XLen, AI->getOperation()), Tys);
13889 
13890  if (XLen == 64) {
13891  Incr = Builder.CreateSExt(Incr, Builder.getInt64Ty());
13892  Mask = Builder.CreateSExt(Mask, Builder.getInt64Ty());
13893  ShiftAmt = Builder.CreateSExt(ShiftAmt, Builder.getInt64Ty());
13894  }
13895 
13896  Value *Result;
13897 
13898  // Must pass the shift amount needed to sign extend the loaded value prior
13899  // to performing a signed comparison for min/max. ShiftAmt is the number of
13900  // bits to shift the value into position. Pass XLen-ShiftAmt-ValWidth, which
13901  // is the number of bits to left+right shift the value in order to
13902  // sign-extend.
13903  if (AI->getOperation() == AtomicRMWInst::Min ||
13904  AI->getOperation() == AtomicRMWInst::Max) {
13905  const DataLayout &DL = AI->getModule()->getDataLayout();
13906  unsigned ValWidth =
13907  DL.getTypeStoreSizeInBits(AI->getValOperand()->getType());
13908  Value *SextShamt =
13909  Builder.CreateSub(Builder.getIntN(XLen, XLen - ValWidth), ShiftAmt);
13910  Result = Builder.CreateCall(LrwOpScwLoop,
13911  {AlignedAddr, Incr, Mask, SextShamt, Ordering});
13912  } else {
13913  Result =
13914  Builder.CreateCall(LrwOpScwLoop, {AlignedAddr, Incr, Mask, Ordering});
13915  }
13916 
13917  if (XLen == 64)
13918  Result = Builder.CreateTrunc(Result, Builder.getInt32Ty());
13919  return Result;
13920 }
13921 
13922 TargetLowering::AtomicExpansionKind
13923 RISCVTargetLowering::shouldExpandAtomicCmpXchgInIR(
13924  AtomicCmpXchgInst *CI) const {
13925  // Don't expand forced atomics, we want to have __sync libcalls instead.
13926  if (Subtarget.hasForcedAtomics())
13927  return AtomicExpansionKind::None;
13928 
13929  unsigned Size = CI->getCompareOperand()->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
13930  if (Size == 8 || Size == 16)
13931  return AtomicExpansionKind::MaskedIntrinsic;
13932  return AtomicExpansionKind::None;
13933 }
13934 
13935 Value *RISCVTargetLowering::emitMaskedAtomicCmpXchgIntrinsic(
13936  IRBuilderBase &Builder, AtomicCmpXchgInst *CI, Value *AlignedAddr,
13937  Value *CmpVal, Value *NewVal, Value *Mask, AtomicOrdering Ord) const {
13938  unsigned XLen = Subtarget.getXLen();
13939  Value *Ordering = Builder.getIntN(XLen, static_cast<uint64_t>(Ord));
13940  Intrinsic::ID CmpXchgIntrID = Intrinsic::riscv_masked_cmpxchg_i32;
13941  if (XLen == 64) {
13942  CmpVal = Builder.CreateSExt(CmpVal, Builder.getInt64Ty());
13943  NewVal = Builder.CreateSExt(NewVal, Builder.getInt64Ty());
13944  Mask = Builder.CreateSExt(Mask, Builder.getInt64Ty());
13945  CmpXchgIntrID = Intrinsic::riscv_masked_cmpxchg_i64;
13946  }
13947  Type *Tys[] = {AlignedAddr->getType()};
13948  Function *MaskedCmpXchg =
13949  Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI->getModule(), CmpXchgIntrID, Tys);
13950  Value *Result = Builder.CreateCall(
13951  MaskedCmpXchg, {AlignedAddr, CmpVal, NewVal, Mask, Ordering});
13952  if (XLen == 64)
13953  Result = Builder.CreateTrunc(Result, Builder.getInt32Ty());
13954  return Result;
13955 }

13962 bool RISCVTargetLowering::shouldConvertFpToSat(unsigned Op, EVT FPVT,
13963  EVT VT) const {
13964  if (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(Op, VT) || !FPVT.isSimple())
13965  return false;
13966 
13967  switch (FPVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy) {
13968  case MVT::f16:
13969  return Subtarget.hasStdExtZfhOrZfhmin();
13970  case MVT::f32:
13971  return Subtarget.hasStdExtF();
13972  case MVT::f64:
13973  return Subtarget.hasStdExtD();
13974  default:
13975  return false;
13976  }
13977 }

13997 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isVScaleKnownToBeAPowerOfTwo() const {
13998  // We define vscale to be VLEN/RVVBitsPerBlock. VLEN is always a power
13999  // of two >= 64, and RVVBitsPerBlock is 64. Thus, vscale must be
14000  // a power of two as well.
14001  // FIXME: This doesn't work for zve32, but that's already broken
14002  // elsewhere for the same reason.
14003  assert(Subtarget.getRealMinVLen() >= 64 && "zve32* unsupported");
14004  static_assert(RISCV::RVVBitsPerBlock == 64,
14005  "RVVBitsPerBlock changed, audit needed");
14006  return true;
14007 }

14009 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isFMAFasterThanFMulAndFAdd(const MachineFunction &MF,
14010  EVT VT) const {
14011  EVT SVT = VT.getScalarType();
14012 
14013  if (!SVT.isSimple())
14014  return false;
14015 
14016  switch (SVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy) {
14017  case MVT::f16:
14018  return VT.isVector() ? Subtarget.hasVInstructionsF16()
14019  : Subtarget.hasStdExtZfh();
14020  case MVT::f32:
14021  return Subtarget.hasStdExtF();
14022  case MVT::f64:
14023  return Subtarget.hasStdExtD();
14024  default:
14025  break;
14026  }
14027 
14028  return false;
14029 }

14057 
14058 bool RISCVTargetLowering::decomposeMulByConstant(LLVMContext &Context, EVT VT,
14059  SDValue C) const {
14060  // Check integral scalar types.
14061  const bool HasExtMOrZmmul =
14062  Subtarget.hasStdExtM() || Subtarget.hasStdExtZmmul();
14063  if (VT.isScalarInteger()) {
14064  // Omit the optimization if the sub target has the M extension and the data
14065  // size exceeds XLen.
14066  if (HasExtMOrZmmul && VT.getSizeInBits() > Subtarget.getXLen())
14067  return false;
14068  if (auto *ConstNode = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(C.getNode())) {
14069  // Break the MUL to a SLLI and an ADD/SUB.
14070  const APInt &Imm = ConstNode->getAPIntValue();
14071  if ((Imm + 1).isPowerOf2() || (Imm - 1).isPowerOf2() ||
14072  (1 - Imm).isPowerOf2() || (-1 - Imm).isPowerOf2())
14073  return true;
14074  // Optimize the MUL to (SH*ADD x, (SLLI x, bits)) if Imm is not simm12.
14075  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZba() && !Imm.isSignedIntN(12) &&
14076  ((Imm - 2).isPowerOf2() || (Imm - 4).isPowerOf2() ||
14077  (Imm - 8).isPowerOf2()))
14078  return true;
14079  // Omit the following optimization if the sub target has the M extension
14080  // and the data size >= XLen.
14081  if (HasExtMOrZmmul && VT.getSizeInBits() >= Subtarget.getXLen())
14082  return false;
14083  // Break the MUL to two SLLI instructions and an ADD/SUB, if Imm needs
14084  // a pair of LUI/ADDI.
14085  if (!Imm.isSignedIntN(12) && Imm.countTrailingZeros() < 12) {
14086  APInt ImmS = Imm.ashr(Imm.countTrailingZeros());
14087  if ((ImmS + 1).isPowerOf2() || (ImmS - 1).isPowerOf2() ||
14088  (1 - ImmS).isPowerOf2())
14089  return true;
14090  }
14091  }
14092  }
14093 
14094  return false;
14095 }
14096 
14097 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isMulAddWithConstProfitable(SDValue AddNode,
14098  SDValue ConstNode) const {
14099  // Let the DAGCombiner decide for vectors.
14100  EVT VT = AddNode.getValueType();
14101  if (VT.isVector())
14102  return true;
14103 
14104  // Let the DAGCombiner decide for larger types.
14105  if (VT.getScalarSizeInBits() > Subtarget.getXLen())
14106  return true;
14107 
14108  // It is worse if c1 is simm12 while c1*c2 is not.
14109  ConstantSDNode *C1Node = cast<ConstantSDNode>(AddNode.getOperand(1));
14110  ConstantSDNode *C2Node = cast<ConstantSDNode>(ConstNode);
14111  const APInt &C1 = C1Node->getAPIntValue();
14112  const APInt &C2 = C2Node->getAPIntValue();
14113  if (C1.isSignedIntN(12) && !(C1 * C2).isSignedIntN(12))
14114  return false;
14115 
14116  // Default to true and let the DAGCombiner decide.
14117  return true;
14118 }
14119 
14120 bool RISCVTargetLowering::allowsMisalignedMemoryAccesses(
14121  EVT VT, unsigned AddrSpace, Align Alignment, MachineMemOperand::Flags Flags,
14122  unsigned *Fast) const {
14123  if (!VT.isVector()) {
14124  if (Fast)
14125  *Fast = 0;
14126  return Subtarget.enableUnalignedScalarMem();
14127  }
14128 
14129  // All vector implementations must support element alignment
14130  EVT ElemVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
14131  if (Alignment >= ElemVT.getStoreSize()) {
14132  if (Fast)
14133  *Fast = 1;
14134  return true;
14135  }
14136 
14137  return false;
14138 }
14139 
14140 bool RISCVTargetLowering::splitValueIntoRegisterParts(
14141  SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &DL, SDValue Val, SDValue *Parts,
14142  unsigned NumParts, MVT PartVT, std::optional<CallingConv::ID> CC) const {
14143  bool IsABIRegCopy = CC.has_value();
14144  EVT ValueVT = Val.getValueType();
14145  if (IsABIRegCopy && ValueVT == MVT::f16 && PartVT == MVT::f32) {
14146  // Cast the f16 to i16, extend to i32, pad with ones to make a float nan,
14147  // and cast to f32.
14148  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::i16, Val);
14149  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i32, Val);
14150  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, MVT::i32, Val,
14151  DAG.getConstant(0xFFFF0000, DL, MVT::i32));
14152  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::f32, Val);
14153  Parts[0] = Val;
14154  return true;
14155  }
14156 
14157  if (ValueVT.isScalableVector() && PartVT.isScalableVector()) {
14158  LLVMContext &Context = *DAG.getContext();
14159  EVT ValueEltVT = ValueVT.getVectorElementType();
14160  EVT PartEltVT = PartVT.getVectorElementType();
14161  unsigned ValueVTBitSize = ValueVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue();
14162  unsigned PartVTBitSize = PartVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue();
14163  if (PartVTBitSize % ValueVTBitSize == 0) {
14164  assert(PartVTBitSize >= ValueVTBitSize);
14165  // If the element types are different, bitcast to the same element type of
14166  // PartVT first.
14167  // Give an example here, we want copy a <vscale x 1 x i8> value to
14168  // <vscale x 4 x i16>.
14169  // We need to convert <vscale x 1 x i8> to <vscale x 8 x i8> by insert
14170  // subvector, then we can bitcast to <vscale x 4 x i16>.
14171  if (ValueEltVT != PartEltVT) {
14172  if (PartVTBitSize > ValueVTBitSize) {
14173  unsigned Count = PartVTBitSize / ValueEltVT.getFixedSizeInBits();
14174  assert(Count != 0 && "The number of element should not be zero.");
14175  EVT SameEltTypeVT =
14176  EVT::getVectorVT(Context, ValueEltVT, Count, /*IsScalable=*/true);
14177  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, SameEltTypeVT,
14178  DAG.getUNDEF(SameEltTypeVT), Val,
14179  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
14180  }
14181  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, PartVT, Val);
14182  } else {
14183  Val =
14184  DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, PartVT, DAG.getUNDEF(PartVT),
14185  Val, DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
14186  }
14187  Parts[0] = Val;
14188  return true;
14189  }
14190  }
14191  return false;
14192 }
14193 
14194 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::joinRegisterPartsIntoValue(
14195  SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &DL, const SDValue *Parts, unsigned NumParts,
14196  MVT PartVT, EVT ValueVT, std::optional<CallingConv::ID> CC) const {
14197  bool IsABIRegCopy = CC.has_value();
14198  if (IsABIRegCopy && ValueVT == MVT::f16 && PartVT == MVT::f32) {
14199  SDValue Val = Parts[0];
14200 
14201  // Cast the f32 to i32, truncate to i16, and cast back to f16.
14202  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::i32, Val);
14203  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i16, Val);
14204  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::f16, Val);
14205  return Val;
14206  }
14207 
14208  if (ValueVT.isScalableVector() && PartVT.isScalableVector()) {
14209  LLVMContext &Context = *DAG.getContext();
14210  SDValue Val = Parts[0];
14211  EVT ValueEltVT = ValueVT.getVectorElementType();
14212  EVT PartEltVT = PartVT.getVectorElementType();
14213  unsigned ValueVTBitSize = ValueVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue();
14214  unsigned PartVTBitSize = PartVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue();
14215  if (PartVTBitSize % ValueVTBitSize == 0) {
14216  assert(PartVTBitSize >= ValueVTBitSize);
14217  EVT SameEltTypeVT = ValueVT;
14218  // If the element types are different, convert it to the same element type
14219  // of PartVT.
14220  // Give an example here, we want copy a <vscale x 1 x i8> value from
14221  // <vscale x 4 x i16>.
14222  // We need to convert <vscale x 4 x i16> to <vscale x 8 x i8> first,
14223  // then we can extract <vscale x 1 x i8>.
14224  if (ValueEltVT != PartEltVT) {
14225  unsigned Count = PartVTBitSize / ValueEltVT.getFixedSizeInBits();
14226  assert(Count != 0 && "The number of element should not be zero.");
14227  SameEltTypeVT =
14228  EVT::getVectorVT(Context, ValueEltVT, Count, /*IsScalable=*/true);
14229  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, SameEltTypeVT, Val);
14230  }
14231  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, ValueVT, Val,
14232  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
14233  return Val;
14234  }
14235  }
14236  return SDValue();
14237 }

14239 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isIntDivCheap(EVT VT, AttributeList Attr) const {
14240  // When aggressively optimizing for code size, we prefer to use a div
14241  // instruction, as it is usually smaller than the alternative sequence.
14242  // TODO: Add vector division?
14243  bool OptSize = Attr.hasFnAttr(Attribute::MinSize);
14244  return OptSize && !VT.isVector();
14245 }

14247 bool RISCVTargetLowering::preferScalarizeSplat(unsigned Opc) const {
14248  // Scalarize zero_ext and sign_ext might stop match to widening instruction in
14249  // some situation.

14251  return false;

14255 static Value *useTpOffset(IRBuilderBase &IRB, unsigned Offset) {
14256  Module *M = IRB.GetInsertBlock()->getParent()->getParent();
14257  Function *ThreadPointerFunc =
14258  Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, Intrinsic::thread_pointer);
14259  return IRB.CreatePointerCast(
14260  IRB.CreateConstGEP1_32(IRB.getInt8Ty(),
14261  IRB.CreateCall(ThreadPointerFunc), Offset),
14262  IRB.getInt8PtrTy()->getPointerTo(0));
14263 }

14265 Value *RISCVTargetLowering::getIRStackGuard(IRBuilderBase &IRB) const {

14277 Register
14278 RISCVTargetLowering::getRegisterByName(const char *RegName, LLT VT,
14279  const MachineFunction &MF) const {
14280  Register Reg = MatchRegisterAltName(RegName);
14281  if (Reg == RISCV::NoRegister)
14282  Reg = MatchRegisterName(RegName);
14283  if (Reg == RISCV::NoRegister)
14284  report_fatal_error(
14285  Twine("Invalid register name \"" + StringRef(RegName) + "\"."));
14286  BitVector ReservedRegs = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo()->getReservedRegs(MF);
14287  if (!ReservedRegs.test(Reg) && !Subtarget.isRegisterReservedByUser(Reg))
14288  report_fatal_error(Twine("Trying to obtain non-reserved register \"" +
14289  StringRef(RegName) + "\"."));
14290  return Reg;
14291 }
